  <book id="ACT" stage="Rev" version="C">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:48:19Z" when="2009-10-02 03:48:19Z" stage="Draft">first draft by Max Jacob based on BIS; 2nd draft revised by Max looking at Buru and Luang back translations; 3rd draft by Barbara doing a KM front translation focusing on appropriate discourse repackaging to move it away from the shackles of the BIS; 4th draft revised thru chapter 21 by June Jacob, Max Jacob, Mus Zacharias and Chuck Grimes in Darwin, March 2000; chapters 1-13 (inclusive) UNS checked in Manutapen (Chuck &amp; Mus) with Yanto, Ena and friends (early April 2000); Max did an additional revision of chapters 22-28, taking off on Barbara's KM front translation; 5th draft chapters 22-28 finished in Kupang with Max, Mus, Dee, and Chuck in May 2000; chapters 14-28 UNS checked in Manutapen/kampus (Chuck &amp; (Mus)) with Yanto, Ena and 3 friends (late May 2000); consultant checked with Dave Glasgow in Kupang (July-Aug 2000) with Max and Mus and ; various revisions; final read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana; Further tightening from Helong (DG) check, plus Barbara's suggestions (versi S);</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 10:49:57Z" when="2014-02-24 10:49:57Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 1-16 August 2000 at Gereja Koinonia in Kupang (6 full days + 3 half days); Consultant: David Glasgow, approved. Report: CnRepAct.doc</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-13 23:44:12Z" when="2015-01-13 23:44:12Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read thru for Kupang mini-Bible at UBB with Chuck, Lena, Rina. BT cleaned up quite a bit.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Utusan dong pung Carita<bt>The *Apostle's Story</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Tuhan Yesus pung utusan dong pung<bt>The Lord Yesus' *apostles'</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Carita<bt>Story</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah janji mau kirim datang Dia pung Roh yang Barisi<bt>God promises to send His *Holy Spirit</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1-3" />Pak Teofilus<bt>Mr Teofilus</bt><note reference="1:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Nama <span class="Italic">Teofilus</span> dalam bahasa Yunani pung arti &lt;orang yang sayang sang Tuhan&gt;. Ini, Lukas pung buku kadua yang dia tulis kasi sang Teofilus. Lia ju <span class="Italic">Lukas </span>1:1-4.<bt>The name Teofilus in the Yunani language means 'person who loves the Lord.' This is Lukas' second book which he wrote to Teofilus. See also Lukas 1:1-4.</bt></note>yang bae. Salam dari beta, Lukas.<bt>who is good (=letter introduction: Dear Mr Teofilus). Greetings from me, Lukas.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Di beta pung buku yang dolu, beta su tulis memang samua-samua so'al Tuhan Yesus pung idop. Andia, samua yang Dia su bekin, deng samua yang Dia su ajar dari dia pung mula-mula. Bilang, Dia pili ame Dia pung utusan dong. Biar orang su bekin susa deng bekin mati sang Dia, ma Tuhan Allah kasi idop kambali. Waktu Dia su idop kambali, ju Dia kasi tunju Dia pung diri sang Dia pung utusan dong. Dong dapa lia sang Dia ulang kali sampe ampa pulu hari, ko dong tau memang bilang, Dia su idop batúl-batúl. Dia ju kasi tau sang dong bilang, Tuhan Allah tu, sama ke Raja yang pegang parenta. Dia ju utus sang dong pake Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi pung kuasa. Sampe-sampe Tuhan Yesus nae kambali pi sorga.<bt>In my previous book, I have already written all about the Lord Yesus' life. That is, all that He did, and all that He had taught from the beginning. That, He chose His *apostles (emissaries/commisioned ones). Even though people made Him suffer and killed Him, nevertheless the Lord God caused Him to live again. When He was alive again, then He showed (caused to appear) Himself to His *apostles. They were able to see Him repeated times until forty days, in order that they really knew that He truly-truly was alive. He also told them that the Lord God is like a Raja who holds government/rules. He also commissioned them using the power/authority of God's Holy Spirit. On and on until the Lord Yesus went back up to heaven.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Key term Holy Spirit; Key term"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Key term Holy Spirit; Key term apostles (utusan dong); Key term kerajaan Allah</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu samua tu, yang beta parná tulis.<bt>It is all that which I have written.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4-5" />Satu kali, Yesus ada bakumpul deng Dia pung utusan dong di gunung Saitun. Dia kasi parenta sang dong bilang,<bt>One time, Yesus was gathered with his apostles (coll) at the Saitun mountain [DISCOURSE: stage setting from vs. 12]. He commanded them saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Inga! Dolu Yohanis sarani orang pake aer sa, ma sakarang bosong musti tunggu barapa hari lai, te Tuhan mau bekin lebe hebat kasi bosong, tagal Dia mau kasi Dia pung Roh yang Barisi sang bosong. Jadi bosong jang jalan kasi tenga ini kota Yerusalem dolu. Ma bosong tunggu di sini sampe Beta pung Bapa kasi Dia pung Roh sang bosong, sama ke Dia su parná janji tu. Deng Beta ju su kasi tau sang bosong bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>"Remember/Listen! Previously Yohanis *baptised people only using water, but now you-pl must wait a few more days, cuz (elaboration) the Lord wants to do even greater to/for you-pl, because He is going to give His *Holy Spirit to you-pl. So (consequently) you-pl don't go leaving behind this city Yerusalem (negative imperative). But you-pl wait here until My Father gives His Spirit to you, just like that which He has previously promised. And I have also told you like that.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Bagini, é. Bosong jang jalan kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">"Bagini, é. Bosong jang jalan kasi tenga ini kota Yerusalem dolu. Te bosong musti tunggu di sini sampe Beta pung Bapa kasi Dia pung Roh sang bosong. Tempo hari Beta su kasi tau memang sang bosong bilang Tuhan Allah su janji bagitu dari dolu. Te dolu Yohanis salalu sarani orang pake aer, ma nanti barapa hari lai Tuhan Allah mau sarani bosong deng Dia pung Roh yang Barisi.&gt;&gt;<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:4-5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 24:49, Mateos 3:11, Markus 1:8, Lukas 3:16, Yohanis 1:33</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ta'angka nae pi sorga<bt>The Lord Yesus is lifted up to heaven</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Waktu Yesus ada bakumpul deng Dia pung utusan dong, ju dong tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Botong mau tanya bagini: Bapa tantu inga dolu-dolu waktu negara Isra'el parenta dia pung diri. Naa. Sakarang Bapa su mau kasi bebas sang kotong dari orang laen pung parenta, ko, kotong musti tunggu waktu yang laen?&gt;&gt;<bt>While Yesus was gathered with His *apostles, they asked Him saying, “Father! We-exc want to ask like this: You (Father) surely remember long ago when the nation of Isra'el governed itself. Are you now going to free us-inc from other people's government, or, must we wait for a different time?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu utusan-utusan dong ada bakumpul sama-sama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Waktu utusan-utusan dong ada bakumpul sama-sama deng Tuhan Yesus, dong tanya sang Dia, bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan! Kira-kira sakarang Tuhan su mau kasi badiri kambali karaja'an Isra'el ko?"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01882b.tif" rtfFormat="width:7.0cm;textWrapping:none">Tuhan Yesus omong deng Dia pung ana bua dong<bt>The Lord Yesus speaks with His *disciples</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sonde usa cari tau dia pung waktu. Cuma Beta pung Bapa sa yang ada hak ator dia pung waktu.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, “You-pl don't need to find.out it's time. Only just My Father who has the right to arrange/set.in.motion its time.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Ju Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung Bapa sandiri yang putus dia pung hari deng dia pung oras. Itu Bapa pung hak, jadi bosong sonde usa cari tau.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma nanti kalo Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi su datang maso sang bosong, baru bosong dapa kuasa. Ais bosong musti pi kasi tau samua orang so'al Beta. Kasi tau orang-orang di kota Yerusalem, deng di samua kampong di propinsi Yudea deng propinsi Samaria, tarús sampe di ini dunya pung huk-huk.&gt;&gt;<bt>But later when the Lord's *Holy Spirit has come entered you-pl, only then you will get power. Then you must go tell all people about Me. Tell people in Yerusalem city, and also in all the villages in Yudea province and Samaria province, continuing until arriving at the world's corners.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dunya pung huk-huk = sudut-sudut (corners)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">dunya pung huk-huk = sudut-sudut (corners)</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 28:19, Markus 16:15, Lukas 24:47-48</note><v n="9" />Omong abis bagitu, ju Yesus ta'angka nae pi langit di dong pung muka. Dia ta'angka sampe awan tutu ame sang Dia, ais dong sonde dapa lia sang Dia lai.<bt>Finishing speaking like that, then Yesus was lifted up to the sky in front of them. He was lifted until the the cloud/s covered him, and then they could not see Him anymore.</bt><note reference="1:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 16:19, Lukas 24:50-51</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Waktu dong masi lia pi langit, takuju sa ada dua orang su badiri di dong pung sablá, deng pake pakean puti barisi.<bt>When they were still looking at the sky, suddenly/unexpectedly there were two people standing at their side, and wearing extremely (lit. clean) white clothes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="balia = reciprocal lia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">balia = reciprocal lia</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Itu dua orang omong bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Orang Galilea dong! Akurang ko bosong masi tanganga bodo lia pi langit? Tadi bosong su lia deng bosong pung mata biji sandiri Yesus ta'angka nae pi langit sampe awan tutu ame sang Dia. Bosong lia Dia nae karmana, nanti Dia ju turun kambali bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Those two people spoke saying, “Weh! Galilea people! Why are you still looking at the sky with your mouths open stupidly [=in amazement]? You-pl just saw with your own eye(balls) Yesus lifted up to the sky until cloud/s covered Him. You saw Him go.up how, later He will also come.down again like that.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Karmana bosong lia Dia nae, bagitu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Karmana bosong lia Dia nae, bagitu ju nanti Dia turun kambali.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong cari orang laen ko ganti sang Yudas<bt>They hunt for another person to replace Yudas</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais itu, ju Yesus pung utusan dong turun dari gunung Saitun kambali pi kota Yerusalem. Itu gunung pung jao dari kota kira-kira ada satu kilo.<bt>After that, then Yesus' *apostles went.down from Saitun mountain returning to Yerusalem city. That mountain's distance from the city was approximately one kilo[meter].</bt><note reference="1:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Itu waktu, guru agama Yahudi dong bekin atoran bilang, pas deng hari barenti karjá, orang Yahudi dong sonde bole jalan jao. Dong ator ko orang jang jalan lebe jao dari dua kilo (pi-pulang). Tulisan bahasa Yunani di ini ayat tulis bilang, ini gunung pung jao dari Yerusalem sama deng &lt;&lt;hari barenti karjá pung jalan.&gt;&gt; Jadi deng bagitu kotong tau bilang, itu gunung ada satu kilo dari kota.<bt>At that time, the Yahudi religious teachers made a regulation saying that on the day of stopping work, Yahudi people could not walk far. They arranged it so that people were not allowed to walk farther than two kilos (there and back). The original Yunani language writing in this verse writes saying, this mountain's distance from Yerusalem was equivalent with "a day of stopping work's travel.” So (consequently), with that we-inc know that that mountain was one kilo from the city.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Sampe di kota, ju dong maso pi dalam satu ruma yang dong pake manumpang. Ais dong nae pi kamar atas. Itu utusan dong pung nama, andia:<bt>Arriving at the city, then they entered into a house that they were using temporarily/as.guests. Then they went.up to the room above. Those *apostles names, they.were:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pake manumpang = pinjam pake"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pake manumpang = pinjam pake</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Petrus,<bt>Petrus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yohanis,<bt>Yohanis,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yakobis,<bt>Yakobis,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Anderias,<bt>Anderias,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Filipus,<bt>Filipus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tomas,<bt>Tomas,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bartolomeos,<bt>Bartolomeos,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Mateos,<bt>Mateos,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yakobis (Alpius pung ana),<bt>Yakobis (Alpius' child),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Simon (anggota partei Selot),<bt>Simon (member of the Selot party),</bt><note reference="1:13" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kata &lt;Selot&gt; deng kata &lt;Patriot&gt; pung arti bilang, Simon ni jadi anggota partei politik pro-mardeka. Dong mau usir buang pamarenta Roma dari orang Isra'el pung tana aer.<bt>The word 'Selot' and the word 'Patriot' meanings say that this Simon was a member of the pro-independence political party. They wanted to expel throwing.out the Roma government from the Isra'el peoples' homeland (lit. land-water).</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Yudas (Yakobis pung ana).<bt>and Yudas (Yakobis' child).</bt><note reference="1:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:2-4, Markus 3:16-19, Lukas 6:14-16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Dong samua biasa bakumpul ko sambayang deng satu hati. Dong ju sambayang sama-sama deng Yesus pung mama Maria, barapa parampuan laen, deng Yesus pung adi-adi dong.<bt>They all habitually gathered to pray with one heart. They also prayed together with Yesus' mama Maria, several other women, and Yesus' younger siblings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong ju sambayang sama-sama deng Yesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Dong ju sambayang sama-sama deng Yesus pung mama Maria, deng mama-mama, deng nona-nona, deng Yesus pung adi-adi dong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais satu kali, ju dong bakumpul lai, kira-kira ada saratus dua pulu orang. Tarús Petrus bangun badiri ko omong bilang,<bt>Then one time, and they gathered again, there were approximately 120 people. Next Petrus stood up to speak saying,</bt><v n="16" />&lt;&lt;Mama-bapa deng sodara dong samua! Tantu bosong masi inga sang Yudas, yang dolu bawa dia pung rombongan ko pi tangkap ame sang Yesus. Samua yang kaná deng Yudas tu, memang su musti bagitu. Te dolu-dolu Tuhan Allah pung Roh su pake sang raja Daud ko tulis so'al Yudas bagitu.<bt>"Fathers-mothers and all siblings/cousins! Certainly you-pl still remember Yudas, who before brought his group to go capture Yesus. Everything connected with Yudas truly had to be like that. Cuz (elaboration) a long time ago the Lord God's Spirit used raja Daud to write about Yudas like that.</bt><v n="17" />Dia tu, dolu kotong pung orang. Dia ju iko karjá deng kotong.&gt;&gt;<bt>He was formerly our-inc person (=one of us). He also participated working with us.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />(Ma waktu Yudas su jual abis sang Yesus, ju dia ame itu doi kotor ko pi béli ame tana sapotong. Ais, itu tana jadi dia pung tampa mati, te dia jato matono di situ sampe dia pung parú tabalá, deng dia pung tali parú dong matlolo kaluar.<bt>(But when Yudas has finished selling Yesus, then he took that dirty money to go buy a piece of land. Then, that land became his dying place, cuz (elaboration) he fell face down there until his stomach split open, and his intestines spilled out. [EXEG: In Acts, the Gk grammar indicates Judas bought the land.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doi kotor = dirty money (not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">doi kotor = dirty money (not transparent to Yanto, but UNS's say keep it); doi panas = quickly passed on; jato matono = fall face down; jato malenggang = fall backwards (face up); matlolo = terburai. ke luar, spill out, hang out ; tabalá = ; tapica = ; balia-balia = looking at something one has no right to see</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-08-20 07:21:59Z" /></Annotation><v n="19" />Ais ju orang dong mulai bacarita dari mulu pi mulu sampe samua orang yang tenga di kota Yerusalem su dengar so'al Yudas pung mati tu. Andia ko dong kasi nama itu tana pake dong pung bahasa Aram bilang, <span class="Italic">&lt;Hakeldama&gt;, </span>deng dia pung arti tu &lt;Tana Dara&gt;.)<bt>And then people began to story from mouth to mouth until all the people who stayed/lived in Yerusalem city had heard about that death of Yudas. That is why they named that land using their Aram language saying <span class="Italic">&lt;Hakeldama&gt;,</span> with it's meaning &lt;Blood Land&gt;.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tana dara = tanah (banyak) perawan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tana dara = tanah (banyak) perawan (anak dara Maria) ; *** Akeldama changed to Hakeldama to be more faithful transcription.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:18-19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 27:3-8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Petrus omong tarús lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Dolu-dolu raja Daud su tulis memang bagitu dalam buku Lagu Puji dong. Dia ada tulis bilang,<bt>Petrus continued speaking more saying, “A long time ago (lit. very before) raja Daud wrote like that in the Songs of Praise book. He wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Biar ko dia pung tampa tenga tu, jadi sunyi;<bt>‘Allow it to be that that living place of his, becomes lonely/abandoned;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sonde bole ada orang yang tenga lai di situ.&gt;<bt>there may no longer be people who live there.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais dia ju tulis lai bilang,<bt>Then he also wrote again/further saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Biar dia pung tugas tu, dong kasi pi orang laen sa.&gt;<bt>‘Allow it to be that that work of his, they just give it to another person.’</bt><note reference="1:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 69:25, 109:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21-22" />Jadi kotong musti cari orang ko ganti sang Yudas. Kotong parlú satu orang yang su lama iko sama-sama deng kotong. Dia tu, musti orang yang iko deka-deka deng Tuhan Yesus pi mana-mana, mulai dari Yohanis sarani sang Yesus. Dia ju musti lia sandiri deng dia pung mata biji bilang, Tuhan Yesus su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati, sampe Dia pung nae kambali pi sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), we-inc must look for a person to replace Yudas. We need one person who has gone together with us for a long time. That him [person], must be a person who went close.close with the Lord Yesus all over the place, starting from when Yohanis *baptized Yesus. He must also have seen with his very own eyeballs that the Lord Yesus has lived again from His death, until His going.up again to heaven.”</bt><note reference="1:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 3:16, Markus 1:9, 16:19, Lukas 3:21, 24:51</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Waktu Petrus omong abis bagitu, ais orang yang iko bakumpul di situ kasi maso dua nama. Satu orang pung nama Matias, deng yang satu lai, nama Yusuf, (yang dong biasa pange Barsabas; dia pung nama satu lai, andia Yustus).<bt>When Petrus finished speaking like that, then the people who were gathered there put in two names. One person's name Matias, and the other's name Yusuf, (whom they usually call Barsabas; who also had another name, Yustus.).</bt><v n="24-25" />Ais dong sambayang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa di sorga! Bapa tau batúl samua orang pung isi hati. Yudas su jato mati kasi tenga dia pung karjá. Jadi Bapa kasi tunju sang botong dari dua orang ni, sapa yang Bapa pili ganti sang Yudas, ko botong mau angka dia jadi Tuhan Yesus pung utusan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they prayed saying, “Father in heaven! Father knows the contents of all people's livers. Yudas has fallen died leaving behind his work. Thus Father show us from these two people here, who Father chooses to replace Yudas, so that we can lift/appoint him to become the Lord Yesus' *apostle.”</bt><v n="26" />Ais dong buang lot pake itu dua orang pung nama. Ju itu lot jato kaná sang Matias. Andia ko dong angka sang dia, jadi utusan sama-sama deng dong sablás orang tu.<bt>Then they threw lots using those two people's names. And that lot fell affecting Matias. That's why they raised/appointed him, to become an *apostle together with the eleven of them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hela undi / buang lot"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hela undi / buang lot</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang dong takaná Tuhan Allah pung Roh<bt>People are affected.by Lord God's Spirit</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1-2" />Pas deng orang Yahudi dong pung hari bae yang dong subu bilang, &lt;Hari Pentakosta&gt;,<bt>Exactly when it was the Yahudi people's good day (=holiday) which they call saying, 'Pentakosta Day',</bt><note reference="2:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang Yahudi itong hari bae Pentakosta, mulai dari hari bae Paska, tamba tuju minggu. Deng bagitu kotong tau bilang, Tuhan Yesus pung mati tu, su lima pulu hari.<bt>The Yahudi people count the Pentakosta holiday, starting from the Paska holiday, adding seven weeks. With that we know that that death of the Lord Yesus, was already fifty days.</bt></note>samua orang yang iko sang Tuhan Yesus ada bakumpul di satu ruma.<bt>all the people who previously went.around.with the Lord Yesus were gathered in one house.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="falai = gila (slang from 'fly'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">falai = gila (slang from 'fly' [~she's flying higher than a kite])</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 23:15-21, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 16:9-11</note>Takuju sa, dong dengar ada bunyi datang dari langit sama ke angin tofan. Itu bunyi talalu bésar, sampe orang dong di situ sonde bisa dapa dengar orang laen pung suara lai.<bt>Just unexpectedly/suddenly, they heard a sound come from the sky like a loud wind. That noise was exceedingly big, to the point that people there could not hear another person's voice anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="angin tofan = ; makamiung ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">angin tofan = ; makamiung = loud muffler noise, jet engine bothering ears; bising = BI ; talinga oek = tuli</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ais ju dong dapa lia ke ada api manyala tabagi-bagi pi atas dong satu-satu.<bt>And then they could see like there was fire shining/burning divided-divided (=flames) on top of each one of them.</bt><v n="4" />Ju dong samua takaná Tuhan Allah pung Roh. Ais dong mulai ba'omong pake orang laen dong pung bahasa macam-macam, iko apa yang Roh kasi sang dong ko omong.<bt>And they all were affected by the Lord God's Spirit. Then they began to talk using other people's various languages, according to what the Spirit gave them to speak.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01890b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none">Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi tabagi-bagi pi Yesus pung orang dong<bt>The Lord's *Holy Spirit is divided.out to Yesus' people</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Itu waktu, ada banya orang Yahudi dari macam-macam negrí di anteru dunya datang bakumpul di Yerusalem. Dong pung hati rindu iko sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>At that time, many Yahudi people from all sorts of countries from the entire world had come to gather in Yerusalem. Their livers longed/desired to follow the Lord God.</bt><v n="6" />Waktu dong dapa dengar itu bunyi, ju dong datang makarubu di itu tampa. Dong satu-satu dapa dengar dia pung bahasa sandiri dari Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong pung mulu. Andia ko dong taheran-heran.<bt>When they heard that noise then they came crowding to that place. And they each one could hear his own language from the Lord Yesus' people's mouths. That's why they were amazed. [NOTE to daughter translations: (alternate) /Deng dong satu-satu dapa dengar dong satu-satu pung bahasa/]</bt><v n="7" />Dong samua tanganga, ju dong omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang yang ba'omong dong ni, dong samua orang Galilea, aa?<bt>They all mouth.hanging.open, and they spoke saying, “These people who are speaking, they all are Galilea people, right?</bt><v n="8" />Ma karmana ko kotong dengar dong bisa omong pake kotong satu-satu pung bahasa negrí sandiri?<bt>But how.is.it that we hear them able to speak using each of our own country's languages?</bt><v n="9" />Kotong ni, datang dari propinsi Partia, Media, Elam, Mesopotamia, Yudea, Kapadokia, Pontus, Asia,<bt>We here, come from the provinces of Partia, Media, Elam, Mesopotamia, Yudea, Kapadokia, Pontus, Asia,</bt><v n="10-11" />Frigia, Pamfilia, Masir, dari Libya deka deng kota Kirene; ada ju kotong saparu yang datang dari kota Roma; ada lai yang datang dari pulo Kreta, deng dari tana Arab. Kotong saparu orang Yahudi, deng ada orang dari suku-bangsa laen yang su maso agama Yahudi ju. Ma kotong samua dapa dengar ini orang dong omong pake kotong pung bahasa satu-satu, so'al hal-hal yang luar biasa, yang Tuhan Allah su bekin. Awii! Kotong heran mau mati na!&gt;&gt;<bt>Frigia, Pamfilia, Masir, from Libya near Kirene city; there are also some of us who come from Roma city; there are others who come from Kreta island, and from Arab land. Some of us are Yahudi people, and there are also people from other ethnic groups who have entered the Yahudi religion. But we all can hear these people speak using each of our languages, an event/affair that is extra-ordinary, which the Lord God has done. Awii [+amazement]! We are extremely amazed obviously!” [DISCOURSE: restructured for information load and type.]</bt></p>
    <fig path="maps\Bible\Hk-pent.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none">Orang datang bakumpul di Yerusalem dari ini negrí dong<bt>From these countries, people came gathering in Yerusalem</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dong samua tanganga, ko dong batanya satu deng satu bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana ko bisa jadi bagitu, é? Dia pung arti apa tu?&gt;&gt;<bt>They all mouth.hangging.open (were amazed), in order that they asked each other saying, “How can it happen like that? What is the meaning of it?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ma ada orang laen yang olok-olok sang dong. Itu orang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Jang toe sang dong! Te dong tu, ada mabok barát na!&gt;&gt;<bt>But there were other other people who ridiculed them. Those people said, “Weh [+critical]! Don't pay.attention to them! Cuz (elaboration) those people are heavily drunk!” [EXEG: ‘new wine’ undertranslated; would be unnatural in context and heavy information load to force it.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus angka omong di orang banya<bt>Petrus begins to talk [implied w/authority or right to speak] to many people</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="angka bicara/omong implies authority or right"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">angka bicara/omong implies authority or right to speak</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Di situ ada Petrus deng Tuhan Yesus pung sablás utusan laen dong. Ais dia maju pi muka ko angka omong kasi itu orang banya dong yang ada makarubu di situ. Dia omong kuat-kuat bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa-bapa, mama-mama, deng sodara-sodara dong samua! Bosong yang orang Yahudi, deng bosong yang datang tenga di ini kota Yerusalem! Pasang talinga bae-bae ko dengar beta pung omong ni, te ada hal pantíng yang beta mau kasi tau sang bosong samua.<bt>There there was Petrus and the Lord Yesus' other eleven *apostles. Then he went.forward to the front in order to begin to talk [with authority/right/formal] to those many people who had coming crowding.around there. He spoke loudly saying, “Fathers, mothers, and all siblings/cousins! You who are Yahudi people, and you who have come stay in this Yerusalem city! Attach your ears well (=pay attention) to hear this talking of mine, cuz (elaboration) there is/are important thing/s which I want to tell to all of you.</bt><v n="15" />Bosong jang kira ini orang dong ada mabo. Sonde mungkin bagitu! Inga, te sonde ada orang yang minum mabo papagi hari. Apalai sakarang baru jam sambilan!<bt>Don't think these people are drunk. It's not possible like that! Remember, cuz (elaboration) there are no people who drink drunk really early in the morning. Especially now it's only nine o'clock!</bt><v n="16" />Bosong dengar ini orang dong ba'omong pake bosong satu-satu pung bahasa. Yang batúl bagini: itu waktu, Tuhan Allah su kasi tau memang ini hal pake Dia pung jubir Yoel bilang:<bt>You hear these people speaking using each of your languages. What is true is like this: at that time the Lord God had already (fore)told this thing using his *prophet Yoel, saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17" />&lt;Tuhan Allah omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti kalo hari-hari su mau abis,<bt>‘The Lord God speaks saying, “Later when the days are wanting to finish,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta mau po'a kasi Beta pung Roh pi samua orang.<bt>I will pour.out My Spirit to all people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Bosong pung ana nyong dong, deng bosong pung ana nona dong,<bt>Your-pl young.male children and your young.female children,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti Beta pake jadi Beta pung jubir.<bt>I will use to become My *prophets.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Bosong pung ana muda dong,<bt>Your young children,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti dapa lia apa yang Beta mau kasi tunju sang dong.<bt>later will be.able.to see what I want to show them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng bosong pung orang tua dong,<bt>And your old people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti dapa mimpi apa yang Beta mau kasi lia sang dong.<bt>later will be.able.to dream what I want to show them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />Pas di waktu hari-hari yang su mau abis tu,<bt>Exactly when those days want to be finishing,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta kasi Beta pung Roh pi Beta pung tukang suru-suru dong.<bt>I will give My Spirit to My servants.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pi di Beta pung ana-ana dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pi di Beta pung ana-ana dong samua.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Beta kasi pi di laki-laki dong,<bt>I will give it to the males,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng Beta ju kasi pi di parampuan dong.<bt>and I will also give it to the females.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti dong omong apa yang Beta kasi tau sang dong.<bt>Later they will speak what I tell them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi sang (path to goal); kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kasi sang (path to goal); kasi di (location at goal); tingka ke</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="19-21" />Nanti Tuhan pung Hari sampe. Itu Hari balóm datang,<bt>Later there will arrive the Lord's Day. That Day will not yet have come,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Beta bekin lebe dolo tanda-tanda heran di langit di atas.<bt>but I will do beforehand amazing signs in the sky above.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Tanda heran ke matahari jadi galáp;<bt>Amazing signs like the sun becoming dark;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng bulan ju jadi mera sama ke dara.<bt>and the moon also becoming red like blood.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta ju mau bekin hal-hal luar biasa di bumi di bawa.<bt>I also will make/do extraordinary things on the earth below.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Itu hal dong, tingka ke dara, api, deng asap kabuak-kabuak nae pi atas.<bt>Those things, [will be] like blood, fire, and smoke in glumps rising up.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaboak = a glump, satu kumpulan,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kaboak = a glump, satu kumpulan, bumbungan, bunch, falungku</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti sampe Tuhan pung hari-hari yang luar biasa tu, orang yang batarea minta tolong sang Tuhan Allah,<bt>Later arriving at those extraordinary days of the Lord, a/the person who shouts requesting help from the Lord God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong tu yang dapa salamat.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>those are who will be saved.’”</bt><note reference="2:17-21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 2:28-32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu tu, yang dolu Yoel su tulis.<bt>That there, what beforehand Yoel has said.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01891b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none">Petrus omong kasi sang orang banya dong<bt>Petrus speaks to many people</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Naa! Sodara-sodara orang Isra'el dong! Bosong pasang talinga ko dengar apa yang beta mau omong sakarang. Tuhan Allah su tunju ame sang Yesus, orang Nasaret tu. Botong su tau bilang, itu batúl, tagal botong su lia sandiri Tuhan Allah pake Yesus ko bekin tanda-tanda heran deng hal-hal luar biasa. Bosong ju su tau ini hal, tagal Yesus su bekin itu tanda heran dong di bosong pung teng-tenga.<bt>So! Israel people siblings! You attach your ears to hear what I want to say now. The Lord God has shown Yesus, that Nasaret person. You all know that that's true, because you yourselves have seen God use Yesus to do amazing signs and extraordinary things. You also already know this thing, because Yesus has made those amazing signs in the midst of you.</bt><v n="23" />Ma bosong bunu bekin mati sang Dia, andia bosong pi buju orang jahat ko dong paku sang Dia di kayu palang. Padahal Tuhan Allah su tau itu samua dari dolu-dolu, yang memang pas deng Dia pung rancana.<bt>But you murdered killed him, that is you went to persuade evil people in order that they nailed Him on a *cross. Nevertheless, Lord God's already knew all that from long ago, and it fit perfectly with His plans.</bt><note reference="2:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 27:35, Markus 15:24, Lukas 23:33, Yohanis 19:18</note><v n="24" />Memang bosong bekin bagitu sampe Dia su mati batúl. Ma Tuhan Allah sonde mau ko Yesus mati tarús. Andia ko Tuhan buka kasi lapás sang Dia dari mati pung kuasa, deng kasi idop kambali sang Dia. Te mati pung kuasa sonde bisa ontong sang Dia na.<bt>It's true that you did like that to the point that He really died. But the Lord God didn't want for Yesus to stay dead. That's why the Lord undid/unfastened/released freeing Him from the power/authority of death and made Him live again. Cuz (elaboration) the power/authority of death could not gain advantage/overcome Him [+obvious]. [EXEG: earlier versions were skewed from the Indonesian Apostles' Creed toward ‘place of dead people’, rather than ‘death’. While vs. 27 &amp; 31 mention Hades, it skews the meaning and raises doctrinal problems here, so it had to be reworked. Bruce, NRSV, NLT, CEV.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if the personification of “mati pung kuasa” doesn't work in other lgs, try “kasi lapás sang Dia dari Dia pung mati...” (which is a bit narrow, but at least it works).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kodo ame ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kodo ame =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Tuhan Allah su kasi idop"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Ma Tuhan Allah su kasi idop ulang sang Dia dari teng-tenga orang mati. Dunia orang mati su kodo ame sang Dia, ma Tuhan Allah su kasi lapás kaluar sang Dia, te mustahil dunya orang mati bisa tahan ame sang Dia tarús di situ. Ma Tuhan Allah sonde mau ko Yesus tenga tarús di orang mati dong pung tampa. Andia ko Tuhan angka kasi lapás sang Dia dari orang mati dong, deng kasi idop kambali sang Dia.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 28:5-6, Markus 16:6, Lukas 24:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Dolu-dolu raja Daud su tulis memang so'al Yesus tu, bagini:<bt>Long ago raja Daud wrote about that matter/issue of Yesus like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Beta tau Tuhan salalu ada sama-sama deng beta.<bt>I know the Lord is always with me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko sonde ada satu apa ju yang bisa kasi jato sang beta,<bt>That's why there is not a single thing that can make me fall,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal Tuhan Allah salalu ada di beta pung sablá.<bt>because the Lord God is always at my side.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rebis = side, sablá"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">rebis = side, sablá</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="26" />Andia ko beta pung dalam hati sanáng;<bt>That's why my inner liver is happy;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lu sonde tau beta pung dalam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lu sonde tau beta pung dalam hati</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ju beta puji-puji tarús sang Dia,<bt>and I continually praise Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng beta tanáng-tanáng tunggu sang Tuhan sa.<bt>and I peacefully-peacefully (being in a settled, not worried state) just wait for Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="27" />Te Dia sonde kasi biar beta pung roh tenga tarús di orang mati dong pung tampa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He will not leave my spirit to remain continually in the dead people's place.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="roh yang tenga kalo orang su"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">roh yang tenga kalo orang su mati</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Tuhan sonde kasi biar Dia pung Orang Barisi pung mayat jadi busuk dalam kubur.<bt>And the Lord will not allow the corpse of His *Holy/Clean Person to become rotten in the grave.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati culas = Ant of hati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hati culas = Ant of hati barisi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="28" />Tuhan su kasi tunju sang beta jalan idop yang batúl.<bt>The Lord has shown me the correct path/road of life.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko beta pung hati sanáng mau mati,<bt>That's why My liver is exceedingly happy,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko Tuhan ada sama-sama deng beta na.&gt;<bt>because obviously God is together with me.’</bt><note reference="2:25-28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 16:8-11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu tu yang dolu raja Daud su tulis.<bt>That there is what raja Daud wrote beforehand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Naa, sodara dong samua! Sakarang kasi isin sang beta dolo, ko beta omong taráng-taráng deng bosong so'al kotong pung ba'i Daud. Dia omong bagitu, ma dia sonde tunju dia pung badan sandiri. Tagal dia su mati, deng su kubur sang dia. Dia pung kubur masi ada di kotong pung teng-tenga sampe ini hari.<bt>Naa, [+shift] all you siblings/cousins! Now give permission to me, in order that I speak openly with you-pl about the matter of that Gf/Ff Daud of ours-inc. He spoke like that, but he was not pointing at his own body. Because he has already died, and they have already buried him. His grave is still in our midst until this day.</bt><v n="30" />Raja Daud tu, jadi Tuhan Allah pung jubir satu. Deng dia tau bilang, Tuhan su janji pake sumpa bilang, Daud pung turunan satu nanti pegang parenta, andia itu Orang yang Tuhan su tunju memang dari dolu.<bt>That Raja Daud, became the Lord God's spokesperson. And he knew that the Lord had promised using an oath saying, one of Daud's descendants would later hold power/authority, that is that person whom the Lord had already chosen from beforehand.</bt><note reference="2:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 132:11, 2 Samuel 7:12-13</note><v n="31" />Itu waktu, Daud lia jao pi muka. Deng dia kasi tau lebe dolo so'al itu Orang yang Tuhan su tunju memang. Nanti itu Orang mati, ma Dia ju idop kambali. Ais Daud ju bilang itu Orang sonde tenga tarús di orang mati dong pung tampa, deng dia pung mayat sonde jadi busuk.<bt>At that time, Daud was looking far to the front [future]. And he told ahead of time the matter of that Person whom God had chosen. Later that Person will die, but He will also live again. Then Daud also said that Person would not stay continually in the dead people's place, and his corpse would not become rotten.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Itu Orang yang Daud su bilang-bilang tu, andia Yesus! Tuhan Allah su kasi idop kambali sang Dia dari Dia pung mati. Ais ko botong samua ni su lia Dia pung idop kambali deng botong pung mata biji sandiri na!<bt>That person whom Daud was talking about, it's that Yesus! The Lord God made Him live again from His death. Then we-exc all here obviously saw His living again with your very own eyes!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bilang-bilang = was talking about;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bilang-bilang = was talking about;</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Deng sakarang ni, Tuhan Allah su angka sang Yesus ko pegang pangkat yang paling tinggi. Ais Dia ada dudu di Tuhan pung sablá kanan di tampa yang Tuhan su sadia memang. Deng Dia pung Bapa su kasi sang Dia, Bapa pung Roh yang Barisi tu, parsís ke Tuhan su janji memang dari dolu. Te Dia janji mau kasi Dia pung Roh Barisi tu, kasi sang kotong ju. Jadi, yang bosong ada dengar deng bosong ada lia sakarang ni, andia Tuhan ada kasi Dia pung Roh.<bt>And now, the Lord God has raised Yesus to hold the rank that is the very highest. Then He is sitting at the Lord's right hand in a place that the Lord has prepared [ahead of time]. And His Father has given Him, that *Holy Spirit of Father's, exactly like what the Lord promised from beforehand. Cuz (elaboration) He promised to give that *Holy Spirit of His, to us-inc also. That which you-pl are hearing and you are seeing now, that is God giving His Spirit. [EXEG: Greek does not make the inclusive-exclusive distinction, and neither does English, so most commentaries do not address the issue. Some Back Translations do show that others have gone with the exclusive reading here, and I understand why that makes sense. From consultant input, we chose us-inc deliberately, from the higher level discourse context. We felt that Peter is trying to bring the audience on board by saying the promise of the Holy Spirit (from Joel, etc) was also intended for Peter's audience. I think this is correct, but it is not actually until Acts 10-11 that Peter becomes more overtly aware of this. So there are pros and cons for both positions.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan Allah su angka sang Dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Tuhan Allah su angka sang Dia pi di tampa yang paling tinggi deng kasi sang Dia kuasa, abis ju Dia tarima Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Allah Bapa su janji memang ko mau kasi sang Dia.</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2018-11-09 00:08:30Z" /></Annotation><v n="34" />Daud sandiri sonde nae pi sorga, ma dia tulis bilang,<bt>Daud himself did not go.up to heaven, but he wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Tuhan Allah ada omong deng beta pung Bos bilang,<bt>‘The Lord God has spoken with my Boss saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;&lt;Dudu di Beta pung sablá kanan di tampa yang Beta su sadia memang,<bt>&lt;&lt;Sit at My right hand in the place which I have already prepared [ahead of time],</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">
      <v n="35" />sampe Beta bekin Lu pung musu dong ta'alok sang Lu.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>until I make your-sg enemies surrender/subjugate to You.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ta'alok = menyerah-kalah, takhluk;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ta'alok = menyerah-kalah, takhluk;</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:34-35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Andia ko samua orang Isra'el musti tau batúl-batúl so'al itu Yesus yang bosong su paku bekin mati di kayu palang. Dia tu, Kristus yang Tuhan Allah su pili memang dari dolu. Deng Dia yang hak parenta sang kotong ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>That's why all the Israel people must truly-truly know about that Yesus whom you nail killing on that cross. He is the Kristus, whom the Lord God forechose from long ago. And He also has the say-so/ordering rights over us-inc!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Dengar bagitu, ju orang dong pung hati tatusuk memang. Ju dong tanya sang Petrus deng utusan laen dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu dong! Ais botong musti bekin apa lai?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, then the people's livers were really pierced (=sad and regret). And they asked Petrus and the other apostles saying, “Elder.brothers! Then what else must we do?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati tatusuk = sedih dan menyesal;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hati tatusuk = sedih dan menyesal;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ju Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong satu-satu musti kasi tenga bosong pung dosa-dosa dong deng bosong pung sala-sala dong samua, ko iko kambali sang Tuhan. Ais itu, bosong musti minta ko dapa sarani, ko jadi tanda bilang, bosong su bale iko Yesus Kristus pung Jalan Idop. Itu ju jadi tanda bilang, Tuhan su hapus buang bosong pung sala-sala dong. Ais bosong ju dapa Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi.<bt>And Petrus replied saying, “Each one of you must leave all your *sins and your *wrongs, to follow in return the Lord. After that, you must request to be *baptised, as a sign that you have turned to follow Yesus Kristus' life path. That will also become a sign saying the Lord has erased thrown away your *wrongs. And/Then you will also get the Lord God's *Holy Spirit.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Te Tuhan Allah su janji memang itu hal kasi sang samua orang yang maso jadi Dia pung orang. Deng bagitu, Dia pung janji tu, kasi sang bosong deng bosong pung turunan. Dia ju janji kasi orang laen dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the Lord God has already promised that thing/matter to all people who enter to become His people. In that way, His promise is for you-pl and your descendants. He also promised [it] to other people.” [NOTE to daughter translations: if it is not clear that /orang laen/ means non-Jews, then use an equivalent of /orang bangsa laen/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te Tuhan Allah su janji memang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Te Tuhan Allah su janji memang itu hal kasi sang bosong, deng bosong pung turunan, deng samua orang yang ada tenga di tampa-tampa yang jao-jao; andia samua orang yang Tuhan Allah pange sang dong datang sang Dia.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Petrus masi omong panjang lebar sang dong bagitu ko kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sakarang banya orang su serong dari jalan idop yang batúl. Andia ko bosong musti ati-ati, ko bosong jang iko orang jahat dong pung jalan. Ma bosong musti iko Tuhan Allah pung jalan lurus sa. Deng bagitu bosong dapa salamat ko idop tarús deng Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Petrus still spoke long wide (=on and on) with them like that in order to tell them saying, “Now many people have strayed/deviated from the correct life path. That's why you-pl must becareful, so that you don't follow evil people's path. But you must just follow the Lord God's straight path. In.that.way you will get *saved/rescued to live continually with Him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasasar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kasasar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ais ju itu orang banya dong tarima Petrus pung omong kasi sang dong. Ju dong maso iko Yesus pung Jalan Idop, deng dong minta ko sarani sang dong. Itu hari ju ada tiga ribu orang yang maso bagabung deng Yesus pung orang dong.<bt>And then those many people accepted that speaking of Petrus to them. And they entered following Yesus' Life Path, and they requested in order that they be *baptised. That day then there were three thousand people who entered joining with Yesus' people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Banya orang dong parcaya apa yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Banya orang dong parcaya apa yang Petrus bilang, ju sarani sang dong. Itu hari orang parcaya pung jumlah nae sampe tiga ribu orang.</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Dong suka bakumpul sama-sama deng orang laen yang iko Yesus. Deng dong bae-bae satu deng satu. Tiap-tiap hari dong rajin dengar Tuhan Yesus pung utusan dong pung ajaran. Dong suka sambayang sama-sama. Deng dong ju suka makan sama-sama.<bt>They liked to gather together with other people who followed Yesus. And they were in.a.state.of.good.relationships with each other. Every day they faithfully listened to teaching from the Lord Yesus' apostles. They like to *pray/worship together. And they also liked to eat together.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong samua sarakan diri ko iko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Dong samua sarakan diri ko iko ajaran dari utusan-utusan dong deng dong salalu bakumpul sama-sama. Dong dudu makan sama-sama deng ibadat sama-sama.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang parcaya dong pung cara idop<bt>The *believers' way of live</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Itu waktu, Tuhan pung utusan dong bekin banya tanda heran, sampe samua orang dong taheran-heran deng taku.<bt>At that time, the Lord's apostles did many amazing signs, to the point that all (sorts.of) people were amazed and afraid.</bt><v n="44" />Itu orang dong yang iko Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop tu, bakumpul deng idop satu hati, sampe apa sa yang dong pung, dong pake sama-sama.<bt>Those people who followed that Life Path of the Lord Yesus, gathered and lived with one liver (in one accord), to the point that what ever they had, they used [it] together.</bt><note reference="2:44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 4:32-35</note><v n="45" />Ais ada yang bajual dong pung barang-barang deng dong pung harta milik, ju dong babagi dia pung doi kasi pi orang parcaya dong, iko satu-satu pung parlú.<bt>Then there were those who sold their things and their inheritance possessions, and they divided its money to the believers, according to each of the needs. [NOTE to daughter translations: some languages require it to be /pi orang parcaya laen dong/, but in Kupang that suggests they were elsewhere, whereas in this context it is talking about believers in Jerusalem.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="papalele = commerce, bajual cari ontong;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">papalele = commerce, bajual cari ontong; harta milik = (n) pusaka</Message></Annotation><v n="46" />Tiap hari dong suka bakumpul di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Dong makan ba'iko-iko dari satu ruma pi satu ruma deng hati sanáng. Deng dong samua idop suka batolong satu deng satu, deng dong sonde kake'ek.<bt>Every day they liked to gather at the Lord God's *Temple. They ate moving from one house to another house and with happy livers. And they all lived liking to help each other, and they were not stingy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sakikir = stingy, kikir; kake'ek ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sakikir = stingy, kikir; kake'ek = sakikir</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deng dong samua idop deng sederhana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">deng dong samua idop deng sederhana di satu-satu pung ruma</Message></Annotation><v n="47" />Saban hari dong samua angka nae puji sang Tuhan Allah sonde putus-putus. Samua orang luar dong suka mau mati deng dong. Tiap hari Tuhan Allah kasi salamat orang, ais dong maso ko bagabung deng Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong. Ais dong tamba banya tarús.<bt>Every day they all kept lifting praises to the Lord God without stopping. All the outside people really-really liked them. Every day the Lord God *saved people, and they entered to join with the Lord Yesus's people. Thus they continually increased greatly.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus bekin bae satu orang lumpu<bt>Petrus heals a crippled person</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pincang = limp, like polio"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pincang = limp, like polio</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Satu hari, jam tiga sore, Petrus deng Yohanis pi Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat ko mau sambayang deng orang laen dong.<bt>One day, at 3 o'clock in the afternoon, Petrus and Yohanis went to the *Temple to pray with other people.</bt><v n="2" />Dong mau maso iko satu pintu garbáng, nama &lt;Pintu Indah&gt;. Di situ dong dapa lia satu laki-laki yang dia pung kaki lumpu memang mulai dari dia pung mama barana sang dia. Tiap hari orang dong dongko bawa sang dia pi itu tampa, ko dia bisa minta-minta dari sapa sa yang mau maso pi itu Ruma Sambayang Pusat.<bt>They were about to enter through a gate(of village,compound) named 'Beautiful Gate/Door'. There they saw a male whose crippled foot/leg started from when his mama gave birth to him. Every day people carried(on.back) brought him to that place, so that he could repeatedly.ask/beg from just whoever was wanting to enter to go to that *Temple.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koko = like a child, difficult"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">koko = like a child, difficult for an adult; dongko = carry on back, piggyback</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Waktu dia dapa lia Petrus deng Yohanis ada mau maso pi dalam, ju dia sorong tangan ko minta bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa dong! Kasian sang beta doo. Kasi beta apa, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>When he saw Petrus and Yohanis were wanting to go inside, then he put out his hand to request saying, “Papa (plural)! Have pity on me, come on. Give me something, [+tag]?”</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01895b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Petrus deng Yohanis lia itu orang kaki lumpu<bt>Petrus and Yohanis see that person with a lame foot/leg</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dong dua lia bae-bae sang dia, ais Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu! Lia sini dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>They two looked closely at him, and then Petrus said, “Elder.brother! Look here!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ju itu orang angka muka ko lia sang dong dua, deng dia ada pikir-pikir kata, &lt;&lt;We! Dong dua ni, pasti mau kasi apa-apa sang beta ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>And that person lifted face to look at the two of them, and he was thinking (to himself) saying, “We! These two here, surely want to give something to me now.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apa-apa = sst, something (not question)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">apa-apa = sst, something (not question)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ma Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu! Beta sonde ada doi satu sen ju. Ma beta mau kasi sang bu apa yang beta ada sakarang. Bu dengar bae-bae, é! Deng kuasa dari Yesus Kristus, itu orang Nasaret tu, beta suru bu bangun badiri ko jalan su!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus said, “Elder.brother! I don't have even one cent. But I will give what I have now. Elder.brother listen carefully, ok! With power from Yesus Kristus, that Nasaret person, I order you to get.up stand.up to walk (imperative)!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peser = (kuno) satu sen bagi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">peser = (kuno) satu sen bagi dua ; figurative money of no value; sen = ; bajalan = tapaleuk (random goal) aimless.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais Petrus pegang itu orang lumpu pung tangan kanan, ko tolong hela kasi badiri sang dia. Itu waktu ju dia pung kaki dong bae memang.<bt>Then Petrus held that lame person's right hand, to help pull making him stand.up. And at that time his feet were truly well/healed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mata kaki = ankle"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">mata kaki = ankle</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Takuju sa, dia malompa badiri, ais mulai bajalan pi-datang, ko coba dia pung kaki. Ais itu, dia iko maso pi dalam Ruma Sambayang sama-sama deng dong dua. Dia jalan malompa-malompa deng puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Suddenly/unexpectedly he jumped standing, after.that begain to walk back-and-forth, to try.out his feet. After that he followed entered into the Temple together with those two. He walked, jumping and praising the Lord God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="malompa = leap up; malompa-malompa ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">malompa = leap up; malompa-malompa = jump around; malompa ~ balompa</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ais samua orang dapa lia sang dia bajalan deng puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Then all people could see him walking and praising the Lord God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Waktu dong kanál sang dia, ju dong tanganga, ko bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia ni, andia itu orang lumpu tukang minta-minta yang suka dudu di Pintu Indah, aa? Karmana ko bisa bagitu, é?&gt;&gt;<bt>When they knew/recognised him, then they mouth.hanging.open, to say, “Him here, is that blind beggar who likes to sit at that Beautiful Gate, right? How can it be like this?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="wuang = conf tag like bukan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">wuang = conf tag like bukan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus angka omong di Ruma Sambayang Pusat<bt>Petrus begins to speak(with authority) in/at the *Temple</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais, itu orang iko deka-deka sang Petrus deng Yohanis. Dong tiga sampe di satu ruma loos yang dia pung nama &lt;Ruma Loos Raja Soleman&gt;. Ju samua orang datang makarubu sang dong deng taheran-heran.<bt>Then, that person followed closely with Petrus and Yohanis. They three arrived at a pavilion/free standing building with no walls called &lt;King Soleman's Pavilion/Freestanding Building&gt;. And all the people came crowding around them with amazement.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="emper = téras, porch, courtyard; ruma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">emper = téras, porch, courtyard; ruma los = tukang pung bengkel, aula, large interior with no rooms and/or no walls</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Waktu Petrus lia itu orang dong, ju dia angka omong bilang, &lt;&lt;We, orang Isra'el dong! Akurang ko sodara dong heran lia ini hal? Akurang ko bosong maen lia-lia tarús sang botong? Bosong kira kata, ini orang bisa jalan tagal botong ada pake ilmu, ko, tagal botong rajin iko sang Tuhan Allah? Ko, karmana?<bt>When Petrus saw those people, then he began to speak (formally) saying, “We! [+get attention] Israel people! Why are siblings/cousins (=you-pl) amazed looking at this thing? Why are you continually looking at us-exc? Do you think that this person can walk because we have used magic, or because we are persistent/enthusiastic in following the Lord God? Or, how.is.it?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="botong pung bekin ; pake ilmu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">botong pung bekin ; pake ilmu ; le'u-le'u = jimat; kata as complementiser;</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Beta mau kasi tau bagini: kotong pung nene-moyang dong, andia ba'i Abraham, ba'i Isak, deng ba'i Yakob, sémba sang Tuhan Allah. Itu Tuhan tu, yang su angka nae tinggi-tinggi Dia pung Orang yang Dia su pili tu, andia Yesus. Yesus tu, andia Orang yang tempo hari bosong su angka buang deng sarakan sang Dia pi di gubernor Pilatus. Te gubernor mau kasi lapás sang Dia, ma bosong malawan dia pung mau, ko biar jang lapás sang Yesus.<bt>I'm going to explain it like this: Our-inc ancestors, that is Gf Abraham, Gf Isak, and Gf Yakob, worshipped the Lord God. That Lord that, is the one who has raised lifting up high-high that Person of His whom He has chosen, that is Yesus. That Yesus, that's the Person whom previously you-pl picked.up throwing.away and surrendered Him to gubernur Pilatus. Cuz (elaboration) the gubernur wanted to free Him, but you opposed his will, so that it.wouldn't happen to free that Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="songgo = agama suku, sembah pada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">songgo = agama suku, sembah pada batu-batu, dsb. overtones of setan-setan (UNS's say the same); ba'i-moyang; mau-mau = desire, keinginan</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 3:15</note><v n="14" />Ma Yesus tu, satu Orang yang sonde ada pung sala. Dia pung hati bae. Gubernor mau kasi lapás itu Orang yang sonde ada pung sala tu, ma bosong samua malawan sang dia. Ais yang lebe jahat lai, bosong tusu-tusu ko suru dia kasi lapás satu orang jahat, yang tukang bunu orang, ko kasi pulang sang bosong.<bt>But that Yesus, was a Person who didn't have wrongs. His liver was good. The Gubernur wanted to free that person who didn't have wrongs, but you all opposed him. Then what's even more evil, you poked.and.poked (=keep on fanning the flame to incite s.o.) to order him to free an evil person, who was a murderer, to let him go home with you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tusu-tusu = bujuk; noki-noki = ask"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tusu-tusu = bujuk; noki-noki = ask persistently (positive), beg (but not as beggar), different from nag</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 27:15-23, Markus 15:6-14, Lukas 23:13-23, Yohanis 19:12-15</note><v n="15" />Ais bosong yang bunu bekin mati sang Yesus. Padahal Dia yang jadi akar dari samua yang idop. Memang Dia su mati, ma Tuhan Allah su kasi idop kambali sang Dia dari Dia pung mati. Deng Dia ni yang botong su lia sandiri deng botong pung mata biji.<bt>Then you murdered killed Yesus. Even though He is the root/source of all that lives. Indeed he died, but the Lord God raised Him again from that death of His. And He is the one whom we-exc have seen with our own eyeballs. [EXEG: Gk ‘author/source of life’.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Naa, bosong su kanál ini orang lumpu ni. Sakarang dia su kuat, ma bukan botong yang bekin bae sang dia. Botong sonde ada pung kuasa apa-apa. Itu kuasa datang dari Yesus sa. Ini orang su jadi kuat kambali, tagal dia parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus. Te Yesus tu, yang su bekin bae sang dia di bosong pung muka.<bt>Now you know this lame person here. Now he is strong, but it is not we-exc who healed him. We don't have any power [what so ever]. That power came only from Yesus. This person has become strong again, because he believed in the Lord Yesus. Cuz (elaboration) that Yesus, is the one who healed him in front of your faces.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Sodara dong samua! Sakarang beta tau bilang, bosong, deng bosong pung bos-bos dong, su bekin jahat sang Yesus, ma bosong sonde tau dia pung akibat dong.<bt>All siblings/cousins! Now I know that you, and your bosses, have done evil to that Yesus, but you didn't know it's consequence/result.</bt><v n="18" />Ma Tuhan Allah su kasi tau memang dari dolu-kala pake Dia pung jubir dong bilang, Kristus, andia itu Orang yang Dia su pili tu, musti pikol sangsara. Deng sakarang itu hal su jadi.<bt>But the Lord God has told ahead of time from way before using his spokespersons, saying the Kristus, that is that Person whom He chose must shoulder.carry suffering/tribulation. And now that thing has happened.</bt><v n="19" />Tagal itu, bosong musti bale kasi tenga bosong pung sala-sala dong, deng kambali pi Tuhan Allah, ko biar Dia hapus buang deng sonde inga lai sang bosong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>Because of that, you must turn leaving behind your *wrongs, and return to the Lord God, so that it will.happen that He erases throws.aways and doesn't remember anymore your wrongs. [NOTE to daughter translations: if the double ‘forgive’ style is heavy in your RL, reduce to /hapus buang/.]</bt><v n="20" />Tuhan Allah nanti kasi kuat bosong pung hati. Deng Tuhan Allah ju mau kirim kambali kasi sang bosong, itu Kristus yang Dia su pili. Deng itu Kristus tu, andia Yesus yang Dia su parná kirim datang kasi sang bosong.<bt>The Lord God will later make your livers strong. And the Lord God also will send in.return to you, that Kristus whom he chose. And that Kristus, that is Yesus whom he once/past sent to come to you.</bt><v n="21" />Dari dolu-kala, Tuhan su omong pake Dia pung jubir dong bilang, &lt;Tuhan Allah nanti bekin lurus samua hal sampe samua jadi baru.&gt; Ais Yesus musti tunggu di Dia pung Tampa yang Barisi sampe Dia pung waktu datang, ko Dia bekin baru samua hal.<bt>From way before, the Lord spoke using his *spokespersons saying, 'The Lord God will later make straight all things to the point that all becomes new.' Then Yesus must wait at His *Holy Place until His time come, for Him to make new all things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia musti tenga di sorga sampe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Dia musti tenga di sorga sampe Tuhan Allah bekin samua parkara jadi baru iko parsís apa yang Dia su bilang dari dolu lewat Dia pung jubir.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dolu-dolu, ba'i Musa ju parná omong kasi orang Isra'el bilang,<bt>Long ago, grandfather/forefather Musa once spoke to the people of Isra'el saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Bosong pung Tuhan Allah yang hak parenta sang bosong, nanti utus satu Orang dari bosong ko jadi Dia pung jubir, sama ke Dia pake sang beta jadi Dia pung jubir. Jadi bosong musti pasang talinga ko dengar samua-samua yang Dia mau kasi tau sang bosong.<bt>'Your-pl Lord God who has the say-so/ordering rights over you, later will commission a Person from you to become His spokesperson, just.as He used me to become His spokesperson. So (consequently) you must fasten your ears (=pay attention) to hear all that He wants to tell you.</bt><note reference="3:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 18:15, 18</note><v n="23" />Ma orang yang sonde mau dengar bae-bae itu Orang pung omong tu, nanti tapisa buang dari Tuhan pung orang dong. Ais sonde ada pung hak lai deng dong.&gt;<bt>But whoever doen't listen/obey well what that Person says, will be separated off/cut off from God2's people. So/then, (s/he) no longer has any rights with them.’ [EXEG: Gk here is not perish, but the translation comes out the same. It is built on /maso/ ‘enter’ becoming His people, and/or being separated/excluded/cut off.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma orang yang sonde kasi dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Ma orang yang sonde kasi dia pung talinga ko dengar apa yang itu jubir omong, itu orang nanti tabuang kaluar dari Tuhan Allah pung orang-orang dong, abis dia ilang parcuma sa. Ma sapa yang sonde mau dengar bae-bae itu Orang pung omong tu, nanti Tuhan iskarobis buang sang dia dari Tuhan pung orang dong, deng kasi ancor sang dia.&gt;<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="onslak = pecat ***revised"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">onslak = pecat ***revised</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 18:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Bukan cuma ba'i Musa sa yang omong bagitu. Te Tuhan ju pake orang-orang laen dong, ko jadi Dia pung jubir, deng dong ada kasi tau bagitu ju. Sama ke itu waktu Tuhan su pake sang ba'i Samuel, ko kasi tau hal-hal yang kotong sakarang ada lia deng kotong pung mata biji sandiri.<bt>It wasn't only just Gf/Ff Musa who spoke like that. Cuz (elaboration) the Lord also used (various) other people, to become His spokespersons, and they also told like that. Like the time the Lord used Gf/Ff Samuel, to tell things which we-inc now are seeing with our very own eyeballs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Samua utusan-utusan yang Tuhan Allah perna"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Samua utusan-utusan yang Tuhan Allah perna utus datang ko kasi tau Dia pung kabar bae, mulai dari jubir Semuel deng jubir-jubir laen yang datang dari balakang. Dong samua datang kasi tau tentang ini zaman.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Tuhan Allah ju janji kasi sang kotong pung ba'i Abraham bilang,<bt>The Lord God also promised to our-inc grandfather/ancestor Abraham saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Dari lu pung turunan, nanti Beta kasi berkat sang samua suku-bangsa di ini dunya.&gt;<bt>'From your descendant/s, later I will give blessing to all the ethnic groups/nations in the world.’</bt><note reference="3:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 22:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa! Itu janji-janji yang Tuhan kasi jubir dolu-dolu dong tu, sakarang su jadi di bosong, andia beta pung sodara-sodara bangsa Isra'el dong.<bt>Naa! [shift] Those promises which God2 gave those spokespeople of long ago, now have happened/come to be/become reality among you, that is my Israeli brothers. [DISCOURSE: cohesion with vs.12] [EXEG: Bruce “in the sense that they were heirs of the promises made by God through the prophets, promises which had found their fulfilment before their very eyes. So too, they were “sons of the covenant” made by God with Abraham, and that in a special sense, for they had lived to see the day when that covenant was realized in Christ:”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** tightened up for lexical cohesion"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** tightened up for lexical cohesion for vs. 21-25 (Lole) MC So those blessings which God had promised to your-pl ancestors, now you-pl who are His prophets' descendants have received. &lt;&lt;heirs of the prophets&gt;&gt;? you brothers of Isra'el ?<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: You are the descendants of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z" status="Information">NRSV: You are the descendants of the prophets and of the covenant that God gave to your ancestors, saying to Abraham, ‘And in your descendants all the families of the earth shall be blessed.’</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Tuhan Allah utus Dia pung Ana yang Dia su pili tu, ko kasi tunju jalan ko biar bosong kasi tenga bosong pung sala-sala dong. Deng bagitu, Dia kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong. Tuhan kirim itu Ana lebe dolo kasi sang bosong, baru Dia kirim kasi sang suku-bangsa laen dong. Itu jadi berkat kasi kotong samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Lord God commissioned that Child of His whom He chose, to show the path for you to leave behind your *wrongs. In that way, He showed His goodness/generosity (‘good liver) to you. The Lord sent that Child first for you, and then He sent [Him] for other nations. That is/was/became a blessing to all of us-inc.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Agama Yahudi pung bos-bos pange Petrus deng Yohanis datang mangada<bt>The Yahudi religious bosses summon Petrus and Yohanis to come appear.before [them]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, Petrus deng Yohanis masi ba'omong deng itu orang dong, te orang bésar barapa orang dong datang. Dong saparu kapala agama Yahudi, saparu orang dari partei agama Saduki, deng kapala jaga Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Dong datang ko mau bakanjar sang Petrus deng Yohanis.<bt>At that time, Petrus and Yohanis still were talking with those people, then [contrary to expectation] several big/important people came. Some of them were Yahudi priests, some people from the religious party Saduki, and the head of guarding the *Temple. They came to cause a stir/argue with Petrus and Yohanis.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong tu, kapala agama Yahudi barapa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Dong tu, kapala agama Yahudi barapa orang, kapala jaga Ruma Sambayang Pusat, deng orang-orang dari partei agama Saduki.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Itu orang bésar dong mara tagal dong dua suka kasi tau orang dong samua bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati! Deng bagitu, Dia buka jalan kasi orang mati dong, ko dong ju bisa idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>Those important people were angry because the two of them liked to tell all people saying, “Yesus has lived again from His death! With that, He opened the path for dead people to also be.able to live again.”</bt><note reference="4:1-2" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang dari partei agama Saduki dong sonde tarima itu ajaran yang bilang, orang mati nanti bisa idop kambali.<bt>People from the religious party Saduki did not accept that teaching that says dead people can later live again.</bt></note><v n="3" />Ais ju dong parenta dong pung orang ko pi tangkap sang dong dua. Ma tagal matahari su mau tanggalám, ju dong tola kasi maso sang dong dua pi dalam bui. Ko dia pung beso, baru dong mau urus itu parkara.<bt>And so they ordered their people to go capture the two of them. But because the sun already wanted to sink, then they forced [&amp;] entered the two of them in jail. So.that the next day, then they could take care of that affair/litigation/problem.</bt><v n="4" />Ma dari orang yang suka dengar itu utusan dong, banya orang su mangaku bilang, apa yang dong ajar tu, memang batúl. Andia ko dong pung orang batamba banya sampe kira-kira lima ribu orang.<bt>But from the people who liked to hear those apostles, many people had already acknowledged that, that which they taught, was truly correct. That's why their people increased a lot until approximately five thousand people.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01901b.tif" rtfFormat="width:7.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Orang bésar dong tudu sang Petrus dong<bt>The important people accuse/criticise Petrus (coll.)</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Dia pung beso ju, orang Yahudi pung orang-orang bésar dong bakumpul di kota Yerusalem. Andia, kapala-kapala, tua-tua adat, deng guru agama Yahudi dong.<bt>The next day, then the big/important/prominent Yahudi people gathered in Yerusalem city. That.is, heads, traditional custom elders, and Yahudi religious teachers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hakim-hakim agama, orang-orang Yahudi pung pamimpin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hakim-hakim agama, orang-orang Yahudi pung pamimpin deng guru-guru agama dong bakumpul di Yerusalem.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Deng kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar ju ada di situ. Dia pung nama Hanas. Orang bésar-bésar laen dong, andia Kayafas, Yohanis, Aleksander, deng bos bésar pung kelu laen dong ju ada di situ.<bt>And the *high priest (big boss of the Yahudi priests) was also there. His name was Hanas. Other big people, they.were Kayafas, Yohanis, Aleksander, and other family [members] of the big boss were also there.</bt><v n="7" />Waktu samua su maso, ju dong parenta orang ko pi ame bawa Petrus deng Yohanis, datang ko mangada di itu bos-bos dong. Waktu dong su maso, tarús dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana ko bosong bisa bekin bae itu orang lumpu? Bosong pake sapa pung kuasa? Sapa yang kasi isin ko bosong barani bekin bagitu?&gt;&gt;<bt>When they all had entered, then they ordered person/people to go bring Petrus and Yohanis, to come appear of front of those bosses. Then they asked saying, “How is it that you-pl can heal that lame person? You-pl used whose power? Who gave permission for you to dare to do like that?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ais Tuhan Allah pung Roh bekin barani sang Petrus, ko dia manyao bilang,<bt>Then the Lord God's Spirit made Petrus brave, so that he replied saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Is bekin barani a good match"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Is bekin barani a good match here for "filled by the Spirit"?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bapa-bapa dong, andia yang jadi orang bésar, deng tua-tua adat bangsa Isra'el dong! Jang mara kalo botong ada bingung sadiki.<bt>"Fathers, that is those who are big/important people and traditional elders of the Israel nation! Don't get angry if you are a little confused.</bt><v n="9" />Tingka ke bapa dong ada mau bekin parkara deng botong, tagal botong su tolong bekin bae satu orang lumpu. Ais bapa dong mau cari tau botong pake sapa pung kuasa?<bt>Such that fathers (=you) are wanting to make a case/litigation with us because we have helped heal a lame person. Then you (fathers) want to know we have used whose power?</bt><v n="10" />Jadi beta mau manyao bagini: bapa dong tantu masi inga itu orang Nasaret yang Dia pung nama, Yesus. Dia tu, andia Kristus, yang Tuhan su tunju memang dari dolu. Ma bosong su paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang. Ma Tuhan Allah su kasi idop Dia kambali dari Dia pung mati. Beta mau ko bapa dong deng samua bangsa Isra'el tau sa, te botong bekin bae itu orang lumpu, pake itu Yesus pung kuasa.<bt>So (consequently), I want to respond like this: fathers (=you) surely still remember that Nasaret person whose name, was Yesus. That He, that's Kristus, whom God appointed from beforehand. But you nailed killing Him on a cross. But the Lord God has made Him alive again from His death. I want so that fathers (=you) and all the nations of Israel just know, cuz (elaboration) we-exc have healed that lame person, using that Yesus' power.</bt><v n="11" />Ini Yesus ni, yang dong su tulis memang di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>This is the Yesus, whom they wrote about in the Lord God's Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Ada satu batu yang tukang dong su angka buang;<bt>'There is a stone which the workers have picked up thrown away;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ma sakarang itu batu su jadi batu alas.&gt;<bt>but now that stone has become a foundation stone (stone that goes between ground and pole).’</bt><note reference="4:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:22</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="12" />Di anteru dunya, Tuhan sonde buka jalan laen lai ko kasi salamat sang kotong dari kotong pung sala-sala dong. Cuma ada satu jalan sa, andia Yesus. Kalo bukan Dia, na, sonde ada satu orang laen lai yang bisa kasi salamat sang kotong.&gt;&gt;<bt>In the entire world, the Lord has not opened any other path to save us from our wrongs. There is only just one path, that is Yesus. If not Him [+certainty], there is no other person who can save us-inc.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="seret = hela rorosa; ?? ais"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">seret = hela rorosa; ?? ais shifts topic (a la Givon's 4?) whereas ju signals continuation??</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Orang yang ada dudu di situ dong tau bilang, Petrus deng Yohanis tu, cuma orang kici sa, sama ke orang yang sonde tau baca-tulis. Ma dong taheran-heran deng dong dua pung barani, tagal dong omong sonde pake pele-pele. Tamba lai dong tau bilang, itu dua orang tu, satu kaki deng Yesus.<bt>The people who were sitting there knew that that Petrus and Yohanis, were only just small (unimportant) ordinary people, like people who do not know how to read-write. But they were amazed at the braveness of them two, because they spoke openly (lit. without using blockages/preventions). Add more that they knew that those two people, were one footed with Yesus. [=intimate friends]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apalai ; mana lai = apalagi;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">apalai ; mana lai = apalagi; tamba lai = selain itu ; omong sonde pele-pele = jujur, terus terang, tanpa takut; suka iko = often (iterative); ada iko = continuous (imperfective)</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Andia ko dong pung mulu su takancing sampe dong sonde bisa omong banya lai, apalai itu orang yang su bae dari dia pung lumpu tu, ada badiri bae-bae di situ ju, pas di dong pung muka idong.<bt>That's why their mouths were already locked up until they didn't know anything else to say, especially since that person who had been healed from his lameness, was also standing right there, in front of their noses (idiom).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="badiri bae-bae ; mulu su takancing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">badiri bae-bae ; mulu su takancing = takonci; check for use di muka idong@@</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ais ju dong suru Yesus pung utusan dua orang tu bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong kaluar tahan dolo.&gt;&gt; Ju dong ba'omong ko mau cari akal.<bt>And they ordered those two apostles of Yesus saying, “You go outside for a bit.” And they spoke to each other to find a reason/cause for litigation.</bt><v n="16" />Dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong samua! Kotong musti bekin apa deng ini dua orang ni? Te samua orang di Yerusalem su tau bilang, dong dua yang bekin ini tanda heran ni. Kotong mau manyangkal apa lai, ko dia pung bukti su ada tu?<bt>They spoke saying, “Siblings/cousins! We-inc must do what with these two people? Cuz (elaboration) all people in Yerusalem know that these two are who have done this miracle. How can we mislead with anything else, when that evidence of it is there?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manyangkal = menyatakan yg tidak sebenarnya,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">manyangkal = menyatakan yg tidak sebenarnya, tipu, mislead, deny s.t. true</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Lebe bae kotong cari jalan ko biar ini hal sonde sampe tasiar pi mana-mana lai. Ada lebe bae kalo kotong bekin taku sang dong dua, ko dong jang ajar lai so'al Yesus pung Jalan Idop. Kalo sampe dong sonde mau dengar, na, dong tau sandiri sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>It's better if we find a path to allow this matter to not get spread all around anymore. It would be good if we make those two afraid, so that they don't teach anymore the matter of Yesus' Life Path. If it gets to the point that they don't hear/listen to us, na, they'll just know themselves [=threat]!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="threat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">threat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ais ju dong pange maso itu dua orang kambali, ko kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Awas, é! Bosong sonde bole ajar orang so'al Yesus lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>And then they called those two people to come back in, to tell saying, “Be careful! You cannot teach people about Yesus anymore!” [EXEG: Gk “in this name” = name/reputation. Follows NLT, CEV = about Jesus. Forcing name here is overtranslation.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ma Petrus deng Yohanis manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba bapa dong pikir sandiri sa. Mana yang lebe bae? Iko bapa dong pung parenta, ko, iko Tuhan Allah pung parenta?<bt>But Petrus and Yohanis replied saying, “Fathers (=you) just try to think for yourselves. Which is better? Follow fathers (=your) command, or follow the Lord God's command?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="co = coba;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">co = coba;</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-20 11:56:24Z" /></Annotation><v n="20" />Te botong sandiri su lia deng mata biji, deng botong su dengar deng botong pung talinga sandiri banya hal. Karmana ko botong musti tutu mulu sampe botong sonde bisa kasi tau orang lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because you have seen with your own eyes, and you have heard with your own ears many things. How.can.it be that we-exc must close [our] mouths to the point that we don't tell any more people!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais, itu orang dong yang dudu urus itu parkara, larang ulang sang dong lai. Ju dong kasi lapás sang itu dua orang, tagal dong sonde tau mau hukum karmana lai. Deng dong ju taku, jang-jangan orang banya di luar dong bangun mangamok. Te dong su puji-puji Tuhan, tagal itu orang lumpu tu su jadi bae.<bt>Then, those people who sat that litigation, forbade them again. And they freed those two people, because they didn't know how to judge/punish them anymore. And they were also afraid, lest the crowd outside rise.up in chaos. Cuz (elaboration) they had praised the Lord, because that lame person, was healed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu hakim-hakim dong su sonde dapa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Itu hakim-hakim dong su sonde dapa alasan ko mau hukum sang Petrus deng Yohanis. Jadi dong ancam sang dong dua, abis lapás sang dong, te samua orang di mana-mana su puji-puji Tuhan Allah pung nama tagal itu kejadian.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jang-jangan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">jang-jangan</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />(Itu orang su lumpu lebe dari ampa pulu taon, baru dia bisa dapa jalan.)<bt>(That person had been lame for more than forty years, before he could walk.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(Itu orang menderita lumpu su lebe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">(Itu orang menderita lumpu su lebe dari ampa pulu taon, baru dia bisa dapa jalan.)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pung orang dong sambayang minta ko dong jang taku<bt>Yesus' people pray requesting that they not be afraid</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Waktu dong kasi lapás sang Petrus deng Yohanis, ju dong dua kambali pi dong pung tamán dong. Ais ju dong carita samua yang itu kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng tua-tua adat dong su larang sang dong.<bt>When they had freed Petrus and Yohanis, then they two returned to their friends. And then they told all that those *chief priests and the traditional elders had forbidden them.</bt><v n="24" />Dengar bagitu, ju dong pung tamán samua tu, bakumpul deng satu hati ko sambayang bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah yang Paling Kuasa. Bapa yang bekin ame langit deng bumi, deng dia pung isi samua.<bt>Hearing like that, then all those friends of theirs, gathered with one liver to pray saying, “Lord God Most Powerful. Father who made the sky and the earth, and all it's contents. [NOTE: Gk here is /despota/, not /kurios/.]</bt><note reference="4:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:11, Nehemia 9:6, Lagu Puji dong 146:6</note><v n="25" />Dolu Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi su pake ba'i Daud jadi Tuhan pung jubir. Dia kasi tau memang bilang, nanti orang lawan sang Yesus. Te dia tulis bilang:<bt>Before the Lord's *Holy Spirit used Ancestor Daud to be the Lord's spokesperson. He foretold that people would oppose Yesus. Cuz (elaboration) he wrote that:</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01903b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Petrus dong sambayang<bt>Petrus (coll) pray</bt></fig>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Orang dari suku-bangsa laen dong su mara tagal kabar burung;<bt>'People from other nations are angry because of rumours (lit. bird news);</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kabar angin = ; kabar burung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kabar angin = ; kabar burung = isu, kabar yg belum tantu benar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong su sambarang sa, ko bekin parkara yang sonde ada pung ujung-pohon.<bt>They have just [talked] aimlessly, to make a problem/litigation which does not have tree.roots(no basis).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ujung-pohon = pangkal, akar masalah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ujung-pohon = pangkal, akar masalah</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="26" />Raja-raja di ini dunya dong bakumpul ko mau paráng lawan sang Tuhan;<bt>The rajas in this world are gathered to war against God;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng kapala-kapala dong ba'akór ko pi lawan sang Tuhan Allah deng Kristus,<bt>and the heads are in agreement to go oppose the Lord God and Kristus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">andia Orang yang Tuhan su tunju memang dari dolu.&gt;<bt>That is, the Person who the Lord has appointed/chosen beforehand from long ago.’</bt><note reference="4:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 2:1-2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Naa, apa yang ba'i Daud su tulis tu, sakarang su jadi. Deng dia pung arti sakarang su jalás ju. Memang di ini kota, raja Herodes deng gubernor Pontius Pilatus su bakumpul deng botong pung orang tua-tua dong dari Isra'el, deng bangsa laen dong pung kapala-kapala. Ais dong samua basakongkol ko malawan Yesus, itu Orang yang Tuhan su pili memang.<bt>Naa, [+shift] that which ancestor Daud wrote, now it has happened. And its meaning is also now clear. Truly in this city, raja Herodes and gubernur Pontius Pilatus gathered with our-exc elders from Israel, and other nation's heads. Then they all made.an.agreement(in secret, to do s.t. bad) to oppose Yesus, that Person whom the Lord had appointed/chosen beforehand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orang-orang tua dong = parents; orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">orang-orang tua dong = parents; orang tua-tua dong = elders, leaders</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 27:1-2, Markus 15:1, Lukas 23:1, 7-11, Yohanis 18:28-29</note><v n="28" />Ma sakarang kotong su tau itu samua kaná pas deng Tuhan pung mau, iko apa yang Tuhan su putus memang dari dolu.<bt>But now we-inc know that that all fits exactly with the Lord's will, according to what the Lord decided from beforehand.</bt><v n="29" />Sakarang Tuhan coba lia, te dong ada garatak bekin taku sang botong. Jadi botong minta ko Tuhan bekin botong barani. Ko botong jalan pi kasi tau orang di mana-mana, Tuhan pung Carita Bae so'al Yesus. Deng botong sonde usa taku apa-apa.<bt>Now the Lord go.ahead and see, cuz (elaboration) they have threatened to make us-exc afraid. So.then we requested that the Lord make us brave. In.order.that we go tell people (generic, not plural) all over the place, the Lord's Good Story about this Yesus. And we-exc don't need to be afraid of anything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="garatak = ancam, gertak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">garatak = ancam, gertak</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Botong ju minta ko Tuhan kasi kuasa sang botong, ko botong bisa bekin bae orang saki dong. Botong ju minta kuasa ko bekin tanda heran macam-macam ko orang dong tau bilang, itu kuasa tu, datang dari Orang Barisi yang Tuhan suru, andia Yesus. Tuhan, bagini sa, botong pung sambayang.&gt;&gt;<bt>We also request that the Lord give power to us, so that we can heal sick people. We also requested power to do various kinds of *miracles so that people would know that that power, comes from that Holy Person whom the Lord ordered, that is Yesus. Lord, just like this, is our prayer.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check if these are seen as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">check if these are seen as separate kinds of powers</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Bagitu dong ada sambayang, te itu ruma yang dong ada bakumpul tu, tagoyang. Ju dong samua takaná Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi. Ais ju dong kaluar ko kasi tau Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae deng sonde pele-pele.<bt>While they were still praying, (te2 -contrary to expectation) that house in which they were gathered, was shaken. And they all were affected by the Lord's *Holy Spirit. And then they went out to tell the Lord God's Good News, without holding anything back.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tagoyang = was shaken (by outside"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tagoyang = was shaken (by outside force); bagoyang = on its own, also means dance; sonde pele-pele der = lf Max ; der =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check with/without der"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">check with/without der</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang parcaya dong idop pikol barát sama-sama, deng sanáng sama-sama<bt>The believers living shoulder.carrying heavyness together, and happiness together</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ais ju samua orang yang parcaya sang Yesus, dong satu hati, deng dong idop basayang satu deng satu. Sonde ada yang sakikir, ais dong suka bakasi apa-apa pi di yang laen. Satu-satu orang yang ada pung barang sandiri, dia ator ko dong pake sama-sama.<bt>And then all those people who believed Yesus, they were of one liver (=in accord), and they each one lived (reciprocally) loving each other. There was no one who was stingy, so they liked to (reciprocally) give all sorts of.things to the other. Each person who had his own things, he arranged so that they used [them] together.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bakasi = recip; ba'ator; basayang; BI"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bakasi = recip; ba'ator; basayang; BI hidup rukun = sira kakawai gosa</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 2:44-45</note><v n="33" />Ais Tuhan kasi kuasa di Dia pung utusan dong, ko kasi tau orang bilang, Tuhan Yesus su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati. Ko dong su lia deng mata kapala sandiri na. Ais Tuhan kasi berkat balimpa-limpa sang dong.<bt>Then the Lord gave power to His apostles, to tell people that the Lord Yesus had lived again from His death. Obviously they had seen with their own eyes. Then the Lord gave extra *blessing to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Key term: grace - memberkati, kasih"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Key term: grace - memberkati, kasih karunia; berkat = can be barang or bahagia, etc.</Message></Annotation><v n="34-35" />Dari dong tu, ada orang yang jual dia pung tana ju, ko, dia pung ruma sandiri. Dia pung doi, dia kasi pi Tuhan pung utusan dong. Ju dong pake ko urus kasi orang banya dong pung parlú. Andia ko dong sonde ada yang kurang satu apa ju.<bt>From those them, there were also persons who sold his land, or his own house. It's money, he gave to the Lord's apostles. And they used [it] to arrange to give to many people's need. That's why they didn't lack a single thing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36-37" />Conto ke Yusuf. Dia ni, Lewi pung turunan, dari pulo Siprus. (Tuhan pung utusan dong pange dia deng nama kici bilang, &lt;Barnabas&gt;, te itu nama pung arti, &lt;orang yang suka kasi samangat orang laen&gt;.) Dia pi jual dia pung tana sapotong, ais bawa dia pung doi, ko pi kasi di Tuhan pung utusan dong.<bt>For example Yusuf. This him, was Lewi's descendant, from Siprus island. (The Lord's apostles called him by the nickname of &lt;Barnabas&gt;, cuz (elaboration) that name's meaning, &lt;person who likes to give enthusiasm to other people&gt;.) He went to sell a piece of land of his, and then brought's it's price to give to the Lord's apostles.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pulo ~ pulu; nama kici ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pulo ~ pulu; nama kici = nickname</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ananias deng Safira mati, tagal dong mau coba Tuhan pung Roh<bt>Ananias and Safira die, because they try to test God's Spirit</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Ma itu waktu ju ada satu laki-laki, nama Ananias. Dia pung maitua, nama Safira. Dong dua ni, ada jual dong pung tana sapotong ju.<bt>But at that time there was also a male, named Ananias. His wife's name was Safira. These two, also sold a piece of land of theirs.</bt><v n="2" />Ma dong dua ada basakongkol ko sambunyi doi saparu dari itu tana pung harga. Jual itu tana abis, ju Ananias pi kasi tau sang Tuhan pung utusan dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong baru jual botong pung tana sapotong. Sakarang botong mau kasi dia pung doi samua sang Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>But they two agreed (in.secret) to hide a bit of the money from that land's price. After selling that land, Ananias went to tell the Lord's apostles saying, “We-exc just sold a piece of land of ours. Now we want to give all its money to the Lord God.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bakong-kali-kong = akor; saparu not same"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bakong-kali-kong = akor; saparu not same as BI</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01905b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Ananias sarakan doi saparu sang Petrus<bt>Ananias hands.over a part of the money to Petrus</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ma Petrus togor sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Ananias! Lu pung talalu lai! Karmana ko lu sampe hati, sambunyi doi dari lu pung tana yang lu su jual tu? Lu pung hati su talalu jahat, tagal lu iko setan dong pung bos pung mau. Lu barani putar-balek deng Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi!<bt>But Petrus scolded him saying, “Weh [+critical]! Ananias! You're too much! How.is.it that you are at the point of hiding in your liver money from that land which you sold? Your liver is exceedingly evil, because you follow *Satan's will. You dare lie (lit. twist turn) with the Lord God's Holy Spirit!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tega = sampe hati, conscience (tega"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tega = sampe hati, conscience (tega = BI/Java)</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Bagini! Lu mau jual itu tana, ko sonde mau jual, tarsará lu sa. Kalo lu su jual, lu mau kasi dia pung doi anteru, ko sonde, itu ju tarsará lu. Ma karmana ko lu sampe bisa bekin bagitu? Lu coba-coba bekin bodo sang botong manusia ni, ma sonde ada orang yang bisa bekin bodo sang Tuhan!&gt;&gt;<bt>It's.like this! You want to sell that land, or don't want to sell, it's just up to you. If you sell, you want to give all it's money, or not, that also is up to you. But how.can.it be that you are to.the.point.of doing like that? You try and try to decieve us humans, but there is no person who can decieve the Lord!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Dengar Petrus omong bagitu ju, takuju sa Ananias jato tabanting di tana, tarús dia mati memang. Ais samua orang yang dengar itu kabar jadi taku mau mati.<bt>Hearing Petrus talk like that, then just suddenly/unexpectedly Ananias fell plop.down on the ground, then he truly died. Then all the people who heard that news became exceedingly afraid.</bt><v n="6" />Ais ju ana-ana muda dong barapa orang maso, ju dong bungkus Ananias pung mayat ko bawa pi kubur sang dia.<bt>And then several youths entered, and they wrapped Ananias' corpse to carry him to the grave.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Abis kira-kira tiga jam lai, ju Ananias pung maitua maso datang. Ma dia sonde tau hal.<bt>After approximately 3 more hours, then Ananias' wife enter came. But she was unaware (of what had happened). (=idiom)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="idiom = not know anything about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">idiom = not know anything about it; completely ignorant on the issue</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ju Petrus tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana, mama? Mama dong su jual itu tana deng dia pung harga bagini, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>And Petrus asked her saying, “How.is.it, mama? Mama (collective) sold that land with it's price like this, right?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dia manyao bale bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, Papa. Dia pung harga, andia bagitu su.&gt;&gt;<bt>And she replied in return saying, “True, Papa. It's price, it's really like that.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais Petrus togor bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana ko lu deng lu pung paitua basakongkol ko mau coba Tuhan pung Roh? Lu lia sa! Itu orang dong yang baru bawa lu pung laki ko pi kubur tu, su kambali. Sonde lama lai, te dong ju dorok bawa lu pung mayat ko pi kubur di lu pung laki pung rebis.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus scolded saying, “How is it that you and your husband agreed secretly to try that Spirit of the Lord's? You just look! Those people who just brought your male to bury, have returned. Soon they also will drag carry your corpse to go bury at your male's side.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sabantar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sabantar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dengar Petrus pung omong tu, ju takuju sa, itu parampuan jato, ju mati memang di tampa. Waktu itu ana-ana muda dong maso kambali, dong dapa lia te itu parampuan ju su mati. Ais dong dorok bawa dia pung mayat ko pi kubur di dia pung laki pung rebis.<bt>When hearing that talking of Petrus, then unexpectedly, that woman fell, and truely died in that place. When those youths entered again, they could see cuz (elaboration) that woman was also dead. So/then they dragged brought her corpse to go bury at her male's side.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01908b.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.0cm;textWrapping:none;horizontalPosition:center">Safira mati takuju tenga tampa<bt>Safira dies on the spot</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais orang yang parcaya sang Yesus dong, jadi taku. Deng samua orang laen yang dapa dengar so'al Ananias deng Safira pung mati tu, ju iko taku.<bt>Then those people who believed Yesus, became afraid. And all the other people who were able to here that matter of Ananias and Safira's death, they also became afraid.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus dong bekin bae banya orang<bt>Petrus(collective) heal many people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Itu waktu, Yesus pung utusan dong ada bekin talalu banya tanda heran, ju orang dong dapa lia. Itu utusan dong suka maso pi Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Dong bakumpul deng satu hati di Ruma Loos Raja Soleman.<bt>At that time, Yesus' apostles wre doing very many *miracles, and people were getting to see [them]. Those apostles like to enter the Lord's *Temple. They gathered with one liver(=in one accord) at the Raja Soleman's Freestanding House.</bt><v n="13" />Itu waktu ju, banya orang puji-puji sang Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong. Ma kalo ada orang yang balóm parcaya sang Yesus, dia sonde barani maso pi bakumpul deng dong di situ.<bt>At that time also, many people praised the Lord Yesus' people. But as for people who did not yet believe in Yesus, he did not dare enter to gather with them there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="angka-angka = like puji-puji, omong hal-hal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">angka-angka = like puji-puji, omong hal-hal yang bae-bae tentang mereka, (UNS, but slightly negative overtones, like sombong)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma orang yang parcaya sang Yesus, tamba lama tamba banya. Ada laki-laki deng ada parampuan ju.<bt>But [+contrary to expectation] those people who believed in Yesus, increased long, increased many (parallelism?). There were both men and also women. [NOTE to daughter translations: the /ma/ here as “contrary to expectation” will not work in all RL lgs.]</bt><v n="15" />Itu waktu su jadi bagitu macam, sampe orang dong bawa datang orang saki dong, ko taro di atas tikar di pinggir jalan. Tagal dong pikir kata, &lt;&lt;Kalo Petrus deng Yohanis jalan lewat sini, biar kaná dong dua pung bayangan sa ju, ini orang saki dong bisa jadi bae.&gt;&gt;<bt>So many amazing things were happening (idiom), to the point that people came bringing sick people, to put on top of mats on the side of the road. Because they thought saying, “Wee! If Petrus and Yohanis walk by here, even if only affected.by their two shadows, these sick people can be healed.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu waktu su jadi bagitu macam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Itu waktu su jadi bagitu macam = Many amazing things were happening...</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ais orang dong datang sonde tau abis, dari kampong-kampong di kota Yerusalem pung pinggir. Dong dorok bawa dong pung orang-orang saki dong, ais ju Tuhan pung utusan dong bekin bae sang dong samua. Dong ju antar bawa dong pung orang yang takaná setan dong, ais Tuhan pung utusan dong usir kasi kaluar itu setan dong samua.<bt>So/then, people came without knowing how to finish (=came endlessly) from villages on the edge of Yerusalem city. They brought carrying their sick people, and then the Lord's apostles made them all well. They also brought escorting their people who were affected.by evil spirits, then the Lord's apostles expelled making leave all those evil spirits.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung utusan dong dapa susa<bt>The Lord Yesus' apostles get difficulty</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Tagal Tuhan Yesus pung utusan dong pung karjá, andia ko kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar deng dia pung konco-konco dari partei Saduki, dong pung hati kakodok.<bt>Because of the Lord Yesus' apostles' work, that is why the *high priest and his cronies from the Saduki party, their livers were tight up to the throat (=upset, frustrated).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="konco-konco = kroni-kroni, kawan-kawan; ada hati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">konco-konco = kroni-kroni, kawan-kawan; ada hati manoso = saki hati mau mati, painful sting (like scorpion bite); rufuk = pake sampe rusak; hati kakodok = hati sesak = jengkel</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Andia ko dong pi tangkap ame Yesus pung utusan dong, ko tola kasi maso sang dong pi dalam bui.<bt>That's why they went to capture Yesus' apostles, to force them putting them into jail.</bt><note reference="5:18" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Itu kata di bahasa Yunani, dia pung arti bisa, &lt;&lt;kasi maso di bui umum.&gt;&gt; Ko, dia pung arti ju bisa, &lt;&lt;kasi maso di bui ko bekin malu sang dong di orang banya pung muka.&gt;&gt;<bt>The word in Yunani language, its meaning can say, “put them in the public jail.” Or, it can also say, “put them in jail to make them ashamed in front of the many people.”</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ma itu malam ju, Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga satu datang di itu bui, ko buka dia pung pintu. Ais dia antar sang dong bawa pi luar. Ju dia pasán bilang,<bt>But then that night, one of the Lord's *angels came to that jail, to open its door. Then he escorted them outside. And he instructed saying,</bt><v n="20" />&lt;&lt;Sakarang bosong pi memang di Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Pi kasi tau samua-samua sang orang di sana dong, ko dong iko Tuhan pung Jalan yang Bawa Idop Baru ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>"Now you-pl go to the *Temple. Go tell all the people there, so that they follow the Lord's Path that Brings New Life.” [EXEG: Gk “message of life”.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Dia pung beso papagi, dong bekin iko itu Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga pung pasán tu. Ais dong maso pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal, ju dong ajar orang di situ.<bt>Early the next morning, they followed that instruction of that *angel. So they entered the Temple's yard, and they taught people there.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01911b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Tuhan pung ana bua kasi kaluar Petrus dong dari bui<bt>An angel gets Petrus (coll) out of jail</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Sonde lama lai, ju itu bos bésar deng dia pung tamán dong datang sama-sama deng orang-orang bésar deng tua-tua adat dari anteru Isra'el. Dong bakumpul ko mau pareksa parkara agama so'al Tuhan Yesus pung utusan dong. Ais dong suru orang jaga ko pi ame Petrus dong dari bui, ko dong mau urus itu parkara.<bt>Then not much longer, that big boss and his friends came together with big/important people and traditional elders from all over Israel. They came in order to investigate the religious litigation regarding the Lord Yesus' apostles. Then they ordered guard/s to go get Petrus(collective) out of jail, so that they could take care of that litigation.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pareksa parkara = ; last ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pareksa parkara = ; last ko changed from te by UNS's = purpose/intention, te reflects reason/cause</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma waktu itu orang jaga dong sampe di bui, Petrus dong su sonde ada lai. Ais orang jaga dong pi kasi tau sang orang-orang bésar di itu tampa urus parkara agama.<bt>But when those guards arrived at the jail, Petrus (collective) were no longer there. So they went to tell the big people at that place of handling religious disputes.</bt><v n="23" />Dong lapor bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa dong jang mara. Waktu botong sampe di bui, botong dapa lia dia pung pintu samua ada takonci mati. Deng orang jaga dong samua ada badiri di situ. Ma waktu botong suru dong buka itu pintu ko botong maso, na, botong sonde dapa lia apa-apa, ma.&gt;&gt;<bt>They reported saying, “Fathers don't get angry. When we arrived at the jail, we saw all its doors were locked dead(=completely). And all the guards were standing there. But when we ordered them to open that door so that we could go in, na, we didn't see anything.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="su ilang buang = completely disappeared,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">su ilang buang = completely disappeared, into thin air</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Dengar bagitu, ju kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos, deng kapala jaga Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat, dong samua babingung bodo, tagal dong su ilang akal.<bt>Hearing that, then the *chief priests, and the head guards of the *Temple, they were all confused-stupidly(=stunned), because they didn't know what to do and where it would all go [+obvious].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ilang akal = bingung (idiom), implications,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ilang akal = bingung (idiom), implications, consequences</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais itu, ada satu orang datang kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa dong, dengar dolo! Itu orang dong yang bosong tahan di bui tu, ada di luar sini! Sakarang ni dong ada badiri ko ajar orang di Ruma Sambayang Pusat ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, there was a person who came telling saying, “Fathers, listen! Those people who you put in that jail, [they] are outside here! Right now they are standing to teach people here in this *Temple!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu kapala jaga Ruma Sambayang pange ame dia pung ana bua dong, ko pi tangkap ulang sang Petrus deng dia pung tamán dong. Ma dia pung ana bua dong taku, tagal orang banya dong ada dengar Petrus ba'omong. Dong pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang sampe orang banya dong mangamok, ais dong lempar sang kotong deng batu.&gt;&gt; Andia ko, waktu dong tangkap ulang Petrus dong, dong sonde barani ame deng paksa.<bt>Hearing that, then that head guard of the Temple called his underlings, to go capture again Petrus and his friends. But his underlings were afraid, because many people were listening to Petrus talk. They thought, &lt;&lt;May it not be/lest/we hope that the crowd (those many people) does not riot (go amuck), and they throw stones at us-inc.&gt;&gt; That is why, when they captured Petrus (collective) again, they did not dare to take them by force. [DISCOURSE: made direct speech following RL style.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eleng = ; tangan karás ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">eleng = ; tangan karás = kasar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ais dong bawa Petrus dong pi tampa urus parkara. Ju bos bésar mulai batanya sang dong,<bt>Then they brought Petrus (collective) to that place for investigating litigations. And the big boss began asking them,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="korek-korek = ganggu, tanya secara mendalam,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">korek-korek = ganggu, tanya secara mendalam, cari tau</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong su larang bosong ko jang ajar orang banya so'al itu Orang yang mau bawa jalan idop yang baru tu, aa?! Bosong ni, kapala batu! Ais bosong sonde toe deng botong pung parenta lai, te bosong bekin iko bosong pung mau sa! Bosong pi ajar kuliling sini-sana di kota Yerusalem ni. Sama ke bosong ada lempar sala di botong bilang, botong ni yang suru orang ko pi bekin mati sang Yesus.&gt;&gt;<bt>saying, &lt;&lt;We have already forbade you-pl to not teach people about that Person who wants to make that new life path, right? You here, are stone heads (idiom = stubborn). So you don't pay attention anymore to our command, cuz (elaboration) you have just done according to your own will. You have gone teaching here-there all around this city Yerusalem. [It is] as if you are accusing us, saying the we here are the ones who ordered people to go kill that Yesus.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lempar sala/buang sala/ muat sala ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lempar sala/buang sala/ muat sala = melempar kesalahan; lempar batu, sambunyi tangan = do wrong, and pretend didn't do anything</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 27:25</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ais Petrus badiri ko jadi utusan dong samua pung jubir. Ju dia manyao bilang,<bt>Then Petrus stood to be all the apostles' spokesperson. And he replied saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bapa dong! Kalo ada manusia pung parenta yang malawan sang Tuhan Allah pung mau, botong sonde bisa iko. Ma botong musti iko Tuhan Allah pung parenta sa!<bt>&lt;&lt;Fathers/sirs! If there is a human's order that opposes the Lord God's will, we cannot follow it. But we must follow only the Lord God's order!</bt><v n="30" />Naa, Orang yang buka botong pung jalan idop baru tu, andia Yesus. Dia tu, Orang yang bosong su paku bekin mati di kayu palang. Dari dolu, kotong pung ba'i-ba'i dong suka sambayang sang Tuhan Allah. Itu Tuhan tu, yang su kasi idop kambali Yesus dari Dia pung mati!<bt>Naa, [+shift] the Person who opened that new life path of ours, it's Yesus. That him, the Person whom you nailed killing on the cross. From before, our-inc grandfather/ ancestors liked to worship the Lord God. That Lord, [he's the one] who has made alive again Yesus from his death!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="31" />Sakarang Tuhan Allah su angka Yesus, ko jadi Dia pung tangan kanan. Ais Yesus su pegang kuasa sama ke raja bésar. Dia su buka jalan ko orang dapa talapás dari dong pung sala-sala dong. Dia mau kasi jalan sang kotong orang Isra'el ni, ko kotong barenti dari kotong pung sala dong samua, ais bale ko iko kambali Tuhan pung jalan lurus. Deng bagitu, Tuhan Allah pung hati bisa jadi dingin sampe Dia su sonde lia kotong bangsa Isra'el pung sala lai.<bt>Now the Lord God has raised Yesus, to become the His right hand. And Yesus already hold authority like a big raja. He has opened the path so that people can be set free from their *wrongs. He wants to give the path/way to we-inc Israel people, to stop from all our-inc *wrongs/sins, and turn to again follow/obey God2's straight path/way. With that, the Lord God's liver can become cool (=no longer angry) to the point that He no longer sees the wrongs of our-inc Israel nation. [EXEG: (2014) second half of ‘repent’ made explicit.]</bt><v n="32" />Te kotong ni, su lia deng mata biji sandiri bilang, Yesus memang su mati, ma Dia idop kambali. Sakarang Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi ju kasi tau ini hal di orang yang iko Yesus pung Jalan Idop.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because we-inc here, have seen with our own eyes that Yesus truly died, but He lived again. Now the Lord's Holy Spirit also tells this matter to people who follow Yesus' Life Path.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Dengar abis Petrus pung omong bagitu, ju samua orang yang dudu di tampa pareksa parkara tu, mulai maruak sampe dong mau bunu bekin mati sang Tuhan pung utusan dong.<bt>After hearing Petrus' talk like that, then all the people who were sitting at that place for investigating litigations, [they] began to get furious to the point that they want to murder kill the Lord's apostles.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maruak = mara talalu, furious"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">maruak = mara talalu, furious</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Ma di situ ju ada satu orang yang iko dudu pareksa itu parkara. Dia pung nama Gamaliel. Banya orang taro hormat sang dia, te dia ni, partei agama Farisi pung guru yang pintar satu. Ais waktu Petrus su omong abis, ko dong mau bunu sang dia, ju Gamaliel badiri ko suru orang dong bawa kaluar tahan sang Petrus dong.<bt>But there there was also a person who sat to investigate the litigation. His name Gamaliel. Many people respected him, cuz (elaboration) this him, [he was] one of the Farisi religious party's intelligent/smart teachers (= a teacher of...). So when Petrus had finished speaking, so that they wanted to kill him, then Gamaliel stood to order people to take Petrus (collective) outside for a bit.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taru hormat = ; kasi hormat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">taru hormat = ; kasi hormat =</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Waktu dong su kaluar, ju dia angka omong deng itu bos-bos di situ bilang,<bt>When they were outside, then he began to speak (formally) to those bosses there saying,</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01913b.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Gamaliel<bt>Gamaliel</bt></fig>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Sodara dong samua! Kotong musti ati-ati, ó! Jang sampe kotong kaburu-kaburu bekin jahat sang ini orang dong. Kotong musti pikir panjang dolo.<bt>“Siblings/cousins! We must be careful, o! Lest we in a hurry do evil to these people. We must think it through first.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaburu-kaburu = in a hurry; pikir"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kaburu-kaburu = in a hurry; pikir panjang = think it through</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Te bosong masi inga satu orang, yang dia pung nama Teudas. Dia su lama mati, ma waktu dia masi idop, dia angka diri sandiri bilang, dia tu, orang bésar, sampe kira-kira ada ampa ratus orang iko sang dia. Ma waktu orang bunu bekin mati sang dia, dia pung ana bua dong lari tasiram, sampe sakarang itu orang yang iko sang dia tu, sonde ada dong pung batang idong lai. Dong su lari ilang pi parsetan!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you-pl still remember a (certain) person who name was Teudas. He has been dead a long time, but when he was still alive, he lifted himself saying, that he, [he was] a big person, until there were approximately four hundred people who followed him. But when people killed him, his underlings/disciples ran hither.thither, until now those people who follow him, their nose bones are no longer around (=they are no where to be seen). They have run off disappearing into invisibility!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde ada dong pung batang idong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sonde ada dong pung batang idong lai = no longer see their faces, no longer exist; su lari pi parsetan! = su lari ilang.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="37" />Ais bosong musti inga satu carita lai. Itu waktu pas pamarenta ada bekin sensus itong orang di anteru negrí. Ada satu orang, nama Yudas, dari propinsi Galilea. Orang banya ju iko sang dia. Ma dia ju kaná bunu. Ais orang-orang yang iko sang dia ju lari tapontas kiri-kanan sampe su sonde dapa lia sang dong lai.<bt>Next you must remember one more story. That time exactly when the government made a census counting people in the entire nation. There was a person, named Yudas, from Galilea province. Many people also followed him. But he also was affected by murder. Then those people who followed him also ran ricochet left right until it was no longer to see them anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lari panta panas = ; lari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lari panta panas = ; lari tapontas = ricochet (like billiard balls ; lari fuik ; lari tarkaruang = lari tapontas</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="38" />Jadi sakarang, sodara-sodara, beta pung pikir bagini sa: sonde usa bekin mati sang dong. Kasi tenga pi sa. Te dong pung ajaran, deng dong pung garák tu, kalo dia dari manusia, tantu sonde akan batahan lama lai, pasti dia su ilang buang.<bt>So (consequently) now, siblings, my thinking is just like this: it's not neccessary to kill them. Just let [them] go. Cuz (elaboration) their teaching, and that movement of theirs, if its from humans, surely it won't last much longer, of.course it will disappear being.discarded.</bt><v n="39" />Ma kalo ini ajaran memang datang dari Tuhan Allah, nanti bosong sonde bisa kasi jato sang dong. Tagal itu, bosong ati-ati dolo. Te jang sampe bosong sandiri ada malawan sang Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>But if this teaching is actually from the Lord God, later you will not be able to make them fall. Because of that, you be careful. Lest you yourselves oppose the Lord God.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dengar bagitu, ju dong samua ia bae sa, iko sang Gamaliel pung nasiat.<bt>Hearing that, then they all just conceded (say yeah, ok), following Gamaliel's advice.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="iya bae = menuruti , satuju;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">iya bae = menuruti , satuju; nasiat</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Ais itu, dong pange bawa maso itu utusan dong, ju dong suru orang dong ko firuk sang dong. Firuk abis, ju dong larang sonde bole subu-subu Yesus pung nama lai. Tarús dong lapás buang itu utusan dong.<bt>After that, they called bringing in those apostles, and they ordered people to whip them. After the whipping was finished, then they forbade them to mention Yesus' name again. Next they freed getting.rid.of those apostles.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ais, itu utusan dong jalan kaluar kasi tenga itu tampa urus parkara. Dong pikir biar dong pung nama su rusak tagal dong su iko sang Yesus, ma dong ju rasa sanáng, tagal Tuhan Allah su anggap sang dong pantas dapa susa bagitu. Andia ko dong pung hati sanáng mau mati.<bt>Then, those apostle went out leaving behing that place of taking.care of litigations. They thought that even though their names were wrecked/broken because they had followed Yesus, but they also felt happy, because the Lord God had already considered them appropriate to get difficulty like that. That's why their hearts were exceedingly happy.</bt><v n="42" />Ju tiap hari, dong pi ajar orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu Orang yang Tuhan Allah su tunju memang dari dolu tu, andia Yesus.&gt;&gt; Ju dong kasi tau itu hal tarús-tarús di orang pung ruma-ruma dong, deng di Ruma Sambayang Pusat ju.<bt>And every day, they went to teach people saying, “That Person who the Lord God appointed/choose from way beforehand, it's Yesus.” And they also told that matter continually in people's houses, and also in the *Temple.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong pili tuju orang ko urus sang orang kici dong<bt>They choose seven people to take care of the little people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong su batamba banya. Ma dong ada dua kalompok bahasa. Dong saparu, andia orang Yahudi yang omong pake bahasa Aram. Deng saparu lai, andia orang Yahudi yang omong pake bahasa Yunani. Lama-lama timbul parkara di ini dua kalompok. Kalompok yang pake bahasa Yunani dong sonde bagitu sanáng deng kalompok yang pake bahasa Aram. Dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini ni, sonde batúl! Kalo bosong ada bagi makan hari-hari, na, bosong jang barát sablá! Te botong pung mama janda dong sonde dapa dong pung bagian.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, the Lord Yesus' people had increased alot. But they were two language groups. Part of them, were Yahudi people who spoke using the Aram language. And part of them, Yahudi people who spoke using the Yunani language. After a while a problem/litigation arose between these two groups. The group that used the Yunani language were not that happy with the group that used the Aram language. They said, “This here, it's not right! If you-pl are dividing food on daily basis, na, you don't be heavy on one side (=unfair). Cuz (elaboration) our-exc mama widows don't get their share.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde fer = unfair; barát sablá"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sonde fer = unfair; barát sablá = partial, berpihak;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Tagal itu, ju Tuhan pung utusan dua blas orang tu, pange bakumpul Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong samua. Ju dong omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong samua! Kalo botong barenti ko urus bosong pung makan-minum sa, itu ju bisa, ma itu sonde pantas! Tagal botong ni, musti ajar Tuhan pung Kata-kata tarús-tarús.<bt>Because of that, then those twelve apostles of the Lord, called gathering all of the Lord Yesus' people. And they spoke saying, “All you siblings! If we-exc stopped (work) to just handle/manage/arrange your-pl eat-drink, we could do that, but it is not appropriate/right! Because we here must keep teaching God2's Word/s/Message.</bt><v n="3" />Jadi botong pung pikir bagini: lebe bae, bosong pili tuju orang dari bosong. Cari orang yang dia pung nama bae, dia tau bawa diri, dia mangarti banya hal, deng Tuhan pung Roh ada ator dia pung idop. Kalo bosong su pili ame orang model bagitu, na, nanti botong angka sang dong ko urus itu so'al makan-minum.<bt>So (consequently) our-exc thinking is like this: it's better if, you-pl choose seven people from you. Hunt for a person/s whose name is good, s/he knows how to relate appropriately socially, s/he understands many things, and the Lord's Spirit is arranging his/her life. After you have obviously chosen people of that kind/type/model, na, later we-exc will lift/appoint them so that they arrange/take.care.of that eat-drink matter.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bijaksana &gt; panjang akal, banya akal,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bijaksana &gt; panjang akal, banya akal, pikir panjang, sonde barat sabla, ; tau bawa diri = relates appropriately socially</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Deng bagitu, botong bisa sambayang lebe banya deng ajar Tuhan pung Kata-kata.&gt;&gt;<bt>With that, then we-exc are able to pray more and teach the Lord's Words.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ais ju dong ia bae deng Petrus dong pung omong tu. Ju dong pili ame tuju orang. Andia:<bt>And then they conceded with that talking of Petrus (collective). And they choose seven people. That.is:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">satu orang, nama Stefanus. Dia tu parcaya batúl-batúl sang Tuhan Yesus, deng Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi ada pake sang dia. Deng dia pung tamán laen dong, andia:<bt>one person, named Stefanus. He truly believed in the Lord Yesus, and the Lord's Holy Spirit was using him. And his other friends, that is:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Filipus,<bt>Filipus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Prokorus,<bt>Prokorus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nikanor,<bt>Nikanor,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Timon,<bt>Timon,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Parmenas,<bt>Parmenas,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Nikolas, dari kota Antiokia. Dia bukan orang Yahudi, ma dia su maso agama Yahudi.<bt>and Nikolas from Antiokia city. He was not a Yahudi person but he had entered Yahudi religion.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Tarús dong antar bawa itu tuju orang yang dong su pili tu, pi Tuhan pung utusan dong. Ju itu utusan dong taro tangan, deng sambayang ko angka sang dong jadi orang yang urus makan-minum ko orang kici dong samua dapa bagian sama rata.<bt>Then2 they escorted bringing those seven people whom they had chosen, going to the Lord's apostles. And they placed hands, and prayed to raise them to become people who take care of eating-drinking in order that all the small people would get their fair (even) share. [EXEG: Earlier version was more literal and succinct. Later explication driven by problems with UNS responses, to clarify purpose and reinforce higher-level dynamics. Done with consultant supervision.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong samua usul itu tuju nama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Dong samua usul itu tuju nama pi di utusan-utusan dong, abis utusan-utusan dong sambayang ko minta Tuhan pung berkat kasih sang dong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Jadi Tuhan pung Kata-kata dong tasiar pi mana-mana. Deng orang yang iko Yesus pung Jalan Idop tu, batamba tarús-tarús di Yerusalem. Tarús, ada banya kapala agama Yahudi ju yang pinda maso di Yesus pung orang dong.<bt>So (consequently) the Lord's Words spread.out to everywhere. And the people who followed that Life Path of Yesus, increased continually in Yerusalem. Then/Next, many Yahudi *priests also moved entered into [to become] Yesus' people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong tangkap ame sang Stefanus<bt>They capture Stefanus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Itu waktu Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae bam-banya sang Stefanus. Dia ju kasi kuasa ko Stefanus bisa bekin tanda-tanda heran deng hal luar biasa ko orang banya dong dapa lia deng dong pung mata biji sandiri.<bt>At that time the Lord God showed His goodness/kindness/grace/generostiy to Stefanus in many ways/quantity. And he also gave power so that Stefanus could do miracles and extra-ordinary things so that many people could see with their very own eyes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dari-dari sa = mana-mana sa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">dari-dari sa = mana-mana sa</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu waktu Tuhan Allah kasi berkat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Itu waktu Tuhan Allah kasi berkat banya sang Stefanus.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Di situ, ada barapa orang Yahudi yang datang dari tampa-tampa yang jao. Andia kota Kirene, kota Aleksandria, propinsi Kilikia, deng propinsi Asia. Dolu dong jadi orang laen pung budak, ma lama-lama ju dong pung tuan su kasi bebas sang dong. Ais, ini orang dong ada bakumpul di Yerusalem. Dong biasa maso pi satu ruma sambayang yang ada pung nama, &lt;Bebas dari Budak&gt;. Ais satu kali, dong su dengar Stefanus pung omong, ma dong sonde suka, ju dong mulai bakanjar deng dia.<bt>There, there were several Yahudi people who came from far away places. That.is Kirene city, Aleksandria city, Kilikia province, and Asia province. Previously they had been other people's slaves, but eventually their owners had given them freedom. So then these people were gathered in Yerusalem. They usually entered a certain *worship house which was named ‘Free from Slavery’. Then one time, they heard Stefanus' talk, but they didn't like [it], and they began to argue with him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV doesn't mention synagogue ***took"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">!@ CEV doesn't mention synagogue ***took out “which they built themselves”</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, ini orang dong ada bakumpul"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Ais, ini orang dong ada bakumpul di Yerusalem. Dong biasa maso pi ruma sambayang yang dong su bekin sandiri. Itu ruma sambayang tu, dong kasi nama, &lt;Bebas dari Budak&gt;.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ma Stefanus tu, orang yang pintar batúl, tagal dia omong pake kuasa dari Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi. Andia ko dong sonde bisa ontong ame sang dia.<bt>But that Stefanus, was truly an intelligent person, because he spoke using power from God2's Holy Spirit. That's why they could not win.advantage.over him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde bisa bawa sang dia ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sonde bisa bawa sang dia = can't win over; ontong sang dia = ;</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Tagal itu, dong cari akal jahat. Ju dong pi sogok ame barapa orang ko biar dong pi omong putar-balek bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong ada dengar ini orang omong tar bae-bae sang Musa deng Tuhan Allah! Dia memang hojat bagitu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, they devised an evil plan. And they went to convince(?) several people in order to.get them to go talk lying saying, “We-exc have heard this person say bad things against Musa and the Lord God! He was truly slandering/blaspheming!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="putar-bale is stronger than omong kosong,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">putar-bale is stronger than omong kosong, more serious</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dong tusu-tusu orang dong, sampe orang Yahudi pung tua-tua adat dong, deng guru agama dong, ju dapa dengar. Dengar bagitu, ju dong mara. Ais dong pi tangkap ame sang Stefanus, ju dong hela bawa sang dia pi mangada di tampa urus parkara agama.<bt>They poked-and-poked [incited] people, to the point that the Yahudi people's traditional leaders, and religious teachers, also got to hear [it]. Hearing like that, then they were angry. So they went to capture Stefanus, and drag bring him to face [stand trial] at the Place of Arranging Religious Litigations/Problems.</bt><v n="13" />Dong pung saksi palsu dong omong karang-karang so'al Stefanus bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang maen omong jahat tarús-tarús so'al Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Deng dia ju suka omong bekin rusak Tuhan Allah pung parenta dong yang ba'i Musa su kasi turun datang sang kotong.<bt>Their false witnesses made up a story about Stefanus saying, “This person habitually speaks evil continually about the *Temple. And he also likes to speak destroying the Lord God's commands which Gf/Ff Musa handed down to us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="omong karang-karang = made up story;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">omong karang-karang = made up story; omong jahat ; omong bekin rusak ; maen ~ suka = iteratirve aspect</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Botong ju su dengar dia omong bilang, Yesus, orang Nasaret tu, mau kasi rubu ini Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Deng Dia ju mau bongkar buang kotong pung atoran adat samua yang ba'i Musa su kasi turun sang kotong tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>We have also heard him say that Yesus, that Nasaret person, wants to knock down thie *Temple. And He also wants to dismantle discard all those traditional regulations of ours-inc which ba'i Musa handed down to us!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais itu ju, samua orang yang ada dudu bakumpul di tampa urus parkara agama tu, lia bae-bae sang Stefanus, tagal dia pung muka sama ke Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga dong pung muka.<bt>After that, then all the people who were sitting gathered at that place of handling religious litigations, looked carefully at Stefanus, because his face was the same as the face of an *angel of the Lord.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lia karás-karás = balalak, stare; aer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lia karás-karás = balalak, stare; aer muka = expression; tar nodek = sonde toe; omong karang-karang = omong bekin-bekin = omong lebe-lebe</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Stefanus bela diri di tampa urus parkara agama<bt>Stefanus defends himself at the Place of Taking.care.of Religious Litigations</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />Ais ju kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar tanya sang Stefanus bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang dong tudu sang lu tu, batúl ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>And then the *high priest asked Stefanus saying, “What they are accusing you of, is it true or not?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tudu = accuse, tuduh, gugat, mendakwa;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tudu = accuse, tuduh, gugat, mendakwa; kalák = tell on, lapor; kaláp = tampeleng, slap, tampar (from clap?)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01915b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none;horizontalPosition:center; verticalPosition:bottom">Stefanus omong deng orang bésar dong di tampa urus parkara agama Yahudi<bt>Stefanus talking to the big people at the Place of Taking.care.of Yahudi Religious Litigations</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2-3" />Stefanus manyao bale bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa-bapa deng sodara dong samua! Bosong coba dengar sang beta dolo. Dolu-dolu, kotong pung nene-moyang Abraham balóm pinda dari dia pung kampong asal. Ma Tuhan yang talalu hebat su kasi tunju diri sang dia. Tuhan parenta sang dia bilang, &lt;Pi jalan kasi tenga lu pung negrí ni, deng kasi tenga lu pung kelu dong. Barangkat su, ko pi satu negrí yang nanti Beta kasi tunju sang lu!&gt; Ais, baru dia barangkat dari itu tana Mesopotamia, ko mau pinda pi kota Haran.<bt>Stefanus replied in returned saying, “Fathers and all siblings! You please hear me. A long time ago, our-inc ancestor Abraham had not yet moved from his village of origin. But the most amazing/glorious God2 had shown himself to him. The Lord ordered him saying, 'Go travel leaving this country of yours, and leave your family. You leave (imperative), to go to a country which later I will show you!” After, then he left from that Mesopotamia land, in order to move to Haran city. [EXEG: Gk: God of glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kampong asal kelu = famili|i(2) |r"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kampong asal kelu = famili<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="7:2-3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tana Mesopotamia tu, sakarang dong subu bilang, negara Irak. Deng kota Haran tu, sakarang ada dia pung tampa bakás di negara Siria. Lia <span class="Italic">Carita Mula-mula</span> 12:1 ju.<bt>That Mesopotamia land, now they call it saying, the country of Irak. At that Haran city, now it's old (left.over) place (=remains) are in Siria country. See <span class="Italic">Genesis</span> 12:1 also.</bt></note><v n="4" />Ais dia jalan kasi tenga orang Kasdim dong pung negrí, ju pinda pi kota Haran.<bt>And he travelled leaving behind the Kasdim people's country, to move to Haran city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="weker = alarm clock (Dutch)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">weker = alarm clock (Dutch)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu dia pung papa barana mati, ju Tuhan Allah bawa sang dia pinda datang di Kana'an, andia ini tana yang bapa-bapa deng sodara dong ada tenga sakarang ni.<bt>When his birth father died, then the Lord God brought him moving coming to Kanaan, that is this land which fathers and siblings (=you) are living in now.</bt><note reference="7:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 11:31, 12:4</note><v n="5" />Itu waktu, Tuhan Allah sonde bagi kasi tana satu jingkal ju dari ini negrí ko jadi ba'i Abraham pung tana pusaka. Ma Tuhan Allah su janji memang bilang, nanti Dia kasi ini tana sang dia, ko jadi dia pung turunan dong pung tana pusaka. Padahal itu waktu dia sonde ada ana barana satu ju.<bt>At that time, the Lord God had not divided giving even one hand.span of land from this land to be ancestor Abraham's inheritance land. But the Lord God had promised beforehand that later he would give this land to him to be his decendant's inheritance land. Even though at that time he did not even have one single birth child (=biological child; used in contrast to classificatory 'children').</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tana pusaka ; jingkal = hand-span"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tana pusaka ; jingkal = hand-span (Buru tufe)</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 12:7, 13:15, 15:18, 17:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ma Tuhan Allah omong sang dia bilang, &lt;Lu pung turunan dong nanti pi tenga di orang laen dong pung negrí. Ju nanti itu orang dong takán sang dong bekin jadi dong pung budak, deng bekin sang dong sonde karu-karuang sampe ampa ratus taon.<bt>But the Lord God said to him saying, 'Your-sg descendants will later go stay in the country of other people (=other ethnic group). And later those people will pressure/apply.force to them making them their slaves, and they make them not like normal people (having their rights taken away from them) until four hundred years.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde karu-karuang = sonde layak sebagai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sonde karu-karuang = sonde layak sebagai manusia biasa, langgar HAM</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ma abis ampa ratus taon tu, nanti Beta hukum itu bangsa yang bekin sang lu pung turunan ko jadi dong pung budak. Ais ju lu pung turunan jalan kasi tenga itu negrí, ko datang di ini tampa ko sambayang minta tarima kasi sang Beta.&gt;<bt>But after those four hundred years, then I will judge/punish that ethnic group that makes your descendants to become their slaves. And then your descendants will travel leaving behind that country, to come to this place to pray saying thankyou to Me.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="budak (abe'at (Timor?) = hamba); songgo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">budak (abe'at (Timor?) = hamba); songgo</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:6-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 15:13-14; Kaluar dari Masir 3:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Omong abis bagitu, ju Dia ika itu janji deng acara sunat ko jadi tanda bilang, Abraham deng dia pung turunan dong, su jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang. Ais waktu dia pung ana Isak baru umur dalapan hari, ju Abraham sunat sang dia. Ais ju Isak sunat sang dia pung ana Yakob. Ais Yakob ju kasi sunat dia pung ana laki-laki dua blas orang, waktu dong satu-satu pung umur dalapan hari. Dong samua ni, andia kotong orang Yahudi pung nene-moyang.<bt>Finishing speaking like that, then He tied that promise with a circumcision ceremony to become a sign that Abraham and his descendants, had become the Lord God's people. Then when his child Isak was only eight days in age, then Abraham circumsized him. After a while (time passed), then Isak circumsized his child Yakob. Then Yakob also circumsized those 12 male children of his, when each one's age was eight days. All of them, they are who are our-inc Yahudi people's ancestors.</bt><note reference="7:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 17:10-14, 21:2-4, 25:26, 29:31--35:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais satu kali, kotong pung nene-moyang dong saki hati sang dong pung adi Yusuf, sampe dong jual buang sang dia ko pi jadi budak di tana Masir sana. Ma Tuhan Allah sonde parná kasi tenga sang dia.<bt>then one time our-inc ancestors had sick livers (=angry) towards their younger sibling Yusuf, to the point that they sold disposing.of him so that he became a slave in that land of Masir (remote). But the Lord God never left him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="saki hati lebe kuat dari iri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">saki hati lebe kuat dari iri hati</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 37:11, 28, 39:2, 21</note><v n="10" />Andia ko Tuhan kasi lapás sang dia dari dia pung susa dong samua. Tuhan Allah ju kasi sang dia otak encer ko bisa mangarti banya hal, sampe raja Masir sayang sang dia, tarús angka sang dia jadi gubernor di anteru tana Masir. Deng dia ju pegang kuasa di dalam raja pung ruma jabatan.<bt>That's why the Lord freed him from all his difficulty. The Lord God also gave him a smart brain so that he could understand many things, to the point that the raja Masir loved him, and then raised him up to become governor in the entire Masir land. And he also held authority/power in the raja's palace (official house).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="otak encer = pintar, cepat mengerti,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">otak encer = pintar, cepat mengerti, cepat tanggap, (Ant = otak kea = slow minded, bodoh); ruma jabatan = istana</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 41:39-41</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais itu, musim lapar datang hantam tana Masir deng tana Kana'an. Musim lapar tu, hebat talalu, sampe banya orang dong sangsara di mana-mana. Andia ko itu waktu, kotong pung nene-moyang dong ju su sonde bisa dapa makanan apa-apa.<bt>After that, the hungry years (=famine) came to beat.upon Masir land and Kanaan land. Those hungry years, were exceeding great, to the point that many people were experiencing tribulation/hardship all over the place. That's why at that time, our ancestors also no longer could get any food what's.so.ever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="musim lapar hantam/musim lapar saráng; dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">musim lapar hantam/musim lapar saráng; dong dua batola-bahela;</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 42:1-2</note><v n="12" />Ma ba'i Yakob dengar kabar bilang, ada makanan di tana Masir. Ais ju dia suru dia pung ana-ana dong, andia kotong pung nene-moyang dong ni, ko jalan pi tana Masir ko béli makanan di sana.<bt>But Gf/Ff Yakob heard news saying there was food in Masir land. Then he ordered his children, that is these ancestors of ours, to travel to Masir land to buy food there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Béli abis, ju dong pulang. Waktu dong pung makanan tu su abis, ju Yakob suru dong pi ulang lai ko coba béli makanan di tana Masir. Baru itu kali Yusuf buka kartu bilang, dia ni, dong pung adi barana Yusuf. Ais itu, baru dia kasi kanál dia pung kelu dong sang Raja Masir.<bt>After buying, then they went.home. When that food of their was all gone, then Yakob ordered them to go again to try to buy foo in Masir land. Only at that turn/time did Yusuf show his cards (reveal a secret) that he, was their younger sibling. After that, then he introduced his family to the Raja Masir.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buka kartu kalo dia ni, ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">buka kartu kalo dia ni, = buka rahasia, (idiom); adi barana = adik kandung</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 45:1, 16</note><v n="14" />Ais Yusuf minta ko dia pung papa deng dia pung kelu samua pinda pi tana Masir. Dong samua yang datang di sana, ada tuju pulu lima orang.<bt>Then Yusuf asked in order that his papa and all his family move to Masir land. All of them who came there, were 75 people.</bt><note reference="7:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 45:9-10, 17-18, 46:27</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Jadi Yakob pinda pi tana Masir, sampe dia deng kotong pung nene-moyang dong mati di sana.<bt>So (consequently) Yakob moved to Masir land, until he and our-inc ancestors died there.</bt><note reference="7:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 46:1-7, 49:33</note><v n="16" />Ma lama-lama, ju dong bawa pulang nene-moyang dong pung tulang pi kampong Sikem di tana Kana'an. Ais dong kubur itu tulang dong di tampa kubur yang tempo hari ba'i Abraham su béli ame dari Hemor pung turunan dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>But after a long time, they brought home ancestors bones to Sikem village. Then they buried those bones in the grave place which before Gf/Ff Abraham had bought from Hemor's descendants.”</bt><note reference="7:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 23:3-16, 33:19, 50:7-13, Yosua 24:32</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Stefanus manyao so'al Musa deng orang yang sonde mau dengar sang dia [\s2]<bt>Stefanus responds to the issue of Musa and people who didn't want to listen/obey him [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Stefanus sambung dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini samua jadi, tagal Tuhan su janji memang bilang, nanti Dia kasi tana pusaka sang Abraham di itu tampa. Waktu su mulai deka-deka dia pung hari ko Tuhan bekin ganáp Dia pung janji tu, kotong pung bangsa Yahudi su batamba-tamba jadi banya di tana Masir sana.<bt>Stefanus continued what he was saying saying, “All of this happened, because the Lord had promised (beforehand) saying, later He would give inheritance land to Abraham at that place. When it started to become close to the day that the Lord would fullfill that promise of His, our-inc Yahudi ethnic group had already increased very greatly in Masir land over.there/in.the.distance.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin iko dia pung janji ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bekin iko dia pung janji ; bekin ganáp dia pung janji</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Itu waktu, ada satu raja baru yang mulai pegang parenta di Masir. Ma dia sonde tau so'al Yusuf.<bt>At that time, there was a new raja who was begining to hold authority in Masir. But he did not know Yusuf.</bt><note reference="7:17-18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 1:7-8</note><v n="19" />Itu raja inja barmaen sang kotong pung bangsa. Dia kajám mau mati deng kotong pung nene-moyang dong. Deng dia paksa sang dong ko buang kasi tenga dong pung ana-ana mea dong, ko biar dong mati.<bt>That raja continually put pressure/forced that ethnic group of ours. He was very cruel to our ancestors. And he forced them to throw away leave.behind their newborn infants, to let them die.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ana-ana mea = infants; tendes barmaen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ana-ana mea = infants; tendes barmaen ~ takán barmaen ~ inja barmaen</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 1:10-11, 22</note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01918b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Raja Masir pung ana parampuan angka ame Musa dari aer<bt>The King of Masir's daughter lifts Musa from the water/river</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Itu waktu, ba'i Musa pung mama barana sang dia. Deng dia pung gaga lai! Dia pung mama deng papa dong sonde iko itu raja pung parenta. Ais dong piara sambunyi-sambunyi itu ana di dong pung ruma sampe dia pung umur tiga bulan.<bt>At that time, Gf/Ff Musa's mama gave birth to him. And his body very very strong and healthy! His mama and his papa did not follow that raja's command. So they took.care.of in secret that child in their house until his age was three months.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="badan sterek = sehat dan kuat;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">badan sterek = sehat dan kuat; badan ba'isi = strong and healthy; bekin gigi asam = (sampe mau cubit-cubit sang dia), makes one feel senang sekali), positive feeling</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 2:2</note><v n="21" />Waktu dong sonde bisa sambunyi itu ana dalam dong pung ruma lai, ju dong lapás buang sang dia. Ma raja Masir pung ana parampuan satu dapa katumu itu ana, ais dia angka ame itu ana ko dia piara sama ke dia pung ana sandiri.<bt>When they could not hide that child in their house anymore, then they let.him.go./set.him.free. But a daughter of the raja Masir found that child, then she lifted up took that child in order that he become like her own child.</bt><note reference="7:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 2:3-10</note><v n="22" />Tagal itu, orang Masir dong ajar kasi dong pung ilmu samua sang Musa, sampe dia sandiri jadi orang hebat. Deng dia tu, pintar ba'omong deng pintar karjá.<bt>Because of that, the Masir people taught all their science/knowledge to Musa, until he himself became a very impressive person. And he, was skilled in talking and skilled in working.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais waktu dia pung umur su ampa pulu taon, Musa mau pi cari kanál sang dia pung orang Isra'el dong sandiri.<bt>Then when his age was forty years, Musa wanted to be introduced himself to his Israel people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kapingin = a desire that has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kapingin = a desire that has been thought about, stewed;</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Waktu dia pi kaluar ju, dia dapa lia satu orang Isra'el kaná papoko dari satu orang Masir. Ais dia pi tolong dia pung orang satu bangsa, ju dia bunu bekin mati itu orang Masir.<bt>When he was out walking, then he saw an Israel person being affected by repeated.beats from a Masir person. Then he went to help his one[=same] ethnic group person, and he murdered killed that Masir person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bela implies words; tolong implies action"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bela implies words; tolong implies action here in context</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Te Musa kira dia pung bangsa su tau bilang, Tuhan Allah su kirim sang dia, ko kasi lapás sang dong dari dong pung susa. Ma dong balóm mangarti itu hal.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) Musa thought his ethnic group already knew that the Lord God had sent him, to free them from their difficulty. But they did not yet understand that matter.</bt><v n="26" />Dia pung beso, Musa kaluar lai ko pi lia dia pung orang Isra'el dong. Ju dia dapa lia dua orang ada bafait. Ais ju dia coba kasi dame sang dong dua bilang, &lt;Weh! Bosong dua ni, bakaka-adi. Ma karmana ko sampe bosong babakalai bagini ni?&gt;<bt>The next day, Musa went.out again to go see his Israel people. And he say two people who were fighting. And then he tried to make peace between them two saying, “Weh [+critical]! You two here, are relatives, right. How.is.it that you-pl are fighting like this?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="babakalai = Ambon baku bakalai; bakaka-adi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">babakalai = Ambon baku bakalai; bakaka-adi = REC; ba-1 = masih; ba-2 = REC</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ma orang yang papoko dia pung kawan tu tola buang sang ba'i Musa pi pinggir, ko bilang, &lt;Sapa yang angka sang lu jadi botong pung kapala! Deng sapa ju yang angka sang lu jadi botong pung tukang putus parkara ni?<bt>But the person who was beating that friend of his rejected throwing.away Gf/Ff Musa to the side, to side, “Who raised you to become our head! And who also raised you to become our person who decides litigations here?</bt><v n="28" />Lu kira lu mau bunu bekin mati sang beta, sama ke lu su bunu bekin mati itu orang Masir kamaren, ko?&gt;<bt>You think you want to murder kill me, just like you murdered killed that Masir person yesterday, right?’</bt><v n="29" />Dengar bagitu, ju Musa bangun bongkar dari Masir. Ais dia pi tenga di orang Median dong pung negrí. Dia kawin di situ, ju dong dapa dua ana laki-laki.<bt>Hearing that, then Musa got.up [and] ran from Masir. Then he went to live in the Median people's country. He married there, and they got two male children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bangun bongkar = lari terburu-buru, tidak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bangun bongkar = lari terburu-buru, tidak pusing apa-apa, clear out in a hurry with no prior preparation</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:23-29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 2:11-15, 18:3-4</note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01919b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Musa deng pohon tabakar yang sonde angus<bt>Musa with the tree on fire that doesn't burn</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Abis ampa pulu taon ju, Musa pi satu tampa karíng deka-deka deng satu gunung yang orang bilang gunung Sinai. Di situ Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga datang katumu deng Musa dari dalam api di pohon kici satu. Itu pohon tabakar, ma sonde angus.<bt>After forty years, then Musa went to a dry place near a mountain that people say Sinai mountain. There the Lord God's *angel came to meet with Musa from inside a fire in a little tree. That tree burned, but it didn't become burnt.</bt><v n="31" />Lia bagitu, ju Musa tanganga bodo sa. Ju dia pi deka-deka ko mau tau ada apa. Ma takuju, te dia dengar Tuhan omong dari dalam itu api bilang,<bt>Seeing that, then Musa just stood with his mouth open (=was amazed). And he went dear to know what was that. But suddenly/unexpectedly, te (contrary to expectation) he heard the Lord speak from inside that fire saying,</bt><v n="32" />&lt;Beta ni, lu pung nene-moyang dong pung Tuhan Allah; andia ba'i Abraham, ba'i Isak, deng ba'i Yakob pung Tuhan Allah.&gt; Dengar bagitu, ju dia taku mau mati sampe dia gamatar dingin, deng dia sonde barani angka muka ko lia itu pohon yang ada tabakar.<bt>'I here, your-sg ancestor's Lord God: that is Gf/Ff Abraham, Gf/Ff Isak, and Gf/Ff Yakob's Lord God.' Hearing that, then he was exceedingly afraid to the point that he shaking(literally shaking cold), and he did not dare lift his face to look at that tree that was burning.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gamatar dingin = lf Max"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">gamatar dingin = lf Max</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ais itu ju Tuhan omong lai bilang, &lt;We, Musa! Lu ada badiri di tana yang barisi. Lapás buang lu pung sandal!<bt>After that then the Lord spoke again saying, 'We [+get attention], Musa! You are standing on land which is *holy. Take.off dispose.of your sandals!</bt><v n="34" />Jang sangka bilang, Beta su lupa buang Beta pung orang Isra'el di Masir sana. Sonde! Beta masi inga sang dong. Beta tau dong pung sangsara. Beta su dengar dong batarea minta tolong. Jadi Beta sakarang turun ko pi kasi lapás sang dong. Mari sini dolo! Beta mau kirim sang lu ko kambali pi Masir sana.&gt;<bt>Don't assume/think that I have forgotten disposed.of My Israel people over.there. No! I still remember them. I know their tribulations. I have heard them yelling requesting help. So I now come.down in order that I will free them. Come here! I want to send you to return to Masir.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@GRAMMAR Beta sakarang turun ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">@@GRAMMAR Beta sakarang turun ko</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:30-34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 3:1-10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Deng bagitu, Tuhan Allah yang kasi tunju diri dalam api tu, parenta sang Musa ko pulang pi Masir. Tuhan tunju sang dia ko kasi lapás orang Isra'el dari dong pung sangsara. Musa ni, andia orang yang dolu dong tanya bilang, &lt;Sapa angka sang lu jadi botong pung kapala?&gt; Ma sakarang Tuhan sandiri yang angka sang dia!<bt>With that, the Lord God who showed Himself inside that fire, commanded Musa to return to Masir. The Lord instructed him to free the Israel people from their tribulation. This Musa, he's.the.one who before they asked saying, 'Who lifted you to become our head?' But now the Lord himself was the one who lifted/appointed him! [NOTE: ‘judge’ is undertranslated here due to heavy style. The phrase here should evoke the whole of the above exchange.]</bt><note reference="7:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 2:14</note><v n="36" />Ais ju Musa kambali pi Masir. Di situ dia bekin tanda heran bésar-bésar. Ais dia bawa kaluar orang Isra'el dong dari Masir. Dia bawa sang dong jalan lewat Laut Mera, tarús dong jalan kuliling tampa kosong sampe ampa pulu taon.<bt>And then Musa returned to Masir. There he did big *miracles. Then he brought out the Israel people from Masir. He brought them travelling along the Mera Sea, then they traveling all around an empty place for 40 years.</bt><note reference="7:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 7:3, 14:21, Daftar Sensus 14:33</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Te Musa sandiri kasi tau sang orang Isra'el dong bilang, &lt;Nanti Tuhan Allah angka ame satu orang dari bosong pung teng-tenga, ko jadi Dia pung jubir, sama ke Dia su angka sang beta ni.&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) Musa himself told the Israel people saying, ‘Later the Lord God will lift.up a person from your midst, to become his spokesperson, just like He has lifted up me here.’</bt><note reference="7:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 8:15, 18</note><v n="38" />Musa ada sama-sama deng kotong pung orang Isra'el dong di tampa kosong. Dia tu, yang jadi jambatan kasi kotong pung nene-moyang dong deng Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga. Te itu ana bua tu, kasi turun Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata sang Musa, yang kasi tunju sang kotong jalan idop yang batúl. Itu Kata-kata dong yang Tuhan kasi turun di gunung Sinai.<bt>Musa was together with our-inc Israel people in that empty place. He there, [was the one] who became a bridge/go.between for our ancestors and the Lord God's angel. Cuz (elaboration) that angel there, brought down the Lord God's Words/Message to Musa which showed us-inc the life path which is correct. Those are the Words/Message which the Lord brought down at that Sinai mountain.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Buru li-kas-mangit; orang tenga = get"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Buru li-kas-mangit; orang tenga = get in the middle of a fight to bring peace, perantara, pembawa pesan; jambatan can also be orang, penghubung (in weddings, matchmaker);</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 19:1--20:17, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:1-33</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Biar bagitu ju, ma kotong pung nene-moyang dong sonde mau dengar sang Musa. Ju dong tola buang sang dia, ko dong mau pulang kambali pi Masir sa.<bt>But even though it was like that, our ancestors didn't want to hear Musa. And they rejected disposing of him, because <span class="Italic">(ko)</span> they just wanted to return to Masir.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tola buang = reject, tolak; tola"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tola buang = reject, tolak; tola kasi ondor = resist,</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Ais dong pi kokoe sang Harun bilang, &lt;Lu pung adi Musa su bawa kaluar sang kotong dari tana Masir. Ma sakarang botong sonde tau dia su ada di mana lobang. Jadi botong minta ko lu bekin kasi botong sosonggo, ko biar dia sandiri sa yang antar bawa sang botong.&gt;<bt>Then they went to try.and.convince Harun saying, 'Your younger sibling Musa has brought us out from Masir land. But now we-exc don't know what hole he is in (=don't know where in the world he is). So we-inc as that you make us an idol, to that it's just he himself (=idol) who escorts us.'</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kokoe = bujuk; di mana lobang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kokoe = bujuk; di mana lobang = where in the world; kayu songgo /sosonggo = (benda) berhala, idol (can be from gold, silver)</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 32:1</note><v n="41" />Ais dong bekin ame satu patong jadi sosonggo. Dia pung model sama ke sapi ana satu. Ais dong horo binatang kasi itu sosonggo. Tarús dong bekin pesta rame-rame, tagal dong pung hati puas deng itu barang yang dong su bekin deng dong pung tangan sandiri.<bt>Thus they made a statue to be (used for) traditional worship. It's shape/model was like a calf. Then they sliced/slaughter/sacrificed (ritually) animals for/to that idol. Next they made a feast with.lots.of.activity, because their livers were satisfied with that thing which they had made with their own hands.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="songgo (kk) =worship (traditional); sosonggo (kb)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">songgo (kk) =worship (traditional); sosonggo (kb) = idol; rupa can be limited to face, model = entire shape, type</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:41" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 32:2-6</note><v n="42" />Lia bagitu, ju Tuhan Allah bale balakang sang dong. Ju dong mulai songgo lai barang di langit sama ke matahari, bulan, deng bintang-bintang. Ma Tuhan Allah kasi tenga sang dong bagitu sa. Itu pas deng apa yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong su tulis dari dolu bilang,<bt>Seeing that, then the Lord God turned his back on them. And they also began to idol (traditional) worship things in the sky like the sun, moon, and stars, but the Lord God just left them like that. That was exactly like what the Lord God's spokepeople had written from before saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Weh! Bosong orang Isra'el dong!<bt>'Weh [+critical]! You-pl Israel people!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ampa pulu taon bosong jalan kuliling di itu tampa kosong,<bt>40 years you have travelled in circles around that empty place,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ais bosong horo binatang dong ko sémba sang Beta, ko,<bt>then you slice/slaughter/sacrifice animals to worship Me, or,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">bosong songgo sang sapa?<bt>you traditional.worship whom?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="foe = increase"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">foe = increase</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="43" />Bosong bukan puji-puji sang Beta!<bt>You are not praising Me!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tiap hari bosong maen songgo bosong pung patong sosonggo dong sa.<bt>Every day you repeatedly traditional.worship only your idols.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Bosong suka maso-kaluar pi setan Molok pung ruma songgo.<bt>You like to go in [and] out of evil spirit Molok's traditional.worship house.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Bosong ju suka songgo sang bintang satu pung setan, nama Refan.<bt>You also like to traditional.worship a star's evil spirit, named Refan.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Jadi bosong maen songgo apa yang bosong su bekin deng bosong pung tangan sandiri!<bt>So (consequently) you repeatedly traditional.worship what you have made with your own hands!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko nanti Beta pasti angka buang jao-jao sang bosong pi Babel pung sablá sana.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>That's why later I will surely pick you up [and] throw you away to Babel's other side over there.’”</bt><note reference="7:42-43" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Amos 5:25-27</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Stefanus manyao so'al Ruma Sambayang Pusat [\s2]<bt>Stefanus responds to the issue of the *Temple [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Stefanus sambung dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah kasi tunju sang ba'i Musa satu tampa sambayang pung model. Ju Musa dong kasi bangun satu Tenda Sambayang<bt>Stefanus continued speaking saying, “The Lord God showed ancestor Musa a worship place's model. And Musa (collective) built a Worship Tent</bt><note reference="7:44" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tuhan ukir Sapulu Hukum di batu plat, ais sarakan kasi ba'i Musa, ko biar orang Isra'el bekin iko samua. Itu batu plat tu, dong subu bilang, &lt;Saksi&gt;. Dong simpan itu batu plat di Tenda Sambayang. Andia ko dong ju subu sang itu Tenda bilang, &lt;&lt;Tenda Saksi&gt;&gt;. Di ini ayat, ada tatulis bilang, Tenda Saksi ju.<bt>God2 carved the 10 Laws/Cammandments on flat stones, and handed them over to Gf Musa, so that the people of Isra'el would follow/obey them all. Those flat stones were referred to as ‘Witness/Testimony’. They stored/kept those flat stones in the Tent of Worship. That is why they also referred to that Tent as ‘Tent of Witness/Testimony’. In this verse it is also written saying, Tent of Witness/Testimony.</bt></note>yang dong bekin dari kulit binatang deng kaen, iko itu model. Jadi orang Isra'el dong datang sambayang sang Tuhan Allah di situ. Kalo dong pinda dari satu tampa pi satu tampa, dong bongkar itu Tenda Sambayang, ais dong ika sang dia, ju dong dorok pi tampa yang baru. Di situ, dong kasi badiri ulang itu Tenda.<bt>which they made from animal skins and cloth, following that model. So (consequently) Israel people came to worship the Lord God there. When they moved from one place to another place, they took.apart that Worship Tent, and they tied it up, and they shoulder carried carrying it to the new place. There, they erected again that Tent. [EXEG: ‘tent of testimony’ undertranslated and put in ftn. See discussion in Bruce, and Carlton.]</bt><note reference="7:44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 25:9, 40</note></p>
    <fig path="hk-lb\lb00259c.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:center">Tenda Sambayang<bt>Tent of Worship</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Lama-lama, waktu Yosua dong baparáng lawan suku-bangsa laen dong di tana Kana'an, Tuhan Allah usir kasi kaluar sang dong. Ais Dia bagi-bagi itu negrí kasi sang kotong pung nene-moyang dong. Waktu dong maso pi rampas ame itu negrí, dong ju bawa Tuhan pung Tenda Sambayang pi situ. Itu Tenda badiri tarús di situ sampe raja Daud pegang parenta.<bt>After awhile, when Yosua (collective) were at war opposing the other ethnic groups in Kanaan land, the Lord God expelled driving them out. Then He divided that country giving it to our ancestors. When they entered to take over that country, they also brought the Lord's Worship Tent there. That Tent stood continually there until raja Daud held authority.</bt><note reference="7:45" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yosua 3:14-17</note><v n="46" />Raja Daud ni, sambayang sang Tuhan Allah yang sama ke kotong pung ba'i Yakob dong ju sambayang sang Dia. Ais Daud bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati, ju Tuhan kasi berkat sang dia. Ais ju dia minta sang Tuhan, ko dia yang kasi bangun Ruma Sambayang Pusat yang baru.<bt>This Raja Daud, prayed to the Lord God which was the same one that our ancestor Yakob (collective) also worshiped Him. Then Daud made the Lord's liver happy. And he asked the Lord, so that he [would be the one] who build a new Temple.</bt><note reference="7:46" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Samuel 7:1-16, 1 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 17:1-14</note><v n="47" />Ma Daud pung ana Soleman yang kasi bangun Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat.<bt>But [it was] David's child Soleman who build the Lord's *Temple.</bt><note reference="7:47" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 6:1-38, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 3:1-17</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Ma kotong tau bilang, Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi sonde tenga di ruma yang manusia bekin, tagal dolu Tuhan pung jubir satu su tulis memang bilang,<bt>But we-inc know that the Lord God Most High does not live in that house which humans made, because long ago one of the Lord's spokespersons wrote beforehand saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="49" />&lt;Langit tu, Beta pung korsi parenta.<bt>&lt;That sky, My commanding chair.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng bumi tu, Beta pung tampa alas kaki.<bt>And that earth, My place for resting feet.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tampa alas kaki = place; alas"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tampa alas kaki = place; alas kaki = sandal; tampa mua(t) kaki = place to stretch and prop feet</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Karmana ko bosong bisa bangun kasi Beta satu ruma yang pantas ko Beta tenga di situ? Sonde mungkin!<bt>How is it that you-pl can build Me a house which is worthy for Me to stay there? No way!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="50" />Ko langit deng bumi pung isi samua, Beta yang bekin!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>For all the sky and earth's contents, I [am the one] who made [them]!&gt;&gt;&gt; [+emphatic]</bt><note reference="7:49-50" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 66:1-2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Stefanus tudu sang kapala-kapala bilang, dong sonde kanál sang Tuhan pung Orang Barisi [\s2]<bt>Stefanus accuses the leaders saying they don't know/recognise the Lord's Holy/Clean Person [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Ais Stefanus sambung dia pung omong, deng masparak sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dasar manusia kapala batu dong! Bosong sama ke orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan Allah, deng sonde mau dengar sang Dia. Bosong tukang malawan sang Tuhan Allah, sama ke nene-moyang dong yang bale balakang sang Dia! Sakarang bosong masi mau malawan sang Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi lai, ko?<bt>Then Stefanus continued his talk, and got.angry at them saying, “You-pl are stone headed (=stubborn) humans! You are like people who do not know the Lord God. People.who.habitually oppose the Lord God, like the ancestors who turned their backs on Him! Now you still want to oppose the Lord's *Holy Spirit, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong manusia dasar kapala batu!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Bosong manusia dasar kapala batu!</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:51" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 63:10</note><v n="52" />Bosong pung nene-moyang dong ju bekin susa tarús sang Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong. Coba bosong kasi tau: jubir mana yang dong sonde bekin sangsara sang dia? Sonde ada, aa?! Dolu Tuhan pung jubir dong, suka kasi tau memang bilang, nanti Tuhan Allah mau kirim Dia pung Orang yang Barisi. Ma bosong pung nene-moyang dong bunu bekin mati Tuhan pung jubir-jubir dong. Sampe bosong sandiri ju pake orang laen bunu bekin mati Tuhan pung Orang yang Barisi tu.<bt>Your ancestors also continually caused difficulty to the Lord God's spokespeople. You go ahaed and try and tell: which spokeperson did they not cuz (elaboration) difficulty to. There's none, right! Before the Lord's spokesperson, like to tell ahead of time saying, later the Lord God will send His Holy Person. But your ancestors murdered kill the Lord's spokesperson. To the point that you yourselves also used other people would murder kill that Holy Person of the Lord's.</bt><v n="53" />Deng Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga dong ju su antar bawa samua atoran adat yang Tuhan mau kasi sang kotong, ma bosong sonde mau toe.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the Lord God's *angels have delivered bringing all the regulations(according to traditional custom) which the Lord wants to give us-inc, but you-pl don't want to pay any attention.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong lempar bekin mati sang Stefanus<bt>They throw [stones] killing Stefanus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="54" />Waktu orang yang ada dudu urus parkara dengar Stefanus pung omong tu, dong tau memang dia ada lempar sala kasi sang dong. Ais dong saki hati deng makan gigi.<bt>When the people who were sitting to take.care of the litigation heard that speaking of Stefanus', they knew that he was accusing them. So they were very angry [lit. sick livered and ate/ground their teeth].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makan gigi = mara mau mati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">makan gigi = mara mau mati sampe mau bertindak dgn keras; maruak = with words; makan gigi lebe karas; ma'ale gigi = keep chewing on tough meat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="55" />Ma Stefanus yang takaná Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi tu, angka mata ko lia pi langit. Di situ, dia dapa lia Tuhan Allah pung hebat samua, deng Tuhan Yesus ada badiri di Tuhan Allah pung sablá kanan di tampa yang paling hormat.<bt>But Stefanus who had been affected by that Holy Spirit of the Lord's, lifted his eyes to look at the sky. There, he saw all the Lord God's amazingness, and the Lord Yesus was stand at the Lord God's right side in that place which is most honorable. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [NOTE to daughter translations: “standing” here is correct. Because of the high frequency of the phrase “seated at the right hand of God” in both the scriptures and in creeds, expect your teams to question you on this. Most commentators see “standing” here as indicating Jesus is standing to welcome Stephen into heaven.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ queried"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">@@ queried</Message></Annotation><v n="56" />Ju Stefanus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini bapa-bapa dong. Beta ada lia langit tabuka, deng Manusia Tulen ada badiri di tampa yang paling hormat di Tuhan Allah pung sablá kanan.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Stefanus spoke saying, “It's like this, fathers. I am seeing the sky open, and Humanity's Child is standing at that place which is most honorable at the Lord God's right side.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="57" />Dengar bagitu, ju orang yang urus itu parkara dong tutu dong pung talinga. Ais dong batarea suru Stefanus paróp dia pung mulu. Ju dong samua malompa rame-rame ko mau ru'i barmaen sang dia.<bt>Hearing that, then the people who take care of that litigation shut their ears. Then they yelled ordering Stefanus to shut up his mouth. And they all jumped with.alot.of excitement wanting to tear apart (viciously) Stefanus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paróp = shut up! ru'i ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">paróp = shut up! ru'i = tear their hair, clothes,</Message></Annotation><v n="58" />Ais dong hela raroso bawa sang dia pi luar kota. Tarús saksi dong buka dong pung baju luar, ko kasi pegang di satu orang muda. Dia pung nama Saulus, deng dia jadi dong pung tukang kipas. Ais ju dong pi lempar barmaen sang Stefanus deng batu.<bt>Then they dragged him along the ground to go outside the city. Next the witnesses took off their outside clothes, to give them to a young person to hold. His name Saulus, and he was their inciter (lit. fanner). And then they went to repeatedly throw stones at Stefanus. [EXEG: UNSs from a couple of groups thought he was in role of underling (like a waterboy holding their clothes), not a leader. “He was their inciter” is deliberate clarification of purpose/implications of action understood by original audience. Handled as a type of symbolic action.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hela raroso = drag along the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hela raroso = drag along the ground; calana komprang = baggy pants that can be easily rolled up at high water ; = baruk nabi = calana komprang; tukang kipas = ring-leader, provokator (metapor of api yg harus dikipas baru panas/manyala)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02154b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;verticalPosition:top;horizontalPosition:center">Dong lempar bekin mati sang Stefanus<bt>They throw killing Stefanus</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="59" />Waktu dong masi lempar sang Stefanus, ju dia batarea deng suara karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Yesus! Beta pung waktu su deka-deka. Tarima sang beta suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>When they were still throwing at Stefanus, then he yelled with a loud voice saying, “Lord Yesus! My time is over. Recieve Me (imperative)!”</bt><v n="60" />Ais ju dia jato talipa di dia pung lutut ko batarea lai deng suara karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa, jang kasi sang dong pikol ini dosa!&gt;&gt; Ais itu, dia pung napas putus, ju dia mati.<bt>Then he fell folding his knees to yell yell again with a loud voice saying, “Father, don't make them shoulder.carry this sin!” And then his breath was cut.off/stopped and [he]died.</bt><c n="8" /><v n="1a" />Deng Saulus ju ada di itu tampa, deng dia tarima bae dong bunu sang Stefanus.<bt>And Saulus was also at that place, and he accepted well [the fact that] they murdered Stefanus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Saulus bekin sangsara sang Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong<bt>Saulus causes tribulation to the Lord Yesus' people</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="siksa = aniaya, bekin susa, bekin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">siksa = aniaya, bekin susa, bekin sengsara (physically, socially, or mentally), persecute (UNS's more like torture than persecute, need to reexamine all occurrences)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="1b-2" />Waktu Stefanus mati tu, ada barapa orang yang rindu sang Tuhan. Dong pi ame Stefanus pung mayat ko pi kubur sang dia, deng manangis makarereu sang dia.<bt>When Stefanus died, there were several people who yearned/longed for the Lord. They took Stefanus' corpse to go bury him, and cried in grief/sobbing for him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makarareu ~ makareu = ratapi orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">makarareu ~ makareu = ratapi orang mati, wail, mourn by weeping</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Mulai itu hari, orang mulai bekin susa Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong di kota Yerusalem, sampe dong sangsara satenga mati. Ais dong lari tasiar pi propinsi Yudea deng propinsi Samaria. Dong samua lari, cuma tenga Yesus pung utusan dong sa di Yerusalem.<bt>Starting from that day, people began to cuz (elaboration) difficulty to the Lord Yesus' people in Yerusalem city, to the point that they got incredibly intense tribulation. So they ran spread.out all.over.the place in Yudea province and Samaria province. They all ran, leaving only Yesus' apostles in Yerusalem.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lari tasiar ~ lari tasiram ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lari tasiar ~ lari tasiram ; lari tabodo-bodo = harba-biruk</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ma Saulus ada cari-cari jalan ko mau bekin ancor Yesus pung orang dong. Dia pi cari sang dong di mana-mana. Dia maso-kaluar ruma-ruma ko cari sang dong. Biar laki-laki ko parampuan, dia tangkap bawa, ais lempar buang pi dalam bui.<bt>But Saulus kept hunting for a way to destroy Yesus' people. He went hunting them all.over.the.place. He went in [and] out of houses to look for them. Regardless of whether male or female, he capture and took them, then threw disposing of them in jail.</bt><note reference="8:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 22:4-5, 26:9-11</note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02155b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none">Dong tangkap ame laki-laki deng parampuan ko mau kasi maso dalam bui<bt>They capture males and females to put in jail</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Filipus kasi tau Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae di propinsi Samaria<bt>Filipus tells/explains the Lord Yesus' Good Story in Samaria province</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Biar orang ada bekin susa sang Yesus pung orang dong, sampe dong lari tasiram, ma dong sonde barenti kasi tau Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae kasi orang di mana-mana.<bt>Even though people were causing difficulty to Yesus' people, to the point that they ran hither-thither, but they did not stop telling the Lord Yesus' Good Story to people everywhere.</bt><v n="5" />Conto ke, satu waktu, Filipus pi satu kota di propinsi Samaria, ko kasi tau orang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus tu, Kristus, andia Orang yang Tuhan Allah su tunju memang dari dolu.&gt;&gt;<bt>For example, one time, Filipus went to a city in Samaria province, to tell people that, that Yesus, is the Kristus, that is, the Person whom the Lord God has appointed beforehand from long ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko kasi tau orang dong itu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ko kasi tau orang dong itu carita so'al Orang yang Tuhan Allah su tunju memang dari dolu, andia Yesus tu.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Waktu orang banya dapa lia tanda-tanda heran yang dia bekin, ju dong bakumpul ko dengar bae-bae apa yang dia omong.<bt>When many people saw the miracles that he did, then they gathered to listen carefully to what he said.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Conto ke, di situ ju ada orang-orang yang takaná setan dong. Deng itu setan dong kaluar kasi tenga itu orang deng batarea kuat-kuat. Ada ju banya orang lumpu deng orang kaki hela dong jadi bae memang.<bt>For example, there there were also people who were affected by evil spirits. And those spirits left leaving behind their people with loud shouts. There were also many crippled people and people [with] a dragging foot were also healed.</bt><v n="8" />Andia ko orang dong di itu kota sanáng mau mati.<bt>That's why the people in that city were very happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orang-orang dong di itu kota ~"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">orang-orang dong di itu kota ~ orang-orang di itu kota dong</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Di itu kota tu, ada satu orang pintar, nama Simon. Su lama dia pake dia pung ilmu, ko bekin orang Samaria dong. Dia angka-angka dia pung diri bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, orang hebat!&gt;&gt;<bt>In that city, there was a magic person (lit. smart person), named Simon. For a long time he had been using his knowledge/magic to (adversely) affect the Samaria people. He elevated himself saying, “I here, am an amazing person!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dia pung suanggi = sorcery (UNS's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">dia pung suanggi = sorcery (UNS's say suanggi is for killing people, whereas ilmu can be used to heal); ilmu ; ilmu galap ; ilmu setan; ilmu hitam; orang pintar = dukun, suanggi, shaman, tukang sihir; obat nona = for getting a reluctant girl</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10-11" />Jadi dari itu kota, ana kici ko orang bésar, laki-laki ko parampuan, samua ada omong-omong itu orang pung nama bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Ini orang ni, hebat talalu! Apa yang dia bekin tu, datang dari Tuhan Allah pung kuasa!&gt;&gt; Gara-gara dia pung ilmu-ilmu, sampe orang dong suka pake sang dia dari dolu.<bt>So from that city, small people or big people, male or female, all were talking about that person's name saying, “Awii! [+impressed] This person here, he's incredibly amazing. That which here is doing there, comes from the power of the Lord God!” On the basis of his sorcery, it got to the point that people liked to used him from before.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kuasa ~ koasa; tukang makan puji"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kuasa ~ koasa; tukang makan puji = suka dipuji, boaster, braggart, puji diri taru kira = perhatikan; Gara-gara dia pung suanggi, = because of his sorcery; lengket = hang around; taru mata = always paying attention (not known by UNS's); taru hati = fall in love</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ma sakarang dong dapa dengar Filipus ajar sang dong so'al Tuhan Allah pung parenta. Deng dia ju kasi tunju jalan ko dong bisa maso jadi Tuhan pung orang, bawa Yesus pung nama. Dengar abis bagitu, ju orang banya dong parcaya, ko maso jadi Tuhan pung kelu. Laki-laki deng parampuan, samua ju jadi bagitu. Andia ko dong dapa sarani.<bt>But now they got to hear Filipus teach about the Lord God's rule/governing. And he also showed the path so that they could enter and become the Lord's people, bearing Yesus' name. After hearing like that, then many people believed and entered to become the Lord's family. Males and females, all became like that. That's why they were *baptised.</bt><v n="13" />Ma tau-tau, te Simon ju parcaya deng mau jadi Yesus pung orang. Ju dong sarani sang dia. Ais dia pi iko-iko deng Filipus pi mana-mana. Waktu dia lia tanda-tanda heran yang Filipus ada bekin tu, ju dia goyang kapala bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Yang bagini ni, su talalu hebat ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they were surprised, cuz (elaboration) Simon also believed and wanted to become Yesus' person. And they baptised him. Then he went following Filipus everywhere. When he saw those miracles that Filipus was doing, then he shook his head saying, “Awii [+amazement]! What's like this here, its exceedingly amazing!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Itu waktu, Tuhan Yesus pung utusan dong yang ada di Yerusalem dapa dengar bilang, orang di propinsi Samaria dong su parcaya sang Tuhan pung Carita Bae. Ais ju dong kirim Petrus deng Yohanis pi sana.<bt>At that time, the Lord Yesus' apostles who were in Yerusalem heard that people in Samaria province had believed the Lord's Good Story. So then they sent Petrus and Yohanis there.</bt><v n="15-17" />Waktu dong dua sampe di sana, ju dong dapa tau bilang, itu orang yang ada di situ dong, balóm tarima Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi. Dong cuma dapa sarani pake Yesus pung nama sa. Ais Petrus deng Yohanis taro tangan di itu orang dong, deng dong sambayang, minta ko orang Samaria ju dapa tarima Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi. Ais ju itu orang dong tarima memang.<bt>When the two of them arrived there, they got to know that the people who were there, had not yet received God2's Holy Spirit. They had only been baptized using just Yesus' name. Then Petrus and Yohanis laid hands on those people, and they prayed, asking that the Samaria people would also receive the Lord's Spirit. Then those people actually did receive [it].</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Itu waktu, Simon dapa lia dong dua taro tangan pi atas itu orang dong, ju dong tarima Tuhan pung Roh. Ais Simon sorong kasi Petrus deng Yohanis doi, deng minta bilang,<bt>At that time, Simon saw them two laying hands on those people's heads, and they received the Lord's Spirit. Then Simon shifted [his hand] sideways to (implied, discretely) give Petrus and Yohanis money, and asked saying,</bt><v n="19" />&lt;&lt;Bapa dong, é! Bosong kasi itu kuasa sang beta ju. Ko biar kalo beta mau taro tangan pi atas sapa sa, na, dong ju tarima Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi.&gt;&gt;<bt>"We! Fathers! You give that power to me also. So that if I want to lay hands on top of whomever, na, they also will receive that Holy Spirit of the Lord God.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma Petrus masparak sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu deng lu pung doi kaná kutuk! Lu kira lu bisa béli kuasa dari Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi deng doi? Sonde! Orang sonde bisa béli Tuhan pung Roh!<bt>But Petrus got angry with him saying, “Curse that money of yours! Do you think you can buy the Lord's Holy Sprit with money? No! People cannot buy God2's Spirit!</bt><v n="21" />Lu sonde ada pung hak apa-apa deng Tuhan pung Roh, te lu pung hati sonde lurus. Lu cuma cari-cari akal sa.<bt>You don't have any authority what's.so.ever with the Lord's Spirit, cuz (elaboration) your liver is not straight(=dishonest). You are only just devising a scheme [eg. to get rich].</bt><v n="22" />Lu barenti suda dari lu pung dosa ni. Lebe bae lu sambayang minta sang Tuhan ko, kalo bisa, na, Dia hapus buang lu pung akal busuk.<bt>You stop this sin of yours (imp.). It's better if you pray asking God, if possible, na, He will wipe away your evil scheme.</bt><v n="23" />Beta tau bilang, lu ponu deng iri hati, deng ada banya hal jahat yang ika sang lu!&gt;&gt;<bt>I know that you are full of jealousy, and there are many evil things which tie you!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ais Simon minta sang dong dua bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa dong! Kalo bagitu, na, bosong tolong sambayang kasi sang beta, ko biar kutuk yang bosong su omong tadi tu, jang kaná sang beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Simon requested them two saying, “Fathers! If it's like that, na, you-pl please pray for me, so that that curse which you spoke earlier/just now, won't affect me.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais itu, Petrus deng Yohanis carita Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae samua, deng dong kasi tau Tuhan pung Kata-kata di itu kota. Ju dong pulang pi Yerusalem. Iko-iko jalan, dong singga di kampong-kampong di propinsi Samaria, ko bawa Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae kasi orang di situ dong.<bt>After that, Petrus and Yohanis storied all the Lord Yesus' Good Story, and they told the Lord's Words in that city. Then they went home to Yerusalem. Along the way, they stopped at villages in Samaria province, to bring the Lord Yesus' Good Story to people there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pulang pi = manuju, still on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pulang pi = manuju, still on the way</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Filipus katumu deng satu pagawe tinggi dari Afrika<bt>Filipus meets with a high [govt] official from Afrika</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ais Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga suru Filipus bilang, &lt;&lt;Ana, é! Lu barangkat iko jalan pi salatan. Iko itu jalan lama yang dari kota Yerusalem tambús pi negrí Gasa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the Lord's *angel ordered Filipus saying, “Child, e! You leave and go travelling toward the south. Follow that old road which goes from Yerusalem to the country of Gasa.” [EXEG: “old road” implies no longer used (much), covering the Gk ‘wilderness road’ or ‘desert road’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="27-28" />Dengar itu parenta, ju Filipus barangkat memang. Waktu dia ada di itu jalan, ju dia dapa lia satu orang. Dia tu, satu orang bésar dari negrí Etiopia.<bt>Hearing that order, then Filipus left right away. When he was on that road, then he saw a person. That him (=person) was a big/important person from Etiopia country.</bt><note reference="8:27-28" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan Yunani ju bilang ini orang bésar ni, orang kabiri. Etiopia tu, satu negrí di Afrika pung sablá timur.<bt>Yunani writings also say that this big person here, was a castrated person. That country of Etiopia is a country on the mainland of Afrika on the eastern side.</bt></note>Dia yang urus ratu Kandake pung harta dong samua. Dia baru abis iko sambayang di Yerusalem, deng sakarang dia ada pulang pake kareta. Waktu Filipus dapa lia sang dia, dia ada dudu baca di atas itu kareta. Dia ada baca dari Tuhan Allah pung jubir ba'i Yesaya pung tulisan.<bt>He was who arranged all queen Kandake's wealth. He had just finished praying in Yerusalem, and now he was going home using a cart. When Filipus saw him, he was sitting reading in that cart. He was reading from the Lord God's spokeperson Gf/Ff Yesaya's book.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="FTN: Add? They sometimes castrated their"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">FTN: Add? They sometimes castrated their slaves. Trusted slaves could become important officials.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Ais Tuhan pung Roh suru sang Filipus ko pi jalan deka-deka deng itu kareta ko katumu deng itu orang.<bt>Then the Lord's Spirit ordered Filipus to go walk close to that cart to meet with that person.</bt><v n="30" />Waktu dia su deka-deka, ju dia dapa dengar itu orang baca dari Ba'i Yesaya pung tulisan. Ju dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Bapa mangarti apa yang bapa ada baca tu, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>When he was close, then he heard that person reading from Gf/Ff Yesaya's book. And he asked saying, “Father! Do Father(=You) understand what you are reading there, or not?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais, itu orang manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde. Musti ada orang yang kasi mangarti sang beta dolo, baru beta bisa tau. Mari nae datang ko dudu deng beta di sini.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that person replied saying, “No. There must be a person who explains it to me first, then I can know. Come up here to sit with me here.”</bt><v n="32" />Naa, itu tulisan yang dia ada baca pung bunyi bagini:<bt>Naa, [+shift] the sound of that writing which he was reading is like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dong hela bawa sang Dia, sama ke orang hela bawa domba,<bt>"They drag [and] brought Him, like a person dragging bringing a sheep,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko mau horo.<bt>to cut.the.throat.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="horo = sembelih, slaughter, cut the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">horo = sembelih, slaughter, cut the throat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia ju jadi sama ke domba ana yang orang gunting Dia pung bulu,<bt>He also is like a lamb that is having its fur cut by a person,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Dia sonde batarea apa-apa.<bt>but He does not yell out at all.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Dia sonde buka Dia pung mulu,<bt>He doesn't open His mouth,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng sonde manyao satu kata ju.<bt>and doesn't reply with even one word.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="domba ana = domba pung ana;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">domba ana = domba pung ana; domba kici = jenis domba (domba Rote/Sabu, dibanding domba Ostrali (domba besar); domba tenak = domba betina kecil yang balom berana; domba mai = ewe</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="33" />Ais dong hina ame sang Dia;<bt>So they have contempt on Him;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong putus sonde batúl Dia pung parkara.<bt>They decide His litigation in an unfair/not.correct manner.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Itu waktu, dong bunu bekin mati sang Dia,<bt>At that time, they murder kill Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">padahal Dia sonde ada pung sala apa-apa.<bt>whereas in fact He does not have any wrongs whatsoever.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Andia ko kotong sonde bisa omong sadiki ju so'al Dia pung turunan.&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why we can't say anything about His descendents.” [EXEG: Who can describe his generation? (NRSV). Note TB incorrectly takes ‘generation’ as ‘origins’, rather than the more common ‘descendents’ (NIV, NLT, CEV, TRT), or the minority “evil people living at Jesus' time’. RQ changed to statement.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Naa, kotong mau bilang apa lai?&gt;&gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Naa, kotong mau bilang apa lai?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:32-33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:7-8</note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01932b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none">Filipus ajar Tuhan pung Kata-kata sang orang bésar dari Afrika<bt>Filipus teaches the Lord's Word to a big person from Afrika</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Baca abis bagitu, itu orang bésar tanya sang Filipus bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Ba'i Yesaya ni ada omong kaná deng dia pung diri, ko, dia omong kaná deng orang laen?&gt;&gt;<bt>Finishing reading like that, that big person asked Filipus saying, “How is it? This Gf/Ff Yesaya was speaking about his own self or, he was speaking about someone else?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ais Filipus ajar kasi ini bapa, Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae. Dia mulai dari Yesaya pung tulisan tadi tu, ko kasi tunju jalan iko sang Yesus.<bt>Then Filipus taught this father, the Lord Yesus' Good Story. He began from that earlier writing of Yesaya, and he also used other spokesperson's writings.</bt><v n="36" />Waktu dong ada jalan, itu bapa dapa lia aer di kali. Ais dia potong Filipus pung omong ko usul bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa. Coba lia dolo, te ada aer di situ. Kalo sonde ada kabaratan, na, mari kotong turun ko bapa sarani sang beta di sini suda.&gt;&gt;<bt>When they were still travelling, that father (=man) saw water in a river. Then he interrupted Filipus to suggest saying, “Father. Look, cuz (elaboration) there is water there. If there are no obvious objections, na, let's get down so that father (=you) baptise me here (imperative).”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />[Ais Filipus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo pak memang parcaya batúl-batúl sang Tuhan Yesus, na neu, sonde ada halangan. Mari kotong turun ko beta sarani sang pak.&gt;&gt;<bt>[Then Filipus replied saying, “If Mr really believes truly on the Lord Yesus, yeah ok, there's no obstacle/objection. Let's get down so that I baptise Mr.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="neu =baiklah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">neu =baiklah</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais dia mangaku bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta parcaya batúl-batúl bilang, Yesus tu, Orang yang Tuhan Allah su tunju memang dari dolu. Dia tu, Tuhan Allah pung Ana.&gt;&gt;]<bt>Then he confessed saying, “I truly believe that that Yesus, is the Person whom the Lord God had promised beforehand from long ago. That him, [He is] the Lord God's Child.”]</bt><note reference="8:37" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ayat 37 ni, sonde ada di barapa tulisan Yunani yang paling tua.<bt>This verse 37, is not in several of the oldest Yunani writings.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ais, itu bapa suru kasi barenti dia pung kareta. Ju dong turun ko maso pi dalam itu aer. Tarús Filipus sarani sang dia di situ.<bt>Then, that father ordered to stop his cart. And they got down to enter into that water. Then Filipus baptised him there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Bagitu dong dua kaluar dari aer, ju Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi angka bawa sang Filipus ko pi tampa laen. Itu orang bésar su sonde dapa lia sang dia lai. Jadi itu pak jalan tarús, deng dia pung hati sanáng mau mati.<bt>When they two were exiting that water, then the Lord's Holy Spirit picked up [and] brought Filipus to another place. That big person could no longer see him. So (consequently), he traveled on, but his liver was exceeding happy.</bt><v n="40" />Ma Filipus muncul di satu kampong, nama Asotus.<bt>Then Filipus appeared in a villaged, name Asotus.</bt><note reference="8:40" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Itu kampong pung nama dalam bahasa Yunani bilang, Asotus. Dolu-dolu, waktu orang Filistin pegang parenta di Isra'el, itu kampong pung nama Asdod.<bt>That village's name in Yunani language, says, Asotus. Long ago, when the Filistin people ruled in Isra'el, that village's name was Asdod.</bt></note>Dari situ dia jalan tarús ko kasi tau orang dong so'al Yesus pung Carita Bae. Dia jalan singga-singga di samua kampong, sampe di kota Kaisarea.<bt>From there he continued travelling to tell people about Yesus' Good Story. He travelled stopping temporarily in all the villages, until Kaisarea city. [NOTE: Indonesian TB uses the older OT Philistine name of Asdod (see Bruce). The Gk here is /Azotus/, as in all English translations. See ftn.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Resumption of Fil after talking about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Resumption of Fil after talking about Ethiopian, so JU doesn't fit to introduce v.40</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Saulus maso iko jadi Yesus pung orang<bt>Saulus enters follows to become Yesus' person</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oba = change; tobat = stop"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">oba = change; tobat = stop a pattern of behaviour (not nec imply pursuing positive in its place</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Utusan dong pung Carita 22:6-16, 26:12-18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, Saulus maen ancam tarús deng bekin sangsara sang orang dong yang iko sang Yesus. Dia ju cari jalan ko mau bunu bekin mati sang dong. Andia ko dia pi di kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos bésar,<bt>At that time, Saulus habitually threatened continually and caused tribulation to the people who followed Yesus. He also sought a way to murder kill them. That's why he went to the big boss of the Yahudi religion</bt><v n="2" />ko minta surat kuasa dong ko dia bawa pi kasi kapala ruma sambayang dong di kota Damsik sana. Dia minta ko kalo dia katumu orang yang iko sang Yesus pung Jalan Idop, mau laki-laki ko parampuan, dia tangkap ame deng ika ame sang dong, ko hela bawa kambali pi Yerusalem.<bt>to request authority letters so that he could bring [them] to the heads/leaders of the worship houses (*synagogues) in Damsik city over.there. He requested that if he met people who followed Yesus' Life Path, either male or female, he wanted to capture/arrest and tie them up, to drag bring them back to Yerusalem.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Tarima ame itu surat kuasa dong, ju dia deng dia pung tamán dong pi Damsik. Waktu dia su deka di itu kota, takuju sa ju ada satu taráng bakilat dari langit senter pas sang Saulus.<bt>Receiving those authority letters, then he and his friends went ot Damsik. When they were close to that city, suddenly/unexpectedly there was a shiny brightness from the sky shining (lit. flashlighting/torching) exactly on Saulus.</bt><v n="4" />Tarús dia jato tabanting pi tana. Ju dia dengar satu suara omong deng dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Saulus! Akurang ko lu bekin sangsara sang Beta bagini?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then he fell flat down (face.down?) on the earth. And he heard a voice speak with him saying, “Saulus! Saulus! Why are you causing tribulation to Me like this, e?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Saulus tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Ko Bos yang omong ni, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Saulus asked saying, “The Boss who is speaking here, who.is.it?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu suara manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, Yesus, yang lu maen siksa satenga mati.<bt>That voice answered saying, “I here, am Yesus, who you keep torturing/persecuting horribly.</bt><v n="6" />Sakarang, bangun ko maso pi dalam kota suda. Nanti di situ baru Beta kasi tau sang lu bilang, lu musti bekin apa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Now, get up and enter into the city. Later there only-then will I tell you what you must do.”</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02022b.tif" rtfFormat="width:7.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Saulus jato di tana<bt>Saulus falls on the ground</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Dia pung tamán dong ada dengar itu bunyi suara, ma dong sonde dapa lia sapa-sapa ju. Ais dong ilang kira sampe dong sonde bisa omong apa-apa.<bt>And his friends heard that voice, but they did not see anyone either. Then they lost their thinking (=were frozen with fright) to. the.point.that they could not speak anything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tino = ser = aim at;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tino = ser = aim at; ilang kira = frozen with fright</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Tarús Saulus bangun badiri. Dia coba buka mata, ma dia su sonde bisa dapa lia apa-apa lai. Ju dong pegang dia pung tangan ko hela bawa sang dia maso pi kota Damsik.<bt>Then2 Saulus got up stood up. He tried to open his eyes, but he could no longer see anything. And they held his hand to pull bring him into Damsik city.</bt><v n="9" />Tiga hari dia sonde bisa dapa lia apa-apa. Deng dia sonde makan-minum satu apa ju.<bt>Three days he could not see anything. And he did not eat drink one thing either.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Di situ ada Tuhan Yesus pung orang satu, nama Ananias. Tuhan datang kasi tunju rupa sang dia sama ke mimpi, abis pange sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Ananias!&gt;&gt;<bt>There there was a person of the Lord Yesus, named Ananias. The Lord came showing his face to him like a dream, and then called him saying, “Ananias!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ananias manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ia, Tuhan!&gt;&gt;<bt>Ananias replied saying, “Yes, Lord!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Tuhan kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari dolo. Lu pi cari Beta pung orang satu. Pi di satu jalan, dia pung nama Jalan Lurus, di satu orang pung ruma. Itu orang, nama Yudas. Di situ, lu cari satu orang kota Tarsus, nama Saulus. Sakarang, itu orang ada sambayang.<bt>The Lord told [him] saying, “Come on. You go look for one of My people. Go to the street name Straight Street, to the house of a (certain) person. That person is named Yudas. There, you look for a person from the city of Tarsus named Saulus. Now that person is praying.</bt><v n="12" />Beta ju ada kasi lia sang dia bilang, nanti ada satu laki-laki datang pi sang dia. Andia lu, Ananias. Jadi lu pi ko taro tangan di dia, ko biar dia bisa dapa lia kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>I have also shown him saying, later there will be a male coming to him. That is you, Ananias. So (consequently) you go to lay hands on his head so that he can see again.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ma Ananias manyao bale bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini, Tuhan! Botong su dengar orang bacarita kiri-kanan so'al itu orang, tagal dia su bekin sangsara mau mati sang Tuhan pung orang dong di Yerusalem. Sampe dong su tar bisa-bisa lai!<bt>But Ananias replied in return saying, “It's.like this, Lord! We-exc have heard people telling right left about that person there, because he had cuz (elaboration) extreme tribulation to the Lord's people in Yerusalem. To the point that they are hopeless/helpless!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="su tar bisa-bisa lai = hopeless,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">su tar bisa-bisa lai = hopeless, helpless; sonde bisa angka muka lai = malu, ; sonde bisa angka kapala lai = powerless; sonde karuang lai = dgn gelisah, balisa</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Sakarang botong dengar lai bilang, itu kapala agama dong pung bos-bos ada kasi sang dia kuasa ko datang tangkap sampe abis orang dong yang su maso iko Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop.&gt;&gt;<bt>Now we hear again that *chief priests have given him authority to come capture until the people who have entered followed that Life Path of the Lord Yesus are all gone.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma Tuhan omong lai deng Ananias bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar bagitu ju, sakarang lu pi sa! Te Beta su pili ame sang dia ko pi buka jalan, ko biar dia bawa Beta pung Kabar Bae kasi suku-bangsa laen dong, raja-raja dong, deng kasi orang Isra'el dong ju.<bt>But the Lord spoke again with Ananias saying, “Even if it's like that too, you just go now! Cuz (elaboration) I have chosen him to open the path, so that he brings My Good News to the other ethnic groups, rajas, and also to the Israel people.</bt><v n="16" />Deng nanti Beta kasi tunju sang dia, ko biar dia tau sangsara macam apa yang ada tunggu sang dia, tagal dia iko sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>And later I will show him, so that he knows what.kind of tribulation is waiting for him, because he follows Me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tepa = hadang, ambush, potong jalan,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tepa = hadang, ambush, potong jalan, intercept</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Dengar Tuhan omong bagitu, ju Ananias jalan pi itu ruma, tarús dia maso di situ. Ju dia taro tangan pi sang Saulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu Saul. Tuhan Yesus yang bu lia di tenga jalan waktu bu datang di sini, Dia yang suru sang beta ko datang katumu deng bu. Dia suru beta sambayang deng taro tangan sang bu, ko biar bu bisa dapa lia lai. Deng Dia mau ko bu tarima Dia pung Roh yang Barisi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing the Lord speak like that, then Ananias went to that house, then he entered there. And he laid hands on Saulus' head saying, “Elder.Brother Saul. The Lord God whom elder.brother (=you) saw in the middle of the road when elder.brother (=you) was coming here, He is the one who order me to pray and put hands on elder.brother (=you), so that elder.brother (=you) can see again. And He wants so that elder.brother (=you) receives His *Holy Spirit.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Waktu dia omong abis ju, Saulus rasa satu barang macam ke ikan pung sisik takupas buang dari dia pung mata, ju dia dapa lia kambali. Ais dia bangun, ju dong sarani sang dia.<bt>When he finished speaking, Saulus felt something like fish scales peeled thown.off from his eyes, and he could see again. Then he got.up, and they baptised him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="macam ke ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">macam ke =</Message></Annotation><v n="19a" />Ais itu ju, dia makan-minum. Tarús dia pung badan kuat kambali.<bt>After that, then he ate-drank. Next his body became strong again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ke'ok = kalah, menyerah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ke'ok = kalah, menyerah</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Saulus kasi tau Carita Bae di kota Damsik<bt>Saulus tells the Good Story in Damsik city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19b" />Saulus masi tenga barapa hari lai deng Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong di kota Damsik.<bt>Saulus still stayed several more days with the Lord Yesus' people in Damsik city.</bt><v n="20" />Deng dia pi maso langsung di orang Yahudi dong pung ruma sambayang, ais dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dengar bae-bae! Memang Yesus, batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung Ana.&gt;&gt;<bt>And he entered straight away into the Yahudi people's worship house, then he told them saying, “You-pl listen carefully! Actually that Yesus, truly-truly is the Lord God's Child.”</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02153b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none">Saulus omong di orang Yahudi pung ruma sambayang<bt>Saulus talks in the Yahudi people's worship house</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Samua orang dong heran deng bingung dengar Saulus omong bagitu. Ju dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ko dia ni yang su bekin ancor Yesus pung orang dong di Yerusalem, aa? Ais dia datang di sini ko mau tangkap bawa sang dong pi kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos! Su karmana ni?&gt;&gt;<bt>All the people were amazed and confused hearing Saulus talk like that. And they asked each other saying, “He here is the one who has destroyed Yesus' people in Yerusalem, right? [+confidence] Then he came here to capture take them to the *chief priests! So how.is.it like this?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma Saulus suka kasi tunju bukti bilang, Yesus tu, andia Kristus yang Tuhan Allah su janji dari dolu-dolu ko mau kirim datang. Saulus ajar bagitu rupa, sampe orang Yahudi dong sonde ontong sang dia. Deng bagitu, Saulus pung pangaru tamba lama, tamba bésar.<bt>But Saulus like to show evidence that Yesus was the Kristus whom the Lord God had promised from long before to send. Saulus taught like that, to.the.point. that the Yahudi people could not win (=come out on top in an argument) over him. And with that, Saulus' influence grew long, grew big. [EXEG: Gk ‘Christ’ restored from OV ‘Person’.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Sonde lama lai, ju orang Yahudi dong basakongkol ko mau bunu bekin mati sang Saulus.<bt>Not long after, then the Yahudi people made an agreement together to murder kill Saulus.</bt><v n="24" />Ma Saulus dapa ciom ame dong pung akal busuk tu. Orang dong su batepa siang-malam di kota pung pintu dong, ko mau bunu sang dia.<bt>But Saulus got to know that rotten scheme of theirs. People were already waiting in ambush day-night at the city's entrance gate, to murder him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batepa = wait to catch, ambush"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">batepa = wait to catch, ambush</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Ma satu malam ju, Saulus pung tamán barapa orang dong ame sang dia, ko dong kasi turun sang dia dalam satu karanjang, lewat kota pung tembok. Deng bagitu, dia lari kasi tenga kota Damsik.<bt>But then one night, several of Saulus' friends took him, and they caused him to descend in a basket, passing the city's (brick)wall. And like that, he ran leaving behind Damsik city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ulur = sorong kasi turun"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ulur = sorong kasi turun</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:23-25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Korintus 11:32-33</note></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00333c.tif" rtfFormat="width:8.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Dong kasi turun sang Paulus pake karanjang<bt>They cuz (elaboration) Paulus to descend using a basket</bt></fig>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Saulus pi Yerusalem<bt>Saulus goes to Yerusalem</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ais ju Saulus pi Yerusalem. Sampe di sana, dia coba pi bagabung deng Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong. Ma dong samua taku sang dia, tagal dong kira kata, dia cuma sangaja bekin diri sama ke orang parcaya yang iko sang Tuhan Yesus. Ma nanti baru dia tangkap bale sang dong.<bt>Then Saulus went to Yerusalem. Arriving there, he tried to go gather.together with the Lord Yesus' people. But they were all afraid of him, because they thought he was only pretending to make himself like a believing person who follows the Lord Yesus. But later only then he would shift/change to capture them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sangaja = pretend"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sangaja = pretend</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Ma ada satu orang, nama Barnabas. Dia yang kasi kanál sang Saulus deng Tuhan Yesus pung utusan dong di situ. Dia carita kasi sang dong so'al apa yang su jadi deng Saulus di itu jalan. Dia ju kasi tau bilang, Saulus su katumu deng Yesus. Deng Tuhan ju su omong langsung deng dia. Dia ju carita sang dong, itu Saulus pung barani kasi tau orang-orang di Damsik so'al Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop.<bt>But there was a person, named Barnabas. He [was the one] who introduced Saulus with the Lord's apostles there. He told them, about that which had happened to Saulus on that road. And he also told them that Saulus had met with Yesus. And the Lord also had spoken directly with him. And he also told them, that braveness of Saulus telling people in Damsik about the Lord Yesus' Life Path.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi kanal construction grammatically interesting;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kasi kanal construction grammatically interesting;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Dengar bagitu, ju dong samua tarima sang Saulus. Ais dia tenga sama-sama deng dong di kota Yerusalem. Dia ju barani kasi tau Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae sang sapa-sapa sa, ko dia sonde taku na.<bt>Hearing that, then they all received Saulus. Then he stayed together with them in Yerusalem city. He also bravely told the Lord Yesus' Good News to just whoever, because he certainly wasn't afraid.</bt><v n="29" />Dia ju baso'al-jawab deng barapa orang Yahudi dong yang omong pake bahasa Yunani. Ma dong sonde mau tarima dia pung omong, andia ko dong cari jalan ko mau bunu bekin mati sang dia.<bt>He also question-answered (=debated) with several Yahudi people who spoke using the Yunani language. But they did not want to accept that talk of lhis, that's.why they sought a way to murder kill him.</bt><v n="30" />Ma waktu Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong dapa dengar bilang, orang su cari akal jahat bagitu, ju dong ame bawa Saulus pi kota Kaisarea di pinggir laut. Tarús dong kirim sang dia pulang pi kota Tarsus.<bt>But when the Lord Yesus' people heard that, people had devised an evil scheme like that, then they took Saulus to Kaisarea city at the edge of the sea. Then they sent him home to Tarsus city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais itu, Yesus pung orang dong di propinsi Yudea, di propinsi Galilea, deng propinsi Samaria, idop deng aman. Dong batamba banya. Dong ada iko Tuhan pung mau. Ju Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi kasi kuat dong pung hati.<bt>After that, Yesus' people in the province of Yudea, the province of Galilea, and the province of Samaria, lived with safety. They increased alot, because they followed the Lord's will. And the Lord's Holy Spirit strengthened/encouraged their livers.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus bekin bae satu laki-laki di Lida<bt>Petrus heal a male at Lida</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Itu waktu, Petrus suka jalan kuliling pi mana-mana ko lia Tuhan pung orang dong. Satu hari dia pi lia sang dong yang ada tenga di kampong Lida.<bt>At that time, Petrus liked to travel all around the place to check.up.on the Lord's people. One day he went to see them who stayed at Lida village</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lia 1) see, 2) supervise, check"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lia 1) see, 2) supervise, check up on, jaga, 3) layani</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Di sana dia katumu deng satu laki-laki, nama Eneas. Itu orang pung kaki lumpu, deng su sonde bangun-bangun dari dia pung tampa tidor su dalapan taon.<bt>There he met a male, named Eneas. The person's foot was paralysed, and he had not gotten up from his sleeping place for eight years.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="degu-degu = sleeping platform, simple"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">degu-degu = sleeping platform, simple</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Petrus bilang sang dia, &lt;&lt;Eneas! Sakarang ni, Yesus Kristus bekin bae sang lu. Jadi bangun suda! Manyimpan lu pung tampa tidor!&gt;&gt;<bt>Petrus said to him, “Eneas! Right now, Yesus Kristus heals you. So (consequently) get up! Put.away your sleeping place!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dengar bagitu, ju itu orang bangun memang.<bt>Hearing that, then that perosn got.up right away.</bt><v n="35" />Samua orang di kampong Lida deng kampong Saron dapa lia Eneas su bae bagitu, ju dong samua parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus.<bt>All the people in Lida village and Saron village could see that Eneas was healed like that, and they all believed in the Lord Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus kasi idop kambali sang mama Tabita yang su mati<bt>Petrus causes a mama to live again from her death</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Itu waktu, ada satu mama nama Tabita yang tenga di pinggir laut di kota Yope. (Itu mama pung nama dalam bahasa Yunani ju bilang, &lt;Dorkas&gt;, yang dia pung arti bilang, &lt;rusa&gt;).<bt>At that time, there was a mama named Tabita who stayed on the side of the sea at Yope city. (That female's name in Yunani language is also said ‘Dorkas’, and it's meaning is ‘deer’).</bt><note reference="9:36" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ini mama pung nama dua, ma dong pung arti sama. Deng bahasa Aram, <span class="Italic">Tabita</span> pung arti bilang, &lt;rusa&gt;. Deng bahasa Yunani, <span class="Italic">Dorkas</span> pung arti ju bilang, &lt;rusa&gt;.<bt>This mama has two names, but their meaning is the same. With Aram language, <span class="Italic">Tabita</span> meaning is ‘deer’. And Yunani language, <span class="Italic">Dorkas'</span> meaning is also ‘deer’.</bt></note>Dia parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus. Deng dia salalu bekin hal-hal yang bae kasi orang dong, deng suka tolong orang kasian dong.<bt>She believed in the Lord Yesus. And she always did good things for people, and like to help the poor people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lari muku = lari paksa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lari muku = lari paksa</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Itu waktu, mama Tabita jato saki, ju dia mati. Ais dong kasi mandi sang dia, ju dong bungkus dia pung mayat, tarús dong kasi baring sang dia di dia pung kamar atas.<bt>At that time, mama Tabita feel sick, and she died. The they bathed her, and wrapped her corpse, then they put her laying down in her upstairs room.</bt><v n="38" />Ais itu waktu, dong dapa dengar bilang, Petrus su ada di Lida, satu kota yang kira-kira jalan kaki satenga hari dari Yope. Tarús dong kirim dua orang ko pi pange sang Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Botong minta ko bapa datang capát-capát di Yope dolo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then at that time, they heard that Petrus was in Lida, a city that is approximately a half day's walk from Yope. Then2 they sent two people to go call Petrus saying, “Father! We-exc request that father (=you) come quickly to Yope (mild imperative).”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Dengar bagitu, ju Petrus bangun ko pi iko memang sang dong. Sampe di sana, ju dia langsung maso pi mama Tabita pung kamar. Itu kamar su ponu deng mama janda dong yang ada datang manangis makarereu di situ. Dong kasi tunju sang Petrus, dong pung baju deng pakean laen yang Dorkas ada jaet kasi sang dong waktu dia masi idop.<bt>Hearing that, then Petrus got up to go follow them right away. Arriving there, then he straight away enter into mama Tabita's room. That room was full with mama widows who were crying in loud wails there. They showed Petrus their shirts and other clothes which Dorkas had sewn for them while she still lived.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jaet = jahit; bangun lantas ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">jaet = jahit; bangun lantas = bangun memang (langsung, segera); makareu ~ makarereu ~ makarareu (Rote: makarereu)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01940b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Petrus kasi idop orang mati<bt>Petrus called to cuz (elaboration) a dead person to live</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Petrus suru sang dong samua ko kaluar dari itu kamar. Ju dia tikam lutut ko sambayang. Ais itu, dia bale mangada itu mayat, ju dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tabita! Bangun suda!&gt;&gt; Takuju sa, itu mama buka dia pung mata. Waktu dia lia sang Petrus, ju dia bangun dudu.<bt>Petrus ordered them all to go out of that room. And he knelt to pray. After that, he turned to face that corpse, and he spoke saying, “Tabita! Get up!” Suddenly, that mama opened her eyes. As soon as she saw Petrus, then she sat up.</bt><v n="41" />Ais Petrus pegang dia pung tangan ko tolong kasi badiri sang dia. Ju Petrus pange mama-mama janda deng orang laen dong, ko sarakan itu mama yang su idop kambali tu, kasi sang dong.<bt>Then Petrus held her hand to help her stand up. And Petrus called the mama widows and the other people, to give that mama who was already living again, to them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Itu kabar tasiar pi mana-mana di anteru kota Yope, sampe banya orang yang jadi parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus.<bt>That news spread all over the place in the entire city of Yope, to the point that many people who came to believe in the Lord Yesus.</bt><v n="43" />Petrus tenga di situ barapa hari lai di satu orang pung ruma. Itu orang, nama Simon. Dia pung karjá, tukang bekin barisi kulit binatang.<bt>Petrus stayed there several more days at the house of a worker who made clean animal skins. That person, named Simon.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukang samak kulit = [BI] yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tukang samak kulit = [BI] yang kerja kulit, tanner (boil the leather), default understanding = kulit sapi, kerbau; tukang bekin barisi kulit binatang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Komandán tantara Roma satu, nama Kornelis, pange sang Petrus<bt>Petrus and the Roma army commander, named Kornelis</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, ada satu tantara Roma, nama Kornelis. Dia jadi komandán dari tantara saratus orang. Dong datang dari jao, dari Italia. Deng dia ada tenga di kota Kaisarea.<bt>At that time, there was a Roma soldier, named Kornelis. He had become the commander of 100 army people. They came from far, from Italia. And he stayed in Kaisarea city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kornelis = nama kici = Ne'i,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Kornelis = nama kici = Ne'i, Nelis; lf Female = Kornelia = nama kici = Kor; serdadu = (kuno) &gt; tantara</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dia pung hati rindu sang Tuhan Allah, deng dia pung isi ruma samua ju bagitu. Ma banya orang Roma laen dong sonde bagitu. Dia banya tolong orang miskin dong, deng dia suka sambayang sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>His liver longed for the Lord God, and his household was also like that. He helped poor people alot, and he like to pray to the Lord God.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01943b.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Komandán Kornelis sambayang sang Tuhan Allah<bt>Commander Kornelis praying to the Lord God</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Satu hari, kira-kira jam tiga sore, sama ke dia ada mimpi, dia dapa lia deng taráng-taráng Tuhan Allah pung ana bua satu dari sorga datang ko pange sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Kornelis!&gt;&gt;<bt>One day, approximately three o'clock in the afternoon, it was like he was dreaming, he could clearly see one of the Lord God's *angel's come to call him saying, “Kornelis!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Kornelis lia itu ana bua dari sorga, ju dia taku mau mati. Ais dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada apa, Bos?&gt;&gt;<bt>Kornelis saw that angel and he was very afraid. So he asked saying, “What is it, Mr?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu ana bua manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan su dengar lu pung sambayang dong, deng Dia inga lu pung hati bae deng samua orang. Ais Tuhan ju ada lia sang lu.<bt>That angel replied saying, “The Lord has heard your-sg your prayers, and He remembers your good liver toward all people. So the Lord is also looking at/after you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati bae = kemurahan hati, generosity;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hati bae = kemurahan hati, generosity;</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Jadi sakarang, suru orang pi kota Yope, ko pange bawa sang satu orang, nama Simon Petrus.<bt>So (consequently) now, order people/person to go to Yope city, to call bring a person, named Simon Petrus.</bt><v n="6" />Dia ada manumpang di satu ruma di pinggir laut, deng satu orang tukang bekin barisi kulit binatang. Dia pung nama ju Simon.&gt;&gt;<bt>He is staying.temporarily at the side of the sea, with a person who habitually makes clean animal skins. His name is also Simon.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manumpang = tenga tahan deng orang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">manumpang = tenga tahan deng orang, sementara</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Waktu itu ana bua dari sorga kasi tenga sang Kornelis, ju dia pange dia pung orang karjá dua orang, deng dia pung tantara satu yang dia pung hati ju rindu sang Tuhan.<bt>As soon as that angel left Kornelis, then he called two of his working people, and one of his army [persons] whose liver also longed after God.</bt><v n="8" />Kornelis carita abis itu hal samua, tarús dia suru sang dong ko pi kota Yope.<bt>Kornelis told all that matter, then he ordered them to go to Yope city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus datang lia sang Kornelis<bt>Petrus comes to see Kornelis</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais dia pung beso, kira-kira tenga hari, Kornelis pung utusan dong su deka di Yope. Itu waktu, Petrus nae ko sambayang di Simon pung ruma pung emper atas.<bt>Then the next day, approximately mid day, they were near Yope. At that time, Petrus went.up to pray up on Simon's house's flat porch.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="emper = porch, teras, baranda, veranda"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">emper = porch, teras, baranda, veranda ; plat = flat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01944b.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.0cm;textWrapping:none;horizontalPosition:center">Petrus sambayang di atas ruma<bt>Petrus praying on top of the house</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dia ada sambayang, ma dia ju su rasa lapar. Dia ada tunggu orang dong ator meja. Waktu dia ada sambayang bagitu, ju Tuhan Allah kasi tunju sang dia tingka ke dia ada mimpi.<bt>He was praying, but he also was already hungry. He was waiting for people to arrange the table. While he was praying like that, then the Lord God appeared to him like he was dreaming.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taro meja = prepare the food"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">taro meja = prepare the food (UNS's prefer ator meja); angka meja = clean off the table after a meal; tingka ke ~ sama ke</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Dia lia sama ke langit tabuka, ais satu isprei bésar muncul, yang ada tagantong di dia pung jiku ampa-ampa. Ju itu isprei mulai turun datang.<bt>He saw like/as if the sky was opened, then a big bedspread/sheet appeared, which was hung-up at its four corners. And that sheet began to come down.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="saprei ~ isprei = sheet, large"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">saprei ~ isprei = sheet, large cloth (implicit, white); jiku = corners; ujung = corners, tips; tasorong = (geser) turun; pikir ulang-aling, pikir bola-bale, pikir pi datang</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Dalam itu isprei, dia dapa lia binatang macam-macam, andia binatang yang kaki ampa, binatang marayap, deng burung macam-macam.<bt>Inside that sheet, he could see all sorts of animals, that is animals with four legs, crawling animals, and all.kinds.of birds.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01945b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top">Petrus lia binatang macam-macam dalam isprei<bt>Petrus seeing all.kinds.of animals inside the sheet</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ju dia dengar satu suara suru sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Pe'u! Bangun suda! Horo ame ini binatang dong ko lu makan suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>And he heard a voice ordering him saying, “Pe'u (nickname for Peter)! Get up! Cut the neck of these animals and then eat them(imp)!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde bisa, Bos! Jang bagitu! Te beta balóm parná makan binatang macam bagitu! Botong orang Yahudi pamali deng itu binatang dong samua!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus replied saying, “Impossible, Boss! Not like that! Cuz (elaboration) I have not yet ever eaten animals like that! All those animals there, are taboo/forbidden to us Yahudi people!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kata senyawa (BI) = @@; kotor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kata senyawa (BI) = @@; kotor = (ritually) unclean, najis, jijik; kotor/noju ; pamali = taboo avoid (argument structure like avoid, not like taboo)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma itu suara balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo Tuhan Allah su omong bilang, satu barang barisi, na, lu jang bilang dia kotor lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>But that voice replied saying, “If the Lord God has already spoken saying a thing is holy/clean, na, you don't say that it is dirty anymore!”</bt><v n="16" />Itu isprei muncul bagitu sampe tiga kali, ju dia ta'angka kambali pi langit.<bt>That sheet appeared like that up to three times, then it was lifted.up returning to the sky.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais Petrus masi bapikir pi-datang ko cari tau itu mimpi pung arti apa. Pas itu waktu, Kornelis pung ana bua dong sampe di Simon pung ruma. Dong su badiri di muka pintu.<bt>Then Petrus was still thinking about it, to find out what that dream's meaning was. Exactly at that time, Kornelis' underlings arrived at Simon's house. They were already standing at the front door.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pikir diam-diam ; pikir dalam hati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pikir diam-diam ; pikir dalam hati ;</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ju dong pange bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong ada cari satu tamu yang ada manumpang di ini ruma. Dia pung nama Simon Petrus. Mangkali papa tau, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>And they called saying, “We-exc are looking for a guest who is staying temporarily at this house. His name Simon Petrus. Probably papa knows [him], right?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Itu waktu, Petrus masi pikir-pikir cari tau itu mimpi pung arti, te Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;We, Pe'u. Ada orang<bt>At that time, Petrus was still thinking to know the meaning of that dream, cuz (elaboration) the Lord's Holy Spirit told him saying, “We, Pe'u. There are person/people</bt><note reference="10:19" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada barapa tulisan Yunani yang bilang &lt;tiga orang&gt; yang datang. Deng ada satu tulisan yang bilang cuma &lt;dua orang&gt; sa. Ma ada banya tulisan yang sonde bilang barapa orang yang datang cari sang Petrus.<bt>There are several Yunani writings which say 'three people' who came. And there is one writing that says only just 'two people'. But there are many writings that don't say how many people who came looking.for Petrus.</bt></note>di bawa, datang cari sang lu.<bt>down.below, come to find you.</bt><v n="20" />Lu turun ko pi iko sang dong suda. Sonde usa pikiran. Biar dong tu, bukan orang Yahudi, ma lu jang noju sang dong deng anggap dong orang kamomos, iko orang Yahudi pung adat. Te Beta ni, yang suru ko dong datang ame sang lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>You go.down to follow them (imp.) It's not necessary to worry. Even though they there, are not Yahudi people, but you do not become grossed.out at them and consider them as dirty/filthy/defiled people in accord with Yahudi people's custom. Cuz (elaboration) I here, am the one who ordered them to come get you.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="noju = some mesolectal speakers don't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">noju = some mesolectal speakers don't know</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ais Petrus turun ko pi katumu deng itu orang dong, ju dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, yang bosong cari. Ma bosong ada parlú apa sang beta?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus went down to go meet those people, and he said, “I here, am the one who you are looking.for. But what do you need with me?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada tantara Roma pung komandán satu yang suru botong datang di sini. Dia tu, komandán dari saratus tantara. Dia pung hati lurus deng rindu sang Tuhan Allah. Banya orang Yahudi dong su tau ini orang pung bae. Baru kamaren sa, Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga datang ko suru botong pung bos minta bapa datang di dia pung ruma, ko dia mau dengar dari bapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they answered saying, “There is a Roma army commander who ordered us to come here. That him, [he is] a commander of 100 soldiers. And his liver is straight, and longs for the Lord God. Many Yahudi peole already know this person's goodness. Only just yesterday, the Lord's angel came to order our boss to request father (=you) to come to his house, so that he can hear from father (=you).”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Dengar bagitu, ju Petrus minta sang dong ko manumpang tidor itu malam di situ. Dia pung beso ju, dong bangun, ais Petrus jalan sama-sama deng dong. Ada barapa dari Tuhan pung orang yang di Yope dong, pi batamán deng dong.<bt>Hearing that, then Petrus requested them to stay sleeping that night there. Then the next day, they got.up, and Petrus travelled together with them. There were several of the Lord's people from Yope, who accompanied them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pi iko = implies following from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pi iko = implies following from behind</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Itu malam dong tidor di jalan, baru dia pung beso dong sampe di kota Kaisarea. Sampe di Kornelis pung ruma, ju dia ada tunggu sang dong. Dia su kumpul ame dia pung kelu deng dia pung tamán satu kaki dong di situ.<bt>That night they slept on the road, then the next day they arrived at Kaisarea city. Arriving at Kornelis' house, then he was waiting for them. He had gathered his family and his friends of one foot (=like.minded friends) there.</bt><v n="25" />Waktu Petrus mau maso di itu ruma, Kornelis lari pi muka, ais dia jato tikam lutut di Petrus pung kaki ko sémba sang dia.<bt>As soon as Petrus was to enter that house, Kornelis run to the front, then he fell kneeling at Petrus' feet to worship him.</bt><v n="26" />Ma Petrus angka kasi bangun sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu! Badiri suda. Jang sémba sang beta. Te beta ni, manusia biasa sama ke bu ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus lifted him up causing him to stand saying, “Elder.brother! Get.up! Don't worship me. Cuz (elaboration) this I, am only an ordinary human just like elder.brother (=you).”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Dengar bagitu, ju Kornelis bangun badiri. Ais dong dua mulai ba'omong, ko jalan maso pi dalam ruma. Tarús Petrus dapa lia orang banya su bakumpul di situ, tunggu sang dia.<bt>Hearing that, then Kornelis stood up. Then they two begain to talk, to walk into the house. Then Petrus could see that many people had gathered there, waiting for him.</bt><v n="28" />Ais dia lia kuliling sang dong, ju dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong samua. Bosong tau memang botong orang Yahudi pung adat. Iko botong pung adat tu, botong sonde bole bacampor deng orang laen dong. Apalai maso pi dalam dong pung ruma. Ma Tuhan Allah su kasi tunju sang beta bilang, kalo Dia sandiri su omong bilang, satu barang barisi, na, beta jang bilang itu barang kotor. Jadi sakarang beta sonde bisa noju sang orang laen lai. Te beta musti anggap sang dong beta pung kelu sandiri.<bt>Then he looked around at them, and he spoke saying, “Siblings! You-pl know already our-exc Yahudi people's custom. Following that custom of ours, we cannot mix with other people. Especially not enter into their house. But the Lord God has shown me saying, if He himself has spoken saying a thing is clean, na, I can't say that thing is dirty. So (consequently) now I cannot be grossed.out/appalled at other people anymore. Cuz (elaboration) I must consider them my own family. [EXEG: Gk. “I should not call any person profane or unclean.” Problem: talking about “clean/unclean people” in RLs in this region, forces the literal/ physical reading, rather than ritually unclean. So we go to the broader principle “anything” resonating with Mrk 7, and then specify people in the recap/elaboration. Unlike Indonesian, KM ‘barang’ can refer to both concrete and abstract ‘things’.]</bt><v n="29" />Andia ko waktu bosong datang pange sang beta, beta barangkat memang. Beta sonde ba'iu, tagal Tuhan su kasi tau bagitu sang beta. Ma coba bosong kasi tau dolo! Bosong ada parlú apa deng beta di sini?&gt;&gt;<bt>That's why when you came calling me, I left right away. I did not stall, because the Lord has told like that to me. But you go.ahead and reveal now! What do you need with me here, huh?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ba'iu = stall, alasan macam-macam, balangsik"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ba'iu = stall, alasan macam-macam, balangsik (given two choices, they choose a third); ba'eok = talalu lama-lama, take unreasonable time to do s.t. (e.g. old women taking forever to get ready to go somewhere --ex from UNS)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ais Kornelis carita samua-samua bilang, &lt;&lt;Ampa hari lalu, waktu su mulai sore, beta ada sambayang di beta pung ruma ni. Takuju sa, ada satu laki-laki badiri di beta pung muka. Dia pung pakean tu, mangkilat.<bt>Then Kornelis told everything saying, “Four days ago, when it was beginning to be late afternoon, I was praying in this house of mine. Suddenly, there was a male standing in front of me. Those clothes of his, were shiny.</bt><v n="31" />Ju dia pange sang beta bilang, &lt;Kornelis! Tuhan su dengar lu pung sambayang dong, deng Dia inga lu pung hati bae kasi samua orang.<bt>And he called me saying, 'Kornelis! The Lord has heard your prayers, and He remembers your good liver (=goodness/kindness/grace/generosity) to all people.</bt><v n="32" />Jadi sakarang suru orang pi kota Yope ko pange bawa sang satu orang, nama Simon Petrus. Dia ada manumpang di satu ruma di pinggir laut, di satu orang tukang bekin barisi kulit binatang. Dia pung nama ju Simon.&gt;<bt>So (consequently) now order people to go to Yope city to call bring a person, named Simon Petrus. He is staying.temporarily at a house on the side of the sea, with a person who habitually cleans animal skins. His name also is Simon.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi sakarang suru orang pi di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Jadi sakarang suru orang pi di Yope ko pange satu orang, dia pung nama Simon Petrus. Sakarang dia ada manumpang di satu orang tukang samak kulis, dia pung nama Simon. Itu ruma ada di pinggir laut.</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Andia ko, beta suru orang memang ko pi pange ame sang pak. Botong ada basukur mau mati, tagal pak datang memang. Jadi sakarang, botong bakumpul di sini ko mau dengar samua yang Tuhan Allah suru sang pak ko kasi tau sang botong!&gt;&gt;<bt>That's why, I ordered people right away to go call bring you sir. We-exc are extremely thankful, because sir (=you) has come right away. So (consequently) now, we gather here to hear all that the Lord God ordered Mr (=you) to tell us.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus omong so'al Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop kasi sang orang yang bukan Yahudi dong [\s2]<bt>Petrus tells about the Lord Yesus' Life Path to people who are not Yahudi [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ais Petrus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sakarang, baru beta tau bilang, Tuhan Allah tu, batúl-batúl lia samua orang sama rata. Dia sonde bapili muka kalo ini orang Yahudi, deng yang laen bukan orang Yahudi.<bt>Then Petrus spoke saying, “Now, only now I know that that Lord God, truly sees all people equally. He does not differentiate, whether/if these are Yahudi people, and these others are not Yahudi.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bapili muka = pandang bulu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bapili muka = pandang bulu</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 10:17</note><v n="35" />Kalo ada orang dari suku mana sa yang dia pung hati lurus, deng dia suka sambayang sang Tuhan, ais bekin iko Dia pung mau, itu orang tantu bekin sanáng Dia pung hati.<bt>If there is a person from whatever tribe whose heart is straight, and he likes to worship the Lord, and follows/obeys His will, that person surely makes His liver happy.</bt><v n="36" />Te bosong tau apa yang Tuhan su kasi tau sang botong bangsa Isra'el bilang, Dia su kirim itu Kristus, andia Yesus. Ais Yesus tu, mati ko bekin dame sang manusia deng Tuhan. Deng Dia yang hak parenta sang samua orang ju.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you know what the Lord has told us-exc Israel ethnic group, that He has sent that Person whom He promised from before, that is that Yesus. Then that Yesus, died to make peace with humans and God. And He is also the one with say-so/ordering/governing rights over everyone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin dame sang manusia deng Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bekin dame sang manusia deng Tuhan = syntax@@</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Bosong ju su dengar apa yang su jadi di anteru propinsi Yudea. Itu carita mulai dari Yohanis kasi tau orang bilang, dong musti barenti dari dong pung sala-sala dong. Deng dong ju musti dapa sarani, ko jadi tanda bilang, dong su babae deng Tuhan.<bt>You have also heard what happened in the entire province of Yudea. That story started from Yohanis telling people that they must stop from their wrongs. And they also must be baptised, to make a sign that they are in a good/right relationship with the Lord.</bt><v n="38" />Ais Tuhan Allah kasi Dia pung Roh yang Barisi sang Yesus, itu orang Nasaret. Tuhan ju kasi Dia pung kuasa sang Yesus. Ais Yesus pi maso-kaluar kampong-kampong, ko bekin hal bae kasi orang dong. Deng Dia tolong orang yang setan dong pung bos ada bekin susa sang dong. Dia bekin bagitu, tagal Tuhan Allah ada sama-sama deng Dia tarús.<bt>The the Lord gave His Holy Spirit to Yesus, that Nasaret person. The Lord also gave His power to Yesus. Then Yesus went entering exiting villages, to do good things for people. And help people whom *Satan (the evil spirit's big boss) had caused difficulty for them. He did like that, because the Lord was continually together with Him.</bt><v n="39" />Ko botong ni, yang lia deng mata biji sandiri, apa yang Dia su bekin di kota Yerusalem deng di orang Yahudi pung tana anteru.<bt>So we-exc here, are who have seen with our own eyes, that which He did in Yerusalem city and in the entire land of the Yahudi people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Biar bagitu ju, ma orang masi paku kasi tagantong sang dia di kayu palang sampe mati.<bt>Even though it's like that, nevertheless people still nailed hanging him on a cross until [he] died.</bt><v n="40" />Dia mati batúl-batúl, ma dia pung lusa ju, Tuhan Allah kasi idop kambali sang Dia. Ais Dia kasi tunju Dia pung diri, ko orang dapa tau bilang, Dia batúl-batúl su idop kambali.<bt>He really died, but on it's day-after-next, then the Lord God caused Him to live again. The He showed his self, so that people could know that He truly-truly was alive again.</bt><v n="41" />Ma sonde samua orang dapa lia sang Dia, cuma botong sa. Waktu Dia su idop kambali tu, botong biasa makan-minum sama-sama deng Dia. Tuhan Allah ju tunju sang botong ko jadi saksi yang pi kasi tau Yesus pung Carita Bae sang banya orang di mana-mana.<bt>But not all people got to see Him, only just us. At that time when He was alive again, we usually ate-drank together with Him. The Lord also appointed us to be *witnesses who go tell that Good Story of Yesus to many people all over the place. [EXEG: ‘witnesses’ added to more closely reflect the Gk.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Jadi Tuhan yang suru botong ko pi kasi tau taráng-taráng so'al itu Orang yang Dia su tunju memang dari dolu, andia Yesus. Deng Tuhan ju angka sang Yesus ko jadi Tukang Putus Parkara yang bilang, sapa yang nanti bisa idop tarús deng Tuhan Allah, deng sapa yang sonde. Yesus tu, yang putus parkara kasi orang yang su mati deng orang yang masi idop dong.<bt>So (consequently) the Lord who ordered us-exc to go tell openly/clearly about that Person who He had appointed from before, that is that Yesus. And the Lord also raised Yesus to become the *Judge (decider of litigations) who says, whom it is who will later live forever with the Lord God; and who will not. That Yesus, who decides litigations for who have died and people who are still living.</bt><v n="43" />Dari dolu-kala, Tuhan Allah pung jubir samua ju tunju sang ini Yesus bilang, samua orang yang parcaya sang Dia, nanti Tuhan Allah tarima sang dong, deng Tuhan nanti hapus buang dong pung sala-sala dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>From way before, all the Lord God's spokesperson also pointed.to this Yesus, saying everyone who believes in Him, later the Lord God will receive them, and the Lord will forget throw away their wrongs.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lupa buang = 1) forgot to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lupa buang = 1) forgot to throw away s.t. that is still there, 2) not remember</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang bukan Yahudi dong tarima Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi [\s2]<bt>People who are not Yahudi receive the Lord's Holy Spirit [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Waktu Petrus masi ba'omong bagitu ju, takuju sa Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi datang maso pi itu orang samua yang ada dengar sang dia.<bt>When Petrus was still talking like that, suddenly the Lord's Holy Spirit entered into all those people who were listening to him.</bt><v n="45" />Di situ ju ada Petrus pung tamán orang Yahudi dong yang datang sama-sama deng dia dari kota Yope pi Kornelis pung ruma di kota Kaisarea. Waktu dong lia itu orang banya tarima Tuhan pung Roh, dong taheran-heran, tagal dong baru lia Tuhan kasi Dia pung Roh sang orang bukan Yahudi.<bt>There there were also Petrus' Yahudi friends who came together with him from Yope city, to that house of Kornelis in Kaisarea city. When they saw that those many people received the Lord's Spirit, they were amazed, because that was the first time they had see the Lord give His Spirit to people who were not Yahudi.</bt><v n="46" />Dong dengar itu orang-orang di Kornelis pung ruma dong ba'omong pake bahasa macam-macam, deng dong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>They heard those people in Kornelis' house speaking using all kinds of languages, and they were praising the Lord God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais Petrus omong bilang,<bt>Then Petrus spoke saying,</bt><v n="47" />&lt;&lt;Bosong lia sandiri sa! Ini orang dong su tarima Tuhan pung Roh sama ke kotong ju. Jadi sakarang, mari ko kotong sarani sang dong suda. Sonde ada yang bisa larang lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>"Go ahead and look for yourselves! These people have received the Lord's Spirit just like we also have. So (consequently) now, lets go baptize them (imperative). There's nothing to forbid it anymore.”</bt><v n="48" />Ais Petrus suru ko dong sarani Kornelis deng orang-orang yang ada di situ dong, ko dong maso jadi Tuhan Yesus pung orang. Ais dong minta ko Petrus tenga deng dong barang barapa hari lai, baru dong lapás sang dia pulang pi Yerusalem.<bt>Then Petrus ordered that they baptise Kornelis and the people who were there, so that entered and became the Lord Yesus' people. Then they requested that Petrus stay with them a few more days, then they would allow them to go home to Yerusalem.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus bela diri tagal dia sarani orang yang bukan Yahudi<bt>Petrus defends himself because he baptized people who are not Yahudi</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Petrus balóm pulang, ma Yesus pung utusan deng orang laen dong yang parcaya di Yerusalem su dapa dengar bilang, orang yang bukan orang Yahudi su tarima ame Tuhan pung Carita Bae.<bt>Petrus had not yet returned.home, but the Yesus' apostles and other people who believed in Yerusalem got to hear that people who are not Yahudi people had accepted the Lord's Good Story.</bt><v n="2" />Jadi waktu Petrus kambali sampe di Yerusalem, ada barapa orang parcaya dari partei Yahudi<bt>So (consequently), when Petrus returned to Yerusalem, there were several people from the Yahudi party</bt><note reference="11:2" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kalo ada orang yang bukan Yahudi mau iko sang Yesus, orang dari partei agama Yahudi ni bilang dong tu, musti sunat iko orang Yahudi pung adat, deng dong ju musti iko samua atoran agama Yahudi yang laen dong.<bt>If a person who was not Yahudi wanted to follow Yesus, people from this religious party said that they there, had to be circumcized following the Yahudi people's custom, and they also must follow all the other regulations of the Yahudi religion.</bt></note>yang kasi sala sang dia,<bt>who accused him,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi sala ; lempar sala ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kasi sala ; lempar sala ; muat sala ; kritik</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Lu su bekin karmana tu? Lu tau kotong pung adat, ko sonde? Lu barani maso pi orang yang bukan Yahudi pung ruma! Makan-minum lai deng dong! Sonde bole bagitu, te dong tu, balóm parná iko kotong pung adat sunat! Kotong sonde pantas bacampor deng dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>saying, “Heh! What have you done there? Do you know our-inc custom, or not? You dare to enter into the houses of people who are not Yahudi! Even eat drink with them! Can't do like that, cuz (elaboration) those them, they have not yet ever followed our circumcision custom! It is not appropriate for us to mix with them!” [NOTE: quote margin moved to vs.3 as in Gk.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais Petrus carita ame samua-samua yang su jadi bilang,<bt>Then Petrus told all that had happened, saying</bt><v n="5" />&lt;&lt;Satu hari waktu beta di kota Yope, pas beta ada sambayang, ju Tuhan kasi tunju sang beta sama ke mimpi. Beta lia sama ke langit tabuka, ais satu isprei bésar muncul datang, yang ada tagantong di dia pung jiku ampa-ampa. Ju itu isprei mulai turun datang sang beta.<bt>"One day when I was at Yope city, just as I was praying, then the Lord showed/appeared to me like a dream. I saw like/as if the sky was opened, then a big sheet appeared, that was hung from its four corners. And that sheet began to come down to me.</bt><v n="6" />Waktu beta maloi pi dalam itu isprei, ju beta dapa lia binatang macam-macam, andia binatang yang kaki ampa, binatang marayap, deng burung macam-macam. Samua tu, kotong orang Yahudi pung binatang pamali.<bt>When I peeped into that sheet, then I could see all sorts of animals, that is animals who have four legs, crawling animals, and all.kinds.of birds. All that, we Yahudi people's taboo animals.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maloi = peep into"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">maloi = peep into</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ju beta dengar satu suara suru bilang, &lt;Pe'u! Bangun suda! Horo ame ini binatang dong, ko lu makan suda!&gt;<bt>And I heard a voice commanding saying, ‘Pe'u! Get up! Cut.the.neck of these animals, and.then you eat them(imp)!’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma beta manyao bilang, &lt;Sonde bisa, Bos! Jang bagitu! Te beta balóm parná makan binatang macam bagitu! Itu binatang dong samua tu, kotong orang Yahudi pamali!&gt;<bt>But I replied saying, ‘Impossible, Boss! Can't do like! Because I have not yet ever eaten animals like that! All those animals there, are certainly taboo for us-inc Yahudi people!’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma itu suara balas bilang, &lt;Kalo Tuhan Allah su omong bilang, satu barang barisi, na, lu jang bilang dia kotor lai!&gt;<bt>But that voice replied saying, ‘If the Lord God has spoken saying a thing is clean, na, you don't say its dirty anymore!’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Beta lia itu isprei muncul bagitu sampe tiga kali, ju dia ta'angka kambali pi langit.<bt>I saw that sheet appear like that until three times, and it was lifted up returning to the sky.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Pas itu waktu, ada tiga orang sampe di itu ruma. Dong datang dari Kaisarea ko cari sang beta.<bt>Exactly at that time, there were three people arriving at that house. They came from Kaisarea to look for me. [NOTE to daughter translations: unlike in 10:19, the Gk here clearly says “three men” in this verse.]</bt><v n="12" />Ais Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi kasi tau sang beta bilang, &lt;Lu turun ko pi iko sang ini orang dong suda. Sonde usa pikir-pikir. Biar dong tu, bukan orang Yahudi, ma lu jang noju sang dong, ko anggap sang dong kamomos.&gt; Waktu beta dengar abis bagitu, kotong pung sodara anam orang ni, dong ju iko sama-sama deng beta pi Kaisarea. Di situ botong samua maso pi tantara Roma pung komandán satu pung ruma.<bt>Then the Lord's Holy Spirit told me saying, ‘You go.down to go with these people(imp). It's not necessary to worry/keep mulling it over. Even though those [people], are not Yahudi people, but you don't become grossed.out at them.’ When I had heard that, these six siblings of ours, they also followed together with me to Kaisarea. There we all entered into a house of a Roma army commander.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rasa was-was = ragu-ragu, bimbang, garogi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">rasa was-was = ragu-ragu, bimbang, garogi (some think was-was is BI)</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Itu komandán bacarita bilang, barang barapa hari yang su lewat ni, dia dapa lia Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga badiri di dia pung ruma, ko bilang, &lt;Suru orang pi kota Yope ko pange satu orang, nama Simon Petrus.<bt>That commander told/narrated saying, that several days before that, he saw the Lord's angel standing in his house, and saying, ‘Tell people to go to Yope to call a person, named Simon Petrus.</bt><v n="14" />Nanti itu orang kasi tunju sang lu, deng lu pung isi ruma dong samua, Tuhan pung jalan karmana ko kasi salamat sang bosong, deng hapus buang bosong pung sala-sala dong.&gt;<bt>Later that person will tell you, and all your household, how the Lord's path is to give salvation to you-pl, and to erase throw away your wrongs.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Tagal itu, beta mulai kasi tunju Tuhan pung Jalan Idop sang dong. Takuju sa, Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi datang maso pi itu orang samua, sama ke yang kotong ju su tarima tempo hari.<bt>Because of that, I began showed/told the Lord's Life Path to them. Suddenly the Lord's Holy Spirit came and entered all of them, just like how we also had received earlier.</bt><v n="16" />Lia bilang dong ju tarima Tuhan pung Roh bagitu, ju beta inga Tuhan Yesus pung omong dolu bilang, &lt;Yohanis kasi sarani sang bosong pake aer sa, ma nanti Tuhan Allah mau bekin lebe hebat kasi bosong, andia Dia kasi Dia pung Roh yang Barisi sang bosong.&gt;<bt>Seeing that they also received the Lord's Spirit like that, then I remembered the Lord Yesus' talk from before saying, 'Yohanis baptised you using only water, but later the Lord God wants to do even greater for you, that is He will give His Holy Spirit to you.'</bt><note reference="11:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 1:5</note><v n="17" />Te Tuhan sandiri yang kasi Dia pung Roh sang itu orang laen dong, parsís ke Dia kasi sang kotong. Jadi bosong pung mau beta lawan sang Tuhan, ko karmana? Jadi beta mau omong apa lai?&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the Lord himself who gave His Spirit to those other people, just like He gave it to us. So (consequently), you want that, I oppose the Lord, or what? So (consequently), what else can I say?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Dengar Petrus bela diri bagitu, ju dong su sonde kasi sala sang dia lai. Ais dong samua puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Talalu hebat! Tuhan su buka jalan ko orang laen ju bisa kasi tenga dong pung idop yang sala, ko Tuhan hapus buang dong pung sala-sala dong, ais dong ju dapa idop tarús deng Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Petrus defend himself like that, then they no longer accused him. And they all praised the Lord God saying, “We! Incredibly amazing! The Lord has opened the path so that other people also can get forgiveness from their wrongs, so that they also can live continually with Him.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong tasiram pi mana-mana. Ada banya dari dong yang bakumpul di kota Antiokia<bt>The Lord Yesus' people are spread all over. There are many of them of gather in Antiokia city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Dolu, waktu dong su bunu bekin mati abis sang Stefanus, ju dong mulai bekin sangsara deng bekin susa Yesus pung orang dong. Andia ko dong lari tasiram pi mana-mana. Saparu lari pi propinsi Fenisia. Saparu ju lari pi pulo Siprus, deng saparu lai lari jao-jao sampe di kota Antiokia di propinsi Siria. Orang-orang yang lari dong ni, ju kasi tau Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae pi mana-mana. Ma dong cuma kasi tau sang dong pung orang Yahudi sandiri sa. Dong sonde kasi tau sang orang laen dong.<bt>When they had finished murdering killing Stefanus, then they began to cuz (elaboration) tribulation and make difficulty for Yesus' people. That's why they ran spreading all.over.the.place. Some ran to Finisia province. Some also ran to Siprus island, and some other ran far-far all the way to Antiokia city in Siria province. These people of Yesus who ran, they also told the Lord Yesus' Good Story all.over.the.place. But they only told [it] to their own Yahudi people. They did not tell it to other people. (other people=way to designate outsiders)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="saparu KM tidak sama dgn separuh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">saparu KM tidak sama dgn separuh BI</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 8:1-4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma ada ju Tuhan pung orang dong dari pulo Siprus deng dari kota Kirene. Dong saparu jalan tarús pi kota Antiokia di propinsi Siria. Dong ni yang kasi tau Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae kasi sang orang yang bukan Yahudi dong di situ.<bt>But there were the Lord's people who ran to Siprus island and to Kirene city. There were also those who went all.the.way to Antiokia city in Siria province. These are the ones who told the Lord Yesus' Good Story to people who are not Yahudi there.</bt><v n="21" />Tuhan kasi Dia pung kuasa sang dong, sampe orang bam-banya jadi parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus.<bt>The Lord gave His power to them, to the point that a great many people believed in the Lord Yesus.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01925b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Yesus pung orang dong lari pi mana-mana<bt>Yesus' people run all.over.the.place</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22-24" />Itu waktu, Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong di Yerusalem dapa dengar bilang, orang laen di Antiokia ju su parcaya sang Yesus. Ais dong kirim satu orang, nama Barnabas, ko pi lia sang dong di sana. Barnabas ni, orang yang hati bae, deng parcaya batúl-batúl sang Tuhan Allah. Tuhan pung Roh ju ada pimpin sang dia.<bt>At that time, the Lord Yesus' people in Yerusalem heard that other people(outsiders=non-Jewish) in Antiokia also had believed in Yesus. Then they sent a person, named Barnabas, to go look.after them there. This Barnabas, a person with a good liver, and truly believed in the Lord God. The Lord's Spirit also was guiding him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jemaat ; pimpin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">jemaat ; pimpin</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu dia datang sampe di sana, dia dapa lia bilang, memang batúl Tuhan Allah su ada karjá di teng-tenga itu orang laen dong pung idop. Ju dia pung hati sanáng. Ais dia kasi samangat sang dong, ko biar dong iko tarús Tuhan pung Jalan Idop deng batúl-batúl. Deng bagitu, Tuhan pung orang dong tamba lama, tamba banya.<bt>When he came arriving there, he saw that, it was really true that the Lord God had worked in the midst of the other people's lives. And his liver was happy. Thus he gave enthusiasm to them, so that they would keep following the Lord's Life Path in a correct manner. With that, the Lord's people increased long, increased many.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi samangat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kasi samangat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais itu, ju Barnabas pi kota Tarsus ko mau cari sang Saulus.<bt>After that, then Barnabas went to Tarsus to look for Saulus.</bt><v n="26" />Waktu katumu deng dia, dia kokoe sang Saulus, ko dong sama-sama kambali pi Antiokia. Ais dong dua tenga di Antiokia sama-sama deng Tuhan pung orang dong, sampe satu taon. Hari-hari, dong dua ajar Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop kasi banya orang. (Di itu kota Antiokia tu, baru orang mulai kasi nama sang Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong bilang, &lt;orang Kristen&gt;).<bt>When he meet him, he persuaded Saulus, so that they return to Antiokia together. Then they two stayed in Antiokia together with the Lord's people, until one year. Each day, they two taught the Lord Yesus' Life Path to many people. (In that Antiokia city there, only then did people begin to give the name to the Lord Yesus' people, saying 'Kristen people').</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kokoe ~ kakoe; orang banya dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kokoe ~ kakoe; orang banya dong = a crowd; banya orang dong = many people</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:26" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kata &lt;Kristen&gt; tu, dia pung asal dari kata &lt;Kristus&gt;. Dia pung arti bilang, &lt;orang yang iko sang Kristus&gt;. Kristus pung arti bilang, &lt;Orang Barisi yang Tuhan Allah tunju memang dari dolu ko mau kirim datang&gt;.<bt>That word ‘Kristen’ there, it's orgin comes from the word ‘Kristus’. It's meaning, says, ‘people who follow Kristus’. Kristus means ‘Holy Person whom God designated beforehand from long ago to come’.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Waktu dong dua masi ada di Antiokia, ada barapa orang datang dari Yerusalem. Tuhan biasa pake itu orang dong ko jadi Dia pung jubir.<bt>When they two were still in Antiokia, there were several people who came from Yerusalem. The Lord often used those people to be His spokespersons.</bt><v n="28" />Dari itu jubir dong, ada satu orang, nama Agabus. Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti ada musim lapar yang hebat di anteru dunya, sampe di huk-huk dong.&gt;&gt; Ju dia pi kasi tau ulang sang orang dong. (Dia pung omong tu, jadi batúl waktu Roma pung raja bésar keser, nama Klaudius, ada pegang parenta.)<bt>From those spokespersons, there was a person, name Agabus. The Lord's Spirit told him saying, “Later there will be an intense hungry season in the entire world, until all the corners.” And he went to tell again to people. (That speaking of his, became true when Roma's big raja Keser, name Klaudius, [was the one] who held authority.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check rank of Kaisar. Probably below"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">check rank of Kaisar. Probably below a raja in traditional Timor system. Keser sama ke Liurai = ; Keser over Uis Pah (local king)</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 21:10</note><v n="29" />Dengar Agabus pung omong bagitu, ju Tuhan Yesus pung orang di Antiokia dong, ba'akór ko dong kumpul doi kasi dong pung sodara dalam Yesus yang idop susa di propinsi Yudea. Satu-satu kasi iko dong pung mampu.<bt>Hearing Agabus' talk like that, then the Lord Yesus' people in Antiokia, were in one accord to collect money to give it to their siblings in Yesus who live in difficulty in Yudea province. Each one gave according to their ability.</bt><v n="30" />Kumpul abis, ju dong tunju Barnabas deng Saulus, ko dong dua antar bawa itu doi, ko kasi sang kapala jama'at dong di sana, ko bagi kasi orang-orang susa.<bt>After collecting [it], then they appointed Barnabas and Saulus, so that they two go take that money, to give it to the leaders of the congregations over there to divide up to the people in difficulty.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doi/sumbangan/bantuan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">doi/sumbangan/bantuan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yakobis pung mati; Petrus pung maso bui; deng orang parcaya dong pung sambayang<bt>Yakobis' death; Petrus' going.into jail; and the congregation's prayer</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, ju raja Herodes<bt>At that time, then raja Herodes</bt><note reference="12:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Raja Herodes ni, dong ju kanál deng nama <span class="Italic">Herodes Agripa.</span> Dia pung ba'i, dong kanál deng nama <span class="Italic">Herodes Bésar</span> (andia Herodes Agung). Dia tu, yang suru bunu ana mea waktu Tuhan Yesus lahir di Betlehem.<bt>This king Herodes here, they also know by the name <span class="Italic">Herodes Agripa</span>. His grandfather, they knew by the name <span class="Italic">Big/Great Herodes</span> (that is, Herodes the Great [Indonesian/Sanskrit]). He was the one who ordered the infants to be killed when the Lord Yesus was born in Betlehem.</bt></note>mulai bekin sangsara satenga mati sang Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong saparu.<bt>began to make extreme tribulation to the some of the Lord Yesus' people.</bt><v n="2" />Dia parenta orang ko dong pi bunu bekin mati sang Yakobis pake kalewang. Yakobis tu, Yohanis pung bu.<bt>He ordered people to go murder kill Yakobis using a sword. That Yakobis, was Yohanis' elder brother.</bt><v n="3" />Waktu Herodes lia bilang, Yakobis pung mati bekin sanáng orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong, ju dia bekin tamba-tamba lai. Pas deng hari bésar yang dong subu bilang, pesta Roti Sonde Pake Ragi,<bt>When Herodes saw that that death of Yakobis, made the Yahudi bosses/leaders happy, then he did it even more. Exactly with the big day (=holiday) that they call feast of Bread Not Using Yeast,</bt><note reference="12:3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Itu hari bae, badeka deng Hari Paska.<bt>That holiday, is close to Easter Day.</bt></note>ju dia suru orang pi tangkap ame sang Petrus lai.<bt>then he ordered people to go capture Petrus again. [EXEG: on ‘the Jews’: see Carson's commentary on John, &amp; Terry Schram's dissertation “The use of ‘the Jews’ in the fourth gospel”; think of this usage as a semi-organised group of ambitious Jewish leaders (crossing Pharisee/Sadducee lines), and not the Jewish race as a whole (translations which unfortunately contributed to antisemitism), nor even all the Jewish leaders. Because it was semi-organised, and a group with an identity in the general knowledge bank, it is always refered to with an article ‘the Jews’.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if Pesta Roti Sonde Pake Ragi is problematic or too heavy on the information load, try Pesta Roti Bakál (and make other references and books conform after the term has been checked.]</bt><v n="4" />Tangkap abis sang dia, ju dong lempar kasi maso sang dia pi dalam bui. Tarús dong tunju ampa kalompok tantara ko jaga baganti sang Petrus siang hari malam. Satu kalompok tantara, ada ampa orang. Herodes mau ko putus Petrus pung parkara di orang banya pung muka, nanti kalo itu pesta su abis.<bt>After capturing/arresting him, then they threw put him in jail. Then they appointed four groups of soldiers to take turns guarding Petrus day-night. One soldier group, had four people. Herodes wanted to decide Petrus' litigation in front of many people, later when the Feast of Bread Not Using Yeast was over.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="regu = kalompok; kalompok serdadu; younger"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">regu = kalompok; kalompok serdadu; younger gen prefers tantara</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 12:1-27</note><v n="5" />Jadi waktu dong tahan sang Petrus dalam bui, Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong sambayang sonde putus-putus, minta ko Tuhan lia sang Petrus.<bt>So (consequently) while they held Petrus in jail, the Lord Yesus' people prayed without stopping, asking that the Lord take care of Petrus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi = Prep for, benefactive; tahan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kasi = Prep for, benefactive; tahan =</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan kasi kaluar sang Petrus dari bui<bt>God2 gets Petrus out of prison</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dia pung beso, raja Herodes mau putus Petrus pung parkara di muka umum. Ma itu malam, dong ika sang Petrus deng dua rante di dalam bui. Ais dia tidor di dua tantara pung teng-tenga. Deng ada tantara laen dong yang bajaga di muka pintu.<bt>The next day, raja Herodes wanted to decide Petrus' ligitation in front of the public. But that night, they tied Petrus with two chains in jail, Then he slept in between two soldiers. And there were other soldiers who guarded the front of the door.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01953b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none">Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga datang ko kasi kaluar Petrus dari bui<bt>The Lord's angel comes to take Petrus out of jail</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Takuju sa, Tuhan pung ana bua satu dari sorga datang badiri di situ, ju itu kamar taráng bacaya. Ais, itu ana bua goyang kasi bangun sang Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Pe'u, é! Bangun capát!&gt;&gt; Itu waktu ju, itu rante bési talapás memang dari Petrus pung tangan.<bt>Suddenly, the Lord's angel came and stood there, and that room was shining bright. Then, that angel shook waking up Petrus saying, “Pe'u, é! Get up fast!” At that time also, that iron chain was freed right away from Petrus' hand/arm.</bt><v n="8" />Ais ju itu ana bua suru sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Pake lu pung baju! Deng pake lu pung sandal!&gt;&gt; Petrus pake abis, ju itu ana bua suru lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Pake lu pung baju luar, ko mari iko sang beta suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, that angel ordered him saying, “Put on your shirt/clothes! And put on your sandals!” Petrus finished putting them on, then that angel ordered him again saying, “Put on your outer clothes, and then come follow me (imp)!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ju Petrus iko itu ana bua, ko jalan kaluar dari dalam bui. Ma Petrus kira kata, dia cuma mimpi sa. Padahal, memang jadi batúl bagitu.<bt>Then Petrus followed that angel, and walked out of the jail. But Petrus thought that he was only just dreaming. However, it actually happened truly like that.</bt><v n="10" />Waktu dong su lewat tampa jaga partama deng kadua, ju dong sampe di pintu bési. Itu pintu tabuka sandiri bagitu sa, ais ju dong dua kaluar ko iko jalan yang pi kota. Takuju sa, Tuhan pung ana bua tu, pi kasi tenga sang Petrus sandiri di situ.<bt>When they had passed the first guard place and the second, then they arrived at the iron door. That door open by itself just.like that, and then they two went out to go.along the road that went to the city. Suddenly, that angel of the Lord, went leaving behind Petrus all by himself there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Itu ana bua ilang abis, ju Petrus sadar bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl, é! Sakarang baru beta tau. Tuhan tu, batúl-batúl su kirim datang Dia pung ana bua ko kasi lapás sang beta dari Herodes pung tangan. Tuhan bekin bagitu ko orang Yahudi dong pung akal busuk sonde kaná di beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that angel had disappeared, then Petrus was aware saying, “It's actually true! Just now I know. That Lord, truly sent His angel to free me from Herodes. The Lord did like that so that the Yahudi people evil scheme would not affect me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sadar = conscious, aware"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sadar = conscious, aware</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais bagitu, ju Petrus pi di mama Maria pung ruma. Dia tu, andia Yohanis pung mama. Yohanis tu, pung nama laen, Markus. Di situ, banya orang ada bakumpul sambayang, minta ko Tuhan tolong Petrus deng dia pung parkara.<bt>After that, then Petrus went to a mama, named Maria, 's house. That her, that.was Yohanis' mama. That Yohanis had another name, that is Markus. There, many people had gathered to pray, asking that the Lord help Petrus with his litigation.</bt><v n="13" />Sampe di itu ruma, ju Petrus toki deng eki dari pagar pung pintu. Tarús satu pambantu parampuan, nama Rode, pi maloi sapa yang ada datang.<bt>Arriving at that house, then Petrus called out from the outside yard gate. Then a female maid, name Rode, went to take a peep to see who it was who had come.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="toki pintu = knock at the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">toki pintu = knock at the door; eki = call out to attract attention, sapa tu yang ba'eki</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Dengar Petrus pung suara tu, ju dia kanál memang. Dia sanáng mau mati, tarús dia lari capát-capát pi dalam, ko kasi tau orang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Petrus ada badiri di luar!&gt;&gt; Ma tagal dia su babingung tu, dia lupa buka pintu kasi sang Petrus.<bt>Hearing that voice of Petrus, then she recognised it right away. That's why she ran fast inside, to tell the people saying, “We! [+attention] Petrus is standing outside!” But because she was confused like that, she forgot to open the door/gate for Petrus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde mungkin! Jang maen gila bagitu!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they replied saying, “Impossible! Don't fool.around/kid like that!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maen gila ; lu ada-ada sa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">maen gila ; lu ada-ada sa = you're just fooling around</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma itu parampuan batahan karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Itu batúl-batúl Petrus pung suara! Dia ada di luar sana!&gt;&gt;<bt>But that woman continued strongly saying, “No! It really was Petrus' voice! He is outside over there!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dong acu sa bilang, &lt;&lt;Mangkali, itu cuma Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga sa, yang ada jaga sang Petrus.&gt;&gt;<bt>But they just ignored [her] saying, “Probably, that was only just an angel, who is guarding Petrus.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Lu gila mangkali!&quot; dong mara sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">"Lu gila mangkali!" dong mara sang dia bilang bagitu. Ma Rode batahan kras bilang itu orang memang batúl-batúl Petrus. Ju dong omong lai, &lt;&lt;Itu pasti dia pung jiwa!"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="acu sa = tidak perduli, acuh,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">acu sa = tidak perduli, acuh, cuek, as advice can also mean 'calm down, be cool'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Dong masi batola-bahela, ma Petrus ada ba'eki tarús, sampe dong pi buka pintu. Buka abis, ju dong tanganga bodo, te dia tu, andia Petrus.<bt>They still were pushing-pulling, but Petrus was still calling out, until they went to open the gate/door. After opening, then they were amazed, cuz (elaboration) that him, it.was Petrus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maen katók makaduduak = keep on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">maen katók makaduduak = keep on knocking</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Petrus goyang dia pung tangan ko biar dong samua tanáng. Ais ju dia carita karmana ko sampe Tuhan Allah su kasi kaluar sang dia dari dalam bui. Ju dia suru sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pi kasi tau ini hal samua sang Yakobis deng utusan laen dong, é.&gt;&gt; Tarús Petrus kaluar pi tampa laen.<bt>Petrus shook his hand so that they would all be quiet. Then he told how it happened taht the Lord God has taken him out from inside the jail. And he ordered them saying, “You you tell all these things to Yakobis and the other apostles, é! Then2 Petrus went out to another place.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Dia pung beso papagi, waktu tantara jaga dong lia bilang, Petrus su sonde ada lai, ju dong bingung, deng dong taku mau mati, tagal dong sonde tau nanti jadi karmana deng dong.<bt>The next day, when the guard soldiers saw that Petrus was no longer there, they were confused, and they were extremely afraid, because they didn't know what would happen to them.</bt><v n="19" />Waktu Herodes dapa tau itu hal, ju dia parenta sang dong ko pi cari sang Petrus. Ma dong sonde katumu sang dia. Ju Herodes parenta ko dong pareksa itu tantara jaga dong. Pareksa abis, ju dia suru ko bunu bekin mati sang itu tantara jaga dong samua.<bt>When Herodes got to know this matter, then he ordered them to go find Petrus. But they did not find him. And Herodes ordered that they go examine the soldier guards. After examining, then they murdered kill all those soldier guards.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais ju Herodes pi jalan kasi tenga Yudea, ko tenga di kota Kaisarea.<bt>After that, Herodes went travelling leaving behind Yudea, to live in Kaisarea city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Raja Herodes Agripa pung mati<bt>The death of Raja Herodes Agripa</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Itu waktu, ada orang dong dari dua kota, nama Tirus deng Sidon, suka béli makan dari raja Herodes pung negrí. Ma su dari lama, itu raja su bamusu deng dong. Ais dong ba'akór ko cari jalan pi badame deng dia. Ju dong pili satu rombongan ko pi katumu deng Herodes. Sampe di Kaisarea, dong batamán deng satu orang dalam, nama Blastus. Dia tu, satu kapala urusan di raja pung ruma jabatan. Dong basakongkol deng Blastus ko dia jadi dong pung tukang buju ko buka jalan sang dong bisa katumu deng Herodes.<bt>At that time, there were people from two cities, named Tirus and Sidon, liked to buy food from raja Herodes' country. But from way before, that raja was enemies with them. So they were in agreement to find a way to have mutual peace with him. And they chose a group to go meet Herodes. Arriving at Kaisarea, they went together with an inside person, name Blastus. That him, he was one of the overseers of the raja's palace. They were in agreement with Blastus so that he became their persuading person to open the way for them to Herodes. [EXEG: Gk ‘chamberlain’, having oversight of one of the functional units of the palace, often the harem.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukang bujuk = orang yang kokoe;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tukang bujuk = orang yang kokoe; orang dalam = their inside man; badame = reciprocal</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Herodes ada mara mo mati sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Herodes ada mara mo mati sang orang-orang Tirus deng Sidon. Tagal itu dong samua datang sama-sama ko mangada sang dia. Mula-mula dong buju sang Blastus ko biar badiri bela sang dong. Abis itu dong samua pi mangada sang Herodes, ko minta badame, te dong pung negrí idop dari makanan yang dong bawa datang dari Herodes pung negrí.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais Herodes satuju ko tarima sang dong, ju dong pili satu waktu ko dong bakatumu. Itu hari, dong bekin acara bésar. Herodes pake dia pung pakean jabatan, ais dudu di dia pung korsi parenta. Ju dia mulai angka omong sang dong.<bt>Then Herodes agreed to receive them, and they choose a time for them to meet together. That day, they made a big ceremony. Herodes wore his official clothes, and then sat in his commanding chair. And he began to speak [with authority] to them.</bt><v n="22" />Dengar dia pung suara, ju orang dong mulai puji angka nae sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar dia pung suara tu! Ini bukan manusia pung suara! Ini dewa pung suara!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing his voice, then people began to praise lifting him up saying, “Listen to that voice of his! This is not a human's voice! This is a god's voice!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dewa = god"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">dewa = god</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Takuju sa, Tuhan Allah pung ana bua satu dari sorga kirim kasi Herodes satu panyaki, tagal dia tarima dong pung puji sang dia, deng dia ju seti kasi ondor sang Tuhan Allah. Ju cacing dong makan buang sang Herodes pung badan sampe dia mati mampos.<bt>Suddenly, the Lord God's angel sent gave Herodes a sickness, because he accepted their praises to him, and he also was willing to set aside the Lord God. And worms ate throwing out Herodes' body until he died in a cursed/derogatory way. [EXEG: Gk: not given the glory to God.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@CHECK 1) Because he accepted praise,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">@@CHECK 1) Because he accepted praise, 2) that is why angel made him sick, 3) so that worms ate him....</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="seti kasi ondor = menyingkirkan, mengenyampingkan;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">seti kasi ondor = menyingkirkan, mengenyampingkan; ma'ale buang = chew up; cacing galáng = roundworm ; cacing pita = tapeworm; mati mampos = derogotory way of s.o. died, died accursedly</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Deng samua hal yang su jadi tu, Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae tasiar tamba luas, deng orang yang iko Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop ju tamba banya.<bt>With all that that happened, the Lord God's Good News spread even wider, and the people who followed the Lord Yesus' Life Path also increased alot.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Waktu Barnabas deng Saulus antar abis orang Antiokia dong pung bantuan pi Yerusalem tu, ju dong pulang kambali pi Antiokia. Dong ada bawa satu orang muda sama-sama deng dong. Dia pung nama Yohanis. Ma dong ju pange sang dia bilang, Markus.<bt>As soon as Barnabas and Saulus finished delivering the Anitiokia people's aid to that Yerusalem, then they returned home to Antiokia. They brought a youth together with them. His name Yohanis. But they also call him saying, Markus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Antiokia utus Barnabas deng Saulus<bt>People of Antiokia commission Barnabas and Saulus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Di kota Antiokia, banya orang su parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus. Ada barapa orang yang Tuhan Allah ada pake sang dong jadi Dia pung jubir, deng ada barapa lai yang Dia pake ko ajar orang. Dong tu, andia:<bt>In Antiokia city, many people had believed in the Lord Yesus. There were several people whom the Lord God used them to be His spokesperson, and there were several others whom He used to teach people. Those them, they.were:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Barnabas,<bt>Barnabas</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Simeon, yang orang biasa pange sang dia &lt;Si Itam&gt;,<bt>Simeon, whom people call him 'The Black One',</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="itam marege = lf Max"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">itam marege = lf Max</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:1a" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani bilang, &lt;Niger&gt;, deng dia pung arti bilang, &lt;itam&gt;, ko, &lt;galáp&gt;.<bt>The Yunani writings say 'Niger', and its meaning is 'black', or 'dark'.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lukius, dari kota Kirene,<bt>Lukius, from Kirene city,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Menahem, yang dong piara dari kici sama-sama deng raja Herodes,<bt>Menahem, whom that cared.for from the time he was little together with raja Herodes,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Greek = Manaen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Greek = Manaen</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:1b" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Raja Herodes ni, dong ju kanál deng nama <span class="Italic">Herodes Antipas.</span> Dia tu, yang bunu bekin mati sang Yohanis, Tukang Sarani. Dia pung bapa, dong kanál deng nama <span class="Italic">Herodes Bésar</span> (andia Herodes Agung). Dia tu, yang suru bunu ana mea waktu Tuhan Yesus lahir di Betlehem. Raja Herodes yang bunu sang Yakobis, deng yang mati kaná cacing tu, dong kanál deng nama <span class="Italic">Herodes Agripa.</span><bt>This king Herodes here, they also knew by the name <span class="Italic">Herodes Antipas.</span> He was the one who killed Yohanis the Baptiser. His father they knew by the name <span class="Italic">Big/Great Herodes</span> (that is Herodes the Great [Indonesian/Sanskrit]). He was the one who ordered that the infants be killed when the Lord Yesus was born in Betlehem. The king Herodes who killed Yakobis, and who died from worms, they knew by the name <span class="Italic">Herodes Agripa.</span></bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Saulus.<bt>and Saulus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Satu waktu, dong ada puasa, deng dong ada bakumpul ko sémba sang Tuhan Allah. Ais Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Pili ame sang Barnabas deng Saulus. Te Beta pung karjá ada banya. Deng dong musti bekin ame karjá yang Beta mau ator kasi sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, they were fasting, and they were gathered to worship the Lord God. Then the Lord's Holy Spirit told them saying, “Choose/Appoint Barnabas and Saulus. Cuz (elaboration) My work is much. And they must do the work which I want to give them.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Waktu dong puasa deng sambayang abis, ju dong taro tangan pi Barnabas deng Saulus ko tabis sang dong. Tarús dong utus sang dong dua pi ko kasi jalan Tuhan pung karjá.<bt>When they were finished fasting and praying, then they laid hands on Barnabas and Saulus' heads, to ordain them. Then they commissioned them two, to go do the Lord's work.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tabis = resmikan, sahkan, ordain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tabis = resmikan, sahkan, ordain</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Barnabas deng Saulus dong pi pulo Siprus<bt>Barnabas and Saulus (collective) go to Siprus island</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4-5" />Waktu Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi parenta Barnabas deng Saulus ko dong dua jalan pi kuliling, partama dong pi satu kota di pante, nama Seleukia. Yohanis (itu orang yang dong ju pange bilang, Markus) ju iko sama-sama deng dong. Sampe di situ, dong nae kapal ko balayar pi pulo Siprus, ais dong turun di satu kota, nama Salamis. Di situ, dong suka maso pi orang Yahudi dong pung ruma sambayang ko ajar Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata kasi orang dong.<bt>When the Lord's Holy Spirit ordered Barnabas and Saulus for them two to travel around, first they went to a city on the beach, named Seleukia. Yohanis (that person whom they also call Markus) also went together with them. Arriving there, they went on a ship to sait to Siprus island, then then disembarked at a city, named Salamis. There, they liked to enter into the Yahudi people's worship houses to teach the Lord God's Words to people.</bt></p>
    <fig path="maps\Bible\hksal-pf.tif" rtfFormat="width:7.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontal_position: right">Dong jalan pi pulo Siprus<bt>They travel to Siprus island</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6-8" />Ais dong jalan singga-singga dari satu kampong pi satu kampong, sampe dong datang di satu kota di itu pulo pung ujung sablá, nama Pafos. Gubernor ada tenga di itu kota. Dia pung nama Sergius Paulus. Dia tu, orang otak encer. Waktu dia dengar bilang, Barnabas dong su datang di dia pung kota, ju dia suru orang ko pi pange sang dong, te dia pung hati su rindu mau dengar nasiat dari Tuhan.<bt>Then they travelled from village to village stopping temporarily, until they came to a city on that island's tip on the other side, named Pafos. The Gubernor was living in that city. His name was Sergius Paulus. That him, [he was] a smart person. When he heard that Barnabas (collective) had come to his city, then he ordered people/person to go call them, cuz (elaboration) his liver was longing to hear advice from the Lord.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orang pintar = tukang suanggi, dukun;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">orang pintar = tukang suanggi, dukun; jalan singga-singga; pulo pung ujung sabla, ; otak encer; pesán</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma di situ, ada satu orang Yahudi ju, nama Bar Yesus (deng dia pung nama laen dalam bahasa Yunani bilang, &lt;Elimas&gt;). Dia tu, tukang suanggi. Dia biasa putar-balek orang bilang, dia ju Tuhan Allah pung jubir. Dia batamán bae deng itu gubernor. Jadi waktu Barnabas dong datang, dia tusu-tusu sang gubernor ko jang tarima sang dong. Dia coba-coba pangaru itu gubernor ko sonde usa parcaya sang Yesus.<bt>But there, there was also a Yahudi person, named Bar Yesus (with his other name in the Yunani language saying, ‘Elimas’). He was a practitioner of black or destructive magic/witchcraft. He often lied to people saying, he was also a spokesperson of the Lord God. He was good friends with the governor. So when Barnabas (collective) came, he persuaded (lit. poked &amp; poked) the governor to not receive them. He was trying to influence that governor that it was not necessary to believe in Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukang suanggi; putar-balek; tusu-tusu; pangaru"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tukang suanggi; putar-balek; tusu-tusu; pangaru</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02116b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Paulus togor sang tukang suanggi<bt>Paulus scolds a practitioner of witchcraft/destructive.magic</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi ada kasi kuasa sang Saulus (yang dong ju pange bilang, Paulus), ju dia pe'e mata ko lia karás-karás itu tukang suanggi. Ais dia omong bilang,<bt>But the Lord's Holy Spirit gave power to Saulus (who they also call Paulus), and he glared to look sternly at that witchcraft practitioner. Then he spoke saying,</bt><v n="10" />&lt;&lt;Heh, Elimas! Lu ana setan! Tukang putar-balek! Sampe kapan lu masi mau tipu orang? Lu malawan samua yang bae. Tagal bagitu, botong tau lu iko setan dong pung bos. Lu jang bekin bagitu lai! Lu jang coba-coba tutu Tuhan pung jalan yang lurus lai!<bt>"He! Elimas! You-sg are the child of an evil spirit! A practitioner of lies! Until when are you still going to decieve people! You oppose all that is good. Because of that, we-inc know you follow *Satan (the evil spirit's big boss). You don't do like that anymore! You must not keep trying any longer to close the Lord's straight path.</bt><v n="11" />Weh! Lu dengar, é! Nanti Tuhan hukum sang lu. Lu pung mata nanti jadi buta, deng lu sonde dapa lia apa-apa, sampe barapa hari.&gt;&gt;<bt>We [+critical]! Listen to this! Later the Lord will judge/punish you. Your eyes will become blind, and you will no longer be able to see anything, for several days.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">buta</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Paulus omong abis bagitu, ju itu orang pung mata buta memang. Ais dia jalan raba-raba, ko cari orang pegang dia pung tangan, ko hela bawa jalan sang dia.<bt>Paulus finished speaking like that, then that person's eyes became blind right away. Then he walked holding.on.to.things, to find a person to hold his hand, to pull &amp; bring him along.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kabut pele dia pung mata"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kabut pele dia pung mata</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Waktu gubernor lia deng dia pung mata kapala sandiri bagitu, deng dia dengar Barnabas dong ajar so'al Yesus, dia taheran-heran, ais ju dia parcaya sang Yesus.<bt>When the governor saw like that with his very own eyes, and he heard Barnabas (collective) teaching about Yesus, he was amazed, and then he believed in Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong bawa Carita Bae pi kota Antiokia laen, di propinsi Pisidia<bt>They bring the Good Story to the city of Antiokia in Pisidia province</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Dari kota Pafos di pulo Siprus, Paulus dong nae kapal ko balayar pi satu kota di propinsi Pamfilia, nama Perga. Di situ, dong turun dari kapal, ais Yohanis Markus jalan kasi tenga sang dong ko pulang pi Yerusalem.<bt>From the city of Pafos on Siprus island, Paulus (collective) got on board a ship to sail to a city in Pamfilia province, named Perga. There, they disembarked from the ship. then Yohanis Markus travelled on leaving them to go.home to Yerusalem.</bt><v n="14" />Dari Perga dong jalan iko darat pi kota Antiokia di propinsi Pisidia.<bt>From Perga they travelled by land to the city of Antiokia in Pisidia province.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong sampe di itu kota. Ais waktu orang Yahudi dong pung hari barenti karjá, ju dong pi iko sambayang di orang Yahudi dong pung ruma sambayang.<bt>They arrived there. Then when it was the Yahudi people's day of stopping work, they went to a service in the Yahudi people's worship house.</bt><v n="15" />Itu waktu, dong ada baca dari ba'i Musa pung tulisan, deng dari Tuhan pung jubir laen dong pung tulisan. Ais, itu ruma sambayang pung bos-bos dong, minta sang Paulus dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa dong. Kalo bosong ada pasán kasi botong, na, botong minta deng hormat ko bosong omong kasi kuat kotong samua di sini pung hati.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, they were reading from Gf/Ff Musa's book, and from the writings of the Lord's other spokespersons. Then, that worship house's bosses, requested Paulus (collective) saying, “Fathers. If you have a request for us-exc, na, we respectively request that you speak to make strong the livers (=encourage) of all of us here.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus mulai angka omong kasi orang Yahudi dong di Antiokia [\s2]<bt>Paulus begins to speak to the Yahudi people in Antiokia [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais Paulus bangun badiri pi di muka. Ju dia angka tangan ko minta sang dong tanáng. Ais dia mulai angka omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara-sodara, bangsa Isra'el dong. Deng mama-bapa yang laen dong yang su maso agama Yahudi, tagal bosong pung hati ju rindu sang bangsa Isra'el pung Tuhan Allah. Beta minta bosong pasang talinga ko dengar sang beta!<bt>Then Paulus got.up &amp; stood in front. And he raised his hand to request that they be quiet. The he began to speak saying, “Siblings, [people of] Israel nation. And other fathers-mothers, who have entered the Yahudi religion, because your livers also long for the Lord God of the Israel nation. I request that you attach your ears (=pay attention) to listen to me!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Tuhan Allah su pili ame kotong bangsa Isra'el pung nene-moyang dong dari dolu. Waktu dong pi tenga di tana Masir, yang bukan dong pung negrí sandiri, Tuhan kasi sang dong tenga deng sejahtara, sampe dong pung turunan tamba banya. Ais ju Tuhan pake Dia pung kuasa bésar ko bawa kasi kaluar sang dong dari Masir.<bt>The Lord has chosen the ancestors of our-inc Israel from long ago. When they went to live in Masir land, which was not their own land, the Lord enabled them to live with prosperity. And then the Lord used his big power to bring them out from Masir.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="idop deng limpa-limpa ; sejahtara ~"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">idop deng limpa-limpa ; sejahtara ~ sejahtra</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 1:7, 12:51</note><v n="18" />Ais itu, dong idop bapinda-pinda di itu tampa kosong sampe ampa pulu taon. Biar dong kapala batu tarús, ma Tuhan antar sang dong deng sabar sa.<bt>After that, they lived moving around and around an empty place for 40 years. At that time, the Lord just escorted them with patience.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati besar = sabar, penuh dgn"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hati besar = sabar, penuh dgn ampunan; idop bapinda-pinda = nomadis</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 14:34, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 1:31</note><v n="19" />Ais ju Tuhan kasi ancor tuju bangsa di tana Kana'an. Tarús dia bagi-bagi dong pung tana kasi kotong pung nene-moyang dong, ko jadi dong pung tana pusaka.<bt>After that, the Lord destroyed seven ethnic groups in Kanaan land. And then He divided their land, giving [it] to our ancestors, to become their inheritance land.</bt><note reference="13:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 7:1, Yosua 14:1</note><v n="20" />Dong idop bagitu sampe ampa ratus lima pulu (450) taon.<bt>They lived like that for/until four hundred and fifty (450) years.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais itu, Tuhan Allah angka kasi sang dong tukang putus parkara dong, ko pimpin sang dong, sampe deng Tuhan angka Dia pung jubir satu, nama Samuel.<bt>After that, the Lord God raised up and gave them litigation deciding practitioners (judges), to lead them, until the Lord raised up one of His spokesperson, named Samuel.</bt><note reference="13:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Tukang Putus Parkara dong2:16, 1 Samuel 3:20</note><v n="21" />Waktu Samuel jadi Tuhan pung jubir, kotong pung nene-moyang dong mau-mau ko dapa raja. Ais Tuhan angka sang Kis pung ana, nama Saul, dari suku Benyamin. Saul pegang parenta sampe ampa pulu taon.<bt>When Samuel became the Lord's spokesperson, our ancestors kept on desiring to have a raja. So the Lord raised up Kis' child, named Saul, from the Benjamin tribe. Saul held authority for forty years.</bt><note reference="13:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Samuel 8:5, 10:21</note><v n="22" />Ju Tuhan kasi turun sang dia. Ais Tuhan angka Isai pung ana, nama Daud, ko ganti sang dia jadi raja baru. Tuhan tau batúl Daud pung hati bilang, &lt;Isai pung ana Daud ni, cocok deng Beta pung hati. Tantu dia nanti bekin iko Beta pung mau samua.&gt;<bt>And the caused him to go down(=took away his authority). Then the Lord raised Isai's child, named Daud, to replace him to be the new raja. The Lord truly knew Daud's hear saying, 'This child of Isai here, matches/fits with My liver. Surely he will do [things] according to all My desires/will.'</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="geser buang = kudeta ; deta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">geser buang = kudeta ; deta = dip finger and pick up (salt, sugar) on tip, and lick s.t. off tip ; lambe = jilat ; kodo = telan</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Samuel 13:14, 16:12, Lagu Puji dong 89:20</note><v n="23" />Itu waktu, Tuhan janji ko mau kirim Daud pung turunan satu, ko kasi salamat sang orang Isra'el dari dong pung sala-sala dong. Beta mau kasi tau sodara dong samua bilang, Daud pung turunan yang Tuhan janji tu, andia Yesus.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, the Lord promised to send one of Daud's descendants, to save the Israel people from their wrongs. I want to tell all (you) siblings that, that descendant of Daud whom the Lord promised, it's Yesus.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus bilang Yesus tu, Orang yang Tuhan janji mau kirim datang [\s2]<bt>Paulus says the Yesus is the Person who God2 promised to send [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Paulus sambung dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Waktu Tuhan Yesus balóm angka Dia pung karjá, ada satu orang, nama Yohanis, pi kasi tau orang Isra'el dong bilang, dong musti barenti dari dong pung sala-sala dong, deng bale ko iko sang Tuhan. Ais dong musti sarani ko jadi tanda bilang, dong su babae deng Tuhan.<bt>Paulus conitnued what he was saying1 saying2, “When the Lord Yesus had not yet begun His work, there was a person, named Yohanis, who went to tell the Israel people, saying they must stop from their wrongs, and turn to follow/obey God2. Then they must be baptised to become a sign that they are in the state of good/right relationship with God2.</bt><note reference="13:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 1:4, Lukas 3:3</note><v n="25" />Ma waktu Yohanis pung karjá su mau abis, dia kasi tau orang dong bilang, &lt;Jang bosong pikir beta ni, Orang yang Tuhan su janji dari dolu ko mau kirim datang. Inga bae-bae! Bosong musti tunggu satu Orang yang nanti mau datang. Dia lebe hebat dari beta, sampe jadi Dia pung tukang suru-suru sa ju, beta sonde pantas.&gt;<bt>But when Yohanis' work was about to finish, he told people saying, ‘Don't you-pl think that I here, am the Person who the Lord has promised from before to send. Remember well! You must wait for a Person who will come later. He is more amazing that me, to the point that just to be his slave (person who gets ordered around), I am not appropriate for that.’</bt><note reference="13:25" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang asli tulis bilang, &lt;tondo ko buka dia pung tali sapatu ju, beta sonde pantas&gt;. Dia pung arti bilang, banding deng Tuhan Yesus, Yohanis rasa diri cuma orang kici sa. Baca di Mateos 3:11, Markus 1:7, Lukas 3:16, Yohanis 1:20, 27.<bt>The original Yunani language writings write, saying ‘even to stoop.down to open his shoe ropes/strings, I am not worthy/ appropriate’. Its meaning is that, compared with the Lord Yesus, Yohanis felt himself to only just be a small (=unimportant) person. Read at Mateos 3:11, Markus 1:7, Lukas 3:16, Yohanis 1:20, 27.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Sodara dong samua! Bosong yang memang ba'i Abraham pung turunan, deng bosong yang laen yang pung hati rindu sang Tuhan. Dengar sang beta dolo! Tuhan Allah su kasi tau ini hal sang kotong, ko kotong dapa tau Dia pung jalan idop. Dia kasi salamat sang kotong dari kotong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>Siblings! You who are truly Gf Abraham's descendants, and you other whose livers long after the Lord. Hear me out! The Lord God has told this matter to us-inc, so that we can know His life path. He saved us from our wrongs.</bt><v n="27" />Dari dolu, Tuhan su pake Dia pung jubir dong ko dong tulis kasi tau orang so'al itu Orang yang Tuhan janji mau kirim datang. Ju kotong pung bos-bos agama dong, deng orang laen di Yerusalem, su baca ulang-ulang apa yang jubir dong su tulis. Tiap hari barenti karjá, dong maso pi ruma sambayang, ko dong baca so'al itu Orang di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi.<bt>From beforehand, the Lord has used His spokespersons so that they write telling people about that Person whom the Lord promised to send. And our religious bosses, and other people in Yerusalem, have read over and over that what the spokespersons wrote. Every work stop day, they enter into the worship houses, in order for them to read like that in the Lord's Holy Book.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dong sonde mangarti bilang itu Orang yang Tuhan su janji mau kirim datang tu, andia Yesus. Ais dong cari akal ko hukum mati sang Dia. Padahal ini hal ju pas deng apa yang Tuhan pung jubir dong su tulis.<bt>But they don't understand that the Person whom the Lord promised to send, that is Yesus. So they hunted for a scheme to judge Him to die. But this matter also matches with what the Lord's spokespersons wrote.</bt><v n="28" />Dong bekin-bekin parkara deng Yesus ko mau hiki kasi jato sang Dia, ma dong sonde dapa Dia pung sala apa-apa. Biar bagitu, ju dong pi minta sang gubernor Pilatus ko bunu bekin mati sang Dia.<bt>They made up litigation with Yesus to trap him and make Him fall, but they did not find any wrongs belonging to Him. Even though it was like that, then they went to ask gubernur Pilatus to murder kill Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalák = accuse; bekin-bekin = fabricate,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kalák = accuse; bekin-bekin = fabricate, made up; cari-cari hal = bekin gara-gara, rekayasa, look for trouble</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 27:22-23, Markus 15:13-14, Lukas 23:21-23, Yohanis 19:15</note><v n="29" />Itu gubernor satuju, ais dong paku kasi tagantong sang Yesus di kayu palang, sampe Dia mati. Ma samua ni, ju pas deng apa yang Tuhan pung jubir dong su tulis. Ais itu, dong kasi turun Dia pung mayat dari itu kayu palang, ju dong koko bawa sang Dia pi taro dalam kubur.<bt>That governor agreed, so they nailed hung Yesus on a cross, until He died. But all this, also exactly matches with what the Lord's spokespersons wrote. After that, they took his corpse down from that tree, and carried Him to go put Him in the grave.</bt><note reference="13:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 27:57-61, Markus 15:42-47, Lukas 23:50-56, Yohanis 19:38-42</note><v n="30" />Ma Tuhan Allah pake Dia pung kuasa, ko kasi idop kambali sang Yesus dari Dia pung mati.<bt>But the Lord God used His power, to cuz (elaboration) Yesus to live again from His death.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Waktu Yesus su idop kambali, Dia kasi tunju Dia pung diri banya kali kasi sang orang-orang. Dong tu, yang su datang sama-sama deng Dia dari propinsi Galilea pi Yerusalem. Deng dong tu yang sakarang jadi saksi kasi sang orang Isra'el dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus was alive again, He showed Himself many times to people. Those them[=people], were who had all come together with Him from Gailiea province to Yerusalem. And they are the ones who have now become witnesses to the Israel people.”</bt><note reference="13:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 1:3</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus kasi tunju bilang, Tuhan su pake Dia pung jubir dong ko kasi tau memang so'al Yesus [\s2]<bt>Paulus points out that God2 has used his spokespeople to foretell about Yesus [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32-33" />Paulus sambung dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa, bagini! Botong dua ni, andia beta deng Barnabas, su datang dari jao ko kasi tau sang bosong, ko biar bosong tau bilang, apa yang Tuhan su janji sang kotong pung nene-moyang dong, sakarang ni, samua su jadi. Tuhan su kasi idop kambali sang Yesus dari Dia pung mati. Di <span class="Italic">Lagu Puji </span>nomer dua, Tuhan su pake orang ko tulis so'al Yesus, itu Orang yang Dia janji mau kirim datang bilang:<bt>Paulus continued what he was saying, saying, &lt;&lt;Naa, it's like this! We two here, that is Barnabas and I, have come from far to tell you-pl, so that you can know that, that which the Lord promised to our ancestors, here now, it all has happened. The Lord has caused Yesus to live again from His death. In the Praise Book number two, the Lord used His person to write about Yesus, that Person whom He promised to send, saying:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Masmur nomer dua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Masmur nomer dua</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Lu ni, Beta pung Ana.<bt>‘You here, are My Child,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ini hari, Beta angka sang Lu ko pegang parenta.&gt;<bt>This day, I lift You up in order to hold authority.’ [EXEG: Ps 2:6 provides context of coronation for making sense out of this. One commentator notes for same quote in Heb “5:5. Citing again Psalm 2:7 (see comment on Heb 1:5), the writer proves from it that *Christ's royal coronation was God's initiative. In the next verse he links this kingship with the high priesthood.” (from CR) Bruce also links this to “enthronement” in same quote at 5:5, and at Heb 1:5 says this same quote may “have preserved the text of a coronation liturgy used by the Davidic dynasty”.]</bt><note reference="13:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 2:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Dari dolu Tuhan Allah ju su janji bilang, nanti Dia mau kasi idop kambali itu Orang yang Dia su janji mau kirim datang, deng itu Orang sonde akan mati lai. Tagal itu, Tuhan su pake Dia pung jubir ko tulis bilang,<bt>From beforehand the Lord God has promised saying, later He would cuz (elaboration) to live again that Person whom He promised to sent, and that Person would not die again. Because of that, the Lord used his spokesperson to writed saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Dari dolu Beta su ika janji deng raja Daud ko mau kasi berkat sang dia.<bt>‘From beforehand I have tied a promise with raja Daud to give a thing that is clean/holy to him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jadi sakarang Beta ju mau ika itu janji lai deng lu, tagal lu jadi Daud pung turunan.&gt;<bt>So (consequently) now I want to tie that promise again with you-sg, because you are Daud's descendant.’ [EXEG: Gk here ‘you’ is pl, quoting from Isaiah context talking to the people of Israel, or God's people. English and Indonesian are able to mask/ignore the differences with ‘you’ and ‘-mu’. CONTEXT: In 32-39 Paul is clearly making Messianic arguments, and even applying this verse to make an argument about the Messiah. So the dilemma is--do we reflect the FORM of the original, or do we reflect Paul's USE of this verse in this context. Hard call. It seems to me that using 2p in local lgs here would skew the focus and badly distract the readers from following the flow of the argument. So we choose 2s. The expansion in TN Display is a bit unwieldy and skews the focus even further. All sources acknowledge this is a tricky verse, but only TN and TRT offer possible solutions. Problem is, those solutions skew the focus from following the flow of Paul's argument.]</bt><note reference="13:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 55:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ada <span class="Italic">Lagu Puji</span> laen yang bilang,<bt>There is another Praise Song (=psalm) that says,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Tuhan sonde kasi tenga Lu pung Orang Barisi pung mayat,<bt>‘God is not going to permit Your Holy Person's corpse,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko jadi ancor-ancor dalam Dia pung kubur.&gt;<bt>to become destroyed/decayed in His grave.’</bt><note reference="13:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 16:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36-37" />Dia pung batúl bagini: ini <span class="Italic">Lagu Puji</span> sonde tunju sang Daud sandiri sa! Kotong tau bagitu, tagal raja Daud su bekin banya hal bae kasi dia pung bangsa dong, ais ju dia mati. Dia mati, ais dong kubur sang dia. Deng dia pung mayat su ancor abis. Jadi kotong tau bilang, itu <span class="Italic">Lagu Puji</span> sonde tunju sang Daud, ma ada tunju sang Orang laen. Itu Orang yang dia su tunju tu, nanti kalo itu Orang su mati, Tuhan Allah kasi idop kambali sang Dia. Andia ko Dia pung mayat sonde ancor sadiki ju.<bt>The truth is like this: this praise song does not point to that Daud! We know like that, because Raja Daud did many good things for his ethnic group, and then he died. He died, then they buried him. And his corpse is completely destroyed. So we know that that Praise Song (=psalm) doesn't point to Daud, but it points to another person. That person whom he selected/appointed, later when that Person died, the Lord God would cuz (elaboration) Him to live again. That's why, His corpse would not decay even a little bit.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde ancor sadiki ana ju ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sonde ancor sadiki ana ju =</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38-39" />Jadi sodara dong, dengar bae-bae! Itu Orang tu, andia Yesus! Ais kalo kotong parcaya sang Dia, baru Dia mau pikol sala-sala, yang kalo iko dia pung batúl, kotong sandiri yang musti pikol. Deng bagitu Tuhan Allah hapus buang kotong pung sala-sala dong. Ma kotong su tau bilang, biar kotong iko ba'i Musa pung atoran adat samua, itu sandiri sa sonde bisa bekin kotong batúl di Tuhan pung muka.<bt>So (consequently) siblings, listen carefully! That Person there, it's Yesus! So if we believe in Him, then He will shoulder.carry wrongs, which if we actually followed the truth, we ourselves should be the ones to shoulder.carry. And like that the Lord God forgets throws.away our wrongs. But we know from our traditions/customs that, Gf/Ff Musa himself, could not make straight all those matters.</bt><v n="40-41" />Andia ko bosong musti pikir bae-bae. Jang sampe, apa yang Tuhan pung jubir dolu-dolu dong su kasi tau, jato kaná sang bosong. Dong su tulis bilang,<bt>That's why we must think carefully. Lest, that which the Lord's spokesperson have told long ago, falls affecting/afflicting us. They wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Awas bosong tukang olok-olok dong, yang suka lia orang deng mata sablá!<bt>'Be careful you-pl, mockers, who like to look down on people/things!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pandang enteng = look disparagingly at,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pandang enteng = look disparagingly at, look down on s.o., be sceptical; olok-olok = mockers; tukang acu = doesn't care at all ; hina = omong kasi jato orang; UNS not know taro kira</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal Beta, Tuhan Allah, ada bekin hal-hal yang bekin orang taheran-heran;<bt>Because I, the Lord God, am doing things which cuz (elaboration) people to be amazed;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ma bosong nanti tarima bosong pung bagian, ko bosong mati mampos.<bt>but you, and your friends, later you will receive your share, so that you die in a horrible state. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK that your equivalent of “later you will receive your share,” comes across clearly as the language of threat/curse = you will die (as a result of getting your just desserts)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta bekin satu hal waktu bosong masi idop,<bt>I am doing something, while you are still alive.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma bosong sonde mau tarima.<bt>but you don't want to accept it.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar orang su kasi tau ju,<bt>Even though people have explained [it],</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bosong sonde mau mangarti.<bt>you don't want to understand it.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Lebe bae bosong pikir bae-bae ini hal dong, ko biar bosong heran ju.&gt;<bt>It's better if you think carefully about these things, so that you are also amazed.’</bt><note reference="13:41" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Habakuk 1:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Jadi sodara dong. Pikir bae-bae apa yang beta su kasi tau tadi. Jang lempar buang apa yang bosong su dengar tadi, sama ke tukang olok-olok dong pung bekin. Bagitu sa, beta pung omong. Makasi banya!&gt;&gt;<bt>So siblings. Think carefully about that which I just told you. Don't throw away that which you just hear, like the hard headed people do. My talk is just that. Many thanks!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Omong abis, ju Paulus deng Barnabas badiri ko mau jalan kasi tenga itu ruma sambayang. Ju orang di situ dong minta ko dong kambali lai minggu datang, ko kasi tau lebe alus lai, apa yang dong su omong tadi tu.<bt>Finishing talking, then Paulus and Barnabas stood to go leaving behind that worship house. And the people there requested that they return again next week, to explain in greater detail again, that which that had spoken about earlier.</bt><v n="43" />Waktu dong kaluar dari itu ruma sambayang, ada banya orang dari situ yang pi iko sang Paulus deng Barnabas. Ais dong dua kasi nasiat sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kotong tau bilang, Tuhan pung hati talalu bae sang kotong. Andia ko bosong ju musti bapegang karás-karás sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>As soon as they went out of that worship house, there were many people there who went following Paulus and Barnabas. Then the two of them gave advice to them saying, “We-inc know that the Lord's liver is exceedingly good to us (=generous). So you-pl must hold on tightly to Him.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong tola buang sang Paulus dong<bt>The Yahudi people's bosses reject &amp; dispose of Paulus (collective)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Dia pung minggu muka, pas deng orang Yahudi pung hari barenti karjá, amper samua orang di itu kota datang ko mau dengar Tuhan pung Kata-kata.<bt>The next week, exactly on the Yahudi people day of stopping work, almost all the people in that city came to hear the Lord's Words.</bt><v n="45" />Ma waktu orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong dapa lia orang banya mau datang dengar sang Paulus dong, ju dong saki hati. Ais waktu Paulus ada omong, dong malawan buta sang dia, deng omong kasi jato sang Paulus dong.<bt>But when the Yahudi people's bosses saw that many people wanted to come hear Paulus (collective), then their liver were sick (=angry). Then when he spoke explaining things, they opposed Paulus blindly (=without thought or reason), and spoke to slander Paulus (collective).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="malawan buta-buta = eplawak ledak; malawan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">malawan buta-buta = eplawak ledak; malawan buta = without thought or reason, asal omong sa; omong kasi jato = slander, hina</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Ma Paulus dong sonde ondor, deng dong omong sonde pele-pele lai. Dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang Tuhan Allah su buka jalan lebe dolo kasi kotong orang Yahudi, deng Dia kasi Kabar Bae sang kotong. Deng itu memang pantas! Ma bosong sonde mau tarima. Jadi deng bosong pili bagitu, bosong kasi tunju bilang, bosong sonde pantas dapa idop tarús deng Tuhan Allah. Jadi sakarang, botong mau bawa itu Kabar Bae kasi suku-bangsa laen dong, tagal bosong su tola buang sang dia.<bt>But Paulus (collective) did not reverse, and they spoke without any more reservation/obscurity (=openly). They said, “It's true the Lord God opened the path first for our-inc Yahudi people, and He gave Good News to us-inc. And that is really appropriate! But you don't want to accept [it]. So (consequently) by you-pl choosing like that, you show that you are not appropriate/worthy to live continually with the Lord God. So (consequently) now, we-exc want to bring that Good New to other ethnic groups, because you have rejected &amp; discarded it. [EXEG: did not judge yourselves worthy of eternal life ’ as result of your own choices you show you are not worthy of eternal life (judge is a bad gloss for the Gk)]</bt><v n="47" />Te Tuhan Allah su utus sang botong, parsís ke Yesaya su tulis bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the Lord has commissioned us saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Beta su angka sang bosong ko jadi sama ke lantera yang bawa taráng kasi suku-bangsa laen dong, yang bukan bangsa Yahudi,<bt>‘I have lifted you to become like a lantern that brings light to the other ethnic groups, who are not the Yahudi ethnic group.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko biar bosong senter bekin taráng itu jalan yang datang di Beta,<bt>so that you can make light/clear that path that comes to Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko biar Beta kasi lapás sang dong dari dong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>so that I will free them from their wrongs.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng bosong ju musti kasi tunju itu jalan di ini dunya dari ujung pi ujung.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>And you must also show that path in this world from tip to tip.’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="loti = maloi (disputed meaning!!)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">loti = maloi (disputed meaning!!)</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:47" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 42:6, 49:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Waktu orang bangsa laen yang bukan Yahudi dong dengar bagitu, ju dong sanáng mau mati. Tarús dong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah bilang, &lt;&lt;Puji Tuhan! Tuhan pung Kabar Bae tu, talalu bae!&gt;&gt; Deng di situ ada orang-orang yang Tuhan Allah su putus dari dolu ko bisa idop tarús deng Dia. Ais dong samua parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus.<bt>When the people from other ethnic groups who were not Yahudi heard like that, they were incredibly happy. Then they praised and praised the Lord God saying, “Praise the Lord! That Good News of the Lord, is very good!” And there there were peole whom the Lord God had decided from ahead of time so that they could live continually with Him. Then they all believed in the Lord Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata tasiar dari mulu pi mulu di itu da'era samua.<bt>The Lord God's Words spread from mouth to mouth in all that area.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Di itu kota, ada orang-orang bésar, laki-laki deng parampuan. Ada saparu yang rindu sang Tuhan. Ma orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong datang ko tusu-tusu sang itu orang bésar dong, sampe dong usir kasi kaluar Paulus deng Barnabas dari dong pung da'era.<bt>In that city, there were big(=important) people, male and female. There were some who longed for the Lord. But the Yahudi people's bosses came to persuade those big people, to the point that they expel Paulus and Barnabas from their region.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="asut = hasut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">asut = hasut</Message></Annotation><v n="51" />Kaluar dari itu kota, ju dong dua bekin satu acara adat deng kabás buang abu dari dong pung kaki ko jadi tanda bilang, orang di itu kota dong sonde mau dengar sang dong dua. Ais dong bale balakang ko jalan kasi tenga itu kota. Ju dong pi satu kota laen, nama Ikonium.<bt>Leaving that city, then the two of them did a tradional ceremony by brushing off dust from their feet to become a sigh saying, people in that city did not want to hear them two. So they turned their back to go leaving behind that city. And they went to another city, named Ikonium.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kabás = gosok buang, brush off,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kabás = gosok buang, brush off, lf Inst = lenso, tangan (front or back)</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:51" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:14, Markus 6:11, Lukas 9:5, 10:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="52" />Ma orang-orang yang su parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus di Antiokia, dong pung hati sanáng, tagal Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi kasi kuat dong pung hati.<bt>But the people who had believed in the Lord Yesus in Antiokia, their livers were happy, because the Holy Spirit strengthened/encouraged their livers.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus deng Barnabas di kota Ikonium<bt>Paulus and Barnabas in Ikonium city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="14" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu Paulus deng Barnabas sampe di kota Ikonium, ju dong maso pi orang Yahudi pung ruma sambayang. Di situ, dong omong panjang lebar Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae, sampe banya orang Yahudi deng banya orang dari suku-bangsa laen ju, parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus.<bt>When Paulus and Barnabas arrived at Ikonium city, then they entered the Yahudi people's worship house. There, they spoke long wide (=for along time, in great depth) about the Lord God's Good News, unti many Yahudi people and also many people of other ethnic groups also, believed in the Lord Yesus.</bt><v n="2" />Ma di situ, ada barapa orang Yahudi yang fanatik, yang sonde mau tarima Paulus dong pung omong. Ais dong tusu-tusu orang laen dong ko dong binci mau mati sang orang-orang yang parcaya sang Yesus.<bt>But there, there were several fanatic Yahudi people, who did not want to accept Paulus' talk. So they persuaded other people for them to really-really hate those people who believed in Yesus.</bt><v n="3" />Ma Paulus dong sonde taku. Dong kasi tau tarús Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae kasi sapa sa. Dong kasi tau bilang, Tuhan Yesus pung hati tabuka kasi samua orang. Dia ju ada kasi kuasa ko dong bisa bekin tanda heran macam-macam, ko biar orang banya dong tau bilang, Tuhan ada pake sang dong.<bt>But Paulus (collective) weren't afraid. They continued to explain the Lord Yesus' Good Story to whom ever. They explained saying, the Lord Yesus' liver was open to all people. He also gave power so that they could do all.kinds.of miracles, so that many people knew that the Lord was using them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu waktu, Paulus dong tenga lama di itu kota.<bt>At that time, Paulus (collective) stayed for a long time at that city.</bt><v n="4" />Ais ada muncul dua kalompok di itu kota. Yang satu iko deng orang Yahudi yang fanatik; deng yang satu lai bela mati deng Tuhan pung utusan dong. Itu dua kalompok dong bakanjar tarús.<bt>There two groups appeared/developed in that city. The one followed the fanatic Yahudi people; and the other totally defended the Lord's apostles. Those two groups were argueing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ais ada barapa orang Yahudi yang fanatik dong basakongkol deng orang laen dong, deng dong pung bos-bos ju, ko bekin susa sang Tuhan pung utusan dong. Dong ju mau lempar Paulus dong deng batu.<bt>Then several Yahudi people who were fanatic were in agreement with other people, and also with their bosses, to make difficulty to the Lord's apostles. They also wanted to throw stones at Paulus (collective).</bt><v n="6" />Ma ada orang yang kasi tau sang Paulus dong bilang, ada kalompok yang mau bekin jahat sang dong. Ju dong lari pi cari salamat di propinsi Likonia, di kota Listra deng kota Derbe, deng kampong-kampong yang badeka di situ.<bt>But there was a person who told Paulus (collective), saying there was a group who wanted to do something bad to them. So they fled seeking safety in the provinse of Likonia, in the city of Listra and the city of Derbe, and in the villages surrounding there.</bt><v n="7" />Di situ dong ju bacarita Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae.<bt>There they also told/narrated the Good Story of the Lord Yesus.</bt></p>
    <fig path="maps\Bible\HkDerbe.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Jalan dari Perga pi Derbe<bt>The road from Perga to Derbe</bt></fig>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus dong di kota Listra deng Derbe<bt>Paulus them in the city of Listra and Derbe</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Sampe di kota Listra, Paulus deng Barnabas dapa katumu satu laki-laki. Dia pung kaki dua-dua lumpu, mulai dari dia pung mama barana sang dia. Jadi dia balóm parná jalan.<bt>Arriving at Listra city, Paulus and Barnabas met a male. Both his feet were crippled, starting from when his mama gave birth to him. So he had not yet ever walked.</bt><v n="9" />Itu orang ada dudu ko dengar Paulus pung carita. Ais Paulus taro mata sang dia, deng pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang pung parcaya bisa bekin bae sang dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>That person was sitting to hear Paulus' story. Then Paulus put his eyes on him, and thought saying, “This person's belief can heal him!”</bt><v n="10" />Ju Paulus pange sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu! Badiri suda!&gt;&gt; Dengar bagitu, ju itu orang malompa bangun memang, ju dia mulai bajalan.<bt>Then Paulus called him saying, “Elder.brother! Stand up!” Hearing that, then that person jumped up straight away, and he began to walk.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02118b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Paulus bekin bae orang lumpu<bt>Paulus heals a crippled person</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Waktu orang dong dapa lia Paulus bekin bagitu, ju dong samua tanganga. Ju dong omong pake dong pung bahasa Likonia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dengar dolu! Ini orang dua ni, dewa-dewa yang turun datang di bumi pake manusia pung badan!&gt;&gt;<bt>When the people saw Paulus do like that, then they were all amazed. And they spoke using their Likonia language saying, “You listen(mild imp.)! These two people here, are gods who have come down to earth using human's bodies!”</bt><v n="12" />Itu orang dong omong bagitu, tagal dong kira Barnabas tu, sama deng dong pung dewa satu, nama Seus. Ais Paulus, yang tukang omong, dong kira dia tu, dewa Hermes.<bt>Those Yunani people spoke like that, because they thought that that Barnabas, the same as one of their gods, named Seus. And Paulus, who was the habitual speaker, they thought that he, was the god Hermes.</bt><note reference="14:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Iko dong pung parcaya, Hermes tu, tukang bawa pasán antara dewa-dewa dong.<bt>According to their beliefs, that Hermes was a messenger among/between the gods.</bt></note><v n="13" />Di luar kota pung pintu maso, ada ruma songgo satu, kasi dong pung dewa Seus. Lia Paulus dong, Seus pung tukang songgo bawa bunga-bunga deng hela bawa barapa sapi laki bésar, ko mau songgo sang dong. Ju orang banya iko itu tukang songgo ko pi songgo sang Tuhan Yesus pung utusan dong.<bt>Outside that city's main gate, there was a [traditional] worship house, for their god Seus. Seeing Paulus them, Seus' [traditional] worship practitioners pulled &amp; brought several big male cows (=bulls), and flowers in order to [traditional] worship them. And many people followed those [traditional] worship practitioners to go [traditonal] worship the Lord Yesus'</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukang songgo bawa sosonggo ko pi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tukang songgo bawa sosonggo ko pi songgo di ruma songgo. ; taro hati = rasa kasian</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02119b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none">Orang dong mau songgo sang Paulus dong<bt>People want to traditional.worship Paulus (them)</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma waktu dong dapa tau bilang, itu orang dong mau songgo sang dong, ju Paulus deng Barnabas protes sang dong. Ais dong lari pi itu orang banya dong pung muka, tarús dong ru'i kasi tarobe dong pung baju sandiri ko bekin tanda bilang, dong sonde satuju deng apa yang orang dong mau bekin. Ais dong dua batarea bilang,<bt>But when they found out that those people wanted to [traditional]worship them, then Paulus and Barnabas protested to them. Then they ran in front of those many people, then they grapped and ripped their own clothers to make a sign that they did not agree with what the people wanted to do. Then the two of them yelled saying,</bt><v n="15" />&lt;&lt;Aduuu! Akurang ko bosong bekin bagini? Jang kira kata, botong ni, dewa. Botong ni, manusia biasa, sama ke bosong ju. Botong datang di sini ko kasi tau sang bosong satu carita yang bae. Bosong musti bale balakang kasi tenga bosong pung dewa dong yang sonde ada pung guna apa-apa. Bosong musti bale iko sang Tuhan Allah yang batúl-batúl idop. Te Dia tu, yang bekin ini langit deng bumi, deng dong pung isi samua.<bt>Oh no! Why are you doing like this? Don't think that we here, are gods. We here, are also normal humans, just like you. We came here to tell you a good story. You must turn your backs &amp; leave behind your gods which do not have any use. You must turn &amp; follow the Lord God who truly lives. Cuz (elaboration) He, [He's the one] who made this sky, earth, sea, and all their contents.</bt><note reference="14:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:11, Lagu Puji dong 146:6</note><v n="16" />Dari dolu, suku-bangsa dong idop iko dong pung mau sandiri-sandiri. Tuhan Allah ju kasi biar sang dong bagitu.<bt>From before, the ethnic groups lived each following their own will/desires. The Lord God also allowed them like that.</bt><v n="17" />Ma Tuhan sonde lupa kasi tanda macam-macam, ko samua suku-bangsa dapa tau bilang, Tuhan tu, bae. Dia yang kirim ujan kasi sang kotong. Dia yang kasi kotong pung kabón dong pung hasil bae. Dia yang kasi makan sang kotong, deng bekin kotong samua pung hati sanáng.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the Lord did not forget to give many.kinds.of signs, so that all the ethnic groups would know that, that Lord, is good. He [is the one] who sends rain to us-inc. He [is the one] who gives us gardens and good harvest. He [is the one] who gives foot to us, and makes all of our livers happy.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Biar Paulus deng Barnabas su larang sang dong ko jang bekin bagitu, ma itu orang dong mati-mati ko mau bawa itu sosonggo kasi sang dong.<bt>Even though Paulus and Barnabas had forbade them to not do like that, but those people kept insisting on trying to bring that sacrifice to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nekat = nekad, paksa; paksa-paksa ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">nekat = nekad, paksa; paksa-paksa = insist</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Itu waktu, ada barapa orang Yahudi yang datang dari kota Antiokia deng kota Ikonium pi kota Listra. Dong tusu-tusu itu orang banya dong ko iko malawan sang Tuhan Yesus pung utusan dong. Ju dong lempar sang Paulus deng batu. Dong kira dia su mati, ais dong hela bawa sang dia ko buang sang dia pi luar kota.<bt>At that time, there were several Yahudi people who came from Antiokia city and Ikonium city to go to Listra city. They persuade those many people to follow them in opposing the Lord Yesus' apostles. And they threw stones at Paulua. They thought he was dead, then they pulled &amp; brought him to throw him outside the city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kipas-kipas = incite, fan the flames"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kipas-kipas = incite, fan the flames (of anger), but tusu-tusu preferred by UNS's; kira takes kata as a complementiser</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02156b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11cm;textWrapping:none">Dong lempar Paulus deng batu, sampe dia jato<bt>They throw stones at Paulus, then leave him</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma waktu Yesus pung orang parcaya dong badiri kuliling sang Paulus, ju dia bangun. Ais ju dia maso kambali pi dalam kota. Dia pung beso, ju dia deng Barnabas jalan sama-sama pi kota laen, nama Derbe.<bt>But when Yesus' believers stood around Paulus, then he got.up. And then he entered again into the city. The next day, then he and Barnabas traveled together to another city, named Derbe.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus deng Barnabas kambali pi jama'at di kota Antiokia di propinsi Siria<bt>Paulus and Barnabas return to the congregations in Antiokia city in Siria province</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Di Derbe, Paulus deng Barnabas kasi tau Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae. Ais itu, banya orang parcaya sang Dia. Tarús dong dua pi ulang di Listra. Dari sana, dong kambali pi Ikonium. Dari situ, dong jalan tarús pi Antiokia di propinsi Pisidia.<bt>In Derbe, Paulus and Barnabas explained the Lord Yesus' Good Story. After that, many people believed in Him. Next the two of them returned again to Listra. From there, they returned to Ikonium. From there, they traveled on to Antiokia in Pisidia province.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kambali ulang = backtrack; seret ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kambali ulang = backtrack; seret = 1) hela, pull, drag, 2) sideswipe, serempet</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Di situ, dong omong deng orang yang iko sang Yesus ko kasi kuat dong pung hati. Dong kasi inga bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong samua! Kalo kotong maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang, jang pikir kata, kotong sonde dapa susa lai. Te biar karmana ju, kotong musti dapa susa. Ma kotong musti batahan, ko iko tarús sang Yesus.&gt;&gt; Dong dua ajar bagitu sang Yesus pung orang dong di itu kota.<bt>There, they spoke with the people who followed Yesus in order to stregthen their livers (encourage them). They reminded/warned saying, “Siblings! If we enter &amp; become the Lord God's people, don't think that we won't get difficulty anymore. Cuz (elaboration) no matter how, we-inc will get difficulty, but we must endure, to follow continually Yesus.” The two of them taught like that to Yesus' people in that city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais ju Paulus deng Barnabas mulai cari orang ko dong angka jadi pimpinan<bt>Because the people who followed Yesus were many, that's.why Paulus and Barnabas began to look for people for them to raise up to become the leaders</bt><note reference="14:23" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Jama'at pung pimpinan di ini ayat, dalam bahasa Yunani bilang, <span class="Italic">presbuteros</span>.<bt>The congregation's leader in this verse, in Yunani language says, <span class="Italic">presbuteros</span>.</bt></note>di jama'at satu-satu. Dong sambayang deng puasa ko cari Tuhan pung mau. Ju dong taro tangan deng sambayang, ko angka itu orang yang Tuhan su kasi tunju, ko jadi jama'at pung pimpinan.<bt>of each congregation. They prayed and fasted to find the Lord's will. And they laid hands and prayed, to raise that person/people whom the Lord had choose, to become the congregation's leader.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pentua ~ penatua = GMIT/PGI version"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pentua ~ penatua = GMIT/PGI version of 'elder', carries baggage;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ais itu, ju Paulus deng Barnabas jalan tarús kasi tenga propinsi Pisidia, ko dong pi propinsi Pamfilia.<bt>After that, then Paulus and Barnabas travelled on leaving Pisidia province, in order for them to go to Pamfilia province.</bt><v n="25" />Dong sampe di satu kota, nama Perga. Di situ, dong kasi tau Tuhan pung Carita Bae. Ais itu, dong jalan tarús, sonde jao lai, ju dong sampe di kota Atalia.<bt>They arrived at a city, named Perga. There, they told the Lord's Good Story. After that, they travelled on, not much further, and they arrived at Atalia city.</bt><v n="26" />Di situ, dong nae kapal ko balayar kambali pi kota Antiokia di propinsi Siria. Tempo hari, Tuhan Yesus pung orang di Antiokia tu, yang utus sang dong, deng sarakan sang dong pi Tuhan pung tangan ko Dia lia bae-bae sang dong. Jadi sakarang Paulus dong mau pulang, ko lapor kasi jama'at Antiokia dong bilang, dong su bekin abis dong pung karjá.<bt>There, they embarked on a ship to sail returning to Antiokia city in Siria province. Earlier, the people of the Lord Yesus in that Antiokia, [were the ones] who commissioned them, and handed them over to the Lord's hand for Him to look after them well. So (consequently) now Paulus (coll) wanted to go home, to report to the Antiokia congregations, that they had finished their work.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01958b.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Kapal layar dari jaman Roma<bt>Sail boat/ship from the Roma era</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Sampe di Antiokia, ju Paulus dong kumpul ame Tuhan pung orang samua yang ada di situ. Ais dong carita panjang lebar samua yang Tuhan su bekin kasi sang dong. Bilang, Tuhan su buka jalan ko orang yang bukan Yahudi dong ju parcaya sang Yesus.<bt>Arriving in Antiokia, then Paulus them gathered together all the Lord's people there. Then they told long wide all that the Lord had done for them. That the Lord had opened the path for people who are not Yahudi to believe in Yesus.</bt><v n="28" />Ais ju Paulus deng Barnabas tenga lama deng Tuhan Yesus pung orang parcaya dong di situ.<bt>Then Paulus and Barnabas stayed a long time with the Lord Yesus' believers there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tua-tua Kristen dong bakumpul di Yerusalem<bt>Kristen leaders gathers in Yerusalem</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tua-tua = leaders, pemimpin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tua-tua = leaders, pemimpin</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="15" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, barapa orang Yahudi Kristen datang jao-jao dari propinsi Yudea pi Antiokia. Sampe di situ, dong ajar Tuhan Yesus pung orang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong su parcaya sang Yesus. Itu ju bae. Ma itu balóm cukup. Kalo bosong mau batúl-batúl salamat, na, bosong ju musti sunat, iko botong pung adat, yang Tuhan sandiri su kasi lewat ba'i Musa.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, several Yahudi Kristen people came from far away Yudea province to Antiokia. Arriving there, they taught the Lord Yesus people saying, “You have believed in Yesus. That is good. But it's not enough. If you want to really-really be saved, na, you must be circumcised, according to our custom, which the Lord himself gave via/by Gf/Ff Musa.”</bt><note reference="15:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 12:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ma Paulus deng Barnabas bamalawan karás deng itu orang dong pung omong. Dong bakanjar satenga mati. Ju Paulus dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sala! Suku-bangsa laen yang bukan Yahudi, yang parcaya sang Yesus sonde parlú iko orang Yahudi pung adat sunat!&gt;&gt; Tagal dong bamalawan bagitu, ju dong ba'akór ko utus sang Paulus deng Barnabas, deng barapa tamán laen dari Antiokia, ko pi bawa ini so'al kasi sang Tuhan pung utusan dong, deng tua-tua Kristen laen di Yerusalem.<bt>But Paulus and Barnabas strongly opposed those people's talk. They argued intensely. And Paulus them said, “You're wrong! The other ethnic groups who are not Yahudi, who believe in Yesus do not need to follow the Yahudi people's circumcision ritual/custom!” Because they were in opposition like that, then they agreed to send/commission Paulus and Barnabas, and several other friends from Antiokia, to go bring that problem to the Lord's apostles, and other Kristen leaders in Yerusalem.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Tagal itu, orang Kristen di Antiokia suru Paulus dong pi Yerusalem. Dong iko jalan darat, lewat propinsi Fenisia deng propinsi Samaria. Di dong pung jalan tu, dong singga-singga di orang parcaya dong pung ruma. Ais dong carita sampe alus-alus bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang bukan Yahudi dong, ju su bale datang ko parcaya sang Tuhan!&gt;&gt; Dengar bagitu, ju samua orang sanáng.<bt>Because of that, they ordered Paulus them to go to Yerusalem. They went on by land, passing through Fenisia province and Samaria province. On that trip of theirs, they stopped alon the way in believer's houses. Then they told in great detail saying, “People who are not Yahudi, have also converted (lit. turned to come) and believe in the Lord!” Hearing like that, then all the people were happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bale datang = convert (religion)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bale datang = convert (religion)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Sampe di Yerusalem, Yesus pung orang samua tarima sang dong deng bae-bae. Tuhan pung utusan dong, deng tua-tua Kristen dong, ju tarima sang dong. Ais ju Paulus dong carita samua yang Tuhan su bekin kasi sang dong, sampe banya orang laen ju su iko sang Tuhan Yesus. Deng dong ju carita dong pung bakanjar so'al sunat.<bt>Arriving in Yerusalem, all of the Yesus' people received them well. The Lord's apostles, and the Kristen leaders, also received them. Then Paulus them told all that which the Lord had done for them, until many other people also followed the Lord Yesus. And they also told their argument about circumcision.</bt><v n="5" />Itu orang yang iko dengar sang Paulus dong pung carita, ada barapa orang Yahudi Kristen dari partei Farisi. Dong bangun badiri, ais dong omong karás-karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae, é! Kalo ada orang bukan Yahudi mana sa, yang mau iko sang Yesus, dong musti iko kotong pung adat sunat deng kotong pung atoran adat laen, yang Tuhan Allah sandiri su kasi turun lewat ba'i Musa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Those people who went to hear Paulus them's story, there were several Yahudi Kristen people from the Farisi party. They stood up, then they spoke sternly saying, “Listen well! If there is a person who is not Yahudi in any place, who wants to follow Yesus, they must following our circumcision ritual, which the Lord God himself sent down via Gf/Ff Musa.”</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01974b.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Petrus<bt>Petrus</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais orang sarani samua ba'akór ko Tuhan pung utusan dong, deng tua-tua Kristen dong, bakumpul ko timbang-timbang itu hal.<bt>Then the baptised people were all in agreement that the Lord's apostles, and the Kristen leaders, gather to weigh/judge that matter. [EXEG: on “all”. This is about agreeing on a PROCESS to decide the matter. Context of vs. 4 (all-encompassing categories: congregation, apostles, elders), and NLT ‘whole church’; implied by CEV ‘including’; this “all” here is deliberate to get the picture of the social dynamics set up about their reception and support. Not addition. Vs. 22 adjusted to clarify the support of the decision was also by “all”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ais dong batukar pikiran panjang lebar. Ahirnya, ju Petrus bangun badiri ko omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong samua! Bosong sandiri tau bilang, dolu Tuhan su tunju sang beta dari bosong pung teng-tenga, ko beta pi kasi tau Yesus pung Carita Bae sang orang bukan Yahudi dong. Te Tuhan ju mau ko dong parcaya sang Yesus.<bt>So they exchanged thinking long and wide. Finally, then Petrus stood up to talk saying, “Siblings! You yourselves know that, beforehand, the Lord appointed me from your midst, for me to go tell Yesus Good Story to the people who are not Yahudi. Cuz (elaboration) the Lord also wills, that they believe in Yesus.</bt><note reference="15:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 10:1-43</note><v n="8" />Tuhan kanál kotong manusia satu-satu pung hati. Deng Dia yang kasi Dia pung Roh yang Barisi sang dong, sama ke Dia su kasi sang kotong. Deng bagitu, kotong tau bilang, Tuhan ju tarima sang dong.<bt>The Lord knows each of us human's livers. And He [is the one] who gave His Holy Spirit to them, just like He gave it to us. And with.that, we know that the Lord also accepts them.</bt><note reference="15:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 2:4, 10:44</note><v n="9" />Te Tuhan Allah sonde bapili-pili muka, dong deng kotong. Dia sonde bekin beda sang dong dari kotong. Te Dia su bekin barisi dong pung hati, tagal dong ju su parcaya sang Yesus, sama ke Dia ju bekin barisi kotong pung hati.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the Lord God does not discriminate, them versus us. He doesn't differentiate between them and us. Cuz (elaboration) He has made their livers *clean/holy, because they also have believed in Yesus, just like He also made clean/holy our livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde bekin sang dong laen, deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sonde bekin sang dong laen, deng kotong laen; carita alus-alus = tell slowly, pelan-pelan; carita sampe alus-alus = tell in detail</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10-11" />Naa, karmana? Kalo Tuhan su tarima sang dong, akurang ko kotong masi mau mua tamba lai, ko bekin barát sang dong deng ini adat sunat? Padahal, kalo mau omong jujur, kotong deng kotong pung nene-moyang dong, sonde mampu pikol kotong pung atoran agama samua! Jadi kotong jang paksa sang dong bagitu! Beta mau tanya bagini: Tuhan kasi salamat sang kotong, tagal kotong iko atoran agama, ko? Sonde, to! Dia kasi salamat, tagal Tuhan Yesus sayang deng hati bae sang kotong. Naa, jang lupa! Tuhan ju sayang deng hati bae sang orang laen bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa, how about it? If the Lord has accepted them why do we-inc still want to bear/carry even more to make them heavy/burdened with this circumcision ritual of ours? Even though, if [we] speak honestly, we, and our ancestors, are not capable of shoulder.carrying all of our religious rules. So (consequently) we should force them like that! I want to ask you like this: The Lord saves us, because we follow religious rules, right? Of course not! He gives salvation, because the Lord Yesus very much loves and has *grace/goodness/kindness/ generosity on us. Naa, don't forget! The Lord also loves and has *grace/goodness/kindness/generosity on other people like that.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sayang deng kasian = kasih karunia,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sayang deng kasian = kasih karunia, grace</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dengar bagitu ju, sonde ada orang yang mau batamba pikiran lai.<bt>Hearing that, then there was no person who wanted to add any more thinking.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ia bae = rubberstamp s.t."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ia bae = rubberstamp s.t.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais itu, Paulus deng Barnabas carita ulang lai, karmana Tuhan su pake sang dong. Dong carita itu tanda-tanda heran, deng hal luar biasa yang Tuhan Allah su bekin di teng-tenga suku-bangsa bukan Yahudi dong.<bt>After that, Paulus and Barnabas told again, how the Lord has used them. They told those miracles and extraordinary things, which the Lord God did in the midst of the ethnic groups who are not Yahudi.</bt><v n="13" />Carita abis, ju satu orang, nama Yakobis, bangun badiri ko omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong! Bosong dengar sang beta dolu!<bt>Finishing talking, then a person, named Yakobis, stood up to talk saying, “Siblings! You-pl listen to me (mild imp)!</bt><v n="14" />Bu Pe'u<bt>Elder.brother Pe'u</bt><note reference="15:14" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani ada tulis bilang, &lt;Simeon&gt;. Simeon deng Simon tu, sama. Simeon/Simon tu, andia Petrus pung nama laen<bt>The Yunani language writings write saying ‘Simeon’. Simeon and Simon are the same. That Simeon/Simon is Petrus' other name.</bt></note>baru carita abis kasi sang kotong bilang, Tuhan Allah su angka ame orang bukan Yahudi dong, ko kasi maso sang dong jadi Tuhan Yesus pung kelu.<bt>has just finished telling us, saying the Lord God ahs raised up people who are not Yahudi, to cuz (elaboration) them to enter to become the Lord Yesus' family.</bt><v n="15" />Naa, itu ju pas deng apa yang Tuhan pung jubir dong su kasi tau memang dari dolu. Te dong su tulis bilang:<bt>Naa, [+shift] that also matches with what the Lord's spokesperson told ahead of time from before. Cuz (elaboration) they wrote, saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="16" />&lt;Pas dia pung waktu, Beta kambali.<bt>'Exactly at the right time, I will return.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lama-lama beta pukul = lama-lama has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lama-lama beta pukul = lama-lama has sense of warning "watch out or else..." but not certainty that it will happen</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal Beta mau kasi bangun ulang raja Daud pung parenta.<bt>Because I want to build (make stand) again raja Daud's authority.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te dia pung turunan yang su ancor-ancor tu,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) those descendants of his are destroyed,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta mau kasi bangun ulang, deng bekin kuat sang dia lai.<bt>I want to build again, and strengthen him again.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17-18" />Deng bekin bagitu, orang-orang dari suku-bangsa laen ju datang cari ko katumu deng Beta.<bt>In doing that, people from other ethnic groups will also come looking to meet Me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Beta ju su pili ame sang dong, ko jadi Beta pung orang.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I have chosen them, to become My people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ko Tuhan Allah su omong bagitu dari dolu na!&gt;<bt>Because the Lord God has obviously spoken like that from before!’</bt><note reference="15:16-18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Amos 9:11-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19-20" />Jadi dari beta, Yakobis, bagini: kalo orang dari suku-bangsa laen mau maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang, kotong orang Yahudi jang bekin susa sang dong. Kotong jang bekin barát sang dong, deng suru ko iko kotong pung adat sunat. Jadi kotong musti tulis satu surat, ko kirim kasi sang dong bilang, dong sonde usa iko kotong pung atoran adat Yahudi samua. Kotong ju kasi inga sang dong bilang, dong jang maen serong deng orang yang bukan dong pung laki ko dong pung bini. Dong sonde bole makan daging sosonggo. Dong sonde bole makan binatang pung dara. Deng dong ju sonde bole makan daging binatang yang mati taceke yang dia pung dara sonde malele kaluar.<bt>So according to me, Yakobis, it's like this: if people from other ethnic groups want to enter &amp; follow the Lord God, we Yahudi people should not cuz (elaboration) difficulty to them. We shouldn't burden them and order them to follow our circumcision ritual. So (consequently) we must write a letter, to send to them saying, they do not need to follow all our traditional Yahudi regulations. We also remind them saying, they should not play off-track (sexually) with a person who is not their husband or wife. They should not eat idol meat. They should not eat animal blood. And they should not eat the meat of animals killed by choking, with result that the blood hasn't flowed out. [EXEG: Bruce, TRT, TH point out that this explication is the real point for Jewish theology. Also 15:29 and 21:25.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bakebo = ; idop serong ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bakebo = ; idop serong = Idiom jalan balakang, take a back road, meaning berzinah, adultery, extramarrital relations' maen salingku = ( ; homoseks, lesi-lesi dong--BI slang); daging mudik = traditional sausage, blood mixed with spices, no meat; binatang mati taceke = strangled, tercekik; jang maen serong deng laki-laki ko parampuan = UNS, implies one is married, but can't offer anything broader or more generic, all other possibilities considered are narrower.; UNS's at consultant check all say can be either married or unmarried</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 34:15-17, Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 17:10-16, 18:6-23</note><v n="21" />Naa, kalo kotong taro atoran bagini, ini bukan hal baru lai. Te banya orang su tau kotong orang Yahudi pung adat memang su bagitu. Tagal itu atoran dari ba'i Musa dong, kotong baca di samua ruma sambayang tiap hari barenti karjá di mana-mana sa. Jadi banya orang suku-bangsa laen dong su tau. Naa, beta pung omong bagitu sa. Makasi!&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa, [+shift] if we put these regulations like that, this not anything new. Cuz (elaboration) many people already know, our Yahudi custom is actually like that. Because those regulations are from Gf/Ff Musa them, we read them in all the worship houses, every day of stopping work, in every place. So many people from other ethnic groups already know. Naa, my talking is just like that. Thanks!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Surat kasi orang parcaya dari suku-bangsa bukan Yahudi<bt>Letter to the people from non-Yahudi ethnic groups who believe</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais itu, Tuhan pung utusan deng tua-tua yang laen dong, ba'akór deng samua orang sarani di Yerusalem ko mau kirim orang ko pi kasi tau dong pung putusan sang orang sarani di mana-mana. Ju dong cari orang yang jama'at dong hormat, yang cocok deng itu tugas. Ais dong pili ame dua orang. Satu pung nama Silas, deng yang satu lai, nama Yudas (yang dong ju pange bilang, Barsabas). Tarús dong suru ko dong dua pi sama-sama deng Paulus deng Barnabas.<bt>After that, the Lord's apostles and other leaders, were in one accord with all the Christians in Yerusalem to send people to go tell their decision to the baptised people in many places. And they look from people whom the congregations respected, who matched this task. Then they chose two people. One's name Silas, and the other, name Yudas (whom they also call saying, Barsabas). Then2 they order these two to go together with Paulus and Barnabas. [EXEG: NRSV “with the consent of the whole church” clarified from earlier version. “in Yerusalem” from context and NLT] [EXEG &amp; RL DISCOURSE: Antioch (specific) subordinated in vs.22 to higher context level purpose of a general message to all believers in several provinces. Antioch still explicit in vs.23 &amp; 30.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pandang hormat = KM? *** (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pandang hormat = KM? *** (2009) added “ba'akór deng samua orang sarani di Yerusalem ko mau...” in 1st sentence ; note added on Antioch</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Dong bawa surat ko kasi orang dari suku-bangsa laen di kota Antiokia, di propinsi Siria, sampe jao di propinsi Kilikia. Itu surat pung bunyi bagini:<bt>They brought a letter to give to people from other ethnic groups in Antiokia city, in Siria province, all the way to Kilikia province. That letter's sound was like this: [NOTE: while some translations put the locations in the body of the letter, the structure above fits well with both the RL and the Gk.; NOTE: in the Gk it is not ‘Antioch of Syria’, but Antioch and /kai/ Syria, and /kai/ Cilicia.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="surat pung bunyi / surat pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">surat pung bunyi / surat pung isi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Salam manis dari botong, Tuhan Yesus pung utusan, deng tua-tua Kristen laen di sini di kota Yerusalem. Botong tulis ini surat kasi sang bosong, yang botong sayang sama ke sodara sandiri.<bt>"Sweet greetings from us, the Lord Yesus' apostles, and other leaders here in Yerusalem city. We-exc are writing this letter to you, whom we love like our own siblings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tabea &gt; kirim tabe(k) &gt; salam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tabea &gt; kirim tabe(k) &gt; salam (former archaic, kuno)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="24" />Botong tulis ini surat, tagal botong ada dengar bilang, ada barapa orang dari Yerusalem sini yang su pi katumu deng bosong di sana. Dong ada ajar sambarang, sampe bekin susa deng bekin bingung sang bosong. Asal bosong tau sa, botong sonde parná utus itu orang dong.<bt>We write this letter, because we are hearing that, there are several people from Yerusalem here who have gone to meet with you there. They are teaching groundlessly, to the point that they are causing you difficulty and making you confused. As long as you just know, we have never commissioned those people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="balisa = feeling one is nearly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">balisa = feeling one is nearly dead, about to die</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Waktu botong su dengar bilang, ada orang yang bekin susa sang bosong bagitu, botong bakumpul di sini ko timbang itu hal. Naa, botong su ba'akór, deng su putus abis itu hal. Jadi sakarang botong su pili ame orang ko pi kasi tau sang bosong, botong pung putusan. Dong ada datang sama-sama deng Barnabas deng Paulus, yang botong sayang.<bt>When we heard that there were people causing you difficulty, we gathered here to weigh the matter. Naa, we are in one accord, and have decided the matter. So (consequently) now we have chosen people to come tell you, that decision of ours. They are coming with Barnabas and Paulus, whom we-exc love.</bt><v n="26" />Te kotong pung dua orang tu, dong su pikol sangsara sampe amper mati. Dong dapa sangsara bagitu, tagal dong iko kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) those two people of ours, they have shoulder carried tribulation until they were almost dead. They got tribulation like that, because they follow our Bos Yesus Kristus.</bt><v n="27" />Jadi botong utus sang Yudas deng Silas, ko biar dong kasi tau sang bosong ini surat pung isi.<bt>So we commissioned Yudas and Silas, so that they tell you, this letter's contents.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="28" />Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi su kasi tau sang botong, deng botong samua satuju bagitu bilang, bosong tar usa iko botong pung adat Yahudi samua, conto ke adat sunat. Te itu adat dong bekin barát parcuma sang bosong. Ma ada satu-dua hal, yang memang bosong musti inga:<bt>The Lord's Holy Spirit has told us, and we all agree like that saying, you do not need to follow all our Yahudi traditions, for example that circumcision ritual. Cuz (elaboration) those rituals/traditions needlessly burden you. But there are one-two things, which you actually must remember:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi (taputar) piong = spinning top,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kasi (taputar) piong = spinning top, gasing</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="29" />Jang maen serong deng orang yang bukan lu pung laki ko lu pung bini.<bt>Don't play off-track/deviate (sexually) with a person who is not your-sg husband or your wife.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jang makan daging sosonggo.<bt>Don't eat idol meat.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sosonggo ~ sasonggo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sosonggo ~ sasonggo</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jang makan dara.<bt>Don't eat blood.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng jang makan daging dari binatang yang mati taceke, sampe dia pung dara sonde malele kaluar.<bt>And don't eat meat from an animal that died choked, with result that its blood hasn't flowed out. [EXEG: Bruce, TRT, TH point out that this explication is the real issue for Jewish theology. Also 15:29 and 21:25.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kalo bosong jaga diri dari itu hal samua, bosong sonde bekin noju bosong pung sodara orang Yahudi Kristen dong. Deng bagitu, bosong bisa bagabung bae-bae deng dong. Botong pung surat ni, bagitu sa. Saloom.&gt;&gt;<bt>If you watch/protect yourselves from all these things, you will not gross.out/offend our Yahudi Kristen siblings. With that, you can join/interact well with them. This letter of ours, is just that. Saloom.” [EXEG: high level implicature explicated here is widely discussed in the commentaries, and is necessary to understand ‘why these issues, and not others?’]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="basundal = visit prostitute"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">basundal = visit prostitute</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Dong tarima ame itu surat abis, ju Paulus dong togor, tarús dong jalan pi kota Antiokia. Sampe di sana, dong kumpul ame samua orang sarani dong, ju dong kasi itu surat.<bt>They finished recieving that letter, then Paulus them took their leave, and then went on to Antiokia city. Arriving there, they gathered all the baptised people, and they gave [them] that letter.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="minta diri = minta pamit ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">minta diri = minta pamit = togor 1) scold, 2) greet 3) take one's leave</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Waktu dong baca abis itu surat, itu orang dong samua sanáng, tagal itu surat pung isi su kasi kuat dong pung hati.<bt>When they finished reading that letter, all those people were happy, because that letter's contents strengthened/encouraged their livers.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Yudas deng Silas ju jadi Tuhan pung jubir. Dong dua tu, bacarita bam-banya deng orang parcaya di itu kota. Dong kasi nasiat deng kasi kuat itu orang dong pung hati.<bt>Yudas and Silas were also God2's *spokespersons. The two of them, told many many things to the believers in that city. They gave them advice and strengthened/encouraged those people's livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yudas deng Silas, ju Tuhan pake"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Yudas deng Silas, ju Tuhan pake sang dong, jadi Dia pung jubir.</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Waktu dong dua su tenga di situ sadiki lama, ju orang sarani di Antiokia kasi loos ko dong pulang kambali pi orang yang su utus sang dong. Dong lapás sang dong dua deng salamat.<bt>When the two of them had stayed in that city a little while, then the baptised people in Antiokia gave permission for them to return home to the the people who had commissioned them. They let the two of them go in peace/well-being.</bt><v n="34" />[Ma Silas mau tenga tarús di Antiokia sa.]<bt>[But Silas want to just continue staying in Antiokia.]</bt><note reference="15:34" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu sonde mua ini ayat 34.<bt>Some Yunani writings do not carry this verse 34.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Paulus deng Barnabas tenga barapa lama di situ. Dong ju tolong orang laen yang ada ajar Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop.<bt>Paulus and Barnabas stayed there a bit. They also help the other people who were teaching the Lord Yesus' Life Path.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus deng Barnabas bapisa jalan<bt>Paulus and Barnabas go separate ways</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Waktu Paulus deng Barnabas su tenga sadiki lama di Antiokia, ju Paulus omong sang Barnabas bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu! Mari ko kotong pi kambali di samua tampa yang dolu kotong parná singga. Kotong pi lia coba kotong pung sodara dong pung idop. Dong tu, su karmana, é? Te ini orang dong balóm lama parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus. Tempo hari tu, kotong su mulai ajar sang dong. Jadi mari ko kotong pi lia sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Paulus and Barnabas has stayed a bit in Antiokia, then Paulus spoke to Barnabas saying, “Elder brother! Let's go return to all those places which we visited before. We can go see/look.after our siblings' life. How are they all doing? Cuz (elaboration) these people, haven't believed Yesus long yet. Earlier, we began to teach them. So (consequently), let's go see/check up on them.”</bt><v n="37" />Dengar Paulus minta bagitu, ju Barnabas ia bae sa.<bt>Hearing Paulus' request like that, then Barnabas conceeded.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa, Barnabas mau bawa sang Yohanis ko iko deng dong. (Dong ju pange sang Yohanis ni bilang, Markus).<bt>Naa, [+shift topic] Barbabas wanted to bring Yohanis to go with them. (They also called this Yohanis, Markus). [DISCOURSE: para added 2014 for RL shift in topic.]</bt><v n="38" />Ma Paulus sonde mau. Tagal tempo hari di propinsi Pamfilia, Markus bangun jalan kasi tenga sang dong.<bt>But Paulus did not want to. Because earlier, in Pamfilia province, Markus had just got up and left them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bangun jalan kasi tenga = just"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bangun jalan kasi tenga = just got up and left them; @@2pairs of serial vbs</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 13:13</note><v n="39" />Paulus deng Barnabas bakanjar hebat bagitu, sampe dong dua bapisa jalan. Ju Barnabas bawa ame sang Markus, ko dong dua nae kapal pi balayar sampe di pulo Siprus.<bt>Paulus and Barnabas argued intensely like that, to the point that the two of them went separate ways. Then Barnabas took Markus, for the two of them to embark on a ship to sail to Siprus island.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Ma Paulus ame bawa sang Silas. Waktu dong mau barangkat, itu orang parcaya dong di Antiokia sambayang minta Tuhan ko jaga sang dong, deng Tuhan ju kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang dong. Sambayang abis, ju dong dua barangkat.<bt>But Paulus took Silas. When they were about to leave, those believers in Antiokia prayed asking the Lord to protect them, and the Lord also show His good liver (generosity/mercy) to them. After praying, then the two of them left.</bt><v n="41" />Ais dong pi kuliling propinsi Siria deng propinsi Kilikia. Di mana-mana dong kasi kuat orang parcaya dong pung hati.<bt>Then they went around Siria province and Kilikia province. Everywhere they strengthened encouraged the believers' livers.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Timotius bagabung deng Paulus deng Silas<bt>Timotius joins with Paulus and Silas</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="16" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Paulus dong jalan tarús ko pi lebe dolo di kota Derbe. Dari situ, dong jalan tarús pi kota Listra. Di itu kota, dong katumu satu orang muda, nama Timotius. Dia pung bapa, orang Yunani. Ma dia pung mama, parampuan Yahudi yang su parcaya sang Yesus. Timotius ju su jadi Yesus pung orang.<bt>After that, Paulus them continued on to go first to Derbe city. From there, they travelled on to Listra city. In that city, they met a young person, named Timotius. His father, was a Yunani person. But his mama, a Yahudi female who had believed in Yesus. Timotius also had become Yesus' person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kehiu (Sabu) = upset because someone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kehiu (Sabu) = upset because someone took their turn</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Samua orang parcaya di kota Listra deng kota Ikonium tau bilang, Timotius tu, orang bae.<bt>All the believers in Listra city and Ikonium city knew that that Timotius, was a good person.</bt><v n="3" />Paulus mau ko Timotius iko sang dong. Ma ada orang Yahudi di situ yang tau bilang, Timotius pung bapa orang Yunani, jadi dia tu, balóm sunat iko adat Yahudi. Tagal itu, Paulus ator ko dong sunat sang Timotius.<bt>Paulus wanted Timotius to go with them. But there were Yahudi people there, who knew that Timotius' father was a Yunani person, so he, was not yet circumcised following Yahudi tradition. Because of that, Paulus arranged that they circumcise Timotius.</bt><note reference="16:3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Paulus tau bilang, orang yang balóm sunat, sonde bole maso pi dalam orang Yahudi dong pung ruma sambayang. Kalo Timotius mau tolong sang Paulus ko kasi tau Yesus pung Carita Bae sang orang Yahudi dong, na, dia musti sunat dolo. Deng bagitu, dia bisa gampang maso-kaluar pi orang Yahudi dong pung teng-tenga.<bt>Paulus knew that people who were not yet circumcised, could not enter in the Yahudi people's worship houses. If Timotius wanted to help Paulus to tell Yesus' Good Story to the Yahudi people, na, he had to circumcised first. With that, he could easily enter &amp; exit from the midst of Yahudi people.</bt></note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02124b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Timotius deng Paulus<bt>Timotius and Paulus</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais itu, dong jalan dari satu tampa pi satu tampa, ko kasi tau itu putusan yang Tuhan Yesus pung utusan deng tua-tua Kristen dong su putus di Yerusalem.<bt>After that, they travelled from place to place, to tell that decision which the Lord Yesus' apostles and the Kristen leaders made in Yerusalem.</bt><v n="5" />Deng bagitu, dong bekin tamba kuat orang parcaya dong pung hati. Tiap hari, orang baru yang parcaya dong, tamba banya.<bt>With that, they made the believer's livers increasingly strong. Every day, new believers, increased more.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus dapa pange pi Makedonia<bt>Paulus is called to Makedonia</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais itu, Paulus dong jalan tarús. Dong pi propinsi Frigia deng propinsi Galatia, tagal Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi larang sang dong ko dong jang pi kasi tau Tuhan pung Carita Bae di propinsi Asia.<bt>After that, Paulus them travelled on. They went to Frigia province and Galatia province, because the Holy Sprit forbade them to not tell the Lord's Good Story in Asia province.</bt><v n="7" />Waktu dong sampe di satu da'era yang babatas deng propinsi Misia, dong mau coba maso pi propinsi Bitinia. Ma Yesus pung Roh larang sang dong ko jang pi sana.<bt>When they arrived in a region that shared a border with Misia province, they wanted to try to enter to go to Bitinia province, the Yesus' Spirit forbade them to not go there.</bt><note reference="16:6-7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sakarang ni, propinsi-propinsi yang dolu dong bilang Frigia, Galatia, Asia, Misia, deng Bitinia, samua ada di negara Turki.<bt>Now adays, the provinces which previously they called Frigia, Galatia, Asia, Misia, and Bitinia, are all in the country of Turki.</bt></note><v n="8" />Ais dong jalan lewat propinsi Misia, ju dong turun sampe di kota Troas di laut pung pinggir.<bt>Then they travelled via Misia province, and they descended arriving at Troas city at the edge of the sea.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Itu malam, Tuhan Allah kasi lia Paulus sama ke dalam mimpi. Dia lia satu orang badiri di laut pung sablá, di satu propinsi, nama Makedonia. Itu orang batarea minta tolong bilang, &lt;&lt;Pak! Mari sini ko tolong sang botong dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>That night, the Lord God made Paulus see like in a dream. He saw a person standing on the other side of the ocean, in a province, named Makedonia. That person yelled requesting help saying, “Mr! Come here to help us (mild imp)!”</bt><v n="10" />Paulus lia bagitu, ju botong<bt>Paulus saw like that, and we-inc</bt><note reference="16:10" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dalam ini carita, di sini mulai pake kata &lt;botong&gt;, tagal Lukas su bagabung deng Paulus dong di sini. Lukas yang tulis ini buku.<bt>In this story, here begins to use the word 'we(inc)', because Lukas had joined with Paulus them here. Lukas is the one who wrote this book.</bt></note>putus ko botong pi Makedonia. Botong pikir bilang, itu memang Tuhan Allah yang suru ko botong pi kasi tau Dia pung Jalan Idop pi orang-orang di laut pung sablá. Andia ko Dia larang sang botong ko sonde bole pi tampa laen.<bt>decided that we would go to Makedonia. We thought that that was truly the Lord God who commanded that we go tell His Life Path to the people on the other side of the sea. That's why He forbade us to not go to other places.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Di kota Filipi, mama Lidia parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>In Filipi city, mama Lidia believes in the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais ju botong nae kapal di kota Troas, ko balayar pi satu pulo kici, nama Samotrake. Dia pung beso, botong balayar tarús sampe di satu kota, nama Neapolis. Ju botong turun di situ.<bt>After that, we-exc got on a ship at Troas city, to sail to a small island, named Samotrake. The next day, we sailed on to a city, named Neapolis. Then we got off there.</bt><v n="12" />Dari situ botong jalan iko darat pi satu kota bésar, nama Filipi. (Filipi tu, kota pantíng di propinsi Makedonia; pamarenta Roma ju pegang kuasa di situ.) Botong tenga barapa hari di situ.<bt>From there we went by land to a big city, named Filipi. (That Filipi, was an important city in Makedonia province, the Roma government also held authority there.) We stayed several days there.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02127b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none">Paulus dong katumu deng mama Lidia<bt>Paulus them meeting mama Lidia</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Pas deng orang Yahudi pung hari barenti karjá, botong pi cari orang Yahudi dong pung tampa sambayang. Botong ba'itong itu tampa sambayang tantu ada di kali pung pinggir. Jadi botong jalan kaluar sadiki dari kota, sampe botong dapa satu kali. Di situ, botong katumu mama-mama barapa orang.<bt>Exactly on the Yahudi people's day of stopping work, we went to look for the Yahudi people's worship place. We reckoned that that worship place surely would be by the side of a river. So (consequently) we walked a bit out of the city, until we arrived at a river. There, we met several mamas (women).</bt><note reference="16:13" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Iko atoran, musti ada 10 laki-laki orang Yahudi, baru bisa bekin ruma sambayang. Dong sonde itong parampuan dong. Jadi, tagal ada barapa parampuan yang sambayang di kali Gangites pung pinggir, kotong dapa tau, di kota Filipi, laki-laki orang Yahudi sadiki sa.<bt>According to regulations, there had to be 10 Yahudi men, only then could they make a house of prayer/worship. They didn't count women. So (consequently), because there were several women who prayed by the edge of the Gangites (‘ FF Bruce) river, we can know that in the city of Filipi, Yahudi men were very few.</bt></note>Jadi botong dudu ba'omong deng dong.<bt>So (consequently), we sat and talked with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ba'itong = assume; bareken(g) = think,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ba'itong = assume; bareken(g) = think, calculate, assume</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Dari itu mama dong samua, ada satu yang nama Lidia. Dia dari satu kota yang jao di propinsi Asia, nama Tiatira. Ini mama bajual kaen warna ungu yang mahal mau mati kasi orang bésar dong. Dia rajin sambayang sang Tuhan Allah. Jadi waktu dia dengar sang Paulus pung omong, dia tarima memang.<bt>From all those women, there was one who name was Lidia. She was from a far away city in Asia province, named Tiatira. This mama sold very expensive purple-coloured cloth to big (=important) people. She was faithful to pray to the Lord God. So (consequently) when she heard Paulus, she immediately accepted.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tarima bae = has sense of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tarima bae = has sense of passive or reluctance, rather than active or sincere receiving of s.t. ~ tarima sa; active and deliberate is just tarima ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais ju botong sarani memang sang mama Lidia deng dia pung isi ruma samua. Sarani abis, ju dia undang sang botong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa dong. Kalo bosong pikir beta ni, su parcaya batúl sang Tuhan Yesus, na, bosong datang ko manumpang di botong pung ruma.&gt;&gt; Dia noki-noki tarús, sampe ahirnya botong iko.<bt>And then we right away baptised mama Lidia and all her household. After baptising, then she invited us saying, “Fathers. If you think that I here, have truly believed in the Lord Yesus, na, you come to stay at our (exc) house.” She continued to insist, until finally we went.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="noki = bujuk tarus-tarus, kokoe, (not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">noki = bujuk tarus-tarus, kokoe, (not nag), insist politely, persistent;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong kasi maso sang Paulus deng Silas pi dalam bui di kota Filipi<bt>They put Paulus and Silas in jail in Filipi city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Satu hari, waktu botong ada jalan pi tampa sambayang, ju botong katumu satu nona di jalan. Dia tu, orang pung budak. Dia takaná setan jahat, sampe dia bisa kasi tau orang pung nasib. Dia ju bisa tau masala dong pung ujung-pohon dari mana. Jadi banya orang suka kasi sang dia doi ko minta tolong lia dong pung nasib. Ma itu doi dong, nona pung bos-bos yang dapa samua, sampe dong jadi kaya.<bt>One day, when we were walking to the worship place, then when met a young girl on the road. That her, [she was] a person's slave. She was affected by an evil spirit, to the point that she could tell people's fate. She also could discern where the root cuz (elaboration) of problems came from. So (consequently) many people liked to give her money to ask help in see their fate. But that money, the girl's bosses who got it all, to the point that they had become rich.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bisa kasi tau orang pung nasib;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bisa kasi tau orang pung nasib; akar/sabab</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Itu hari waktu botong ada jalan, itu nona maen iko-iko sang botong tarús. Ais dia batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang dong, Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi pung tukang suru-suru dong. Dong datang ko mau kasi tunju jalan bilang, karmana ko orang bisa dapa salamat, deng lapás dari dong pung sala-sala dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>That day, when we were walking, that girl kept continually following us. Then she yelled saying, “These people, are servants of the Lord God who Most High. They came to show the way how people can be saved, and freed from their wrongs!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Itu nona bekin bagitu sampe barapa hari. Lama-lama ju Paulus jadi bosan dengar itu parampuan pung eki-eki tu. Ais dia bale ko lia karás-karás sang itu nona, ju dia parenta itu setan bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Lu setan jahat! Deng Tuhan Yesus pung kuasa, beta parenta sang lu, kaluar dari ini parampuan, sakarang ju!&gt;&gt; Paulus omong abis bagitu, ju itu setan kaluar memang.<bt>That girl did like that for several days. After a while then Paulus became tired of hearing those shouts of that female. So he turned to look sternly at that girl, and he commanded that evil spirit saying, “Heh [+something is amiss]! You evil spirit! With the Lord Yesus' power, I order you, come out of this female, and now!” Paulus finished speaking like that, and that evil spirit came out right away.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sesak = jengkel; senu = bingung;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sesak = jengkel; senu = bingung; eki = shout (deng kata); emos = angry</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02129b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Paulus usir setan dari parampuan<bt>Paulus expels an evil spirit from a female</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Waktu itu nona pung bos dong dapa tau bilang, dong pung budak pung kuasa su ilang, ju dong mara, tagal dong sonde dapa doi lai. Ais dong pegang ame sang Paulus deng Silas, ko hela bawa sang dong pi pasar, di tampa yang orang biasa pake ko urus parkara.<bt>When that girl's bosses found out that, their slave's power was lost, then they got angry, because they could not get any more money. So they took ahold of Paulus and Silas, to pull bring them to the market, to the place that people usually use to handle litigations/disputes.</bt><v n="20" />Di situ, dong batarea karás-karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang dong ni datang ko bekin rusak kotong pung kota. Padahal dong bukan orang dari sini. Ini Yahudi dong, datang dari jao-jao ko bekin kaco sa di sini!<bt>There, they yelled loudly saying, “These people here, have come to destroy our city. Even though they are not people from here. These Yahudis, have come from far away to just make things chaotic here! [EXEG: magistrates/officials covered in vs.19, so would be heavy to make explicit here. Carried from context, and explicit in vs.20.]</bt><v n="21" />Dong ju ajar orang bilang, kotong jang toe deng pamarenta Roma pung atoran dong, ko iko dong pung atoran.&gt;&gt;<bt>They also teach people saying, we must not be concerned about the Roma governments regulations, to just follow their regulations.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dengar bagitu, ju orang banya dong mangamok, ais dong pi papoko sang Paulus deng Silas. Ju tukang putus parkara di situ dong suru orang dong pi robe buang dong dua pung pakean, ais firuk sang dong.<bt>Hearing that, then many people went amuck, then they hit Paulus and Silas. Then the judges there ordered people to tear &amp; throw away Paulus and Silas' clothes and whip/beat them. [EXEG: magistrates/(city) officials in Gk is plural. Term used here should also match with vs. 35.]</bt><v n="23" />Dong firuk barmaen sang Paulus deng Silas, ais tola buang sang dong pi dalam bui. Dong suru komandán jaga di situ, ko jaga bae-bae sang itu dua orang. Jang sampe dong lari.<bt>They whipped over and over Paulus and Silas, then rejected and threw them in jail. They ordered a guard commander there, to guard very carefully those two people. Lest they run/escape.</bt><v n="24" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu komandán jaga kasi maso dong di satu kamar di itu bui pung tenga. Ju dia gepe dong pung kaki pake kayu pasung.<bt>Hearing that, then that guard commander put them in a room in that jail's middle. And he clamped their feet using wood stocks.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kayu pasung = wooden stocks (known"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kayu pasung = wooden stocks (known by younger UNS's in association with restraining crazy people)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02132b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm:textWrapping:none">Dong gepe Paulus dong pung kaki di kayu pasung dalam bui<bt>They clamp Paulus them's feet in the wood stocks in jail</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Kira-kira waktu tenga malam, Paulus deng Silas ada sambayang deng manyanyi ko puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah. Itu orang bui laen dong di situ ada iko dengar dong pung manyanyi tu.<bt>When it was around midnight, Paulus and Silas were praying and singing to praise the Lord God. Those other people in that jail, were listening to that singing of theirs</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manyanyi = n/v; kasi manyanyi itu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">manyanyi = n/v; kasi manyanyi itu tep/radio/tv dolu</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Takuju sa, tana tagoyang mati pung, sampe anteru ruma bui tu, ju tagoyang. Deng dia pung pintu tabuka lebar. Tarús orang bui dong pung rante samua, ju talapás buang.<bt>Suddenly, a strong earthquake, to the point that that entire jail house, also quaked. And its doors were opened wide. Then all the jail people's chains, also came.off thrown.off.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tagoyang = s.t. else is the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tagoyang = s.t. else is the cause; bagoyang = subject is Actor, so effect is like dancing; thus tana tagoyang works, but tana bagoyang is awkward</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Itu waktu, ju komandán jaga di ruma bui takuju bangun, ju dia lia itu bui pung pintu dong samua tabuka lebar. Lia bagitu, ju dia kira ke orang bui samua su lari fuik. Ais ju dia cabu ame dia pung parang, ko mau bunu diri.<bt>At that time, then the guard commander in the jail house suddenly got up, and he saw those jail doors all opened wide. Seeing like that, then he thought tht the jail people had all run away. And so, he pulled out his machete, to kill himself.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalewang kudung = short sword, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kalewang kudung = short sword, but contradiction, since kalewang is inherently long;</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Ma Paulus batarea deng suara karás deng larang bilang, &lt;&lt;We, Pak! Jang bunu diri! Te botong samua masi ada di sini, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Paulus yelled in a loud voice forbiding saying, “We, Mr! Don't kill yourself! Cuz (elaboration) we are all still here!”</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02134b.tif" rtfFormat="width:7.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Dong kasi barisi Paulus pung luka dong<bt>They clean Paulus' wounds</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Dengar itu suara, ju komandán tu, taku mau mati, deng dia tabingung-bingung. Ais dia suru ko dong bawa kasi sang dia obor, tarús dia lari maso pi dalam itu bui, deng badan gamatar dingin. Ju dia pi jato tikam lutut di Paulus deng Silas pung kaki.<bt>Hearing that voice, then that commander, was very afraid, and he was completely confused. Then he ordered that they bring him a light, and he ran into the jail, with his body trembling in fear. And he knelt at Paulus and Silas' feet.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="obor; gamatar dingin = tremble in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">obor; gamatar dingin = tremble in fear, (w/a cold sweat), taku mau mati</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ais dia bawa kasi kaluar dong dari dalam bui, ju dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa dong. Beta ni, ada susa mau mati. Beta musti bekin apa, ko bisa talapás dari ini susa dong?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then he brought them out of that jail, and asked them saying, “Fathers/Sirs. I here, am in terrible difficulties. What must I do, so that I can be freed from these difficulties?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Paulus dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia pung jalan bagini: lu parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus, ko nanti Dia kasi salamat sang lu. Bagitu ju deng lu pung isi ruma dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Paulus them answered saying, “Its way is like this: you believe in the Lord Yesus, so that He will give salvation to you. And like that also for your household.”</bt><v n="32" />Ais Paulus deng Silas ba'omong deng itu komandán bui, deng dia pung isi ruma dong samua. Dong kasi tau Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop kasi sang dong.<bt>Then Paulus and Silas spoke with that jail commander, and all his household. They told the Lord Yesus' Life Path to them.</bt><v n="33" />Lewat tenga malam sadiki, ju itu komandán bui bawa ame Paulus deng Silas ko pi kasi barisi dong pung luka kaná firuk kamaren. Ais itu, Paulus dong sarani sang itu komandán deng dia pung isi ruma dong samua.<bt>A bit after midnight, then that jail commander took Paulus and Silas to clean their wounds which had been afficted by whipping the day before. After that, they *baptised that commander and all his household.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kamarin ~ kalmarin (archaic)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kamarin ~ kalmarin (archaic)</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Tarús dia bawa sang dong pi dalam dia pung ruma, ko dia kasi dong makan. Dia deng dia pung kelu dong samua talalu sanáng, tagal dong su parcaya sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>And he brought them to his house, to give them food. He and all his family were very happy, because they had believed in the Lord God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Dia pung papagi hari, ju tukang putus parkara dong kirim pasán kasi sang itu komandán bui, ko suru dia kasi lapás Paulus dong dari dalam bui.<bt>Early morning the next day, then the big people who decide litigations, sent a request to that jail commander, to order him to free Paulus them from jail. [NOTE to daughter translations: term for magistrates/(city) officials here should match vs. 22.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="take a look at @@ kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">take a look at @@ kasi sang combos</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Dengar bagitu, ju komandán bui kasi tau itu pasán sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa dong. Orang bésar dong su putus ko kasi lapás sang bosong. Jadi bapa dong pi deng salamat suda.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, then the jail commander told that request to Paulus saying, “Fathers. The big/important people have decided to let you go free. So fathers  (=you) go with safety/salvation/well-being (imperative).”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Dengar bagitu, ju Paulus sonde mau tarima bae. Ju dia kasi tau bale sang tukang jaga dong yang bawa itu pasán tadi bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang bagitu! Te botong ni, ada pung hak warga Roma. Jadi botong tuntut botong pung hak! Pamarenta dong musti urus botong pung parkara ni, iko atoran. Iko dia pung batúl, musti dudu parkara dolo, baru hukum orang. Ma dong sonde bekin bagitu. Dong sonde dudu parkara dolo, ko, cari tau botong pung sala apa, ma dong su firuk barmaen sang botong di orang banya pung muka. Sonde ada pung alasan apa-apa, ju dong lempar buang sang botong pi dalam bui. Ini su taráng-taráng, dong langgar pamarenta Roma pung atoran. Ais sakarang, dong mau kasi kaluar sambunyi-sambunyi sang botong dari dalam bui, ko biar orang sonde dapa tau bilang, botong pung sala apa? Sonde bisa bagitu! Suru itu bos dong datang sandiri ko kasi lapás sang botong. Bagitu dolo, baru botong tarima.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, then Paulus didn't want to accept it as good. And he told in return the guards who had just brought the message saying, “Not like that! Cuz (elaboration) we here, have the rights of citizens of Roma. So we demand our rights. The government must arrange this litigation of ours, according to regulation. According to the correct way, [they] must sit and listen to the litigation first, and only then judge/punish the person. But they did not do like that. They did not sit and listen to the litigation first, or, find out what our wrong/sin was, but they whipped us in front of many people. There was no reason what.so.ever. Then they threw us in jail. It's obviously clear, they have violated the Roma government's regulations. And now they secretly want to take us out of jail so that people do not know what our sin was? It can't be like that! Tell those bosses to come themselves to free us. It has to be like that first, only then will we accept.” [EXEG: police/constables in vs. 38 who brought the message. NRSV, NLT, CEV, LN.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukang suru-suru = opas (archaic) ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tukang suru-suru = opas (archaic) = pesuruh; tuntut = demand, insist on; dolo = segera, lebih dahulu; dolu = waktu lampau @@ TAM system!! Check other occurrences</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Waktu itu tukang jaga dong pi lapor kambali Paulus pung omong tu, itu bos-bos dong dapa tau bilang, dong dua ada pung hak warga Roma. Ju dong jadi taku mau mati.<bt>When those people who brought the commands when to report back that talk of Paulus', those bosses found out that those two had the rights of Roma citizens. And they became very afraid.</bt><v n="39" />Ais ju orang bésar dong datang di bui, ko mangaku dong pung sala, deng minta ma'af sang Paulus deng Silas. Ais ju dong kasi kaluar sang dong dua dari dalam bui, tarús dong minta ko dong jalan kasi tenga itu kota.<bt>And then the big people came to that jail, to acknowledge their sin, and ask forgiveness from Paulus and Silas. Then they took the two of them out of jail, and they requested that they go leaving behind that city.</bt><v n="40" />Kaluar dari bui, ju Paulus dong pi mama Lidia pung ruma. Di situ, dong bakumpul deng orang parcaya dong. Dong ajar deng kasi kuat dong pung hati satu kali lai. Ais itu, dong jalan kasi tenga itu kota.<bt>Getting out of jail, then Paulus them went to mama Lidia's house. There, they gathered with the believers. They taught them, and encouraged them one more time. After that, they went leaving behind that city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus dong pi kota Tesalonika<bt>Paulus them in Tesalonika city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="17" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Paulus deng Silas jalan tarús. Dong lewat satu kota, nama Amfipolis. Ais dong pi kota laen, nama Apolonia. Dari situ, dong jalan tarús sampe di kota Tesalonika. Di itu kota, ada satu ruma sambayang orang Yahudi.<bt>After that, Paulus and Silas travelled on. They passed a city, named Amfipolis. After that, they went to another city, named Apolonia. From there, they travelled on until Tesalonika city. At that city, there was a Yahudi people's worship house.</bt></p>
    <fig path="maps\Bible\Hkfil-br.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Jalan dari Filipi pi Berea<bt>The road from Filipi to Berea</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Kalo dong sampe di satu tampa yang ada ruma sambayang Yahudi di situ, pas deng hari barenti karjá, na, Paulus biasa maso ko iko sambayang deng orang dong. Di Tesalonika, dia ju iko maso di dong pung ruma sambayang. Tarús dia batukar pikiran deng dong di situ, pake Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata. Dia iko sambayang deng dong bagitu, tiap hari barenti karjá, sampe tiga minggu ba'iko-ba'iko.<bt>If they arrived at a place that had a Yahudi worship house there, exactly on the day of stopping work, na, Paulus usually entered to go pray with the people. In Tesalonika, then he went in to their worship house. The he exchanged thoughts with them there, using *Words/Sayings of God. He went praying with them like that, every day of stopping work, for three weeks in a row.</bt><v n="3" />Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo kotong pareksa bae-bae di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi tu, kotong dapa tau bilang, dong su omong dari dolu bilang, itu Orang yang Tuhan su janji mau kirim tu, nanti dapa susa banya. Dia nanti mati. Ma abis itu, Tuhan pake Dia pung kuasa ko kasi idop kambali sang Dia. Naa, sakarang kotong su tau bilang, itu Orang yang Tuhan janji tu, andia Yesus!&gt;&gt;<bt>He told them saying, “If we examine carefully in that Book of the Lord, we can know that they have spoken from before hand saying, that that Person whom the Lord promised to send, later would get much difficulty. He would die. But after that, the Lord would use His power to cuz (elaboration) Him to live again. Naa [+shift] now we know that, that Person whom the Lord promised there, it's Yesus!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dengar bagitu, ada orang Yahudi yang tarima Paulus pung omong, ais dong bagabung deng Paulus dong. Dari orang yang tarima tu, ada ju banya orang Yunani yang su rindu sang Tuhan, deng ada barapa mama-mama yang pung pangaru bésar di itu kota.<bt>Hearing that, there where those who accepted Paulus' talk and then they joined with Paulus them. From those people who accepted, there were many Yunani people who longed for God, and there were several mamas who had big influence in that city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma orang Yahudi pung bos-bos di situ jengkel deng iri hati. Ju dong tusu-tusu tukang tapaleuk dong, ko dong bekin kaco. Waktu orang dong su bakumpul bam-banya, dong mulai bekin kaco di itu kota. Dong cari sang Paulus deng Silas, ko dong mau hela bawa pi itu orang banya yang ada mangamok dong. Ais dong pi sarbú Yason pung ruma, tagal Paulus deng Silas ada manumpang di situ.<bt>But the Yahudi people bosses there were upset, and jealous. So they persuaded some provocators to go make things chaotic. When many people where gathered, they began to make things chaotic in that city. They hunted for Paulus and Silas, so that they could drag bring them to that crowd that had gone amuck. Then they went attacking Yason's house, because Paulus and Silas were staying there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukang tapaleuk = preman; jadi taceke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tukang tapaleuk = preman; jadi taceke = jealous</Message></Annotation><v n="6-7" />Ma dong sonde dapa Paulus dong di situ. Ais ju dong hela bawa sang Yason deng orang parcaya laen dong barapa orang pi tampa urus parkara. Dong tudu sang Yason dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sakarang ada orang-orang yang su datang di kotong pung kota. Dong pi mana-mana sa, dong bekin kaco di situ! Sakarang dong datang ko mau bongkar bekin tabale kotong pung atoran di sini, ais ganti deng dong pung atoran! Ini Yason ni, dia su tarima ini orang dong manumpang di dia pung ruma! Ma dong samua malawan kotong pung atoran, tagal dong sonde mau mangaku raja bésar keser. Dong cuma mau mangaku dong pung bos bésar satu, nama Yesus.&gt;&gt;<bt>But they did not find Paulus them there. So they drag brought Yason and other several other believers to the places of taking.care of litigations. They accused Yason them saying, “Now there are people who have come to our city. Whereever they go, they make it chaotic there! Now they come to destroy &amp; turn over our regulations here, then exchange them with their regulations! This Yason here, he has received these people to stay in his house! But they all oppose our regulations, because they don't want to acknowledge big raja Keser. They only want to acknowledge a big boss of theirs, named Yesus.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tudu = accuse"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tudu = accuse</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Dengar bagitu, ju orang bésar dong, deng orang-orang di situ pung pikiran dong mulai kaco-balo.<bt>Hearing that, then the big people, and the people there's thinking began to get all confused.</bt><v n="9" />Ais orang bésar di itu kota suru Yason deng orang parcaya dong, ko dong bayar doi jaminan, jadi tanda bilang, dong sonde bekin kaco lai, deng janji sonde bole lari. Bayar abis, ju itu orang dong kasi lapás sang Yason dong.<bt>The the big people in that city ordered Yason and the believers, to pay promise money (bond), to be a sign that they would not make things chaotic anymore, and promise not to flee. After paying, then those people freed Yason them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doi jaminan = bail, bond"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">doi jaminan = bail, bond</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus dong pi kota Berea<bt>Paulus them at Berea city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Itu malam, orang parcaya dari kota Tesalonika pikir-pikir lebe bae dong kirim Paulus deng Silas pi tampa laen. Ais ju dong kirim dong dua pi satu kota, nama Berea. Sampe di situ, dong maso pi orang Yahudi pung ruma sambayang.<bt>That night, the believers from that city of Tesalonika, thought its was best if they sent Paulus and Silas to another place. And so they sent the two of them to a city, named Berea. Arriving there, they entered the Yahudi people's worship house.</bt><v n="11" />Ma itu orang Yahudi dong yang ada di Berea tu, laen dari orang Tesalonika dong. Ini orang dong ni, talalu suka dengar, deng dong sadia tarima Paulus dong pung omong. Te dong di Berea dengar bae-bae sang Paulus dong, deng lia bae-bae Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi. Dong mau cari tau Paulus dong pung omong tu, batúl, ko sonde. Andia ko, siang-malam dong pareksa sampe alus-alus Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi.<bt>But those Yahudi people who were in that Berea, were different from the people who were in Tesalonika. These people here, liked very much to listen and they were ready to accept Paulus them's talk. Cuz (elaboration) them in Berea there, [they] listened carefully to Paulus them, and looked carefully in the Lord God's Holy Writings. They wanted to know if, that talking of Paulus them, was correct, or not. That's why, day-night they examined in great detail the Lord's Writings like that.</bt><v n="12" />Tagal itu, banya orang Yahudi di situ parcaya sang Yesus. Bagitu ju deng orang Yunani dong. Dong yang parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus ada pung pangaru bésar. Ada laki-laki, deng ada parampuan ju.<bt>Because of that, many Yahudi people there believed in Yesus. Like that also with the Yunani people. They, [the ones] who had big influence, were who believed in the Lord Yesus. There were males, and females.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ma waktu orang Yahudi dari Tesalonika dong dengar bilang, Paulus dong ada ajar Tuhan pung Kata-kata di Berea, ju dong datang iko, ais tusu-tusu orang ko bekin kaco lai di sana.<bt>But when those Yahudi people from Tesalonika heard that Paulus them were teaching the Lord's words in Berea, then they went there, and stirred up people to make things chaotic again there.</bt><v n="14" />Andia ko orang parcaya di Berea dong, bawa capát-capát sang Paulus pi pante. Ma Timotius deng Silas tenga tarús di Berea.<bt>That's why the believers in Berea, quickly brought Paulus to the coast. But Timotius and Silas stayed on in Berea.</bt><v n="15" />Itu orang dong antar sang Paulus sampe di satu kota, nama Atena. Ais dong kasi tenga dia di situ, ko dong pulang kambali pi Berea. Dong bawa pasán dari Paulus bilang, Silas deng Timotius datang capát ko bagabung deng dia.<bt>Those people escorted Paulus to a city, named Atena. Then they left him there, to return again to Berea. They brought request from Paulus saying, Silas and Timotius (should) come quickly to join him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus di kota bésar Atena<bt>Paulus in the big city Atena</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Waktu Paulus ada tunggu-tunggu sang Silas deng Timotius pung datang di Atena, dia pung hati jadi susa, tagal dia lia di itu kota ada tampa songgo di mana-mana.<bt>While Paulus was waiting for Silas and Timotius' arrival in Atena, his liver became distressed, because he saw that that city, had [traditional] worshiping places all over the place.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01996b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none">Paulus lia-lia orang Atena pung tampa songgo dong<bt>Paulus looking at the Atena people's traditional worshiping places</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE [for TEXT BOX in PICTURE]:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">NOTE [for TEXT BOX in PICTURE]: kasi dewa yang kotong sonde kanál</Message></Annotation></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ma di situ ada barapa orang Yahudi, deng barapa orang bukan Yahudi yang suka sambayang sang Tuhan Allah. Paulus maso pi dong pung ruma sambayang, ais batukar pikiran deng dong. Saban hari, dia ju pi pasar ko ba'omong deng sapa sa yang datang di situ.<bt>But there, there were several Yahudi people, and several people who were not Yahudi who liked to/often worshipped the Lord God. Paulus entered in their worship house, then exchanged thoughts with them. Each day, he also went to the market to talk with just whoever came there.</bt><v n="18" />Ais dia baso'al-jawab deng barapa guru dari dua kalompok di itu kota, andia kalompok Epikuros, deng kalompok Stoa.<bt>So he question-answered (=debated) with several teachers from two groups in that city, that is the Epikuros group, and the Stoa group.</bt><note reference="17:18" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang dari kalompok Epikuros ni, dong iko satu guru, nama Epikuros. Dia ajar bilang, yang paling pantíng, idop yang bae, andia idop yang rasa sanáng sa. Sonde usa pusing deng hal laen. Deng orang dari kalompok Stoa, dong iko satu guru laen, nama Seno. Dia ajar bilang, orang musti tau jaga dia pung diri bae-bae, deng ator dia pung pikiran, sampe dia sonde bisa rasa saki apa-apa lai.<bt>People from this Epikuros group, they followed a guru, named Epikuros. He taught that, what was most important, for a good life, that.was a life which only felt happiness. It was not necessary to worry about other things. And people from the Stoa group, they followed another guru, named Seno. He taught that, a person must control him/herself well, and arrange his/her thinking, to the point that he/she cannot feel any pain about anything anymore.</bt></note>Ma waktu dia ba'omong so'al Yesus bilang, Dia tu, su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati, ju ada dari dong yang buang luda bilang, &lt;&lt;Phueh! Dasar tukang omong kosong pung ba'i!&gt;&gt; Ada ju yang olok-olok bilang, &lt;&lt;Wueh! Ini orang mau paksa sang kotong ko songgo dong pung dewa asing dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>But when he talked about Yesus, saying that He, had lived again from His death, then there were those of them who spit, (implies rejecting) saying, “Phueh! [+disgust, dismissal] His nature is the grandfather of all liars!” There were also those who rejected saying, “Wueh! This person wants to force us to worship their foreign gods!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buang luda = implies menolak, ejek,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">buang luda = implies menolak, ejek, olok, pandang enteng, hina,; dasar = his nature is...</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19-21" />Naa, orang Atena, deng orang luar yang tenga di itu kota, kalo dong dapa dengar hal apa sa yang baru, conto ke ajaran baru, ko, pikiran baru, na, dong pung orang yang pintar biasa dudu bakumpul di satu gunung kici, nama Areopagus ko batukar pikiran panjang lebar. Ais ada dari dong yang ame bawa Paulus pi situ, ju minta sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba kasi tau sang botong, itu ajaran baru tu! Ko lu ada omong hal baru yang bekin botong jadi bingung sadiki. Jadi botong minta ko lu omong tamba sadiki lai ko biar botong bisa mangarti.&gt;&gt;<bt>Now Atena people, and outsiders who lived in that city, if they heard any matter which was new, for example new teaching, or new thinking, na, their smart people usually sat together at a small mountain, named Areopagus to exchange thinking long wide (=discuss in great detail). So there were those from them who took Paulus there, and asked him saying, “Please tell/explain.to us, that new teaching. Because <span class="Italic">(ko)</span> you are talking about something new, which makes us become a bit confused. [+emphatic] So we ask that you speak adding a bit more so that we can understand.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@restructured 19-21 background-foreground"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">@@restructured 19-21 background-foreground</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais ju, ada dari dong yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Ais ju, ada dari dong yang ame bawa Paulus pi di satu gunung kici, nama Areopagus. Di situ, banya orang yang pintar dong biasa bakumpul, ko batukar pikiran. Ais dong minta sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba kasi tau sang botong, itu ajaran baru tu! Ko lu ada omong hal baru, yang bekin botong jadi bingung sadiki. Jadi botong minta ko lu omong tamba sadiki lai ko biar botong bisa mangarti.&gt;&gt;<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>(Dong minta bagitu, te orang Atena, deng orang luar yang tenga di itu kota, kalo dong dapa dengar hal apa sa yang baru, conto ke ajaran baru, ko pikiran baru, na, dong biasa dudu ko batukar pikiran panjang lebar di Areopagus.)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22-23" />Ais Paulus badiri ko angka omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang Atena dong samua! Beta su jalan kuliling bosong pung kota ni, deng beta lia bilang, bosong memang orang yang rajin kasi jalan agama. Beta lia bosong pung tampa songgo dong ada di mana-mana. Ma beta ada lia satu batu songgo yang ada tulis bilang, &lt;Ini sosonggo kasi dewa yang kotong sonde kanál.&gt; Dia pung arti, bosong su songgo sang Tuhan Allah, padahal bosong balóm kanál sang Dia. Naa, Dia ni yang beta ada kasi tau sang bosong.<bt>Then Paulus stood to begin speaking saying, “All Atena people! I have travelled all around this city of yours, and I have seen that you truly are people who are faithful in carrying out religion. I see your [traditional] worship places are all over the place. But I have see one [traditional] worship stone on which is written, 'This [traditional] worships the god whom we do not know.' That means, you already [traditional] worship the Lord God, even though you do not yet know Him. Naa, He is the one whom I am telling you about.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Te Dia ni, yang bekin ame langit deng bumi, deng dong pung isi samua. Dia ju yang hak parenta samua yang ada di langit deng di bumi. Jadi Dia sonde tenga di ruma songgo yang manusia bekin.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who made the earth and all its contents. He is also the one with the say-so/ordering rights over everything that exists in the sky and the earth. So (consequently), He does not stay in a [traditional] worship house which humans make.</bt><v n="25" />Dia yang kasi napas, deng kasi idop sang kotong manusia. Pende kata, Dia yang kasi samua yang kotong parlú. Ma Dia sandiri sonde parlú apa-apa. Jadi manusia sonde bisa tolong sang Dia.<bt>He is the one who gives breath, and gives life to all humans. The main point is, He is the one who gives all that we-inc need. But He himself doesn't need anything. Thus humans cannot help Him</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pende kata = In short, @"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Pende kata = In short, @</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:24-25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 8:27, Yesaya 42:5, Utusan dong pung Carita 8:47</note><v n="26" />Dari cuma satu orang sa, Dia bekin ame samua suku-bangsa di anteru bumi. Dia yang bagi kasi suku-bangsa dong, satu-satu deng dia pung tana. Deng Dia yang ator tiap suku-bangsa pung nae, deng dia pung jato, satu-satu deng dia pung waktu.<bt>From only one person, He made all the ethnic groups in the whole world. He is the one who divided giving each ethnic group its land. And He is the one who arranged each ethnic group's rise, and its descent, each one with its appointed time.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check metaphor of nae and jato,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">check metaphor of nae and jato, datang deng pi; terbit deng tanggalam,; nae ~ turun; muncul ~ ilang ; jato ~ badiri ; jato ~ bangun @@</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Naa, Dia bekin bagitu, tagal Dia mau kotong manusia cari ko kanál bae-bae sang Dia. Manusia memang ada cari-cari kalo-kalo dong bisa katumu sang Dia. Tau-tau te Dia sonde jao dari kotong.<bt>Naa, [+shift] He did like that, because He wanted us humans to seek to know Him well. Humans really have been seeking and seeking trying to meet/know Him. But actually He is not far from us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalo-kalo = as if, moga-moga ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kalo-kalo = as if, moga-moga ; Tau-tau te = padahal, actually</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Ada orang parná omong bilang,<bt>A person once wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Dia memang sumber dari kotong pung napas.<bt>‘He truly is the source of our-inc breath.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia memang akar dari kotong pung idop.&gt;<bt>He truly is the root of our-inc lives.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="try to get Eastern Indonesian traditional"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">try to get Eastern Indonesian traditional parallelism poetry style here --</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ada ju bosong pung tukang bekin pantun parná omong bilang,<bt>There is also one of your statute/idol makers who once wrote saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manahelo/tukang sa'ir = manahelo not known"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">manahelo/tukang sa'ir = manahelo not known by June</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Kotong idop, tagal dia.<bt>‘We-inc live, because of him [NOTE to daughter translations: don't capitalise, because this is Athenian poet, who balóm kanál Tuhan Allah, so probably not poet's intent.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko, kotong jadi dia pung turunan.&gt;<bt>That's why we are his descendants.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Naa, itu memang batúl. Kotong samua ni, Tuhan Allah pung turunan. Jadi jang pikir bilang, Tuhan Allah sama ke patong sosonggo yang manusia bisa bekin dari mas ko, perak ko, batu ko, iko dong pung pikiran sandiri.<bt>Naa, [discourse shift] that's really true. All of us here, are His descendants. So (consequently) don't think that the Lord God is the same as idols [lit. traditional worship statues] whom humans make from gold or, silver or, stone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="iko dong pung angan-angan (BI); patong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">iko dong pung angan-angan (BI); patong sosonggo = idol ; angan-angan = desire, imagination, fantasy (BI)</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Dolu-dolu, memang manusia balóm mangarti ini hal. Andia ko Tuhan Allah kasi tenga ko dong idop deng dong pung bodo tu. Ma sakarang Dia sonde mau kotong idop bagitu lai. Andia ko Dia parenta bilang, kotong musti jalan kasi tenga pi parsetan itu sosonggo dong, ais pi iko sang Dia suda.<bt>Long ago, it's true that humans did not yet understand this matter. That's why the Lord God allowed that them to live with that stupidity of theirs. But now He no longer wants us to live like that anymore. That's why He ordered that we must go leaving behind without caring/thinking about those traditional worship things, then go follow Him (imperative). [NOTE to daughter translations: if the /parsetan/ construction is difficult, try alternate /kasi tenga buang itu sosonggo dong/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pi parsetan = without care"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pi parsetan = without care</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Dia ju su tunju satu waktu, ko mau hukum ini dunya pung isi samua, tagal dong pung sala-sala dong. Deng Dia tunju memang satu Orang jadi Dia pung Hakim. Nanti itu Orang kasi jato hukuman deng batúl. Sakarang su jalás, itu Hakim tu, sapa. Andia Dia yang su mati, ma yang Tuhan Allah su kasi idop kambali sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>He also chose a time, to judge all of the contents of this world, because of their wrongs. And He choose a Person to become His Judge. Later that Person will send down judgements which are correct. Now it's clear, who that Judge is. That is, [it's the one] who died, but the Lord God caused Him to live again from that death of His.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ma waktu orang-orang yang ada bakumpul di situ dengar Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;ada Orang yang su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati&gt;&gt;, ju dong katawa olok-olok sang dia. Ma ada barapa orang yang taro perhatian sang dia ju. Dong kasi tau sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong masi mau dengar bapa omong itu so'al lai. Ma nanti laen kali sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But when the people who were gather there heard Paulus say, “there was a Person who had lived again from His death”, then they laughed mocking him. But there were several people who paid attention to him. They told Paulus saying, “We still want to hear, father (=you) talk about that matter more. But another time.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taru hati = love? ; taru"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">taru hati = love? ; taru perhatian = gave their attention</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Ais Paulus pi jalan kasi tenga itu tampa.<bt>Then Paulus went leaving behind that place.</bt><v n="34" />Ma ada yang bagabung deng dia, tagal dong su parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus. Dari dong, ada satu tukang urus parkara di Areopagus, nama Dionisius. Deng ada satu parampuan, nama Damaris. Deng ada barapa orang laen lai yang iko sama-sama deng dong.<bt>But there were those who joined him, because they believed in the Lord Yesus. From them, there was an officer of the court [person who handles disputes/issues] of Areopagus, named Dionisius. And there was a female, named Damaris. And there several other people who went together with them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus bakanál deng susi Priskila deng bu Akila di kota Korintus<bt>Paulus is introduced/gets.to.know elder sister Priskila and elder brother Akila in Korintus city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="18" />
      <v n="1-3" />Itu waktu, ada raja bésar dari pamarenta Roma, nama Klaudius. Dia mara sang orang Yahudi dong, ais dia usir kasi kaluar sang dong dari kota Roma di propinsi Italia. Ju dong tasiram pi mana-mana. Ada satu orang Yahudi, nama Akila, deng dia pung bini Priskila. Dong dua iko lari kaluar dari propinsi Italia, pi satu kota, nama Korintus. Akila ni, asal dari propinsi Pontus. Dia pung karjá, tukang bekin barang dari kulit.<bt>At that time, there was a big raja from the Roma government, named Klaudius. He was angry with the Yahudi people, so he expelled them from Roma city in the province of Italia. And they spread out all over the place. There was a Yahudi person, named Akila, and his wife Priskila. They two ran leaving Italia province, to go to a city, named Korintus. This Akila, was originally from Pontus province. His work, was a worker who made things from skins/leather.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu waktu, Paulus ju kasi tenga kota Atena, ais dia jalan pi kota Korintus. Di situ, Paulus bakanál sang Akila deng Priskila, te dia ju tukang bekin barang dari kulit. Dong tenga sama-sama, deng dong karjá sama-sama.<bt>At that time, Paulus also left Atena city, then he went to Korintus city. There, Paulus got.to.know Akila and Priskila, cuz (elaboration) he also was a worker who made things out of skins. [+emphatic] They lived together, and they worked together. [DISCOURSE: vs.1-3 restructured to get background-foreground and chronology right.]</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02138b.tif" rtfFormat="width:8.0cm;textWrapping:none;horizontalPosition:center">Paulus, Akila deng Priskila dong karjá sama-sama<bt>Paulus and Akila and Priskila doing their work together</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Kalo su sampe orang Yahudi dong pung hari barenti karjá, Paulus maso pi dong pung ruma sambayang. Di situ, dia coba buju orang Yahudi, deng orang laen dong, ko parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus.<bt>When it came to be the Yahudi people's day of stopping work, Paulus entered into their worship house. There, he tried to persuade the Yahudi people, and the other people, to believe in the Lord Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma waktu Silas deng Timotius datang dari propinsi Makedonia, Paulus barenti karjá kulit. Siang-malam dia tasibu kasi tau orang Yahudi dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu Orang yang kotong samua su tunggu dari dolu-dolu, yang Tuhan Allah su janji mau kirim, Dia tu, su datang. Andia, Yesus!&gt;&gt;<bt>But when Silas and Timotius came from Makedonia province, Paulus stopped working skins. Day-night he was busy telling the Yahudi people saying, “That Person who we-inc all have waited for from long ago, who the Lord God promised to send, that person, He's come. It's Yesus!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ma ada orang Yahudi yang lawan tarús sang Paulus, deng maen omong kasi jato sang dia. Ais Paulus kabás abu dari dia pung pakean, ko jadi tanda bilang, dia su sonde mau pusing sang dong lai, tagal dong sonde mau tarima Kabar Bae yang dia kasi tau sang dong. Ju dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong ni, su talalu! Bosong sangaja bekin tuli bosong pung diri! Ma biar sa! Nanti bosong yang pikol bosong pung sala sandiri. Beta sonde ada tanggong-jawab deng bosong lai. Mulai sakarang, beta su sonde ada urusan lai deng bosong orang Yahudi dong. Beta mau pi ajar suku-bangsa laen yang bukan Yahudi dong sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But ther were Yahudi people who continually opposed him, and they kept talking to make him fall. So Paulus brushed the dust from his clothes, to make a sign saying, he no longer wanted to worry/be.concerned about them, because they did not want to accept the Good News that he had told them. And he also spoke saying, “You (pl) here, are too much! You purposefully make your ownselves deaf! But just leave it like that! Later you will shoulder.carry your wrongs yourselves. I am not going to be responsible to answer for you anymore. From now on, I no longer have any affairs/matters/business among you Yahudi people. I want to only go teach the other ethnic groups who are not Yahudi.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tanggong jawab"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tanggong jawab</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ada satu ruma di itu ruma sambayang pung sablá. Itu tuan ruma pung nama, Titius Yustus. Dia bukan orang Yahudi, ma dia pung hati rindu sang Tuhan Allah. Ais waktu Paulus bale balakang kasi tenga itu orang Yahudi dong, ju dia maso pi bapa Titius pung ruma.<bt>There was house on that worship house's side. It's owner, named Titius Yustus. He was not a Yahudi person, but his liver longed for the Lord God. So when Paulus turned his back leaving behind those Yahudi people, then he enter father Titius' house.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ruma pung tuan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ruma pung tuan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Sonde lama ju, itu ruma sambayang pung kapala, parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus. Dia pung nama Krispus. Dia pung isi ruma samua ju parcaya, sama-sama deng orang Korintus yang laen dong yang ada dengar sang Paulus. Ais ju Paulus ator ko sarani sang dong samua.<bt>Not long also, that worship house's head believed in the Lord Yesus. His name Krispus. All his household also believed, together with other Korintus people who were hearing Paulus. And so, Paulus arranged to baptise them all. [EXEG: The Gk in last sentence is passive “and were baptized”, so agent is up for grabs. What we had (Paul baptized them) is not unreasonable, but also not the only option. The suggestion of “Paulus dong” for KM clashes, since it would have two /dong/ in close proximity. Bruce reads this as Crispus was baptized by Paul personally. (The 1 Cor 1:14-16 passage does not necessarily exclude Crispus' household [metonymy], where Paul is explicitly a bit foggy in his memory.) TH discusses this explicitly in their suggestion to say “Paul baptized them.” I think we can satisfy all issues by making indirect agency “Paul arranged to baptize them all” (/Paulus ator ko dong samua sarani/ would be an implied passive in the Kupang that is difficult to mirror for some daughter translations).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) changed structure of last"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) changed structure of last sentence, note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais ju, Paulus sarani sang dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Ais ju, Paulus sarani sang dong samua.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Satu malam, tingka ke dalam mimpi, Paulus dapa dengar Tuhan Allah omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Paulus! Lu sonde usa taku, deng sonde usa pata samangat deng ini karjá, te lu pung tanggong-jawab balóm abis. Lu musti ajar tarús ini orang dong deng Beta pung Carita Bae.<bt>One night, sort.of.like in a dream, Paulus could hear the Lord God speaking saying, “Paulus! You do not need to be afraid, and do not need to loose enthusiasm with this work, cuz (elaboration) your responsibility is certainly not over yet. You must keep.on teaching this people My Good Story.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pata samangat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pata samangat</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Inga, ó! Lu sonde karjá sandiri. Te Beta ada sama-sama deng lu. Biar orang mau bekin susa sang lu, ma Beta pasang kaki deng lu. Deng Beta ada taro mata sang lu siang-malam. Jang lupa, di ini kota Beta pung orang ada banya.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember, ó! You are not working alone. I am with you. Even if people want to/try to cause difficulty to you, nevertheless I am fastening my feet with you (idiom: standing with you in every situation, every difficulty). And I am putting my eyes on you (idiom: paying attention to) day-night. Don't forget, in this city, I have many people.” [EXEG: in English, literal “no one will harm you” is ambiguous between process “try to harm you” and end result “succeed in harming you”. Signals in Gk grammar favour the latter.] [NOTE to daughter translations: Need for care noted here by several consultants: From one aspectual reading “No one will hurt you/cause you difficulty” (process) is actually a false statement (according to Luke's testimony and Paul's testimony). The point is that “even though people try to harm you, they will not entirely succeed, because I am with you….” (end result) So we have to be really careful here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@kacang sonde lupa kulit; pasang kaki"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">@@kacang sonde lupa kulit; pasang kaki = stand by in every difficulty, accompany and participate together !! (Gen 3) vs. tanam kaki = unmoveable, can have positive sense of firm, or negative sense of stubborn ; *** (2009) note added /mau/ added, BT revised</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Dengar bagitu, ju Paulus tenga cukup lama di kota Korintus. Dia ajar Tuhan pung Jalan Idop di situ sampe satu taon satenga.<bt>Hearing that, then Paulus stayed quite a while in Korintus city. He taught the Lord's Life Path there, until a year and a half.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Itu waktu, dong angka satu orang ko jadi gubernor di propinsi Akaya. Dia pung nama Galio.<bt>At that time, they raised a person to become governor in Akaya province. His name Galio.</bt><note reference="18:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Iko tulisan di satu batu, dong angka sang Galio jadi gubernor di Akaya tu, bulan Juli, taon 51.<bt>According to the writings on one stone, they installed Galio as governor in the Akaya, in the month of Juli, in the year 51.</bt></note>Ada barapa orang Yahudi ju yang basakongkol, ko hela bawa Paulus pi gubernor di tampa urus parkara.<bt>And there were some Yahudi people who agreed to drag bring Paulus to the governor, at the place of taking.care.of litigations.</bt><v n="13" />Ju dong mangadu so'al Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang su buju banya orang ko dong iko agama baru. Padahal pamarenta Roma sonde mangaku itu agama!&gt;&gt;<bt>And the tattle-taled on Paulus saying, “This person has persuaded many people to enter a new religion. Whereas in fact the Roma government doesn't recognize/acknowledge that religion!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangadu = dakwa, lapor, tell on,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">mangadu = dakwa, lapor, tell on, tattle; tukang mangadu = tattle-tale; buju ; CHECK mangadu sang vs. mangadu so'al</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma waktu Paulus mau buka mulu ko bela diri, ju gubernor langsung potong dia pung omong. Dia togor memang itu orang dong yang mangadu sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Bosong orang Yahudi dong, pasang talinga, é! Kalo bosong mau bawa parkara orang bekin jahat, ko, orang dong babunu, beta musti dengar bosong pung parkara.<bt>But when Paulus wanted to open his mouth to defend himself, then the governor immediately interrrupted him. He straight away scolded those people who had tattle-taled on Paulus saying, “Weh [+critical]! You Yahudi people, put your ears on (listen carefully)! If you want to bring a litigation of a person/people doing evil, or, people recip-murdering, I must hear your litigation.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Seumpama/andekata/ = kalo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Seumpama/andekata/ = kalo</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ma parkara yang bosong bawa ni, bosong pung urusan dalam ruma sandiri! Bosong cuma bakanjar so'al atoran agama Yahudi sa, deng dia pung kata-kata dong, deng dia pung nama-nama dong. Itu parkara, bukan pamarenta di sini pung urusan!&gt;&gt;<bt>But this litigation which you are bringing, is your own in.house matter! You are just argueing about the Yahudi religion's own regulations, and his words, and his names. That litigation, is not a matter for the government here!”</bt><note reference="18:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang Yahudi suka baparkara so'al sil-sila.<bt>The Jahudi people liked to dispute over genealogies.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais ju, itu gubernor usir kasi kaluar sang dong dari itu tampa urus parkara.<bt>And then, that governor expelled them from that place of taking.care.of litigations.</bt><v n="17" />Ju orang Yunani dong di situ tangkap ame satu orang, nama Sostenes. Dia tu, kapala dari orang Yahudi pung ruma sambayang. Tarús dong hela bawa sang dia, ko papoko sang dia di gubernor pung muka. Ma itu gubernor sonde toe sang dong.<bt>And the Yunani people there captured a person, named Sostenes. That him, [he was] the head of the Yahudi people's worship house. Then they drag brought him, and beat him in front of the governor. But that governor didn't pay any attention to them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dari Korintus, Paulus pi ulang lai di kota Antiokia di propinsi Siria<bt>From Korintus, Paulus goes again to Antiokia city in Siria province</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18-19" />Ais itu, ju Paulus tenga tarús di Korintus. Ma lama-lama, dia minta parmisi dari orang parcaya di situ. Ais ju dia, deng Priskila deng Akila, pi satu kota, nama Kengkrea, ko dong tunggu kapal. Di situ, Paulus cukur bekin polik dia pung kapala, ko jadi tanda bilang, apa yang dolu dia su janji sang Tuhan, sakarang dia su bekin abis.<bt>After that, then Paulus stayed on in Korintus. But after a while, he requested leave from the believers there. And then he, with Priskila and Akila, went to a city, named Kengkrea, to wait for a ship. There, Paulus shaved making bald his head, to become a sign saying, that which beforehand he had promised to the Lord, now he had finished it.</bt><note reference="18:18-19" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kalo ada orang Yahudi yang mau ika janji deng Tuhan, dia musti puasa. Nanti kalo dia su bekin abis itu janji, dia cukur bekin polik dia pung kapala. Lia <span class="Italic">Daftar Sensus</span> 6:18.<bt>If there is a Yahudi person who wants to tie a promise with the Lord, he must fast. Then if he as finished doing that promise, he shaves making bald his head. See <span class="Italic">Number</span>s 6:18.</bt></note>Ais dong nae kapal ko balayar pi kota Efesus. Sampe di situ, dong turun dari itu kapal. Tarús Paulus kasi tenga dia pung tamán dua orang tu, ko dia maso pi dalam orang Yahudi pung ruma sambayang. Di situ, dia batukar pikiran deng orang Yahudi dong.<bt>Then they got on the ship to sail to Efesus city. Arriving there, they got down from that ship. Then Paulus left those two friends of his, for him to go enter in the Yahudi people's worship house. There, he exchanged thinking with the Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="minta parmisi ; cukur bekin polik"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">minta parmisi ; cukur bekin polik = shave bald; polik = botak, gundul ; kojek</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Dong omong-omong bagitu, ju orang Yahudi dong minta ko Paulus tenga lebe lama lai sadiki deng dong. Ma dia tolak deng alus.<bt>The spoke and spoke like that, and the Yahudi people asked that Paulus stay a bit longer with them. But he politely refused.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deng alus = politely"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">deng alus = politely</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ais dia minta parmisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara sayang dong! Jang kurang hati, é! Kalo Tuhan buka jalan, nanti beta datang lia sang bosong lai.&gt;&gt; Omong bagitu, ju dia kasi tenga Efesus.<bt>Then he requested permission (take leave) saying, “Dear siblings! Don't be disappointed/offended, é! If the Lord opens the way, I will come see you again.” Speaking like that, then he left Efesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaki kareta = itchy feet; panta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kaki kareta = itchy feet; panta bensin ~ panta motor = itchy feet on a motorcycle</Message></Annotation><note reference="18:21" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada orang yang pintar tulis bilang, alasan Paulus mau kasi tenga sang dong, tagal dia rindu iko Paska di Yerusalem. Kalo dia tunda, nanti musim galombang bésar datang, deng dia pung rancana su sonde jadi.<bt>There are experts who write saying, the reason Paulus wanted to leave them, was because he longed to attend Passover/Easter [Paska] in Yerusalem. If he delayed, then the big wave season would come, and his plan would not work out.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais dia balayar tarús, sampe di kota Kaisarea. Ju dia turun di situ. Tarús dia nae pi Yerusalem, ko kasi salam sang orang parcaya dong di situ. Ais dia pulang pi kota Antiokia.<bt>Then he sailed on, until the city of Kaisarea. And he disembarked there. Then he went up to Yerusalem, to give greetings to the believers there. Then he returned home to Antiokia city. [NOTE to daughter translations; because 1st two sentences are about ships, CHECK to make sure that /nae pi/ is not also interpreted as embarking on a ship. This is jalan darat going up into the mountains.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) fixed BT"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) fixed BT</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Dia tenga barapa lama di situ, ais ju dia barangkat, ko jalan kuliling di propinsi Galatia deng propinsi Frigia. Di sana, dia kasi kuat orang parcaya dong pung hati.<bt>He stayed a while there, and then he left, to travel all around Galatia province and Frigia province. There, he strengthened/encouraged the believers' livers.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Apolos di kota Efesus deng kota Korintus<bt>Apolos in the city of Efesus and the city of Korintus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Itu waktu, ada orang Yahudi satu dari kota Aleksandria di propinsi Masir sana. Dia pung nama Apolos. Dia tu, orang yang pintar omong. Dia ju tau sampe alus-alus Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan pung isi. Dia baru sampe di kota Efesus.<bt>At that time, there was a Yahudi person from Aleksandria city in the province of Masir over.there(distant). His name Apolos. That him, [he was] a person skilled in speaking. He also knew completely the contents of the Lord God's Holy Book. He had only just arrived in Efesus city.</bt><v n="25" />Dia parná dengar carita so'al Yesus, deng dia suka carita ulang kasi orang laen. Dia carita deng samangat, deng apa yang dia omong tu, memang batúl. Cuma dia balóm mangarti samua hal. Dia cuma tau Yohanis sarani orang, kalo dong su barenti dari dong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>He had heard the story about Yesus, and he like to tell it again to other people. He told it with enthusiasm, and what the told those people, was really true. Only he did not yet understand all matters. He only knew that Yohanis baptised people, if they had stopped their wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati manyala-manyala = samangat ; sapo'ong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hati manyala-manyala = samangat ; sapo'ong = sepotong, sepenggal</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Ais satu kali, dia ba'omong tar pake pele-pele di orang Yahudi pung ruma sambayang. Priskila deng Akila ju ada dengar sang dia di situ. Sambayang abis, ju dong undang bawa sang dia pi dong pung ruma. Di situ, dong kasi tau sang dia, Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop samua, sampe di hal kici-kici dong.<bt>So one time, he was talking boldly in the Yahudi people's worship house. Priskila and Akila also were listening to him there. After praying/worshiping, they invited brought him to their house. There, they told him, all about the Lord Yesus' Life Path, even the little tiny things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="baomong tar pele-pele = boldly, fearlessly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">baomong tar pele-pele = boldly, fearlessly</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ais itu, Apolos putus ko mau pi propinsi Akaya. Orang parcaya di Efesus satu hati deng dia pung mau. Ais dong bekin satu surat kasi dong pung sodara orang parcaya di Akaya, ko minta dong tarima Apolos deng bae. Pegang ame itu surat, ju dia barangkat. Sampe di Akaya, dia batúl-batúl tolong sang orang parcaya di situ. Dong su parcaya sang Yesus tagal Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang dong.<bt>After that, Apolos decided that he would go to Akaya province. The believers in Efesus were in one accord with his desire, So they made a letter to their fellow believers in Akaya, to request them to recieive Apolos well. After getting ahold of that letter, then he left. Arriving at Akaya, he really-really helped the believers there. They had believed in Yesus because God showed His good liver/ grace/ kindness/ generosity to them. [EXEG: OV undertranslated Gk “who through grace...”. Fixed 2019.]</bt><v n="28" />Dia ju ada baso'al-jawab deng orang Yahudi di situ di muka banya orang, ma dong sonde ontong sang dia. Dia suka pake Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi ko ajar sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu Orang yang Tuhan su janji mau kirim datang, yang kotong su tunggu bagini lama, andia Yesus!&gt;&gt;<bt>And he also debated with the Yahudi people there in front of many people, but they could not defeat him. He liked to use the Lord God's Scriptures to teach them saying, “That Person whom the Lord promised to send, whom we-inc have been waiting for this long time, it's Yesus!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus kambali pi kota Efesus<bt>Paulus returns to Efesus city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="19" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu Apolos masi ada di Korintus di propinsi Akaya, Paulus jalan kuliling kampong-kampong di gunung. Ais ju dia sampe di kota Efesus. Di situ, dia katumu deng barapa orang yang su parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus.<bt>While Apolos was still in Korintus in the province of Akaya, Paulus went travelling around to all the villages in the mountains. And then he arrived at Efesus city. There, he met with several people who believed in the Lord Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ju dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara sayang dong. Tempo hari, waktu bosong taro parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus, bosong ada tarima Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi ju, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>And he asked them saying, “Dear siblings. Earlier, when you-pl put your trust in the Lord Yesus, did you also receive the Lord's Holy Spirit?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde. Botong balóm parná dengar bilang, ada Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>They replied saying, “No. We have never heard that there is the Lord God's Spirit like that.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ju Paulus tanya lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, dong sarani sang bosong, pake sarani yang mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>And Paulus asked again/further saying, If that's the case, when they baptised you, they used which (of choices)/ what.kind.of baptism?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dong sarani sang botong iko Yohanis pung cara.&gt;&gt;<bt>And they replied saying, “They baptised us following Yohanis' method.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ju Paulus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar dolo! Yohanis sarani orang ko jadi tanda bilang, dong su barenti dari dong pung sala-sala dong. Ma inga bagini! Tiap hari dia sandiri yang ajar sang orang Isra'el dong bilang, dong musti parcaya sang Yesus, itu Orang yang nanti Tuhan mau kirim datang.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Paulus told/explained saying, “Listen! Yohanis baptised people to make a sign saying they had stopped their wrongs. But remember this! Every day he himself taught the Israel people, saying they must believe in Yesus, that Person whom the Lord would send.”</bt><note reference="19:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 3:11, Markus 1:4, 7-8, Lukas 3:4, 16, Yohanis 1:26-27</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Dengar bagitu, ju dong minta ko dia sarani sang dong, ko dong maso jadi Tuhan Yesus pung kelu.<bt>Hearing that, then they requested that he baptise them, so that they enter &amp; become the Lord Yesus' family.</bt><v n="6" />Ais waktu Paulus taro tangan di dong deng sambayang, ju Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi turun pi dong. Ju dong mulai ba'omong deng bahasa macam-macam yang dong balóm parná tau. Deng Tuhan pake sang dong ko kasi tau apa yang nanti jadi.<bt>Then when Paulus put his hands on their heads and prayed, then the Lord's Holy Spirit came down on them. And they began to speak in different kinds.of languages which they had never known. And the Lord used them to foretell what would happen later.</bt><v n="7" />Dong samua ada dua blas orang.<bt>All of them were twelve people</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan pake sang Paulus di Efesus<bt>The Lord uses Paulus in Efesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Waktu Paulus tenga di kota Efesus, dia biasa maso orang Yahudi dong pung ruma sambayang ko ajar sampe alus-alus so'al Tuhan Allah pung parenta. Dia ju omong sonde pake pele-pele. Dia bekin bagitu sampe tiga bulan.<bt>When Paulus left Efesus city, he usually entered the Yahudi people's worship houses to teach in detail about the Lord God's commands. And he spoke without holding any thing back. He did like that for three months.</bt><v n="9" />Ma ada orang yang sonde tarima dia pung ajaran, jadi dong bamalawan deng dia. Dong ju tusu-tusu orang di situ, ko dong jang iko Yesus pung Jalan Idop. Tagal itu, Paulus deng orang parcaya dong ondor kasi tenga itu ruma sambayang. Ais dong pi bakumpul di satu ruma sakola. Yang pung ruma tu, satu orang, nama Tiranus.<bt>But there were people who did not accept that teaching of his, so they opposed him. They also incited the people there, so that they not follow that Life Path of Yesus. Because of that, Paulus and the believers there reversed leaving behind that worship house. Then they went to gather in a school house. The one who owned that house, a person, named Tiranus.</bt><v n="10" />Paulus ajar bagitu sang dong, sampe dua taon; sampe orang-orang di propinsi Asia anteru su dengar Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae. Yang dengar tu, orang Yahudi, deng orang yang bukan Yahudi ju.<bt>Paulus taught like that to them, for two years; until various people throughout Asia province heard the Good Story about the Lord Yesus. Those who heard it, Yahudi people, and not Yahudi people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sakewa pung ana-ana dong<bt>Sakewa's children</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Itu waktu, Tuhan kasi kuasa sang Paulus ko dia bekin tanda heran macam-macam yang luar biasa.<bt>At that time, the Lord gave power to Paulus so that he did all sorts of miracles amazing/unusual.</bt><v n="12" />Conto ke, kalo orang pinjam ame Paulus pung ika kapala, ko, dia pung ika pinggang, ko dong taro itu barang di orang saki, tarús itu orang dong pung panyaki tu, ilang memang. Sampe setan-setan jahat ju kaluar kasi tenga orang dong.<bt>For example, a person touched Paulus' head cloth, or, his belt, in order to put that thing on sick people, then those illnesses of those people, disappeared right away. To the point that evil spirits also went out leaving behind people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lenso kapala = (kuno) = ika"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lenso kapala = (kuno) = ika kapala</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13-14" />Di situ, ada orang Yahudi dong pung kapala agama satu, deng dia pung ana laki-laki tuju orang. Itu kapala agama pung nama Sakewa. Dia pung ana dong biasa pi mana-mana ko usir kasi kaluar setan dari orang. Dong ju coba-coba usir setan pake Yesus pung nama bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu kanál sang itu Yesus yang Paulus kasi tau, ko? Sakarang beta parenta sang lu, pake Yesus pung nama, ko lu kaluar dari ini orang suda!&gt;&gt; Deng ada barapa orang pintar Yahudi laen yang coba bekin bagitu ju.<bt>There, there was an intelligent person of the Yahudi people, and his seven male children. That intelligent person's name was Sakewa. His children usually went all around to expel evil spirits from people. They also tried to expel spirits using Yesus' name saying, “You-pl know that Yesus whom that Paulus tells about, right? Now I order you, using Yesus' name, so that you leave this people (imperative)!” And there were several other Yahudi seers/magicians/trad.healers who also tried to do like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Di situ, ada orang Yahudi dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Di situ, ada orang Yahudi dong pung kapala agama satu, deng dia pung ana laki-laki tuju orang. Itu kapala agama pung nama Sakewa. Dia pung ana dong biasa pi mana-mana ko usir kasi kaluar setan dari orang. Dong ju coba-coba usir setan pake Yesus pung nama, bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu kanál sang itu Yesus yang Paulus kasi tau itu, ko? Sakarang beta parenta sang lu, pake Yesus pung nama, ko lu kaluar dari ini orang suda!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais satu kali, waktu Sakewa pung ana dong parenta bagitu, ju ada setan jahat yang manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta kanál sang Yesus. Beta ju kanál sang Paulus. Ma bosong ni, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>But one time, when Sakewa's sons were ordering/commanding like that, then there was an evil spirit who replied saying, “I know Yesus. I also know Paulus. But you-pl here, who.are.you?”</bt><v n="16" />Ais, itu orang yang takaná setan tu, mara mau mati. Ais dia kosi inja deng habok sang dong. Dia bekin luka sang dong, deng robe buang dong pung baju, sampe dong lari panta panas deng talanjang bulat dari itu ruma.<bt>Then that person who was affected by that spirit, got very angry. Then he kicked, stepped on and beat them up. He wounded them, and tore their clothes, to the point that they ran completely naked from that house.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kosi injak deng habok = kick,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kosi injak deng habok = kick, step on and beat up; lari panta panas ; talanjang bulat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais, itu carita tasiar dari mulu pi mulu, sampe samua orang di kota Efesus tau; bae orang Yahudi, deng yang bukan Yahudi dong ju tau. Pokonya, sapa sa yang dengar itu carita, dong jadi taku deng heran. Ju dong puji-puji sang Tuhan Yesus, tagal Dia su kasi kuasa bésar sang Paulus.<bt>So then that story spread from mouth to mouth, until all the people in Efesus city knew, both Yahudi people, and also those who were not Yahudi. The important/main thing, was that whoever heard that story, they became afraid and amazed. [EXEG: NRSV &amp; Message] And they praised the Lord Yesus, because He had given big power to Paulus.</bt><v n="18" />Ais orang yang baru parcaya dong tu, datang di dong pung sodara yang su parcaya dong, ko buka dong pung hati, ais mangaku dong pung sala.<bt>After that, those people who had just believed, came to their siblings who believed, to open their livers, then confess their sins.</bt><v n="19" />Dari dong ni, ada yang biasa pake ilmu-ilmu galáp. Ais dong kumpul ame dong pung buku-buku ilmu galáp, ko dong bakar bekin abis. Kalo itong itu buku-buku dong, dia pung harga, lima pulu ribu doi perak.<bt>From among them, there were those who had often used dark magic. So they gathered their dark magic books, so that they could completely burned them. If [we] count the price of those book, it's like fifty thousand silver coins.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ilmu galáp is broad and inclusive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ilmu galáp is broad and inclusive of other spec types</Message></Annotation><note reference="19:19" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dong bakar dong pung buku tu, ko jadi tanda bilang, dong sonde iko lai itu buku-buku dong pung isi. Satu doi perak tu, sama ke tukang pung gaji satu hari. Jadi buku-buku yang dong bakar itu, mahal mau mati.<bt>They burned those books of theirs, to.make a sign saying, they no longer followed those book's contents. One of those silver coins, like a worker's one day wage. Thus those books which they burned, were very valuable/expensive.</bt></note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02002b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Orang Efesus bakar dong pung buku-buku ilmu galáp dong<bt>Efesus people burning their dark magic books</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais ju orang dong bacarita Tuhan pung Kabar Bae siang-malam pi mana-mana. Ju orang yang parcaya dong tamba banya. Ko Tuhan pung Kata-kata tu, maso sampe di orang pung dalam hati deng pung pangaru bésar.<bt>Then people told the Lord's Good News day-night everywhere. And they people who believed, increased. So.that that speaking of the Lord's, entered to the point of reaching people's inner livers and had great influence. [NOTE: the first is focusing on the individual, the second on the community. The Gk is both vague and complicated, and translations go in many directions here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makan dalam sampe di orang pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">makan dalam sampe di orang pung hati = has great effect; afuk = sonde laku, tar pake</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makan dalam sampe di orang pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">makan dalam sampe di orang pung hati.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang bekin huru-hara di kota Efesus<bt>People make a riot in Efesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais itu, Paulus putus ko pulang pi Yerusalem. Ma dia pung hati rindu ko pi lebe dolo di propinsi Makedonia deng propinsi Akaya, baru dia mau jalan tarús pi Yerusalem. Dia su pikir memang bilang, &lt;&lt;Lebe bae, beta pi lia orang parcaya dong di ini tampa dong dolo. Te biar karmana ju, beta musti sampe di kota Roma.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Paulus decided to go to Yerusalem. But his liver longed to go first to Makedonia province and Akaya province, and then travel on to Yerusalem. He had thought beforehand saying, “It's better, if I go check up on the believers in these places first. Cuz (elaboration) however it might happen, I must arrive in Roma city. [EXEG: there is multiple support for ‘visit’. There is no commentary support for ‘complete the work’.]</bt><v n="22" />Ais dia suru dia pung tamán bajalan dua orang, andia Timotius deng Erastus, ko dong pi lebe dolo di Makedonia. Ma dia sandiri masi tenga lebe lama lai di propinsi Asia.<bt>Then he ordered his two travelling friends, that is Timotius and Erastus, for them to go ahead to Makedonia. But he himself still stayed longer in Asia province.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teman seperjalanan (BI)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">teman seperjalanan (BI)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Itu waktu, ada muncul parkara bésar di kota Efesus so'al Yesus pung Jalan Idop.<bt>At that time, a big litigation/problem arose in Efesus city about Yesus' Life Path.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="huru hara = keributan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">huru hara = keributan</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Itu parkara pung akar bagini: di situ, ada satu tukang perak, nama Demetrius. Dia biasa bekin ruma-ruma songgo kici dari perak, ko jual kasi sang orang Efesus ko dong songgo dong pung dewi satu, nama Artemis. Tagal dia pung usaha laku karás, jadi dia pake ana bua banya. Andia ko doi malele maso pi dia.<bt>That litigation's roots [origins] were like this: there, there was a silversmith, named Demetrius. He usually made small traditional.worship houses from silver, to sell to the people of Efesus for them to traditional.worship one of their gods, named Artemis. Because his efforts/business were extremely in demand, therefore he used very many underlings. That's why money flowed &amp; came in to him [= he made lots of money].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="malele = flow, mengalir; usaha ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">malele = flow, mengalir; usaha = hasil kerja; parkara pung akar = the thing that set off the dispute in the first place; peti doi = merchant's money box, cash box</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Ais satu kali, Demetrius kumpul ame dia pung tukang dong, deng tukang yang laen dong, ais dia omong sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa-bapa, deng sodara-sodara samua! Bosong su tau bilang, kotong pung idop jadi bae bagini ni, tagal doi banya malele dari kotong pung usaha ni.<bt>Then one time, Demetrius gathered his workers, and other workers, then he spoke to them saying, "Fathers, and all brothers/cousins! You all know that our-inc lives have been good in this way, because much money flows from our efforts/business here.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Would a person who follows Artemis,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Would a person who follows Artemis, refer to worshiping her as songgo? or is that only what Christians call it? Songgo derogatory.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Ma sakarang kotong su lia deng kotong pung mata biji sandiri, deng su dengar pake kotong pung talinga sandiri, itu gara-gara Paulus pung omong. Te dia pangaru orang banya dong bilang, barang-barang yang kotong bekin ni, sonde ada guna apa-apa. Dia bilang, patong yang kotong bekin ni, cuma dewa-dewi omong kosong sa.<bt>But now we have seen with our very own eyes, and heard with our very own ears, the consequences of Paulus' talk. Cuz (elaboration) he influences many people saying, this things which we make, are worthless. He says, these statues which we make, are only just lying/not.true gods.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gara-gara = akibat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">gara-gara = akibat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa, bukan cuma orang di kota Efesus sa, yang dengar sang dia, ma orang di anteru propinsi Asia ju su dengar.<bt>Naa, [+shift] it's not only just people in Efesus city, who listen to him, but people in the entire province of Asia have heard him.</bt><v n="27" />Jadi dengar bae-bae, ó! Nanti kotong ni mau jadi apa lai, kalo banya orang maen iko tarús sang Paulus dong? Su tantu orang sonde mau béli kotong pung hasil karjá ni lai! Inga, ó! Sakarang banya orang sémba sang kotong pung dewi manis, Artemis. Di anteru propinsi Asia, sampe di dunya pung huk-huk, ju orang dong maen datang ko puji sang dia di dia pung ruma songgo pusat, andia di kotong pung kota Efesus ni. Jadi, jang sampe orang su sonde toe sang dia, ju dong su sonde mau datang di sini lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>So listen carefully! Later what will we-inc here become, if many people continually keep on following Paulus (collective)? For sure people won't want to buy our handiwork anymore! Remember! Now many people worship our sweet/pretty godess, Artemis. In the entire province of Asia, until the world's corners, there are people who come to worship here in her central/main worship house, that is in our city of Efesus here. So (consequently), don't let it happen that people don't pay any attention to her, and they don't want to come here anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalo bagini-bagini ni, kotong su gulung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kalo bagini-bagini ni, kotong su gulung tikar ni = rugi besar, might as well pack up and go</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Dengar bagitu, ju dong pung hati panas memang. Ais dong batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Hidup Artemis! Artemis yang manis! Kotong orang Efesus puji-puji sang Artemis!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, then their livers were hot right away (=angry). Then then yelled out saying, “(Long) Live Artemis! Artemis who is sweet/pretty! We the people of Efesus praise Artemis!”</bt><v n="29" />Dengar orang batarea-batarea bagitu, ju orang mulai lari dari mana-mana ko pi bakumpul di situ, sampe itu kota ponu sesak deng orang dong. Ma dong samua babingung. Ju orang mulai rame-rame bekin kaco iko-iko jalan, sampe di kota pung tana lapang bésar.<bt>Hearing people yell like that, then people began to ran from everywhere to gather there, until the city with packed full with people. But they all were confused. And people began to make great chaos following along the road, until the city's big (open/meeting) field.</bt><note reference="19:29" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kota Efesus pung tana lapang bésar tu, dong pake ko 1) bekin rapat kota, 2) maen drama, deng 3) maen olaraga. 26.000 orang bisa bakumpul di dalam. Dia pung lokasi di gunung Pion pung kaki. Ais dia sonde jao beda dari satu stadion bola kaki jaman sakarang.<bt>That large meeting field in the city of Efesus, they used to 1) hold city meetings, 2) do dramas/plays, and 3) play sports. 26,000 people could gather inside it. Its location was at the foot of mount Pion. So then it is not too different from a soccer/football stadium these days.</bt></note>Dong ada tangkap dua orang ko hela bawa pi situ. Dong dua pung nama, Gayus deng Aristarkus. Orang dong tangkap sang dong, tagal dong dua ni, Paulus pung ana bua dari Makedonia.<bt>They captured two people to drag bring there. Their two names, Gaya and Aristarkus. People captured them, because these two, were Paulus' underlings/followers from Makedonia.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tana lapang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tana lapang</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Dengar bagitu, ju Paulus mau maso pi orang yang bekin kaco dong pung teng-tenga, ma orang parcaya di situ sonde kasi loos sang dia.<bt>Hearing like that, then Paulus wanted to enter into the midst of the people who making the chaos, but the believers there did not allow him.</bt><v n="31" />Ada barapa orang bésar dari propinsi Asia yang kanál bae deng Paulus. Dong suru orang ko pi kasi tau bilang, Paulus sonde bole maso pi itu tana lapang, di itu orang banya yang ada mangamok dong.<bt>There were several big people from Asis province who knew Paulus well. They also forbade saying Paulus should not enter into open field that crowd that was running amuck.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ais di itu tana lapang bésar tu, orang mulai cari itu parkara pung asal-mula. Ada yang batarea omong kosong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini!&gt;&gt; Yang laen ba'eki bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagitu!&gt;&gt; Padahal banya ju yang sonde tau itu parkara pung dudu-badiri karmana. Dong tu, cuma iko-iko rame sa.<bt>So in that big field there, people began to hunt for that litigation/problem's origins. There were those who yelled emptily (=w/o truth) saying, “It's like this!” The others called out saying, “It's like that!” However, there were many who did not know what that litigation's sit-stand (origin) was. Those, only just followed with great activity/ethusiasm.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parkara pung dudu-badiri = the cause"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">parkara pung dudu-badiri = the cause of the matter; iko-iko rame ; iko-iko arus = going with the flow</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Di situ ju ada orang Yahudi dong yang mulai taku, tagal dong pikir bilang, jang-jangan orang banya dong nanti tudu orang Yahudi jadi ini parkara pung tukang kipas dong. Andia ko dong sorong satu orang pi muka ko jadi dong pung jubir. Itu orang pung nama, Aleksander. Dong minta ko dia bela sang dong bilang, itu parkara, bukan orang Yahudi pung gara-gara. Ais Aleksander angka dia pung tangan ko dong jang baribut. Ais dia coba omong ko bela orang Yahudi dong.<bt>There there were also Yahudi people who became afraid, because they thought that it could happen that the crowd would accuse the Yahudi people as the fanners (provocators) of this litigation. That's why they pushed a person to the front to be their spokesperson. That person's name, was Aleksander. They asked they he defend them, saying that that litigation, was not the consequence of the Yahudi people. So Aleksander lifted his hand so that they would not be noisy. Then he tried to speak to defend the Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gara-gara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">gara-gara</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Ma waktu dong tau kalo dia tu, orang Yahudi, ju dong batarea tamba karás lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Hidup Artemis! Artemis yang manis! Kotong orang Efesus puji-puji sang Artemis!&gt;&gt; Dong batarea-batarea bagitu, sampe dua jam.<bt>But when they knew that that person, was an Yahudi person, then they yelled even louder saying, “Live Artemis! Artemis who is sweet/pretty! We Efesus people praise Artemis! They yelled and yelled like.like, for two hours.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalo here as complementiser"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kalo here as complementiser</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35-36" />Ais ju kapala pamarenta dari kota Efesus badiri ko omong kasi tanáng itu orang dong. Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Adi-kaka dong dari kota Efesus! Samua orang su tau bilang, kotong pung dewi Artemis pung model yang asli jato turun dari langit, ko datang di kotong sini. Jadi kotong orang Efesus ni, yang piara bae-bae sang dia. Sonde ada orang yang bisa cabu kotong pung hak jaga, tagal itu su jadi sajara yang samua orang su tau memang. Jadi, akurang ko bosong batarea bagini? Biar orang omong kosong iko dong pung mau, ma bosong sonde usa mangamok sambarang bagini!<bt>Then the head of the government from Efesus city stood to speak to calm the crowd. He spoke saying, “Younger-elder siblings from Efesus city! All people know that the original model/shape of our godess Artemis fell down form the sky, to come to us here. So (consequently) we Efesus people here, [are the ones] who have taken good care of her. No one can take away our right to guard [the goddess], because that has become history which all people truly know. So (consequently), why are you yelling like this? Even if people speak emptily (lie) following their own will, you don't need to run.riot for no reason like this!</bt><v n="37" />Bosong hela bawa ini orang dua di sini, sama ke dong ada bekin jahat. Padahal dong sonde curi apa-apa dari Artemis pung ruma songgo pusat. Dong ju sonde omong kasi jato kotong pung dewi pung nama bae. Jadi bosong mau lempar sala apa pi dong?<bt>You have dragged &amp; brought these two people here, like they have done something evil. However, they have not stolen a thing from Artemis' Main Worship House. They also have not spoken emptily (lied) to make our goddess' good name/reputation fall. So you want to throw what wrong at them? (accuse them of what?)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hoka = ajak, pange ko iko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hoka = ajak, pange ko iko</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Inga bae-bae, ó! Kotong ada pung tampa urus parkara. Orang yang urus parkara ju ada tunggu. Jadi, kalo Demetrius dong mau bekin parkara, na, dong musti iko dia pung atoran, ko bawa itu parkara pi tampa urus parkara.<bt>Remember this well! We have a place to handle litigations. People who handle litigations are also waiting. So (consequently), if Demetrius (collective) want to make a litigation, na, they must follow the regulations, and take that litigation to the place for handling litigations.</bt><v n="39" />Deng kalo ada hal laen yang dong mau angka, biar ko dong pi ba'ator deng tua-tua adat dong.<bt>And if there are other matters which they want to bring up, let them go arrange it with the traditional elders.</bt><v n="40" />Jang sampe pamarenta Roma mau lempar sala sang kotong, tagal ini kaco-balo ni. Kalo dong mau cari tau dia pung dudu-badiri, na, kotong mau manyao apa, coba? Te ini parkara sonde ada dia pung ujung-pohon na!&gt;&gt;<bt>Don't let it be that the Roma government want to accuse us, because of this commotion here. If they want to find out the cuz (elaboration), na, what will we reply, huh? Cuz (elaboration) this litigation obviously has no basis!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="huru-hara ; co &gt; coba (tag"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">huru-hara ; co &gt; coba (tag Q); dudu-badiri =cause ; ujung-pohon = basis</Message></Annotation><v n="41" />Omong abis bagitu, ju itu bos suru ko samua orang dong bubar. Ju dong bubar memang.<bt>Finishing speaking like that, then that boss ordered all the people to disperse. And they dispersed right away.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bubar = disperse"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bubar = disperse</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus dong pi kambali di propinsi Makedonia<bt>Paulus them go again to Makedonia province</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="20" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu orang su sonde bakaco-balo lai, itu kota Efesus tanáng kambali sama ke biasa. Ais Paulus kumpul ame orang parcaya dong di situ, ko kasi kuat dong pung hati. Ais itu, dia minta parmisi, ju dia barangkat pi propinsi Makedonia.<bt>When the people were no longer rioting, that city Efesus was peaceful again like usual. Then Paulus gathered the believers there, to strengthen/encourage their livers. After that, he requested permission (=took his leave), and he left to Makedonia province.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="panta tepos = plat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">panta tepos = plat</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Di situ, dia kuliling samua kampong, ko kasi kuat orang parcaya dong pung hati. Dia bekin bagitu, sampe dia maso di negrí Yunani.<bt>There, he went all around to all the villages, to encourage the believers. He did like that, until he entered Yunani country.</bt><v n="3" />Dia tenga di situ sampe tiga bulan. Ais dia siap-siap ko mau balayar pi propinsi Siria, ma dia dapa dengar bilang, orang Yahudi dong ada basakongkol ko mau bunu bekin mati sang dia. Dengar bagitu, ju dia sonde mau balayar langsung pi propinsi Siria. Jadi dia jalan kambali lewat propinsi Makedonia sa.<bt>There, he stayed three months. Then he got ready, to go sail to Siria province, but he heard people say, the Yahudi people were in agreement, to murder kill him. Hearing that, then he did not sail straight away to Siria province. So (consequently) he just travelled returning via Makedonia province.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="siap-siap = pack ; niat ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">siap-siap = pack ; niat = maksud</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ada satu rombongan kici yang iko sang Paulus. Andia, Timotius; bapa Pirus pung ana Sopater dari kota Berea; dua orang dari kota Tesalonika, nama Aristarkus deng Sekundus; satu orang dari kota Derbe, nama Gayus; deng dua orang dari propinsi Asia, andia Tikikus, deng Trofimus.<bt>There was a little group that went with Paulus. That is, Timotius; father Pirus' child Sopater from Berea city; two people from Tesalonika city, their names Aristarkus and Sekundus, one person from Derbe city, named Gayus; and two people from Asia province, that is Tikikus and Trofimus. [EXEG: in Gk 2 from Asia; not Tim.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ada satu rombongan kici yang iko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Ada satu rombongan kici yang iko sang Paulus. Andia, bapa Pirus pung ana Sopater dari kota Berea; dua orang dari kota Tesalonika, dong pung nama Aristarkus deng Sekundus; satu orang dari kota Derbe, nama Gayus; deng tiga orang dari propinsi Asia, andia Timotius, Tikikus, deng Trofimus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6" />Ais ju beta (andia Lukas yang tulis ini surat), katumu ulang deng Paulus di kota Filipi di propinsi Makedonia. Ju Paulus pung ana bua dong barangkat lebe dolo, ko dong tunggu sang botong di kota Troas di laut pung sablá. Waktu orang Yahudi pung hari-hari bésar Paska<bt>After that, I (that is Lukas who writes this letter), met again with Paulus. Then Paulus' underlings left first, to wait for us two in Troas city. When the Yahudi people's big days (holidays) Paska</bt><note reference="20:5-6" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;hari-hari bae Roti Sonde Pake Ragi&gt;, deng dia pung arti bilang, &lt;hari-hari bésar sadia Paska&gt;.<bt>The Yunani writings say, 'holidays of Bread Not Using Yeast', and it's meaning says 'holidays of preparing for Paska'.</bt></note>su lewat, botong dua nae kapal, ais balayar pi kota Troas. Itu waktu, botong balayar lima hari. Waktu botong sampe di Troas, botong turun dari kapal. Ais botong katumu ulang deng tamán laen dong, ju botong tenga di situ satu minggu.<bt>had past, we embarked on a ship in Filipi city in Makedonia province, then we sailed to Troas city on the other side of the sea. At that time, we sailed five days. When we arrived in Troas, we disembarked from the ship, and then we stayed there one week. [EXEG: on Unleavened Bread ~ Passover, see how NLT handled it &amp; our ftn.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pende kata = In short, pokonya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Pende kata = In short, pokonya</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nyong Yutikus jato dari jandela di kota Troas<bt>Young.man Yutikus falls from a window in Troas city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Itu hari, kaná hari Minggu. Paulus su putus bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong. Beso beta mau jalan tarús.&gt;&gt; Jadi botong, orang parcaya samua, bakumpul ko mau makan-makan. Tagal Paulus su mau jalan, jadi dia omong deng botong sampe tenga malam.<bt>That day, fell on Sunday. Paulus had decided saying, “Siblings. Tomorrow I want to continue travelling.” So we, all the believers, gathered to eat together. Because Paulus wanted to get going, therefore he spoke to us until the middle of the night.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin makan-makan = pesta (perpisahan)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bekin makan-makan = pesta (perpisahan)</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Botong ada bakumpul di satu ruma pung lante tiga. Itu malam dong bakar lampu bam-banya.<bt>We were gathered on the third floor of a house. That night they burnt many lamps.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lante"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lante</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Itu waktu, ada satu nyong, nama Yutikus,<bt>At that time, there was a young man, named Yutikus,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mati tenga tampa = doa (on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">mati tenga tampa = doa (on the spot); tatidor = OK; jato ~ *tajato</Message></Annotation><note reference="20:9" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Iko tulisan bahasa Yunani, <span class="Italic">&lt;Eutikus&gt;, </span>kotong baca bilang, &lt;Yutikus&gt;.<bt>According to the Yunani language writing, &lt;Eutikus&gt;, we read saying &lt;Yutikus&gt;.</bt></note>yang dudu di jandela. Dia ju iko dengar sang Paulus. Ma lama-lama dia pung mata barát, ju dia tatidor sonu. Takuju sa, dia jato dari itu jandela. Ju dia mati memang.<bt>who sat in the window. He also was listening to Paulus. But after awhile his eyes were heavy, and he fell sound asleep. Suddenly, he fell from that window. And he died straight away.</bt><v n="10" />Ais Paulus turun, ju paló ame itu nyong. Ais dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde usa taku. Dia idop.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Paulus went down, and held that young man. Then he spoke saying, “It's not necessary to be afraid. He lives.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paló ame"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">paló ame</Message></Annotation><v n="11-12" />Botong samua sanáng, tagal itu nyong idop. Ais dong bawa pulang sang dia pi dia pung ruma. Ju botong samua nae ulang pi lante atas, ko dudu makan sama-sama. Tarús Paulus sambung dia pung omong sampe pagi. Waktu matahari kaluar, ju botong minta parmisi, ko su mau barangkat.<bt>We were all happy, because that young.man lived. Then they brought him home to his house. And we all went upstairs again, to sit and eat together. Then Paulus continued his talking until morning. When the sun came out, then we took our leave, so that we could leave.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dari kota Troas pi kota Miletus<bt>From Troas city to Miletus city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais itu, botong ba'akór ko babagi jalan sampe botong bakatumu lai di satu kota, nama Asos. Ju botong nae kapal ko balayar pi Asos. Ma Paulus jalan kaki sa pi sana.<bt>After that, we agreed to split the journey until we met again in a city, named Asos. Then we got on a ship to sail to Asos. But Paulus just walked there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jalan kaki iko darat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">jalan kaki iko darat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="maps\Bible\HkKorPat.tif" rtfFormat="width:11cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Jalan dari Korintus pi Patara<bt>The road from Korintus to Patara</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Waktu botong katumu sang Paulus di Asos, ju dia nae di atas kapal, abis botong balayar tarús pi kota Metilene.<bt>When we met Paulus in Asos, and he got on the ship, then we sailed on to Metilene city.</bt><v n="15" />Dari Metilene, botong balayar tarús. Ais dia pung beso, botong balayar deka-deka deng satu pulo, nama Kios. Dia pung lusa, botong mangada pi pulo Samos. Dia pung tula, ju botong sampe di kota Miletus.<bt>From Metilene, we sailed on. Then the next day, we sailed close to an island, named Kios. On the second day, we were facing/in.front.of Samos island. On the third day, then we arrived at Miletus city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dia pung beso &gt; dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">dia pung beso &gt; dia pung lusa &gt; dia pung tula; mangada = faced, in front of</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ma Paulus su rindu ko capát-capát sampe di Yerusalem, ko dia bisa iko hari bésar Pentakosta di sana. Ais dia sonde mau buang waktu ko jalan nae pi kota Efesus, tagal dia su sonde ada waktu lai.<bt>But Paulus was longing to arrive quickly in Yerusalem, so that he could attend the Pentakosta holiday there. So then he didn't want to waste time to travel up to Efesus city, because he did not have any more time.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus ba'omong deng tua-tua Kristen di kota Efesus<bt>Paulus talks with the Kristen elders at (from?) Efesus city</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mate'a = berpisah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">mate'a = berpisah</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Jadi di Miletus, Paulus kirim kabar kasi sang tua-tua Kristen di Efesus, ko dong datang bakatumu deng dia.<bt>So (consequently) in Miletus, Paulus sent news to the Kristen elders in Efesus, for them to come meet him.</bt><v n="18" />Waktu dong datang sampe, ju Paulus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong samua. Bosong su tau beta pung cara idop, mulai dari hari partama beta inja kaki di propinsi Asia, sampe sakarang.<bt>When they arrived, then Paulus told them saying, “All siblings. You-pl know my way of life, begining from the first day I stepped on Asia province, until now.</bt><v n="19" />Bosong ju tau beta karjá banting tulang di bosong pung teng-tenga, ma beta sonde parná angka-angka diri. Dalam beta pung karjá ni, beta kasi tumpa aer mata banya, deng pikol susa sonde sadiki. Beta ju dapa sangsara banya dari orang Yahudi dong pung niat jahat.<bt>You also know my hard work in the midst of you, but I never raised myself up. In this work of mine, I poured out alot of tears, and (shoulder) carried not a little difficulty. I also got much tribulation from the Yahudi people's evil plans/intentions.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde angka-angka diri ; pukul dada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sonde angka-angka diri ; pukul dada = sombongkan diri ; karja banting tulang = karja karas ; cobaan = godaan, temptation ; niat ;</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Waktu beta ajar sang bosong, beta kasi kaluar samua yang bae, yang beta tau, kasi sang bosong. Deng beta ju ajar sang bosong di muka-muka. Beta ju pi di orang dong pung ruma satu-satu, ko kasi inga sang dong Tuhan pung mau.<bt>When I taught you, I put out all that I know. And I also taught you in front (openly and bravely). I also went to people's individual houses, to remind them of the Lord's will. [NOTE: ‘the Lord's will’ is the way to say ‘the things of God’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="di muka-muka = openly and bravely;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">di muka-muka = openly and bravely; po'a = pour out</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Beta ju kasi tau sang orang Yahudi, deng orang bukan Yahudi bilang, dong musti barenti dari dong pung sala-sala dong, ko bale iko sang Tuhan Allah. Deng dong ju musti parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus, yang hak parenta sang kotong.<bt>I also told the Yahudi people, and the people not Yahudi, that they must stop their sins, and follow the Lord God. And they also must believe in the Lord Yesus, who has the say-so/ordering rights over us-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@bale iko = bale has implication"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">@@bale iko = bale has implication of parna iko</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-06-10 05:47:07Z">inc</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Naa, beta mau kasi tau bagini: sakarang beta ada mau pi Yerusalem, tagal Tuhan pung Roh ada hela bawa sang beta ko pi sana. Beta iko sa, biar beta sonde tau nanti apa yang jadi deng beta di sana.<bt>Naa, I want to tell you like this: now I want to go to Yerusalem, because the Lord's Spirit has pulled me there. I will just go, even though I don't know what will happen to me there.</bt><v n="23" />Ma dari satu kota pi satu kota, Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi su kasi tau lebe dolo sang beta bilang, beta nanti maso bui deng pikol banya sangsara di sana.<bt>But from one city to the next, the Lord's Holy Spirit has told me ahead of time saying, I will later enter jail and (shoulder) carry much tribulation there.</bt><v n="24" />Beta su tau pasti bagitu, tagal Tuhan Yesus yang mua ini karjá di beta pung bahu, ko beta pi kasi tau Kabar Bae bilang, Tuhan ada sayang sang kotong, deng Dia pung hati ju bae sang kotong. Kalo beta sonde iko Dia pung mau, ko bekin abis Dia pung karjá ni, beta rasa beta pung idop sonde ada guna apa-apa.<bt>I know that for sure, because the Lord Yesus [is the one] who placed this work on my shoulders, so that I go tell Good News that the Lord loves us-inc, and His liver is good to us (=kind). If I don't follow His will, to finish this work of His, I feel my life will not have any worth/use. [EXEG: the ‘but’ between 22-23 is more important, reflecting the Gk /plein/ ‘except’. The Gk. /alla/ introducing vs.24 is a hypercoordinating polysemous 1) but, 2) and, 3) yet. In this context it hovers between meaning 2-3 best rendered ‘however’ or even ‘furthermore’. Stylistically KM and other lgs would find introducing both 23 &amp; 24 with ‘but’ to be inelegant. More importantly, the ‘but’ conjunction doesn't actually make sense in this context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="garis finis ~ fenis *** (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">garis finis ~ fenis *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="20:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Timotius 4:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Sakarang beta tau bilang, bosong su sonde akan lia sang beta lai. Andia, bosong yang beta su lama ajar so'al maso jadi Tuhan pung kelu.<bt>Now I am telling you will not see me any more. That is, you whom I have taught about the Lord's family for so long.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju beta su ajar sang bosong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Ju beta su ajar sang bosong di sini so'al Tuhan pung Kelu tu. Sakarang, beta pikir bosong sonde akan lia lai sang beta.</Message></Annotation><v n="26-28" />Tagal bagitu, dengar bae-bae. Beta su bekin abis beta pung karjá di bosong. Jadi sakarang bosong sandiri yang musti karjá tarús. Kalo ada orang dari bosong yang sonde maso Tuhan pung kelu, na, bosong yang tanggong-jawab! Te itu bukan beta pung sala. Inga bae-bae! Te beta su kasi tau memang Tuhan pung mau samua sang bosong. Sonde ada satu hal ju yang beta sambunyi sang bosong. Jadi bosong musti jaga bae-bae bosong pung idop sandiri, deng piara bae-bae samua orang yang Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi ada suru bosong ko jaga. Jang lupa bilang, Tuhan Yesus su mati ko bayar abis itu orang dong, deng Dia pung dara sandiri. Dia ju tunju sang bosong ko jaga sang dong, sama ke gambala piara dia pung domba dong.<bt>Because of that, listen carefully. I have finished my work among you. So (consequently) now you yourselves must continue working. If there is someone among you who has not enter the Lord's family, na, [it's] you who are responsible! Cuz (elaboration) that is not my wrong. Because of that, listen carefully. I have finished my work among you. So now, you yourselves must continue working. If there is someone among you who has not enter the Lord's family, na, [it's] you who are responsible! Cuz (elaboration) that is not my wrong. So you must guard well your own lives, and carefully take care of all the people whom the Lord's Holy Spirit has ordered you take care of. Don't forget that the Lord Yesus has completely paid for those people, with His own blood. He has also shown you so that you watch/guard/care them, like a shepherd takes.care.of his sheep.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="foo = menggiring, gembalakan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">foo = menggiring, gembalakan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Jadi sakarang beta kasi tenga sang bosong. Ma inga, é! Nanti ada orang datang ko ajar sambarang-sambarang di bosong pung teng-tenga. Dong maso sama ke anjing jahat yang maso pi dalam domba pung kandang.<bt>So (consequently) now I am leaving you. But remember! Later there will be people coming to teach any.old.thing (incorrectly) in the midst of you. They will come in like evil dogs who enter into the sheep cage/pen.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="herder = large dog, German shepherd,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">herder = large dog, German shepherd, fig. for vicious dog</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Ada orang putar-balek bagitu yang datang dari luar. Ma inga, te ada yang muncul dari bosong pung teng-tenga ju. Dong ajar sonde batúl sang bosong. Dong mau ko orang iko sang dong sa. Andia ko dong coba-coba hela orang ko jang iko sang Yesus lai.<bt>There were me lying people like that who come from outside. But remember. There will also be those who arise in your midst. And they will teach incorrectly to you. They just want people to follow them. That's why they try to pull people to not follow Yesus anymore.</bt><v n="31" />Tagal bagitu, bosong musti jaga diri bae-bae. Jang lupa, te beta su tenga sama-sama deng bosong sampe tiga taon. Beta ju kasi nasiat sang bosong siang-malam, deng sonde pikir beta pung cape. Beta pung aer mata su jato bam-banya, tagal bosong.<bt>Because of that, you must watch yourselves carefully. Don't forget, cuz (elaboration) I have lived together with you for three years. I also have given you advice day-night, and have not thought about my tiredness. Many of my tears have fallen, because of you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde pikir cape"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sonde pikir cape</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Sakarang kotong su mau bapisa. Jadi beta sarakan sang bosong samua pi Tuhan pung tangan, ko Dia piara sang bosong. Deng bosong musti pegang kuat-kuat samua yang beta su kasi tau sang bosong dari partama so'al Tuhan pung hati bae. Tuhan ada pung kuasa ko bekin kuat sang bosong. Dia ju su janji ko kasi berkat sang Dia pung orang dong. Jadi, kalo bosong iko tarús sang Dia deng hati yang barisi, tantu bosong ju dapa Dia pung berkat.<bt>Now we want to separate. So (consequently) I surrender you all into the Lord's hand, so that He watches you. And you must hold on tightly all that I have told your from the first, about the Lord's good heart. The Lord has power to strengthen you. He also has promised to bless His people. So (consequnetly), if you continually follow Him with a clean liver, surely you will get His blessing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Waktu beta karjá di bosong pung teng-tenga, beta sonde kapingin ame bosong pung barang satu apa ju. Beta sonde minta coba bosong pung barang mas, ko perak, ko pakean, ko apa sa.<bt>When I worked in the midst of you, I did not desire even one of your things. I did not ask for you gold things, or silver, or clothes, or anything.</bt><v n="34" />Bosong ju tau, waktu beta tenga deng bosong, beta karjá banting tulang satenga mati ko biar beta bisa dapa idop. Bukan cuma buat beta sandiri sa, ma beta ju karjá ko kasi idop dong yang iko sang beta.<bt>You also know, when I lived with you, I worked extremely hard so that I could live. Not only me myself, but I also worked to give life [living needs] to those who follow me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buat = Prep BEN"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">buat = Prep BEN</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Jadi, deng samua hal ni, beta su kasi tunju jalan ko bosong ju iko tolong orang kasian yang sonde mampu dong. Inga bae-bae Tuhan Yesus pung omong bilang, &lt;Ada lebe bae kotong kasi, daripada kotong tarima.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), with all these things here, I have shown the way for you to also follow helping the poor people who cannot afford things. Remember well, the Lord Yesus' talk saying, 'It's better for us to give, than for us to receive.'</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Paulus omong abis bagitu, ju dia tikam lutut, ais sambayang sama-sama deng dong, deng minta ko Tuhan jaga sang dong samua.<bt>Paulus finished talking like that, then he knelt, then prayed together with them, and asked that the Lord watch over them all.</bt><v n="37-38" />Ju dong samua pung hati susa, tagal Paulus su omong bilang, nanti dong su sonde bakatumu deng dia lai. Jadi waktu dong su mau bapisa, ju dong paló-ciom sang Paulus, deng manangis maskakeduk. Ais ju dong antar sang botong<bt>And all their livers were in difficulty, because Paulus has spoken saying later they would not meet him anymore. So (consequently) when they were about to separate, then they embraced-kissed Paulus, and cried in loud.sobs. Then they escorted us-exc</bt><note reference="20:37-38" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">&lt;&lt;Botong&gt;&gt; di sini tu, andia Lukas, yang tulis ini surat, Paulus, deng dong pung tamán.<bt>“We’ here, is Lukas, who wrote this letter, Paulus, and their friends.</bt></note>pi di kapal.<bt>to the ship. [EXEG: ‘us’ from 21:1. See ftn.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="susa tar ontong = ; manangis"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">susa tar ontong = ; manangis maskakeduk = mengangis terisak-isak; pakean ~ pakian; ciom</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus dong kambali pi Yerusalem<bt>Paulus them return to Yerusalem</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="21" />
      <v n="1" />Abis bapamit deng tua-tua Kristen dari Efesus dong deng hati barát, ju botong nae kapal, ais balayar langsung pi pulo Kos. Dia pung beso, ju botong balayar sampe di pulo Rodos. Dari situ, botong balayar tarús pi kota pelabuan Patara.<bt>After taking leave from the Kristen elders from Efesus with heavy livers, then we embarked on the ship, and sailed on to Kos island. The next day, then we sailed until Rodos island. From there, we sailed on to the harbour at Patara city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mate'a = pamit (not known by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">mate'a = pamit (not known by UNS's)</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Di situ botong turun dari itu kapal. Ais botong ganti kapal laen yang mau balayar pi propinsi Fenisia deka deng Siria. Jadi botong nae itu kapal, ais langsung angka jangkar.<bt>At there we disembarked from that ship. Then we changed to a different ship that was to sail to Fenisia province close to Siria. So we embarked on that ship, and straight away raised anchor.</bt><v n="3" />Sonde lama, ju botong lia pulo Siprus di botong pung sablá kiri, ma botong lewat sa, ju balayar tarús sampe botong buang jangkar di kota Tirus di propinsi Siria. Di situ, dong mau kasi turun muatan dari itu kapal.<bt>Not long (=soon), then we saw Siprus island on our left side, but we just passed it, and we sailed on until we threw out the anchor at Tirus city in Siria province. There, they wanted to take cargo off that ship.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buang jangkar ; bongkar muatan for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">buang jangkar ; bongkar muatan for some UNS's has dual sense of both loading and unloading</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00214C.tif" rtfFormat="width:11cm;textWrapping:none">Bongkar muatan dari kapal<bt>Taking cargo off the ship</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Tagal dong masi kasi turun muatan, ju botong turun ko pi cari orang parcaya dong. Dapa katumu sang dong, ais botong tenga deng dong sampe satu minggu. Orang di situ dong su dapa sein dari Tuhan pung Roh, ko larang sang Paulus bilang, dia sonde usa pi Yerusalem lai.<bt>There, they were still taking the cargo off, so we go off to go find the believers. Finding them, then we stayed with them for one week. The people there had received a sign from the Lord's Spirit, to forbid Paulus saying, he did not need to go to Yerusalem anymore. [EXEG: NRSV, NLT, CEV. 2 Consultants encouraged us towards the current rendering in the Kupang. It seems the Greek text is clearly attributing the source of their message for Paul as being from the HS. Let's take the HS as the genuine source of the message. So it seems that Paul is now left to reexamine and discern by faith whether his earlier prompting/ instructions to go to Jerusalem were still in effect, whether this news of certain trouble ahead is meant simply as a test of his resolve, or whether he should take it at face value and bail out. Regardless, it would have made him review, “What did God want me to do? What does God want me to do?” A healthy position to be in.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kusu-kusu = bisik, whisper; sein ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kusu-kusu = bisik, whisper; sein = sign (Bel.), tanda</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ma abis satu minggu, ju botong kambali pi kapal. Orang parcaya dong samua, laki-laki parampuan, kici-bésar, tua-muda, dong antar sang botong sampe di pante. Di situ, botong samua tikam lutut ko sambayang sama-sama.<bt>But after one week, then we returned to the ship. All the believers, male female, little big, old young, they escorted us to the beach. There we all knelt to pray together.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="laki-laki parampuan, kici-besar, tua-muda,;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">laki-laki parampuan, kici-besar, tua-muda,;</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Abis bapamit, tarús botong nae pi kapal, deng dong samua pulang.<bt>After saying goodbye, then we embarked on the ship, and they all went home.</bt></p>
    <fig path="maps\Bible\HkPatYer.tif" rtfFormat="width:6cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Dari Patara pi Yerusalem<bt>From Patara to Yerusalem</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Botong barangkat dari Tirus, ais botong singga di kota Ptolemais. Di situ, botong turun dari kapal, ju botong pi cari katumu deng orang parcaya dong. Botong dapa sang dong, jadi botong tenga deng dong satu hari.<bt>We left from Tirus, then we stopped at Ptolemais city. There, we got down from the ship, and we went to find the believers. We found them, then we stayed with them one day.</bt><v n="8" />Dia pung beso, botong barangkat dari situ, ju botong sampe di kota Kaisarea. Di situ, botong pi manumpang di Filipus pung ruma. Dia tu, yang mula-mula bawa Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae di situ. Deng dia tu, satu dari itu tuju orang yang dong pili ame ko bagi makanan kasi mama-mama janda di Yerusalem.<bt>The next day, we left from there, and we arrived at Kaisarea city. There, we stayed (as guests) at Filipus' house. He there, [was the one] who originally brought the Lord Yesus' Good Story there. And he there, was one of those seven people whom they chose to distribute food to widows in Yerusalem.</bt><note reference="21:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 6:5, 8:5</note><v n="9" />Filipus ada pung ampa ana nona. Tuhan Allah ada pake sang dong, jadi jubir ko kasi tau Dia pung pasán dong.<bt>Filipus had four young.girl daughters. The Lord God used them, to tell His messages/instructions.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Waktu botong su tenga deng dong barapa hari, ju satu orang, nama Agabus, datang dari propinsi Yudea. Tuhan ada pake sang dia, jadi jubir ko kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán dong.<bt>But when we had stayed with them for several days, then one person, named Agabus, came from Yudea province. The Lord was using him, to be His spokesperson to tell the Lord's messages/instructions.</bt><note reference="21:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 11:28</note><v n="11" />Dia datang langsung sang botong. Ais dia ame Paulus pung ika pinggang, ju ika dia pung kaki-tangan sandiri pake itu ika pinggang. Ais dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi bilang bagini: &lt;Ini ika pinggang pung tuan ni, nanti orang Yahudi dong ika rorobi ame sang dia bagini di Yerusalem. Abis dong sarakan sang dia pi orang bukan Yahudi dong pung tangan.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>He came straight away to us. Then he took Paulus' belt, and tied his own hands feet using that belt, then he spoke saying, “The Lord's Holy Spirit says like this: ‘The owner of this belt here, later the Yahudi people will tie him up like this in Yerusalem. Then they will surrender him to the hands of the non-Yahudi people.’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rorobi ~ feo = lilit (BI),"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">rorobi ~ feo = lilit (BI), bind up by winding/tying around; foe = kumat, kambuh</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dengar itu orang omong bagitu, ju botong samua minta sang Paulus deng paksa, ko dia jang pi Yerusalem lai. Botong yang jadi dia pung ana bua deng orang-orang parcaya dari itu tampa, minta bagitu.<bt>Hearing that person speak like that, all of us asked Paulus earnestly so that he would not go on to Yerusalem. We who were his followers and the believers in that place asked that.</bt><v n="13" />Ma dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Akurang ko bosong manangis bagitu? Bosong su bekin beta pung hati jadi barát. Bagini! Ada orang yang memang sonde suka sang beta, tagal beta iko sang Tuhan Yesus. Ma biar dong ika rorobi sang beta, ko, bunu bekin mati sang beta, ko bekin karmana ju, beta su siap tarima.&gt;&gt;<bt>But he replied saying, “No! Why are you crying like that? You have made by liver heavy. It's like this! There are truly people who are not happy with me, because I follow the Lord Yesus. But even if they tie me up, or, murder killing me, or do what ever to me, I am ready to accept it.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati noe ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hati noe =</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Waktu botong tau bilang, Paulus sonde mau dengar sang botong lai, ju botong kasi biar sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Neu! Biar Tuhan pung mau sa yang jadi.&gt;&gt;<bt>When we knew that Paulus did not want to hear us anymore, then we allowed him saying, “Ok.then! May it just be the Lord's will that happens.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan pung mau (sang Paulus) karmana,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Tuhan pung mau (sang Paulus) karmana, ju botong iko sa. / Mana-mana sa, Tuhan pung mau, ju bae.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus dong sampe di Yerusalem<bt>Paulus them arrive in Yerusalem</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Su barapa hari botong tenga di Kaisarea, ju botong manyimpan barang-barang, ais barangkat pi Yerusalem.<bt>After several days of staying in Kaisarea, then we packed up our stuff, then we left for Yerusalem.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bapák-pák barang = manyimpan barang (KM"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bapák-pák barang = manyimpan barang (KM takes O; AM does not require it)@@</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ada barapa orang parcaya dari Kaisarea yang iko sama-sama deng botong ju. Dong antar sang botong sampe di satu ruma, ko botong tidor manumpang di situ. Dia pung tuan ruma, nama Manason. Dia dari pulo Siprus. Deng dia su lama iko sang Tuhan Yesus.<bt>There were also several believers from Kaisarea who went together with us. They escorted us to a house, so that we could sleep (at house, without pay) there. The house owner, named, Manason. He was from Siprus island. And he had followed the Lord Yesus for a long time.</bt><v n="17" />Waktu botong sampe di Yerusalem, samua sodara orang parcaya dong sambut sang botong deng hati sanáng.<bt>When we arrived in Yerusalem, all the fellow believers greeted us with happy livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sambut = tarima, welcome"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sambut = tarima, welcome</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus dong pi lia sang Yakobis<bt>Paulus (coll) go to see Yakobis</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Dia pung beso, botong samua pi katumu deng Yakobis. Deng samua tua-tua Kristen ju ada bakumpul di situ.<bt>The next day, we all went to meet with Yakobis. And all the Kristen elders were also gathered there.</bt><v n="19" />Botong bakasi hormat satu deng satu, ais Paulus carita panjang lebar samua yang Tuhan su bekin di mana-mana, kasi orang bukan Yahudi dong. Bilang, Tuhan Yesus su buka jalan ko dong parcaya sang Dia. Dia ju carita karmana Tuhan su pake sang dia deng dia pung tamán samua dalam ini karjá.<bt>We gave honor to each one, then Paulus told long wide all that the Lord had done everywhere, for the non-Yahudi people. That, the Lord Yesus had opened the path for them to believe, and to live continually with the Lord God, as long as they stopped their sins. He also told how the Lord had used him, and all his friends in this work.</bt><v n="20" />Dengar abis Paulus pung carita tu, dong samua puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>After finishing hearing that story of Paulus', they all praised the Lord God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais dong kasi tau sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu Paul! Asal bu tau sa, ada ribu-ribu orang Yahudi ju su parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus. Dong ju masi pegang karás itu atoran dong yang ba'i Musa kasi turun sang kotong.<bt>Then they told Paulus saying, “Elder.brother Paul! As long as elder.brother (=you) know, there are thousands of Yahudi people who have believed in the Lord Yesus. They also still hold tightly to the regulations which Gf/Ff Musa brought down to us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maliung = juta, million"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">maliung = juta, million</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ma ada orang yang su bawa-bawa mulu di sini bilang, bu suka ajar sang orang Yahudi dong di tampa-tampa laen bilang, dong sonde parlú iko lai ba'i Musa pung atoran agama dong. Dong ju lapor bilang, bu su larang sang dong, ko sonde usa bekin iko adat sunat kasi dong pung ana laki-laki dong. Deng bu ju ada larang ko orang sarani dong sonde usa iko lai kotong orang Yahudi pung adat laen dong.<bt>But there are people who have brought word here saying, elder.brother (=you) like to teach the Yahudi people in other places saying, they don't need to follow Gf/Ff Musa's religious regulations any longer. They also report that, elder.brother (=you) forbids them, so that they don't need to do the circumcision ritual for their male children. And elder.brother (=you) also forbids so that the baptised people don't need follow the other customs of us Yahudi people</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bawa-bawa mulu = gossip, bawa kabar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bawa-bawa mulu = gossip, bawa kabar angin, suara burung; mulu badodol = gossip; ana nyong = teenager, unmarried; ana laki-laki = boy</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Naa, inga, ó! Su tantu orang Yahudi dong nanti dengar bilang, bu Paul su ada di sini. Deng orang-orang yang su dengar itu kabar angin dong, tantu dong mara. Jadi kotong mau cari jalan kaluar karmana?<bt>Naa, remember! Surely the Yahudi people will hear that elder.brother Paul is here. And the people who have heard those rumours, surely they will be angry. So (consequently), what are we going to do about it?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Jadi botong usul bagini: ada ampa orang dari botong yang su ika janji deng Tuhan. Sakarang dong mau cukur bekin polik dong pung kapala, ko bekin tanda bilang, dong su bekin iko abis dong pung janji.<bt>So (consequently), we suggest like this: there are four people from you who have tied a promise with the Lord. Now they want to shave make bald their heads, to make a sign that they have done according to their promise.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalár = genap"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kalár = genap</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Naa, kalo bisa, bu Paul maso sama-sama deng dong pi Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Bu ju iko sang dong, ko bekin iko itu adat bekin barisi diri. Bu ju musti tanggong bayar dong pung ongkos bekin iko itu adat. Kalo bu bekin bagitu, nanti orang dong tau bilang, bu masi pegang karás atoran agama Yahudi yang ba'i Musa kasi turun sang kotong. Deng dong ju nanti tau itu carita yang bilang, bu larang orang ko dong jang iko adat Yahudi tu, omong kosong samua!<bt>Naa, if possible, elder.brother Paul enter together with them to the Lord God's temple. Elder.brother also follow them, to do according to that ritual of making oneself clean. Elder.brother also must be responsible for paying their cost of doing that ritual. If elder.brother does like that, later people will know that, elder.brother still holds tightly to the Yahudi religious regulations which Gf/Ff Musa brought down to us. And they also will know that that story that says, elder.brother forbids people to not follow Yahudi rituals, it's all empty talk (lies)!</bt><note reference="21:23-24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 6:13-21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ma buat orang bukan Yahudi yang su parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus, kotong su kirim surat kasi sang dong. Kotong su kasi tau kotong pung putusan tempo hari tu bilang, dong sonde parlú iko kotong pung atoran adat Yahudi samua. Yang dong musti inga ko bekin iko, andia: jang maen serong deng orang yang bukan dong pung laki ko dong pung bini. Jang campor deng barang sosonggo, deng jang makan yang bekin sodara orang Yahudi dong noju sang bosong. Andia: jang makan daging sosonggo; jang makan dara; deng jang makan daging dari binatang yang mati taceke, sampe dia pung dara sonde malele kaluar.&gt;&gt;<bt>But for people who are not Yahudi who already believe in the Lord Yesus, we-inc have already sent a letter to them. We-inc have told them our decision at that time that, they don't need to follow all of you Yahudi customs. Those which they must remember and follow are: don't play off-track/deviate (sexually) with a person who is not their husband or their wife. Don't get involved with traditional worship things, and don't eat things which make your Yahudi siblings repulsed by you-pl. That is (specifically): don't eat traditional-worship meat; don't eat blood; and don't eat meat from animals that died of strangulation, with result that its blood hasn't flowed out.” [EXEG: Higher level cohesion with 15:20, 29, bringing out reason so not seem petty. See also: the Message “avoid serving food offensive to Jewish Christians”. TH, MC. TH, TRT and Bruce also point out that the Jewish theological problem with ‘strangled’ was that the blood hadn't been drained out, so that is explicated, and is familiar to people in contact with Muslims.] [DISCOURSE: reordered for info load and RL hierarchy.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) conto ke to andia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) conto ke to andia in last sentence; note expanded</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-08-23 01:53:08Z" /></Annotation><note reference="21:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 15:29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ais Paulus tarima bae dong pung usul. Jadi dia pung beso, dia deng itu ampa orang dong pi sama-sama di Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ju bekin barisi dong pung diri iko atoran agama Yahudi. Ais itu, Paulus kasi tau kapala agama di situ bilang, masi barapa hari lai, baru dong bekin kalár dong pung janji. Te kalo itu waktu su abis, na, dong satu-satu musti kasi maso dong pung persembahan sang Tuhan.<bt>Then Paulus accepted their suggestion. So (consequently) the next day, he and those four people went together to the *Temple, and they cleansed/purified themselves following the regulations of the Yahudi religion. After that, Paulus told the religious leader of that place saying, there were still several more days before they would fulfill/complete their promise/vow. Cuz (elaboration) when that time was over, na, each of them must put in their offering to the Lord.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="korban = kecelakaan, in context of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">korban = kecelakaan, in context of gifts, worship, most UNS's associate with animals before thinking about money or other stuff; korban bakaran</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus kaná tangkap di Ruma Sambayang Pusat<bt>Paulus is captured in the Temple</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27-29" />Waktu mau amper abis tuju hari yang dong janji ko bekin abis itu adat, ada barapa orang Yahudi dari propinsi Asia yang dapa lia sang Paulus jalan pi dalam kota Yerusalem sama-sama deng dia pung tamán satu, nama Trofimus. Trofimus ni, asal dari kota Efesus, deng dia bukan orang Yahudi. Jadi waktu dong lia Paulus maso pi dalam Ruma Sambayang Pusat, dong kira, dia ada bawa dia pung tamán Trofimus pi di situ ju. Padahal orang bukan Yahudi sonde bole maso pi situ. Ju dong ame ini hal jadi alasan, ko bekin parkara. Jadi dong tusu-tusu orang di situ, ko tangkap ame sang Paulus. Deng dong batarea kasi tau orang di situ bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Orang Isra'el dong! Mari ko tolong sang botong dolo. Ini dia, orang yang maen ajar di mana-mana bilang, angka buang sa, kotong pung adat Yahudi. Dia ju omong tar bae so'al Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat ni. Ais sakarang lai, dia maso ko mau bekin kamomos Tuhan pung tampa yang barisi ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>When the seven days were almost over in which they promised to finish that ritual, there were several Yahudi people from Asia province who saw Paulus walking in Yerusalem city together with a friend of his, named Trofimus. This Trofimus, originally from Efesus city, and he was not a Yahudi person. So (consequently) when they saw Paulus enter the Temple, they thought, he was bringing his friend Trofimus to there also. However non Yahudi people cannot enter there. And they took this matter to become a reason, to make a litigation. So they poked/incited the people there, to capture Paulus. And they yelled telling peole there saying, “We! Israel people! Come help us. This him, [he is] a person who keeps teach everywhere saying, just pick up and throw away, our Yahudi traditions. And he speaks bad about this Temple of the Lord's. And what's more now, he has entered to defile the Lord's place that is holy/clean here!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="padahal = signals background explanation @@"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">padahal = signals background explanation @@</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 20:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Dengar bagitu, ju satu kota Yerusalem pung isi dong pung hati panas mau mati. Ais orang banya dong lari pi makarubu di Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Ju dong tangkap ame sang Paulus, ais dong hela raroso kasi kaluar sang dia dari itu Ruma Sambayang. Ais ju dong tutu memang pintu-pintu dong.<bt>Hearing that, then the contents of entire city of Yerusalem's (=all the people) livers were very exceedingly hot (=angry). Then many people went running crowding around the Temple. And they captured Paulus, then dragged him along taking him out of the Temple. Then they immediately shut the main gates.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="why did they close the doors?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">why did they close the doors? so orang non-yahudi would not enter? According to trans handbook -- so Paul would not be able to get back inside and seek refuge as they could not kill someone in the temple.</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:30" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada orang yang pintar dong tulis bilang, sonde bole bunu bekin mati orang di dalam Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Deng kalo ada orang sapa sa, yang maso pi dalam ko pegang tandok di meja persembahan, iko agama Yahudi pung atoran, na, orang sonde bole bekin apa-apa sang itu orang. Andia ko orang Yahudi dong sonde mau Paulus dapa maso kambali pi dalam Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal. Jadi dong tutu pintu-pintu hek dong.<bt>There are experts who write saying, it is not allowed to kill a person in the Temple. And if a person whoever, who enters in to hold the horns of the sacrificing table, following the Yahudi religious regulations, na, people cannot do anything to that person. [NOTE: changed from him 2018, because for some it was ambiguous the horns, or the person.] That's why the Yahudi people did not want Paulus to enter again into the Temple's yard. So (consequently), they closed the main gates.</bt></note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02013b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none;horizontalPosition:center">Dong tangkap sang Paulus<bt>They capture Paulus</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Waktu dong batasibu ko mau bunu bekin mati sang dia, ju tantara Roma pung komandán di situ, dengar itu kaco-balo.<bt>When they were busy trying to kill him, then the Roma military commander there, heard that chaos.</bt><v n="32" />Ju dia pange memang dia pung tantara, deng dong pung bos-bos dong, ko dong maso pi dalam orang banya yang batasibu dong. Waktu dong dapa lia tantara deng komandán bésar datang, ju dong barenti papoko sang Paulus.<bt>And he immediately called his soldiers, and their bosses, for them to go into the crowd that was acting like busybodies. When they saw the soldiers and the big commander coming, then they stopped beating Paulus.</bt><v n="33" />Ais ju itu komandán tangkap sang Paulus, deng suru ko dong ika sang dia pake rante besi dua. Dong ika abis, ju dia tanya itu orang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang ni, sapa? Dia ada bekin sala apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>And then that commander captured Paulus, and ordered that they tie him using two iron chains. They finished tieing him, then he asked those people saying, “This person here, who.is.he? What wrong has he done?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ma dong sonde manyao deng satu suara. Ada yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia su bekin bagini.&gt;&gt; Ma ada yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia su bekin bagitu.&gt;&gt; Ais itu komandán jadi pusing. Dia sonde mangarti itu parkara pung ujung-pohon, tagal orang banya dong ada batarea rame-rame. Andia ko dia suru ko dong bawa Paulus pi benteng.<bt>But they didn't answer with one voice. There were those who said, “He has done like this.” But there were those who said, “He has done like that.” Then that commander became confused. He didn't understand that litigation's origin, because the crowd was yelling wildly. That's why he ordered that they take Paulus to the fort.</bt><v n="35-36" />Tantara dong hela bawa Paulus, ma itu orang dong iko sama-sama, deng mangamok tamba lai. Waktu mau nae tangga, itu orang dong sarbú pi muka. Sampe tantara dong tarpaksa musti dorok sang Paulus, ko biar itu orang dong jang ru'i bekin ancor sang dia. Ju dong batarea karás-karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Bunu sang dia! Bunu sang dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>The soldiers pulled brought Paulus, but those people followed them, and became even more riotous. When wanting to go up the stairs, those people surged forward to the front. To the point that the soldiers were forced to carry Paulus, so that those people didn't pluck him out and destroy him. And they yelled loudly saying, “Murder him! Murder him!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dorok = manner is not clear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">dorok = manner is not clear to UNS's of all backgrounds, but carry is, and they get from context that soldiers protected Paul; fi'i = wihik; sarbu = surge forward</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus minta bela diri di muka orang banya<bt>Paulus requests to defend himself in front of many people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Waktu dong su mau maso pi dalam itu benteng, ju Paulus minta sang itu komandán pake bahasa Yunani bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Beta bole omong sadiki, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>When they were about to enter into that fort, then Paulus asked that commander saying, “Father! May I speak a little bit, ok?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dengar Paulus omong bagitu, ju komandán takuju, ais dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu ju tau bahasa Yunani? Karmana ko lu bisa omong bahasa Yunani?<bt>Hearing Paulus talk like that, then the commander was startled, and he asked saying, “You also know the Yunani language? How is it that you can speak the Yunani language?</bt><v n="38" />Kalo bagitu, beta su sala kira. Beta pikir lu ni, itu orang Masir yang tempo hari tusu-tusu orang ko dong barontak. Ais dia ame bawa ampa ribu orang yang pegang sanjata ko dong pi tampa kosong. Ma lu ni, bukan dia, aa?&gt;&gt;<bt>If it's like that, I was mistaken. I thought that you here, were that Masir person who earlier incited people so that they would riot. Then he took four thousand people who held weapons for them to run hide in an empty place. But you here, you're not him, right?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ju Paulus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde, bapa! Beta ni, orang Yahudi. Beta pung mama barana sang beta di kota Tarsus, di propinsi Kilikia. Beta minta bapa kasi loos sang beta, ko beta bisa omong deng ini orang banya dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Paulus replied saying, “No, father! I here, am a Yahudi person. My mama gave birth to me in Tarsus city, in Kilikia province. I request that father (=you) allow me, so that I can speak with these many people here.” [EXEG: ‘citizen of an important city’ undertranslated so as not to make heavy info load.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Itu komandán satuju. Ais Paulus badiri di atas tangga, deng angka dia pung tangan, ko minta dong diam, ko dia mau omong. Ais ju dia angka omong pake dong pung bahasa Aram sandiri. (Te di situ, orang Ibrani dong omong pake bahasa Aram.)<bt>That commander agreed. Then Paulus stood on top of the stairs, and lifted his hand, to ask them to be quiet, so that he could speak. And he began to speak using their own language Aram. (Because there, the Ibrani people spoke using the Aram language.)</bt><note reference="21:40" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kata &lt;orang Ibrani&gt; deng &lt;orang Yahudi&gt; tu, dua nama kasi satu bangsa.<bt>The Ibrani people and the Yahudi people, are two names for the same people/race.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus bela diri [\s2]<bt>Paulus defends himself [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="22" />
      <v n="1" />Ju Paulus angka omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa-bapa, deng sodara dong samua! Beta minta bosong dengar sang beta, ko beta mau bela diri.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Paulus began to speak saying, “Fathers, and all siblings! I request that you listen to me, so that I can defend myself.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Itu waktu orang banya dong dengar Paulus omong pake dong pung bahasa sandiri. Ju dong diam memang, ko mau dengar bae-bae dia pung omong. Tarús dia sambung bilang,<bt>At that time many people heard Paulus speak using their own language. And they were quiet right away, so that they could listen carefully to that talk of his. Then2 he continued saying,</bt><v n="3" />&lt;&lt;Asal bosong samua tau bilang, beta ni orang Yahudi. Mama barana sang beta di kota Tarsus, di propinsi Kilikia. Ma beta bésar di sini, di Yerusalem. Yang ajar sang beta, andia guru bésar di sini, nama Gamaliel. Dia ajar sang beta ba'i Musa pung atoran samua, sampe alus-alus. Beta ju rajin iko Tuhan Allah, sama ke bosong samua ni.<bt>"So that you all know that, I here am a Yahudi person. Mama gave birth to me in Tarsus city, in Kilikia province. But I grew up here, in Yerusalem. Those who taught me, that's the big teacher here, named Gamaliel. He taught me all Gf/Ff Musa's regulation, in fine detail. I was also faithful in following the Lord God, like all of you here.</bt><note reference="22:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 5:34-39</note><v n="4" />Tempo hari beta sonde barenti-barenti pi buru deng bekin susa sang itu orang dong yang iko Yesus pung Jalan Idop. Beta hela bawa sang dong, laki-laki deng parampuan, datang di Yerusalem sini, ais lempar kasi maso sang dong pi dalam bui. Itu waktu ada yang mati ju.<bt>In earlier times I did not stop hunting for and causing difficulty to those people who follow Yesus' Life Path. I dragged them in, male and female, to come here to Yerusalem, then threw them in jail. At that time, there were also some who died.</bt><v n="5" />Kotong pung kapala agama pung bos bésar, deng bos-bos laen yang urus parkara agama dong samua tau bilang, apa yang beta omong ni memang batúl bagitu! Beta sonde omong kosong. Te dong tu yang kasi surat kuasa sang beta, ko pi tangkap ame sang orang dong yang ada iko sang Yesus, sampe di kota Damsik. Di sana, beta mau tangkap sang dong, ais mau hela bawa datang di Yerusalem. Beta pung maksud, biar ko orang yang putus parkara agama, yang nanti hukum sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Our *high priest and the other bosses who decide religious dsiputes all know that what I am saying here is really true. I am not lying. Because they are the ones who gave that authority letter to me, to go capture/arrest people who were following Yesus, all the way until Damsik city. There, I wanted to capture them, then bring them to Yerusalem. My intent, was to have it so that the people who judge religious litigations, would be the ones who later judge/punish them.</bt><note reference="22:4-5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 8:3, 26:9-11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus carita dia pung pangalaman [\s2]<bt>Paulus tells his experience [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Utusan dong pung Carita 9:1-19, 26:12-18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais Paulus sambung dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Jadi beta barangkat pi Damsik, ko mau cari sang dong di sana. Kira-kira tenga hari, botong su amper sampe di kota. Tukuju sa, ada satu taráng bakilat dari langit senter pas sang beta.<bt>Then Paulus continued speaking saying, “So (consequently), I left for Damsik, to hunt for them there. Approximately mid day, we were almost at the city. Suddenly, there was a bright light from the sky shinning exactly on me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pengalaman = seen as frozen lexeme,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pengalaman = seen as frozen lexeme, not productive morphology</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Tarús beta jato tabanting pi tana, ju beta dengar satu suara omong bilang, &lt;He, Saulus! Akurang ko lu bekin sangsara sang Beta bagini, é?&gt;<bt>Then I fell flat on the ground, and I heard a voice saying, 'He, Saulus! Why are you causing tribulation to Me like this?'</bt><v n="8" />Beta memang dengar itu suara, ma sonde dapa lia orang. Ju beta tanya bilang, &lt;Ko Bos yang omong ni, sapa?&gt;<bt>I actually heard that voice, but didn't see a person. And I asked saying, ‘The Boss who is speaking now, who [are you]?’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais, itu suara manyao bilang, &lt;Beta ni, Yesus, orang Nasaret, yang lu ada bekin sangsara sang Beta!&gt;<bt>Then that voice answered saying, 'I here, am Yesus, the Nasaret person, whom you who are causing tribulation to Me!'</bt><v n="9" />Ma orang yang jalan batamán deng beta dong, dapa lia itu taráng, ma sonde dapa dengar itu suara.<bt>But the people who were traveling together with me, could see that light, but did not hear that voice.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ju beta manyao bilang, &lt;Kalo bagitu, beta musti bekin apa sakarang?&gt;<bt>And I replied saying, ‘If that the case, what must I do now?’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu suara kasi tau bilang, &lt;Bangun suda, ko maso pi dalam kota. Nanti di situ, baru Beta kasi tau samua yang lu musti bekin.&gt;<bt>That voice told saying, ‘Get up, and go into the city. Later there, then I will tell you all you must do.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Dengar abis bagitu, ju beta bangun badiri. Ma beta su sonde bisa dapa lia apa-apa lai, tagal itu taráng pung tajam. Ju beta pung tamán dong pegang sang beta ko hela bawa maso sang beta pi kota Damsik.<bt>After hearing like that, then I stood up. But I could no longer see anything, because of that light's sharpness. And may friends held me to pull bring me into Damsik city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tarang pung tajam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tarang pung tajam</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Di situ ada satu orang, nama Ananias. Dia ni, satu orang yang hati lurus, deng dia ju pegang karás ba'i Musa pung atoran dong. Samua orang Yahudi yang tenga di itu kota suka sang dia, deng dong ju hormat sang dia.<bt>There there was a person, named Ananias. This him, [he was] a person who liver was straight (righteous), and he also held tightly to all grandfather's Musa's regulations. All the Yahudi people who live in the city liked him, and they also respected him.</bt><v n="13" />Dia datang cari beta, ais dia omong bilang, &lt;Bu Saul! Buka mata ko lia suda! Te bu pung mata su bae.&gt; Dia omong abis bagitu, tarús beta angka muka, ju beta bisa dapa lia sang dia.<bt>He came looking for me, then he spoke saying, ‘Elder.brother Saul! Open your eyes to see! Cuz (elaboration) elder.brother's eyes are healed.’ He finished speaking like that, then I lifted my face up, and I could see him.</bt><v n="14" />Ais itu, dia ajar sang beta bilang, &lt;Tuhan Allah, yang kotong pung nene-moyang dong sambayang sang Dia, sakarang su pili ame sang bu. Bu pung tugas, andia mangarti bae-bae Dia pung mau. Deng kanál sang Yesus, yang dari dolu, kotong subu-subu sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang Barisi&gt;&gt;. Sakarang Tuhan su buka jalan ko bu dengar langsung dari Yesus.<bt>After that, he taught me saying, ‘The Lord God, whom our ancestors worshiped Him, now has chosen elder.brother (=you). Elder.brother's job, it is to understand well His will. And know that Yesus, whom from before, we called/mentioned Him saying, “Holy Person”. Now the Lord has opened the path so that elder.brother hears directly from Yesus.</bt><v n="15" />Dia sandiri yang su pili ame sang bu, ko pi jalan kasi tau orang di mana-mana, Dia pung Carita Bae. Bu musti kasi tau samua yang bu dapa lia deng mata kapala sandiri, deng samua yang bu dapa dengar dari Dia.<bt>He himself is the one who choose elder.brother (=you), to go tell people everywhere, His Good Story. Elder.brother (=you) must tell all which elder.brother (=you) has seen with your own eyes, and all which elder.brother (=you) has heard from Him.</bt><v n="16" />Bu sonde usa tunggu lama-lama lai. Pi ko minta dong sarani sang bu, suda! Ko jadi tanda bilang, bu su minta ko Tuhan Yesus hapus buang bu pung sala samua.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Elder.brother (=you) does not need to wait any longer. Go ask them to baptise elder.brother (=you) (imperative)! To become a sign that elder.brother (=you) has received the Lord Yesus, and He has erased thrown away all of elder.brother's sins.’”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah suru Paulus bawa Kabar Bae kasi suku-bangsa yang bukan Yahudi [\s2]<bt>The Lord God orders Paulus to take the Good News to the non Yahudi ethnic groups [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ju Paulus sambung dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ais itu, ju beta pulang pi Yerusalem. Satu hari, beta pi sambayang di Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Waktu beta ada sambayang, Tuhan kasi lia sang beta, tingka ke mimpi.<bt>And Paulus continued what he was saying saying, “After that, then I returned to Yerusalem. One day, I was praying at the Temple. When I was praying, the Lord showed me, like a dream.</bt><v n="18" />Beta lia sang Yesus. Ju Dia parenta sang beta bilang, &lt;Sakarang, lu musti jalan kasi tenga ini kota Yerusalem, suda! Te orang di sini dong, sonde mau tarima apa yang lu ajar so'al Beta.&gt;<bt>I saw Yesus. And He ordered me saying, 'Now, you must go leave this Yerusalem city! Cuz (elaboration) the people there, don't want to accept that which you teach about Me.'</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ma beta sonde tarima bae itu parenta, tagal dolu kapala agama dong memang suka sang beta. Jadi beta manyao bilang, &lt;Ma bagini, Bos! Dong samua tau bilang, tempo hari, beta yang maso-kaluar ruma sambayang di mana-mana, ko tangkap deng papoko orang-orang yang parcaya sang Bos.<bt>But I didn't accept that command, because previously the religious heads had really like me. So (consequently) I replied saying, 'But, it's like this, Bos! They all know that, earlier, I am the one who entered-exited the worship houses everywhere, to capture and beat the people who believe in Boss.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mata kaki = ankle"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">mata kaki = ankle</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Dong ju tau, waktu dong lempar bekin mati Bos pung utusan, Stefanus, beta ada di situ, deng beta ju satuju. Waktu dong kumpul batu ko lempar sang dia, beta yang ator sang dong, deng jaga dong pung baju.&gt;<bt>They also know, when they threw killing Boss' commissioned one, Stefanus, I was there, and I also agreed. When they gathered stones to throw at him, I am the one who arranged them, and watched their clothes.’ [EXEG: implicit to explicit: UNSs thought he was a bystander and/or waterboy without “I am the one who arranged them,” Overwhelming commentary support that this is the implication of “keeping the coats” understood by the original audience (most of the discussion on this is at 7:58 and surrounding verses). Type of symbolic action. Not addition.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 7:58</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Biar beta kasi inga bagitu, ma Yesus parenta ulang lai bilang, &lt;Sonde usa cari alasan macam-macam! Kasi tenga Yerusalem sakarang, ko lu pi suda! Te Beta mau suru sang lu, pi di tampa yang jao-jao dong, ko ajar orang yang bukan Yahudi dong.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Even though I reminded like that, nevertheless Yesus commanded again/further saying, ‘It's not necessary to look for all sorts of excuses! Leave Yerusalem now, and go! Cuz (elaboration) I want to order you, to go to far away places, to teach the people who are not Yahudi.’”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Waktu itu orang banya dong dengar Paulus omong bilang, Tuhan su suru sang dia pi suku-bangsa laen, ju dong su sonde mau dengar lai sang dia. Dong samua mara, ais batarea rame-rame bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang dengar sang ini orang lai! Bunu sang dia sa! Dia sonde pantas idop lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>When that crowd heard Paulus talk saying the Lord had ordered him to go to other ethnic groups, then they did not want to hear anything more from him. They were very angry, so they yelled wildly saying, “Don't listen to this person anymore! Murder him! It's not appropriate for him to live anymore.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tantara dong bawa Paulus pi benteng<bt>The soldiers bring Paulus to the fort</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Dong batarea bagitu, ju dong buka buang dong pung baju, deng ra'u ame abu, ko buang pi atas, tagal dong su mara mau mati.<bt>They yelled like that, and they took off threw away their clothes, and scooped up dust, to throw it up, because they were very angry.</bt><v n="24" />Waktu komandán lia bilang, itu orang dong su kaco lai bagitu, ju dia suru dia pung ana bua dong ko hela bawa sang Paulus maso pi dalam benteng. Ais komandán suru dong firuk sang dia, ko biar dia mau mangaku bilang, dia ada bekin sala apa, sampe orang Yahudi dong mau bunu sang dia.<bt>When the commander saw that those people where chaotic like that again, then he ordered his underlings to drag bring Paulus into the fort. Then the commander ordered them to whip him, in order that he would confess saying, what his wrong was that he had done, to the point that the Yahudi people wanted to murder him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="firuk implies pake alat; bonggo ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">firuk implies pake alat; bonggo = beat with large bat, or alu (as in killing a dog for eating); ika malengga (Rote) ~ ika malenggang (UNS) = tie face up</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Waktu dong ika sang Paulus ko mau firuk sang dia, ju dia bale tanya sang itu tantara bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko pamarenta Roma pung atoran, mana yang batúl? Kalo satu orang ada pung hak warga Roma, ais dia dapa parkara, bosong musti bekin karmana sang dia? Bosong papoko lebe dolo sang dia, ko, bosong pareksa lebe dolo?&gt;&gt;<bt>When they tied Paulus, to whip him, then he replied asking that soldier saying, “According to the Roma government's regulations, what is true? If a person has the rights of Roma citizenship, and he gets [involved in] a litigation, how must you treat him? You beat him first, or, you investigate/interrogate first?”</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02025b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horozontalPosition:right">Dong ika sang Paulus ko mau firuk sang dia<bt>They tie Paulus to whip him</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu tantara capát-capát pi cari dia pung komandán. Ju dia lapor bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Ini orang ni, ada pung hak warga Roma! Jadi bapa mau bekin apa sang dia?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, then that soldier quickly went to find his commander. And he reported saying, “Father! This person here, has the rights of Roma citizens. So (consequently) what does father (=you) want to do with him?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu komandán sandiri pi tanya langsung sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bilang, lu ada pung hak warga Roma? Batúl, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, then that commander himself went to ask Paulus directly saying, “They say, you have the rights of Roma citizenship? Is that right?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bilang here is like &quot;they say&quot;@@"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bilang here is like "they say"@@ = katanya</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Paulus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl! Beta pegang itu hak.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Paulus responded saying, “That's right! I hold that right.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ais, itu komandán bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ju bagitu. Beta bayar talalu mahal, ko bisa dapa itu hak.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, that commander said, “I do also. I paid very expensively, so that I could get those rights.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Paulus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo beta, na, beta sonde bayar apa-apa. Mulai dari mama barana sang beta, beta su pegang itu hak. Beta pung papa ju pegang itu hak.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Paulus answered saying, “As for me, na, I didn't pay anything. Beginning from mama giving birth to me, I have held that right. My father also held that right.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Waktu dong dengar bilang, Paulus ada pegang hak warga Roma, ju itu tantara dong ondor, deng dong sonde barani firuk deng pareksa sang dia lai. Itu komandán jadi taku, tagal dia su ika sang Paulus, deng tau bilang, dia su langgar atoran.<bt>When they heard that Paulus held the rights of Roma citizenship, then those soldiers backed away, and they did not dare whip and examine him anymore. That commander became afraid, because he had tied Paulus, and knew that he had not followed regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hedek = (Rote) takuju, ais ondor;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hedek = (Rote) takuju, ais ondor; mondor ~ ondor (UNS prefer ondor)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus di tampa urus parkara agama Yahudi<bt>Paulus in the Place of Taking.care of Yahudi Religious Litigations</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Dia pung beso, itu komandán masi mau cari tau parsís itu parkara pung akar karmana. Ais dia suru dia pung ana bua dong ko pi pange kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng samua orang bésar yang biasa urus parkara agama Yahudi ko dong bakumpul. Ju dia suru ko dong pi buka Paulus pung rante, ais bawa sang dia pi mangada itu orang dong samua.<bt>The next day, that commander still wanted to know exactly what that litigation's roots happened to be. So he ordered his underlings to go call the *chief priests and all the big/important people who normally handled Yahudi religious litigations so that they would gather together. And he ordered that they go open Paulus' chain, and bring him to face all those people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="23" />
      <v n="1" />Sampe di situ, ju dong suru sang Paulus ko bela diri. Ais dia lia bae-bae sang itu orang dong samua, ju dia angka omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong! Beta badiri di sini deng hati lurus. Tuhan Allah tau bilang, mulai dari kici sampe sakarang, beta pung hati barisi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Arriving there, then they ordered Paulus to defend himself. Then he looked carefully at all those people, and he began to talk (formally) saying, “Siblings! I stand here with straight liver (righteous/pure motives). The Lord God knows that from when I was small until now, my liver has been clean.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Dengar Paulus omong bagitu, ju Ananias,<bt>Hearing Paulus talk like that, then Ananias,</bt><note reference="23:2" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ananias yang ini, dia ju kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos bésar, ma bukan Ananias yang dolu hukum sang Tuhan Yesus. Dong dua pung nama sama.<bt>This Ananias, he was also the *high priest, but not the Ananias who before judged the Lord Yesus. They two had the same name.</bt></note>kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos bésar, mara mau mati. Ju dia parenta orang-orang yang badiri deka sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Tampar dia pung mulu!&gt;&gt;<bt>the *high priest, was very angry. And he ordered the people who stood close to Paulus saying, “Slap his mouth!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tampar = slap over the mouth,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tampar = slap over the mouth, clap ~ kaláp (archaic); moot = punch with fist = habok; falungku = punch straight on with fist; swing = hook;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ju Paulus balas sang Ananias bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti Tuhan Allah tampar balas sang lu. Te lu memang manusia macam ke tiang yang baru kaná cet di luar, ma ane-ane su makan bekin hol dia pung dalam. Lu dudu di sini, ko bekin diri pura-pura suci. Ais lu mau hukum sang beta iko kotong pung atoran adat. Ma lu sandiri langgar itu atoran waktu lu suru dong tampar sang beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Paulus replied to Ananias saying, “May the Lord God slap you in return. Cuz (elaboration) you are really a human like a pole that has just been painted on the outside, but termites have eaten the inside making it inside. You sit here, to make yourself pretend to be holy. Then you want to judge me according to our traditional regulations. But you yourself have not followed those regulations when you ordered them to slap me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="puruk = rotten and smelly ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">puruk = rotten and smelly ; su nonek; hol = hole, empty, ; ane-ane ~ mir puti = termites; Metafor: hai tembok yang dikapur putih-putih! = Orang yang pura-pura bae (menipu orang). Seperti tembok yg dicet putih untuk menipu orang. Diebler: "false as a rickety wall covered with whitewash to make it look strong."<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="23:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 23:27-28</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dengar Paulus omong bagitu, ju itu orang di situ togor sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Lu sonde pantas omong bagitu sang kotong pung kapala agama dong pung bos bésar ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Paulus talk like that, then those people there scolded him saying, “He! You are not talking appropriatly to our *high priest here!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ju Paulus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, ko? Kalo bagitu, beta minta ma'af, ko beta sonde tau bilang, dia tu, kotong pung kapala agama dong pung bos bésar. Memang Tuhan Allah su pake orang ko tulis bilang, &lt;Bosong sonde bole omong jahat sang bosong pung kapala dong.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>And Paulus replied saying, “Is that right? If so, I apologize, because <span class="Italic">(ko)</span> I did not know that that he, was our *high priest. [+emphatic] It's true, the Lord God has used a person to write saying, ‘You may not speak evil of your heads.’”</bt><note reference="23:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 22:28</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6-8" />Waktu Paulus lia itu orang yang dudu urus parkara agama, dia tau bilang, dong ada tabagi jadi dua partei. Saparu iko partei Saduki, yang parcaya bilang, orang mati sonde bisa idop lai. Dong ju parcaya bilang, Tuhan pung ana bua di sorga, sonde ada. Deng roh ju sonde ada. Saparu lai iko partei Farisi yang parcaya bilang, nanti Tuhan Allah bisa kasi idop orang mati dong. Dong ju parcaya bilang, ada roh, deng di sorga Tuhan ada pung ana bua dong.<bt>When Paulus saw those people who sat taking care of religious litigations, he knew that they were divided into two parties. Some followed the Saduki party, which believed taht dead people cannot live again. They also believed that the Lord's angels, did not exist. And [human's dead/alive] spirits also don't exist. The other followed the Farisi party which believed that the Lord God will cuz (elaboration) dead people to live again. They also believe that there are spirits, and in heaven the Lord has angels.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orang-orang yang tau-tau ; tampar ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">orang-orang yang tau-tau ; tampar = hit on mouth or cheek; tampeleng = hit/slap cheek; tabagi dua blok = divided into two factions</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Paulus omong deng suara karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong! Asal bosong samua tau bilang, beta ni, orang Farisi. Beta pung bapa, deng beta pung ba'i dong ju orang Farisi. Sakarang bosong mau hukum sang beta, tagal beta parcaya bilang, Tuhan Allah bisa kasi idop orang mati.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Paulus spoke with a loud voice saying, “Siblings! So that you all know that, I here, am a Farisi person. My father, and my grandfathers also were Farisi people. Now you want to judge me, because I believe that the Lord God can make dead people live.”</bt><note reference="23:6-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 26:5, Filipi 3:5, Mateos 22:23, Markus 12:18, Lukas 20:27</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu Paulus omong bagitu, ju itu orang Farisi deng orang Saduki dong mulai bakanjar, sampe dong su sonde bacocok lai. Ais ju dong tapica bagi dua.<bt>When Paulus spoke like that, then those Farisi people and Saduki people began to argue, until they they didn't match/agree anymore. And they were broken into two.</bt><v n="9" />Jadi itu orang dong batangkár sampe samua jadi kaco. Ais ju ada barapa guru dari partei Farisi yang badiri ko bela sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang sonde sala! Sapa tau, mangkali ada roh, ko, mangkali ada Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga satu datang omong deng dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), those people argued until everything was chaos. Then there were several teachers from the Farisi party who stood to defend Paulus saying, “This person is not wrong! Who knows, perhaps there was a spirit, or, perhaps there was an angel who came to speak with him!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batangkar = bertengkar, basambung mulut, argue,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">batangkar = bertengkar, basambung mulut, argue, bakanjar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Itu guru dong su omong bagitu, ma dong pung bakanjar tamba hebat lai, sampe itu komandán mulai taku. Dia pikir, jang sampe dong karoyok kasi mati sang Paulus. Jadi dia suru dia pung ana bua dong turun ko hela bawa maso sang Paulus pi dalam benteng.<bt>Those teachers had spoken like that, but their arguement increased even more, until that commander became afraid. He taught, don't let it be that they attack vigourously from all directions and kill Paulus. So he ordered his underlings to pull bring Paulus into the fort.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karoyok = attack vigorously from all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">karoyok = attack vigorously from all directions, hantam rame-rame, turun = 1) descend, 2) turun tangan (jump into it)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Dia pung malam, ju Tuhan Yesus datang kasi tunju diri sang Paulus. Dia kasi kuat Paulus pung hati bilang, &lt;&lt;Paul! Lu jang taku, ó! Sakarang lu su omong so'al Beta di Yerusalem sini. Inga bae-bae! Nanti lu musti omong bagitu di Roma sana ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>That night, then the Lord Yesus came and showed himself to Paulus. He encouraged Paulus saying, “Paul! You don't be afraid! Now you have spoken about Me in Yerusalem here. Remember well! Later you must talk like that in Roma over.there/distant.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang dong basakongkol ko mau bunu sang Paulus<bt>People agree to murder Paulus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12-13" />Dia pung beso pagi, ada lebe dari ampa pulu orang Yahudi yang basakongkol ko mau kasi mati sang Paulus. Dong angka sumpa bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong sonde mau makan-minum, kalo botong balóm bunu sang Paulus.&gt;&gt;<bt>The next morning, there were more that forty Yahudi people who agreed to kill Paulus. They took up an oath saying, “We will not eat-drink, if we have not yet murdered Paulus.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Dong angka sumpa abis bagitu, ju dong pi lapor sang kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng tua-tua adat dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa dong! Botong su sumpa bilang, botong sonde akan makan-minum, kalo botong balóm bunu sang Paulus.<bt>They finished taking up the oath like that, then they went to report to the *chief priests and the traditional elders saying, “Fathers! We have oathed that we will not eat-drink, if we have not yet murdered Paulus.</bt><v n="15" />Naa, botong pung mau bagini: bapa dong musti pi mangada sang komandán, ko minta sang dia bawa sang Paulus pi tampa urus parkara agama. Bekin tingka ke bapa dong mau pareksa ulang dia pung parkara. Nanti botong tepa sang dong di tenga jalan, ko bunu sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa, our desire is like this: fathers (=you-pl) must go face the commander, to request him to bring Paulus to the place of taking care of religious litigations. Make as if fathers (=you) want to examine his litigation again. Then we will ambush them in the middle of road/trip, to murder him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tepa = hadang, cegat, ambush; te'e"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tepa = hadang, cegat, ambush; te'e = tekan seseorang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ma Paulus pung sodara parampuan pung ana laki-laki satu dapa dengar dong pung basakongkol bagitu, ais ju dia lari pi benteng ko kasi tau sang Paulus.<bt>But one of Paulus' sister's sons heard their agreement like that, and then he ran to the fort to tell Paulus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="is there a term for Sister's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">is there a term for Sister's Child (opposite relation from om)? Rote sele (tanam) da'di (tante pung ana); KM none!!! MISKIN = anak</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Dengar abis itu ana pung carita, ju Paulus pange ame satu parwira bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini, beta pung ana. Lu bawa sang dia capát-capát pi di lu pung komandán. Ko dia mau kasi tau satu hal.&gt;&gt;<bt>After hearing that child's story, then Paulus called an official saying, “This is my [classificatory] child. You take him quickly to your commander. So that he can tell something.”</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02029b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Ana datang lapor orang jahat pung basakongkol<bt>The child comes to report the evil people's agreement</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ju itu parwira antar itu ana pi dia pung komandán. Dia lapor bilang, &lt;&lt;Pak! Paulus, yang kotong ada tahan tu, minta sang beta ko bawa ini ana datang mangada sang bapa. Dia ada mau kasi tau satu hal pantíng.&gt;&gt;<bt>And that official escorted that child to his commander. He reported saying, “Father! Paulus, that one whom we are detaining, requests me to bring this child to come face father (=you). He wants to tell you something important.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais komandán hela bawa itu ana pi satu tampa ko dong dua sandiri. Ju dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu mau kasi tau apa sang beta?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the commander pulled brought that child to a place. And he asked saying, “What do you want to tell me?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ju itu ana kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada barapa orang Yahudi dong yang su basakongkol ko mau bunu sang om Paul. Dong mau datang minta sang bapa, ko beso, na, bapa antar sang Paulus pi tampa urus parkara agama. Bilang, dong pura-pura mau pareksa lebe alus om pung parkara.<bt>And that child told saying, “There are several Yahudi people who have agreed to murder uncle Paul. They want to come request father (=you), so that tomorrow, na, father (=you) escort Paulus to the Place of Taking Care of Religious Litigations. Saying, they pretend to want to investigate uncle's litigation more carefully.</bt><v n="21" />Ma bapa jang iko dong pung mau. Te nanti ada lebe dari ampa pulu orang yang mau tepa bapa pung rombongan di jalan, ko dong mau bunu sang om Paul. Tagal dong samua su sumpa bilang, dong sonde mau makan-minum, kalo dong balóm bunu sang om Paul. Sakarang dong samua su siap. Dong cuma tunggu bapa manyao bilang apa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But father (=you) don't follow their desire. Cuz (elaboration) there are more than forty people who want to ambush father's group on the road, so that they can murder uncle Paul. Because they all have oathed saying, they will not eat-drink, if they have not yet murdered uncle Paul. Now they all are ready. They only await what father's response will be.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="te'e = 1) siap untuk cegat,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">te'e = 1) siap untuk cegat, ready for ambush; 2) barenti di sini, sonde bagarák (in playing marbles, marking the spot to shoot from)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dengar itu ana pung carita, ju itu komandán bilang sang dia, &lt;&lt;Lu jang kasi tau sapa-sapa bilang, lu ada datang kasi tau ini hal sang beta.&gt;&gt; Omong abis bagitu, ju dia suru itu ana pulang suda.<bt>Hearing that child's story, then that commander said to him, “You don't tell anyone that, you have come to tell me this matter.” Finishing speaking like that, then he told that child to go home.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong antar sang Paulus pi di gubernor Feliks di kota Kaisarea<bt>They escort Paulus to governor Feliks in Kaisarea city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais ju itu komandán pange parwira dua orang. Dia kasi parenta sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Siap tantara biasa dua ratus orang; deng tantara nae kuda tuju pulu orang; deng tantara yang bawa tombak, dua ratus orang. Bosong barangkat memang ini malam jam sambilan, pi kota Kaisarea.<bt>After that, that commander call two soldiers. He gave them a command saying, “Prepare two hundred normal soldiers, and seventy soldiers on horses, and two hundred soldiers who carry spears. You leave immediately this night at nine o'clock, go to Kaisarea city.</bt><v n="24" />Bosong ju sadia satu kuda kasi Paulus. Bosong musti antar bawa sang dia deng bae-bae sampe di gubernor Feliks.&gt;&gt;<bt>You also prepare a horse for Paulus. You must escort him safely to governor Feliks.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais itu, dia tulis surat kasi sang gubernor Feliks bilang:<bt>After that, he wrote a letter to governor Feliks, saying like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="26" />&lt;&lt;Bapa gubernor Feliks yang beta hormat. Salam dari beta, Klaudius Lisias.<bt>“Father governor Feliks whom I respect. Greetings from me, Klaudius Lisias.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="27" />Orang yang sakarang beta kirim datang ni, dia pung nama Paulus. Orang Yahudi dong su pegang ame sang dia, deng su amper bunu sang dia. Itu waktu, beta pung ana bua dong pi hela kasi kaluar sang dia dari orang Yahudi dong pung tangan. Ais beta dapa tau bilang, dia ada pegang hak warga Roma.<bt>The person whom I am now sending here, his name is Paulus. The Yahudi people have grabbed him, and have almost murdered him. At that time, my underlings dragged him out of those Yahudi people's hands. Then I found out that, he has the rights of Roma citizenship. [EXEG: The Gk is a jumbled sequence of participles whose temporal relationship is unclear and can reflect simultaneous events as well. Note NRSV and NLT interpret the sequence differently. Changed under consultant supervision from an earlier version that was closer to the NLT. Now mirrors the sequence of actual events.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pegang ame = kobo = grab"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pegang ame = kobo = grab close (like keeper in soccer) ; *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta tulis ini orang Paulus pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Beta tulis ini orang Paulus pung parkara. Waktu beta dapa dia, orang Yahudi dong su tangkap sang dia. Ais dong ampir kasi bunu sang dia. Waktu beta dengar, bilang, dia pegang hak/warga Roma, beta suru beta pung orang ame dia dari itu orang Yahudi dong.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Beta mau cari tau, akurang ko orang Yahudi dong mau bunu sang dia. Andia ko beta bawa sang dia pi orang Yahudi dong pung tampa urus parkara agama.<bt>I want to know, they Yahudi people wanted to murder him. That's why I brought him to the Yahudi people's place of takingCare of religious litigations.</bt><v n="29" />Ma dong sonde dapa dia pung sala apa-apa. Ko memang dia sonde bekin jahat apa-apa. Jadi ini orang sonde bisa maso bui, deng sonde pantas kaná hukum mati ju. Padahal itu orang di tampa urus parkara agama dong ada babakalai, tagal dong pung ajaran agama sonde bacocok. Jadi beta bawa kambali ini orang pi benteng.<bt>But they did not find any wrongs of his. Because <span class="Italic">(ko) </span>it is true that he has not done anything evil. [+emphatic] So this person could not enter jail, and it is not appropriate for him to be given a death sentence either. However, those people in the Place of Taking.Care of Religious Litigations were argueing, because their religious teachings did not match each other. So I brought this person back to the fort.</bt><v n="30" />Ma dia pung beso, beta dengar bilang, ada orang Yahudi yang su basakongkol ko mau bunu sang dia. Jadi beta yang langsung kasi parenta ko antar ini orang pi di bapa. Beta ju kasi tau itu orang Yahudi dong yang mau bekin parkara lawan ini orang, ko dong datang mangada sang bapa. Biar bapa sandiri yang dengar dong mau tudu kasi sala apa sang dia.<bt>But the next day, I heard that there were Yahudi people who had agreed to murder him. So I was the one who immediately gave an order to escort this person to father (=you). I also told those Yahudi people who want to make a litigation against this person, for them to come face father (=you). So that father himself(=you yourself) hears what wrong they want to accuse him of.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tudu = accuse, tuduh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tudu = accuse, tuduh</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta pung surat, bagitu sa. Makasi!&gt;&gt;<bt>My letter, is only that. Thanks!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais, itu tantara dong samua su siap ko kasi jalan komandán pung parenta. Itu malam ju, dong langsung antar bawa sang Paulus sampe di satu kota, nama Antipatris.<bt>Then all those soldiers were ready to carry out their commander's order. That night, then they straight away escorted Paulus to a city, named Antipatris.</bt><v n="32" />Dia pung beso, tantara nae kuda dong antar sang Paulus tarús sampe di kota Kaisarea. Ma tantara yang laen dong, pulang pi Yerusalem.<bt>The next day, the soldiers on horses escorted Paulus on until Kaisarea city. But the other soldiers, went home to Yerusalem.</bt><v n="33" />Waktu dong sampe di Kaisarea, ju dong antar bawa itu surat kasi sang gubernor. Deng dong sarakan sang Paulus pi dia pung tangan.<bt>When they arrived in Kaisarea, then they delievered that letter to the governor. And they surrendered Paulus into his hands.</bt><v n="34" />Baca abis itu surat, ju gubernor tanya sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu orang mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>After reading that letter, then the governor asked Paulus saying, “What kind of person are you? (region)” [DISCOURSE: RL driven. This is how you ask that question in lgs around here to get the desired response.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais Paulus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, orang dari propinsi Kilikia, bapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Paulus replied saying, “I here, am a person from Kilikia province, father/sir.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Dengar Paulus bilang bagitu, ju gubernor tau bilang, dia memang ada pegang hak warga Roma. Ais dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta yang pegang parenta di sini. Jadi beta sandiri yang nanti urus lu pung parkara. Ma kotong musti tunggu itu orang-orang yang mau baparkara deng lu datang sampe di sini, baru beta pareksa lu pung parkara.&gt;&gt; Ais ju dia suru tantara dong tahan sang Paulus di dong pung tampa, di dalam kompleks gubernor pung ruma jabatan, yang dolu raja Herodes kasi badiri.<bt>Hearing Paulus talk like that, then the governor knew that he actually did hold the rights of Roma citizenship. Then he spoke saying, “I am the one holding authority here. Thus I myself will the the one who takes.care.of/judges this litigation of yours. But we must wait for those people who want to have a litigation with you to arrive here, then I will examine your litigation. " And then he told the soldiers to detain Paulus in their place, in the governor's official house, which before raja Herodes built. [EXEG: on Roman citizenship here: vs. 26 mentions it explicitly. Bruce discusses it explicitly; IVP entries on Tarsus and Cilicia also support it. It is that implication that determines Felix's action, and brings a kind of cohesion to chapters 22-28.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Yahudi dong datang baparkara deng Paulus di Kaisarea<bt>The Yahudi people come to dispute/litigate with Paulus in Kaisarea</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="24" />
      <v n="1" />Lewat lima hari ju, orang-orang Yahudi yang mau baparkara deng Paulus datang sampe di kota Kaisarea. Di itu rombongan ada Ananias, andia kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar. Bos-bos laen dong ada iko ju. Dong ju datang deng satu orang laen, nama Tertulus. Dia tu, pintar omong. Andia ko dong pake sang dia jadi dong pung jubir ko lawan sang Paulus.<bt>After five days, then the Yahudi people who wanted to be involved in a litigation with Paulus arrived in Kaisarea city. In that group there was Ananias, the *high priest. Other bosses also went. They came with another person, named Tertulus. That him, was a person skilled in speaking. That's why they used him to be their spokesperson to oppose Paulus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pokoról = pembela parkara, pengacara (Yanto"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pokoról = pembela parkara, pengacara (Yanto sonde tau) (Dutch)</Message></Annotation><v n="2-3" />Waktu orang dong samua su bakumpul di tampa urus parkara, ju gubernor suru bawa maso sang Paulus. Ais Tertulus bangun badiri, ko mau omong kasi jato sang Paulus. Dia kasi hormat sang gubernor, ais dia angka omong bilang,<bt>When all the people had gathered at the place of taking.care.of litigations, then the governor ordered that they bring Paulus in. Then Tertulus stood up, wanting to talk making Paulus fall (lose the case). He gave respect to the governor, then he began to speak (formally) saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">&lt;&lt;Bapa gubernor yang beta hormat! Su bagini lama ni, mulai dari bapa pegang parenta di sini, bapa su tau lebe dolo apa yang bae kasi sang botong. Ais bapa su bekin bae banya hal ju, sampe botong orang Yahudi su bisa idop aman, sanáng, deng tanáng. Jadi botong mau pake ini waktu ko minta tarima kasi bam-banya sang bapa gubernor. Ko sapa lai yang bisa bekin bae bagitu banya di mana-mana sama ke bapa.<bt>Father governor whom I respect! It has been a long time now, starting from when father (=you) held authority here, father (=you) has known from before what is good for us-exc. Thus father (=you) has done many good things, to the point that we-exc Yahudi people can live safely, happily, and with calmness/peace. So (consequently) we-exc want to use this time to say many thanks to father governor. For who else could do so much good all over the place like this father (=you).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tagal bapa kasi jalan parenta deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tagal bapa kasi jalan parenta deng bae-bae.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ma biar beta sonde usa pake waktu talalu banya, beta omong langsung di dia pung isi sa. Jadi beta minta bapa dengar bae-bae hal-hal yang beta mau kasi tau so'al Paulus ni.<bt>But so that I don't need to use too much time, I will speak directly to the point. So (consequently) I ask that father (=you) listen carefully to the matters I want to tell about this Paulus here.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dia pung isi = dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">dia pung isi = dia pung pokok / (BI inti masalah)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Bagini, bapa. Buat botong orang Yahudi, Paulus ni, sama ke satu panyaki yang pinda dari satu tampa pi tampa laen. Dia suka lawan botong pung agama, deng tukang bekin kaco botong pung adat di mana-mana. Di mana sa dia pi, pasti orang Yahudi dong baparkara satu deng satu. Dia ni, satu kapala tukang propaganda dari partei agama yang iko satu orang dari Nasaret, yang botong bilang &lt;partei Nasarani&gt;. Ma apa yang dong ajar tu, batasala bésar deng apa yang botong pung agama ajar.<bt>It's like this, father. For us-exc Yahudi people, this Paulus, is like an illness that moves from one place to another place. He likes to oppose our religion, and he habitually makes chaos our rituals/customs everywhere. Whereever he goes, surely the Yahudi people will get in litigations with each other. This him, [he is] the head of the propaganda workers from a religious party that follows a person from Nasaret, whom we call ‘Nasarani party’. But that which he teaches, is very wrong according to what our religion teaches.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kutu loncat = flea; tukang porpaganda"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kutu loncat = flea; tukang porpaganda ~ propaganda = evangelist, salesmen, penyebar berita, ~ tukang promosi</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ini orang su coba mau bekin kamomos botong pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat yang barisi, deng dia bawa orang kafir pi dalam. Andia ko botong tangkap sang dia. [Iko botong pung mau, botong mau hukum sang dia pake botong pung atoran sandiri.<bt>That holy/clean Temple of ours-exc, has become defiled because this person brought a heathen inside. That's why we captured him. [According to our desire, we want to judge him using our own regulations.</bt><v n="7" />Ma komandán Lisias datang rampas ame sang dia dari botong pung tangan.<bt>But commander Lisias came and snatched him from our hands.</bt><v n="8" />Ais dia parenta bilang, kalo ada yang mau baparkara deng Paulus, na, dong musti datang mangada sang bapa di Kaisarea. Dia pung maksud, biar ko gubernor urus langsung ini parkara].<bt>The he commanded saying, if there is any who want to have a litigation with Paulus, na, they must come face father (=you) in Kaisarea. His intention, was that the governor directly take care of this litigation].</bt><note reference="24:6-8" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kata-kata dalam kurung ni, sonde ada di Alkitab bahasa Yunani paling tua dong.<bt>The words in these brackets here, do not exist in some of the old Yunani language writings.</bt></note>Jadi sakarang botong datang di sini, ko bapa pareksa ini parkara. Nanti bapa sandiri dapa tau bilang, samua yang botong omong ni, memang batúl.<bt>So (consequently) now we came here, so that father (=you) investigate this litigation. Later father himself (=you) will find out that all that we say here, is really true.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Bagitu sa. Makasi, bapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>That's all. Thanks, father.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Tertulus omong abis bagitu, ju orang Yahudi laen dong sokong dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, bapa! Memang bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Tertulus finished speaking like that, then the other Yahudi people backed up his talk saying, “True, father! It's really like that.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sokong = back up, mendukung, membenarkan,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sokong = back up, mendukung, membenarkan, setuju</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus bela diri di muka Feliks<bt>Paulus defends himself in front of Feliks</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais gubernor kasi sein ko Paulus mulai omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sakarang beta kasi loos sang lu ko bela diri.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the governor geave a sign/motion for Paulus to begin speaking saying, “Now I give permission for you to defend yourself.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi luas = opportunity = los"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kasi luas = opportunity = los</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais Paulus badiri, ju dia angka omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa gubernor! Bapa su parenta di botong pung propinsi ni, su bagini lama. Jadi bapa su mangarti batúl botong orang Yahudi pung dudu-badiri di sini. Tagal itu, beta sonde taku bela diri di bapa pung muka.<bt>Then Paulus stood, and he began to speak (formally) saying, “Father governor! Father (=you) has commanded in this province of ours, already a long time. So (consequently) father (=you) truly understand our Jewish situation here. Because of that, I am not afraid to defend myself in front of father (=you).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dudu-badiri = keadaan ; kuatir"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">dudu-badiri = keadaan ; kuatir</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Kira-kira dua blas hari yang su lewat ni, beta ada pi Yerusalem ko sambayang di Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Bapa bisa tanya sa deng orang-orang yang ada iko sambayang itu waktu.<bt>Approximately twelve days ago, I went to Yerusalem to pray at the Temple. Father (=you) can ask anyone of the people who were going to pray at that time.</bt><v n="12" />Di Ruma Sambayang Pusat tu, beta sonde basambung mulu deng sapa-sapa. Deng di ruma sambayang laen dong, beta sonde kumpul orang ko bekin kaco. Bagitu ju di Yerusalem, beta sonde bekin onar apa-apa.<bt>At the Temple, I did not quarrel with anyone. And at the other worship/prayer houses (synagogues) I did not gather people to make chaos. Like that also in Yerusalem, I did not make any disturbance what so ever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="basambung mulu = quarrel, argue, bertengkar,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">basambung mulu = quarrel, argue, bertengkar, bakanjar; bekin onar = bekin kaco, rusuh, ribut;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ma sakarang, ini orang dong mau kasi jato sang beta. Apa yang dong omong tadi tu, ju sonde ada pung bukti apa-apa.<bt>But now, these people want to accuse/defeat me. What they said earlier, there is no evidence what so ever.</bt><v n="14" />Bagini, bapa gubernor. Beta musti mangaku sang bapa satu hal. Beta ada iko satu partei baru yang orang kasi nama bilang, &lt;Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop&gt;. Beta sambayang sang Tuhan Allah, sama deng beta pung nene-moyang dong sambayang sang Dia. Beta ju iko ba'i Musa pung atoran dong samua, deng parcaya batúl apa yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir dolu-dolu dong su tulis kasi tenga sang botong.<bt>It's like this, father governor. I must acknowledge/confess to father (=you) one thing. I do follow a new party whom people have given the name ‘The Lord Yesus' Life Path’. I pray to the Lord God, the same as my ancestors prayed to him. I also follow all Gf/Ff Musa's regulations, and truly believe that which the Lord God's spokesperson long ago wrote leaving behind for us. [EXEG: Be careful about noise from English ‘sect’. Primary sense of the Gk word in LN is ‘religious party’, (i.e. denomination, sect)’. LN lists ‘false teaching’ and ‘division‘ (faction) as secondary senses. I.e. it means a different flavour of beliefs, not necessarily with the derogatory sense of “sect, wrong teaching”. Note also that TB uses ‘aliran (stream)’ which is the normal word for ‘(different) denomination’. There is no reason from the Gk to force Paul to appear to trash his own people.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Beta ada harap sang Tuhan Allah sama ke ini orang dong ju, yang sakarang ada badiri di sini ko lawan sang beta. Botong parcaya bilang, nanti Tuhan Allah kasi idop orang mati: orang bae ko, orang jahat ko, sama sa.<bt>I hope in the Lord God the same as these people also, who now are standing here to oppose me. We-exc believe that the Lord God can cuz (elaboration) dead people to live: good people or, evil people or (whatever), it's all the same.</bt><v n="16" />Andia ko beta salalu usaha deng karás ko biar beta bisa idop deng hati lurus di Tuhan Allah deng manusia pung muka. Deng bagitu, sonde ada orang yang bisa kasi jato sang beta.<bt>That's why I always try hard so that I live with a straight liver (righteous/no wrongs) in front of the Lord God and humans. With that, there is no person who can make me fall(=accuse me).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karang-karang (bahasa/ tuduhan) = make up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">karang-karang (bahasa/ tuduhan) = make up s.t.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Beta ada karjá barapa taon di luar tana Isra'el, baru beta pulang pi Yerusalem. Waktu beta datang, beta ada bawa doi yang orang dong ada kumpul kasi, ko bantu botong pung orang-orang yang idop susa. Ais beta ju pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat ko mau sambayang, deng mau kasi korban macam-macam sang Tuhan Allah di situ.<bt>I worked several years outside of Israel land, then I was coming home to Yerusalem. When I came, I brought money which the people gathered, to help our-exc people who live in difficulty. Then I also went to the Temple to pray, and want to give various sacrifices to the Lord God there.</bt><v n="18" />Waktu beta ada bekin barisi diri di Ruma Sambayang Pusat iko botong pung atoran adat, ju dong datang ko mau tangkap sang beta. Ma itu waktu, sonde ada orang banya di situ, deng sonde ada yang bekin kaco apa-apa ju!<bt>When I was cleansing myself in the Temple according to our ritual regulations, then they came to capture me. But at that time, there were not many people there, and there was no one who was making choas either!</bt><note reference="24:17-18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 21:17-28</note><v n="19" />Yang ada, cuma barapa orang Yahudi yang datang dari propinsi Asia ko mau sambayang di situ ju. Jadi, kalo memang dong ada so'al deng beta, na, dong tu, yang musti bekin parkara deng beta di sini. Bukan ini bapa-bapa dong!<bt>What there was, only a few Yahudi peole who came from Asia province to also pray there. So (consequently), if there actually is a problem with me, na, those people, [are the ones] who must make a litigation with me here. Not these fathers!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orang yang musti parkara deng beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">orang yang musti parkara deng beta di sini, andia itu orang Asia dong. . Tau-tau te itu orang dong mulai bekin gara-gara deng kasi sala sang beta, bilang, beta su bekin kamomos itu Ruma Sambayang. Ais yang jadi saksi, cuma itu orang Asia tu. Cuma dong yang lia deng mata kapala sandiri. Jadi kalo beta bekin sala, musti dong yang datang kasi jato sala sang beta di sini ju.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ma itu orang dong sonde datang. Jadi bapa tanya coba sang ini orang dong, beta pung sala apa? Tempo hari, waktu dong pareksa sang beta di tampa urus parkara agama, dong sonde dapa beta pung sala satu ju. Bapa tanya sang dong sa!<bt>But those people did not come. So (consequently) father (=you) please ask these people, what is my wrong? Before, when they examined me in the Place of Handling Religious Litigations, they did not find a single wrong of mine either. Father just ask them!</bt><v n="21" />Cuma mangkali ada satu hal sa yang bekin dong kaco, deng sonde sanáng sang beta. Waktu beta omong deng suara karás bilang, &lt;Bosong mau hukum sang beta, tagal beta parcaya bilang, Tuhan Allah bisa kasi idop orang mati!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>There's only perhaps just one thing that made them chaotic, and not happy with me. When I spoke in a loud voice saying, ‘You want to judge/punish me, because I believe that the Lord God can make dead people live!’”</bt><note reference="24:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 23:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Paulus omong bagitu, ma tagal gubernor Feliks ju su tau banya, so'al &lt;Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop&gt;, ju dia tutu sidang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Beta mau pange sang komandán Lisias, ko dengar dia pung carita dolo. Kalo beta su omong abis deng dia, baru beta bisa putus ini parkara.&gt;&gt;<bt>Paulus spoke like that, but because governor Feliks also already knew alot, about ‘The Lord Yesus' Life Path,’ then he closed the assembly saying, “It's like this. I want to call commander Lisias, to hear his story first. When I have finished speaking with him, then I can decide on this litigation.”</bt><v n="23" />Ais dia suru parwira satu ko pi tahan sang Paulus. Ma dia parenta ko kasi sadiki bebas sang Paulus, deng jang larang dia pung tamán dong ko datang layani sang dia.<bt>Then he ordered a soldier to detain Paulus. But he commanded to give a bit of freedom to Paulus, and not to forbid his friends to come take care of him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus omong deng Feliks deng dia pung bini Drusila<bt>Paulus speaks with Feliks and his wife Drusila</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Gubernor Feliks pung bini, orang Yahudi, nama Drusila. Su lewat barapa hari, ju dia cari waktu, ko dia deng dia pung bini mau omong-omong deng Paulus. Jadi dia suru bawa sang Paulus ko mangada sang dong dua. Ju Paulus kasi tau sang dong, jalan karmana ko orang bisa parcaya sang Yesus Kristus, andia Orang yang Tuhan su janji memang dari dolu.<bt>Governor Feliks' wife, a Yahudi person, named Drusila. After several days, then found an opportuunity, for he and wife to talk with Paulus. So (consequently) he ordered them to bring Paulus to face the two of them. And Paulus told the, the path/way so that people could believe in Yesus Kristus, that is the Person whom the Lord had promised from beforehand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kans = kesempatan (Du) take opportunity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kans = kesempatan (Du) take opportunity that is known to be available; salák = take advantage of opportunity as it becomes available; lale = slack off, melalaikan, not doing the assigned job</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Dia ju kasi tau jalan karmana ko orang dapa idop lurus, deng karmana ko orang bisa jaga diri ko jang bekin sala. Dia ju kasi tau bilang, nanti Tuhan Allah mau hukum sang samua orang.<bt>He also explained the path/way so that people could guard themselves to not make wrongs. He also told that the Lord God would judge all people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu Feliks dengar bagitu, ju dia taku satenga mati. Ais dia bilang sang Paulus, &lt;&lt;Paulus. Su cukup. Sampe di sini sa, suda! Nanti kalo ada waktu, beta pange sang lu lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Feliks heard like that, then he was very afraid. Then he said to Paulus, “Paulus. That's enough. Just to there, that's all! Later if there is time, I will call you again.”</bt><v n="26" />Itu waktu, Feliks ada cari-cari salák ko biar Paulus sogok sang dia deng doi, ko dia lapás sang dia. Ais dia maen pange Paulus ko omong-omong deng dia tarús.<bt>At that time, Feliks was looking for an opportunity for Paulus to (discretely) hand over him some money, so that he free him. So he repeatedly called Paulus to talk with him over and over.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sorok = sogok (from Rote), not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sorok = sogok (from Rote), not known by UNS's, but implied from context, group of UNS's only know fishing sense, they prefer sogok, or sorong; makan sorok = sim to makan meti (put basket under rock)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ma di sablá laen, gubernor Feliks ju ada ame hati sang orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong. Andia ko dia sonde putus capát Paulus pung parkara. Dia kasi tenga itu parkara tarendam sampe dua taon. Ais itu, ada gubernor baru yang datang ganti sang Feliks. Dia pung nama Porkius Festus. Ma dong ju masi tahan tarús sang Paulus.<bt>But on the other side, governor Felik also was trying to please the Yahudi bosses. That's why he did not decide on Paulus' litigation quickly. He left that litigation soaking (=stagnate) for two years. After that, there was a new governor who came to replace Feliks. His name was Porkius Festus. But they still continued to detain Paulus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ame hati = cari muka, want"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ame hati = cari muka, want to please, bekin supaya orang senang; tarendam = kasi tadudu, stagnate</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Gubernor Feliks ju cari ko itu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Gubernor Feliks ju cari ko itu kapala-kapala Yahudi dong suka sang dia. Ais dia sonde mau putus Paulus pung parkara. Dia biar Paulus tenga di bui bagitu sa, sampe dua taon. Abis dua taon, Feliks turun dari gubernor te dong mau angka gubernor baru, dia pung nama Porkius Festus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Gubernor Festus pareksa Paulus pung parkara<bt>Governor Festus examines Paulus' litigation</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="25" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, gubernor baru, Festus, pinda pi Kaisarea ko mau mulai kasi jalan parenta. Dia cuma tenga tiga hari sa di situ, ais dia barangkat tarús pi Yerusalem.<bt>At that time, the new governor, Festus, moved to Kaisarea to start is authority/job. He had only stayed there just three days, then he left straight away to go to Yerusalem.</bt><v n="2" />Di situ, kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos, deng bos-bos laen dong datang katumu ko bakanál deng gubernor baru. Dong ju angka Paulus pung parkara dalam dong pung omong.<bt>There, the *chief priests, and the other bosses/leaders came to meet to get.to.know the new governor. They also raised Paulus' litigation in their talking. [EXEG: chief priests and other leaders (not elders) here.]</bt><v n="3" />Dong ju minta, kalo bisa, na, gubernor suru dia pung orang dong ko bawa pulang sang Paulus datang di Yerusalem. Padahal dong su basakongkol ko mau bunu sang Paulus di tenga jalan.<bt>Then also requested, if possible, na, the governor (should) order his people to bring Paulus back to Yerusalem. However, they had agreed to murder Paulus in the middle of the road.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ma gubernor manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa-bapa dong. Bagini. Biar ko dong tahan sang dia di Kaisarea dolu. Te beta ju mau pulang capát-capát pi sana.<bt>But the governor replied saying, “Fathers. It's like this. Just let them detain him Kaisarea. Cuz (elaboration) I am quickly going home to there.</bt><v n="5" />Jadi, kalo ada dari bosong yang dapa kuasa ko urus ini parkara, na, dong bole pi sama-sama deng beta di Kaisarea. Kalo memang ini orang ada bekin sala apa-apa, na, bosong bole bekin parkara deng dia di sana sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), if there are those from you who have the power to arrange this litigation, na, they can go together with me to Kaisarea. If this person truly has done something wrong, na, you can bring the litigation with him there.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6-7" />Ais itu, Festus tenga kira-kira sapulu hari di Yerusalem, baru dia pulang pi Kaisarea. Itu waktu, ada barapa orang Yahudi yang iko sang dia, sampe di sana. Dia pung beso, ju gubernor buka itu parkara. Dia suru dong bawa maso sang Paulus ko mangada sang dia.<bt>After that, Festus stayed approximately ten days in Yerusalem, then he returned home to Kaisarea. At that time, there were several Yahudi people who went with him, to there. The next day, then the governor opened that litigation. He ordered them to bring Paulus to face him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu Paulus maso di situ, ju itu orang Yahudi dong badiri kuliling sang dia, ais dong mulai lempar sala macam-macam sang dia. Ma dong sonde bisa kasi tunju satu bukti ju.<bt>When Paulus entered there, then those Yahudi people stood around him, and they began to show all sorts of evil things he had done. But they could not show even one [bit of ] evidence.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ais ju Paulus bela diri bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa gubernor. Beta sonde parná bekin jahat apa-apa. Beta ju sonde bekin hal-hal yang lawan botong pung agama Yahudi pung atoran. Beta sonde bekin kamomos Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat di Yerusalem. Deng beta ju sonde bekin apa-apa yang lawan pamarenta Roma pung atoran.&gt;&gt;<bt>And then Paulus defended himself saying, “Father governor. I have never done anything evil. I also have not done things that oppose our Yahudi religion's regulations. I did not defile the Lord God's Temple in Yerusalem. And I also have not done any thing to oppose the Roma government's regulations.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma gubernor mau cari muka deng ame hati sang orang Yahudi dong. Andia ko dia tanya sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu pikir karmana? Lu tarima bae ko sonde, kalo beta urus lu pung parkara ni di Yerusalem?&gt;&gt;<bt>But the governor wanted to get in good with the Yahudi people. That's why he asked Paulus saying, “What do you think? Do you agree, or not, for me to arrange this litigation of yours in Yerusalem?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dengar gubernor tanya bagitu, ju Paulus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa gubernor. Beta ni, warga Roma. Deng sakarang ni, beta ada badiri di muka bapa gubernor dari pamarenta Roma yang ada pung hak ko urus beta pung parkara iko dia pung atoran. Jadi beta sonde mau pi Yerusalem, ko putus beta pung parkara di sana. Bapa sandiri su tau bilang, beta sonde bekin sala apa-apa, ko lawan ini orang Yahudi dong.<bt>Hearing the governor ask like that, then Paulus replied saying, “Father governor. I here, am citizen of Roma. And now, I am standing in front of father governor of the Roma government which has the right to arrange my litigation following his regulations. So (consequently) I don't want to go to Yerusalem, to decide my litigation there. Father (=you) himself knows that that, I have not done any wrong, opposing these Yahudi people.</bt><v n="11" />Jadi, kalo memang beta ada bekin sala apa-apa, yang pantas kaná hukum mati, beta tarima. Ma kalo apa yang dong omong tu, sonde batúl, iko atoran Roma, sonde ada yang bisa sarakan sang beta pi ini orang dong pung tangan. Dong cuma cari-cari jalan, ko mau bunu sang beta deng parcuma sa. Jadi sakarang, iko beta pung hak, beta minta nae banding pi raja bésar keser, di pusat, di kota Roma. Biar dia sandiri yang putus langsung ini parkara!&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), if it's true that I have done wrong, that is apppropriate to a death sentence, I will accept it. But if that which they speak there, is not true, following the regulations of Roma, there is nothing that allows for me to be surrendered into these people's hands. They are only hunting for a way, to murder me for no reason. So (consequently) now, in line with my rights, I request to appeal this case to the big raja, Keser, at the center/capital, Roma city. May it be that he himself is the one who directly decides this litigation!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nae banding (parkara) = appeal court"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">nae banding (parkara) = appeal court case</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dengar Paulus minta bagitu, ju gubernor barunding deng dia pung tamán yang iko urus itu parkara. Ais itu, dia kasi tau sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal lu su minta nae banding pi keser, jadi lu musti pi kota Roma.&gt;&gt; Omong abis bagitu, ju gubernor kasi bubar itu sidang.<bt>Hearing Paulus request like that, then the governor took council with his friends who followed that litigation. After that, he told Paulus saying, “Because you have requested to appeal to Keser, then you must go to Roma.” After speaking like that, then the governor dispersed that assembly.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Festus minta nasiat sang raja Agripa so'al Paulus<bt>Festus requests advice from raja Agripa about Paulus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais itu, orang Yahudi pung raja, nama Agripa,<bt>After that, the Yahudi people's raja, named Agripa,</bt><note reference="25:13" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Raja Agripa ni, raja Herodes Agripa II. Dia pung bapa, raja Herodes Agripa I, yang bunu bekin mati sang Yakobis, deng yang mati kaná cacing, tagal dia makan puji yang angka dia sama ke dewa.<bt>This raja Agripa is raja Herodes Agripa II. His father was raja Herodes Agripa I, who killed Yakobis, and died of worms, because he accepted praise that elevated him to be the same as a god/deity.</bt></note>deng dia pung adi parampuan, nama Bernike, datang di Kaisarea. Dong dua mau kasi hormat sang gubernor baru.<bt>and his female younger sibling, named Bernike, came to Kaisarea. They two wanted to give honor to the new governor.</bt><v n="14" />Dong manumpang barapa hari deng gubernor Festus. Satu kali, Festus carita Paulus pung parkara kasi sang dong dua. Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa raja! Di Kaisarea sini, botong ada tahan satu orang, nama Paulus. Dolu gubernor lama sonde sampat putus dia pung parkara.<bt>They stayed [as guests] several days with governor Festus. One time, Festus told Paulus' litigation to the two of them. He said, “In Kaisarea here, we have detained a person, named Paulus. Previously the old governor didn't have an opportunity to decide his case.</bt><v n="15" />Baru-baru ni, waktu beta ada di Yerusalem, kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos deng tua-tua adat dong, datang lapor Paulus pung sala. Ais dong minta sang beta ko hukum sang dia.<bt>Just recently, when I was in Yerusalem, the *chief priests and the traditional elders, came to report Paulus' wrongs. And they requested me to judge him.</bt><v n="16" />Ma beta kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;Iko pamarenta Roma pung atoran, beta musti pareksa dolo itu parkara, baru kasi turun dia pung hukuman. Orang yang baparkara dong musti bamangada dolo. Beta mau dengar bosong kasi sala apa sang dia. Deng dia ju musti dapa kans ko bela diri. Baru beta bisa putus itu parkara, deng kasi jato hukuman apa sang dia.&gt;<bt>But I told them saying, ‘Following the regulations of the Roma government, I must first examine the case, only then give the punishment. The people who are involved in the litigation must appear [before me] first. I must hear what you accuse him of. And he also must have a chance to defend himself. Then I can decide the case, and send down the punishment/judgement for him.’</bt><v n="17" />Ais waktu beta kambali datang di Kaisarea, ada barapa orang Yahudi yang iko datang di sini. Dia pung beso, ju beta buka memang itu parkara. Beta suru dong bawa sang Paulus datang mangada sang beta, ko biar beta bisa dengar ini parkara pung dudu-badiri.<bt>So when I came back to Kaisarea, there were several Yahudi people who followed coming here. The next day, then I straight away opened that litigation. I ordered them to bring Paulus to face me, so that I could hear this litigation's background.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dudu-badiri = ujung pangkal (BI), ujung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">dudu-badiri = ujung pangkal (BI), ujung pohon (KM) +~ keadaan</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ais itu, orang Yahudi dong badiri ko mulai kasi tunju Paulus pung sala-sala dong. Ma apa yang dong kasi tunju sang beta tu, sonde sama barát deng apa yang beta su kira.<bt>After that, the Yahudi people stood to begin to show Paulus' wrongs. But what they showed me there, was not as heavy as that what I had thought.</bt><v n="19" />Dong cuma sonde bacocok so'al dong pung agama sandiri. Deng dong bakanjar lawan sang Paulus so'al satu Orang, nama Yesus. Iko itu orang Yahudi dong, Yesus tu, su mati. Ma Paulus bakincang bilang, Yesus tu, su idop ulang.<bt>They just could not agree about their own religious matters. And they argued against Paulus about a (certain) Person, named Yesus. According to those Yahudi people, that Yesus, was dead. But Paulus insisted that, that Yesus, was alive again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mati-mati = insisted, tegas tegar; bakincang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">mati-mati = insisted, tegas tegar; bakincang = insist ; batahan = insist, endure, persevere</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Dong bakanjar bagitu, ma tagal beta orang baru, jadi beta sonde tau mau putus parkara agama ni, karmana. Andia ko beta tanya sang Paulus bilang, &lt;Karmana kalo beta pareksa lu pung parkara ni di Yerusalem sa?&gt;<bt>They argued like that, but because I am a new person (recently arrived), thus I did not want to decide how this religious case should be. That's why I asked Paulus saying, ‘How about it if I just examine this case of yours in Yerusalem?’ [EXEG: Why is he uncertain? Not because of incompetence, but because he is a political animal who is still getting his bearings. He's only been in the job for days (see vs. 1,6,13) and still can use that as an excuse to get others' input without losing face. This “new person” makes perfect sense as a basis for uncertainty in Timor worldviews.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ma dia sonde mau. Jadi dia minta nae banding pi sang keser di pusat. Andia ko beta tahan tarús sang dia, sampe beta dapa sampát ko kirim sang dia pi Roma.&gt;&gt;<bt>But he refused. So (consequently) he requested to appeal to keser in the center (=seat of govt). That's why I have continued to detain him, until I get the chance to send him to Roma.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sampat = kans = salák ~"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sampat = kans = salák ~ waktu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dengar Festus pung carita bagitu, ju raja Agripa bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bisa, beta mau dengar langsung dari itu orang sandiri.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Festus' story like that, then raja Agripa said, “If possible, I would like to hear directly from that person himself.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Festus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bisa! Nanti beta ator ko beso bapa bisa dengar sandiri dari itu orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Festus replied saying, “It can be done. I will arrange things so that tomorrow, father (=you) himself can hear that person.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Raja Agripa mau dengar Paulus pung omong<bt>Raja Agripa wants to hear Paulus' talk</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Dia pung beso, gubernor Festus ator ko raja Agripa bisa dengar Paulus omong. Dia ator ko banya orang ju bisa dengar sang Paulus. Andia: komandán-komandán tantara, deng orang-orang bésar dari kota Kaisarea. Ais raja Agripa deng Bernike maso datang deng bastél pake pakean raja-raja. Ju orang dong samua kasi hormat sang dong dua. Waktu dong samua su bakumpul, ju gubernor suru bawa maso sang Paulus.<bt>The next day, governor Festus arrranged things so raja Agripa could hear Paulus talk. He arranged so that many people also could hear Paulus. That is: army commanders, and the big people from Kaisarea city. Then raja Agripa and Bernike entered coming with their raja clothes. And all the people there gave honor to the two of them. They they had all gathered, then the governor ordered to bring Paulus in.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02034b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none;horizontalPosition:center">Paulus di muka orang bésar dong<bt>Paulus in front of the big (important) people</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ju dong bawa maso sang Paulus. Ais gubernor angka omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Raja Agripa, bapa-bapa, deng tamu dong samua yang beta hormat. Ini orang ni, dia pung nama Paulus. Ada barapa kapala orang Yahudi yang angka parkara deng dia. Ais ada yang datang sang beta, bae di Yerusalem, bae di sini, ko mau paksa sang beta bilang, ini orang ni, sonde pantas idop lai.<bt>And they brought in Paulus. Then the governor began to talk saying, “King Agripa, fathers, and all guests whom I respect. This person here, his name is Paulus. There are several Yahudi leaders who are making a litigation case with him. So then there are those who have come to me, both in Yerusalem, and also here, to force me saying, this person here, is no longer worthy of living.</bt><v n="25" />Andia ko beta pareksa sang dia, ma beta sonde dapa dia pung sala yang pas deng hukum mati. Ma tagal dia sandiri su minta nae banding pi pusat, andia ko mau tar mau, beta musti kirim sang dia pi Roma sa.<bt>That's why I examined him, but I cannot find a wrong of his that fits with the death sentence. But because he himself has requested an appeal to the centre, that is why whether (I) want to or not, I must just send him to Roma.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mau tar mau ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">mau tar mau =</Message></Annotation><v n="26-27" />Kalo beta kirim sang dia, tantu beta musti tulis satu surat pangantar. Ma sakarang, beta musti tulis apa, kasi sang raja bésar? Andia ko beta kumpul bapa dong samua, ko dengar sang dia. Dengar abis sang dia, beta harap bapa raja Agripa bisa kasi nasiat sang beta, ko biar beta bisa tulis hal yang maso akal kasi sang raja bésar. Beta rasa sonde enak, kalo beta kirim ini parkara pi sang keser, ma sonde kasi tau ini orang pung sala apa.<bt>If I send him, surely I must write an introductory letter. But now, what must I write, to the big raja? That's why I have gathered all (you) fathers, to listen to him. After hearing him, I hope that father raja Agripa can give advice to me, so that I can write something that makes sense to that big raja. I don't feel good about it, if I send this case to keser, but don't tell what this person's wrong is.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta pung omong bagitu sa. Makasi.&gt;&gt;<bt>My talk is just that. Thanks.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus bela diri di muka raja Agripa [\s2]<bt>Paulus defends himself in front of raja Agripa [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="26" />
      <v n="1" />Ais ju raja Agripa suru sang Paulus bilang, &lt;&lt;Sakarang lu bisa bela lu pung diri. Botong samua su siap ko mau dengar sang lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then raja Agripa ordered Paulus saying, “Now you can defend yourself. We all are ready to hear you.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Paulus kasi sein deng dia pung tangan, ais dia angka omong bilang,<bt>Paulus made a sign with his hand, then he spoke saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />&lt;&lt;Bapa raja Agripa yang beta hormat. Beta rasa ontong, tagal bapa kasi loos sang beta ko bole carita kasi sang bapa dong, samua hal yang orang Yahudi ada tudu sang beta.<bt>“Father raja Agripa whom I respect. I fell fortunate, because father  (=you) has given permission for me to tell the fathers, all the things which the Yahudi people are accusing me of. [EXEG: RL driven-this is the natural way in these lgs of saying “thank you for letting me speak to the accusations”. Don't force the word ‘defense’ to be here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tudu = tuduh, accuse ; ***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tudu = tuduh, accuse ; *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mua pi atas beta pung diri."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">mua pi atas beta pung diri.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Beta tau bilang, bapa mangarti batúl kotong orang Yahudi pung adat, deng kotong pung so'al mati-idop. Jadi beta minta bapa dengar bae-bae sang beta.<bt>I know that father (=you) understands well our Yahudi people's rituals/customs, and our problems. So (consequently) I ask that father (=you) listen carefully to me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="so'al mati-idop = masalah, problems"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">so'al mati-idop = masalah, problems</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Mulai dari kici, dong su ajar sang beta ko idop iko kotong orang Yahudi pung adat. Mula-mula beta dapa ajar di beta pung kampong; ais beta datang ko sakola tamba lai di Yerusalem. Orang Yahudi yang ada di Yerusalem dong, tau beta pung jalan idop, deng dong kanál batúl sang beta.<bt>Starting from when I was small, they taught me to live following our Yahudi people's rituals. At the beginning I was taught in my village, then I went to go to more school in Yerusalem. The Yahudi people who are in Yerusalem, know my life path, and they truly know me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jalan idop = life, way of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">jalan idop = life, way of life, lifestyle</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Kalo bos-bos agama dong mau, dong bisa carita bilang, dong su kanál sang beta dari dolu. Ko beta ni, ju maso partei agama Farisi. Samua orang tau bilang, botong orang Farisi ni, yang paling karás iko orang Yahudi pung atoran agama samua.<bt>If the religious bosses want to, they can tell that they knew me from before. Because <span class="Italic">(ko)</span> I here, also am a member of the Farisi party. [+emphatic] All people know that, we Farisi people here, [are the ones] who are the most forceful/careful in following all the Yahudi people's religious regulations.</bt><note reference="26:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 23:6, Filipi 3:5</note><v n="6-8" />Beta, deng orang Isra'el dari 12 suku samua, ada tunggu-tunggu ko Tuhan Allah bekin iko Dia pung janji. Itu janji tu, Dia su kasi tau sang kotong pung nene-moyang dari dolu-kala. Jadi sampe sakarang ni, kotong samua sambayang siang-malam, ko biar Tuhan pung janji tu, jadi suda. Itu janji pung isi bilang, nanti Dia kasi idop kambali orang yang su mati dong.<bt>I, and Israel people from all 12 tribes, are waiting for the Lord God to do according to His promise. That promise there, He told to our ancestors long ago. So up until now, we all have worshiped/prayed day-night, so that that promise of the Lord's, would happen. That promise's contents, say, He will give life to the dead people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Bapa raja Agripa yang beta hormat. Tagal beta parcaya bilang, nanti Tuhan kasi idop kambali orang mati, andia ko dong bekin parkara deng beta. Beta mau tanya: akurang ko ada dari bosong yang sonde mau parcaya bilang, Tuhan Allah mampu kasi idop orang yang su mati? Tantu Dia mampu!<bt>Father raja Agripa whom I respect. Because I believe, that the Lord will give live to dead people, that's why they make a litigation with me. I want to ask: why are those of you who do not want to believe that the Lord God is able to give life to people who are dead? Of course He is able!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong ju parcaya bilang Tuhan Allah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Dong ju parcaya bilang Tuhan Allah mampu kasi idop orang mati, tagal Dia su janji bagitu dari dolu deng kotong pung nene-moyang dong. Di kotong pung karaja'an dua blas suku Isra'el sakarang, orang su banya. Siang-malam dong samua sambayang sang Tuhan deng baharap bilang nanti Tuhan kasi idop orang mati. Ma, Raja Agripa, dia pung masala bagini. Beta tapaksa badiri di ini pangadilan ni, tagal beta percaya bilang Tuhan su kasi idop ulang sang Yesus. Ma iko ini orang dong yang lawan sang beta, beta sonde pantas parcaya bagitu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Dolu memang beta bekin apa sa, ko malawan deng karás samua orang yang iko sang Yesus, orang Nasaret.<bt>Previously I did what ever I could, to strongly oppose all the people who follow Yesus, the Nasaret person.</bt><v n="10-11" />Itu waktu, kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos kasi kuasa sang beta, ko beta pi bekin susa sang Yesus pung orang dong di mana-mana. Beta tangkap sang dong, ais beta hela bawa datang di Yerusalem, ko buang kasi maso sang dong pi dalam bui. Beta ju iko putus ko kasi hukum mati sang dong saparu. Beta ju maso pi dalam ruma-ruma sambayang, ko bekin sangsara sang dong. Ais beta mau paksa sang dong ko manyangkal sang Yesus. Banya kali, beta pi buru sang dong deng hati panas. Asal beta dengar itu orang yang parcaya sang Yesus dong ada di mana sa, biar sampe di luar negrí, beta pi buru sang dong ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, the chief priests gave power to me, so that I could go cuz (elaboration) difficultly to Yesus people everywhere. I captured them, then I dragged brought them to Yerusalem, to throw them in jail. I also followed the decision to have some of them sentenced to death. I also entered into worship houses, to cuz (elaboration) tribulation to them. Then I wanted to force them to reject Yesus. Many times, I went to hunt them with a hot liver (=anger). Whenever I heard that there were believers in Yesus where ever, even outside the country, I would go hunt them!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="toe / nodek / pusing /"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">toe / nodek / pusing / hosek bale balakang kasi tenga = reject ~ manyangkal; hati mandidi/panas = inspired (neg), 1) anger, 2) consumed by s.t., tidak pikir laen, obsessed; buang luda = (fig) menghinakan, reject,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bukan beta sandiri yang bekin susa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Bukan beta sandiri yang bekin susa sang dong, te kotong pung bos-bos agama yang suru beta bagitu. Waktu itu, beta maen buang Yesus pung orang pi dalam bui di Yerusalem. Beta ju satuju sampe ada yang kaná hukuman mati.</Message></Annotation><note reference="26:9-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 8:3, 22:4-5</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus carita ulang dia pung pangalaman [\s2]<bt>Paulus tells his experience [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Utusan dong pung Carita 9:1-19, 22:6-16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Paulus omong sambung bilang, &lt;&lt;Satu kali, kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos kasi surat kuasa sang beta ko pi buru sang Yesus pung orang dong di kota Damsik. Ais beta pi.<bt>One time, the *chief priests gave a letter of authority to me to go hunt Yesus' people in Damsik city. So I went.</bt><v n="13" />Bapa raja Agripa! Waktu botong masi ada di tenga jalan, kira-kira tenga hari, takuju sa, ada satu taráng dari langit yang tajam mau mati, datang senter kaná sang beta deng beta pung tamán dong.<bt>Father raja Agripa! When we-exc were still in the middle of the road, approximately mid day, suddenly, there was a light from the sky that was exceedingly sharp, coming to shine on me and my friends.</bt><v n="14" />Botong samua jato tabanting pi tana, tagal itu taráng pung tajam. Ais beta dengar satu suara omong deng beta, pake bahasa Aram,<bt>We all fell flat down on the ground, because of that light's sharpness. Then I heard a voice talking to me, using the Aram</bt><note reference="26:14" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Di tulisan bahasa Yunani ada tulis bilang, &lt;orang Ibrani pung bahasa&gt;. Dong pung bahasa hari-hari, andia bahasa Aram. Ada tulis umpama ju, bilang, &lt;susa kalo lu kosi itu kosa tarús&gt; Dong biasa pake kosa ko tusu foo sapi. Sapi yang malawan, kosi itu kosa, ais kaná saki. Itu umpama pung arti bilang, &lt;susa kalo lu maen malawan tarús Beta pung mau.&gt;<bt>In the bahasa Yunani writing it is written saying, ‘the Ibrani people's language’. Their everyday language, it.was Aram langauge. There is also written a parable saying, ‘it's hard if you kick those goads continually’. [NOTE: English <span class="Italic">goad, </span>Kupang <span class="Italic">kosa: </span>a sharp stick used to poke/ goad/ prod/ tusuk cattle to go into a narrow chute.] They often used a goad to herd cows. Cows that rebelled kicked that goad, and so felt pain. That parable's meaning is ‘it's hard if you repeated oppose My will.’</bt></note>bilang, &lt;We, Saul! Akurang ko lu maen bekin sangsara sang Beta tarús-tarús? Talalu susa kalo lu maen malawan tarús Beta pung mau.&gt;<bt>langauge saying, ‘We, [+attention] Saul! Why are you repeatedly causing tribulation to Me over and over? If very hard if you continually oppose My will.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kosa = goad, used for horses"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kosa = goad, used for horses (BI), (historically cognate with memperkosa = rape)</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Beta dengar itu suara, ma sonde dapa lia dia pung orang. Jadi beta tanya bilang, &lt;Bos yang omong ni, sapa, é?&gt;<bt>I heard that voice, but didn't see it's person. Then I asked saying, ‘The Boss who is speaking this, who are you, é?’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais itu suara manyao sang beta bilang, &lt;Beta ni, Yesus, yang lu maen bekin sangsara tarús.<bt>Then that voice replied to me saying, 'I here, Yesus, whom you continually cuz (elaboration) tribulation.</bt><v n="16" />Saul! Bangun suda! Beta kasi tunju diri sang lu ni, ko lu jadi Beta pung orang parcaya. Lu musti pi kasi tau orang dong samua, apa yang lu su lia dari Beta ini hari. Nanti Beta kasi tunju tamba sang lu lai, hal-hal yang baru, ko lu bisa pi kasi tau sang orang dong samua.<bt>Saul! Get up! I have shown Myself to you now/here, so that you become My trusted person. And, you must go tell all people that which you have seen from Me this day. I will show more to you, new matters, so that you can go tell all people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sakoleng = swing = (right) hook;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sakoleng = swing = (right) hook; ka'o = K.O.; keok = menyerah, kalah ko bangun lari; utusan ~ tangan kanan ~ orang parcaya ~ wakil</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Nanti lu dapa susa macam-macam. Ma Beta jaga sang lu dari orang-orang yang mau bekin susa sang lu, bae dari orang Yahudi, bae dari orang bangsa laen dong. Batúl! Beta utus sang lu pi orang-orang yang bukan Yahudi dong.<bt>Later you will get all kinds of difficulty. But I will protect you from the people who want to cuz (elaboration) difficulty to you, both from Yahudi people, and from other people. It's true! I am commissioning you to go to the people who are not Yahudi.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bae...bae = both ... and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bae...bae = both ... and</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nanti Beta jaga lu dari orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Nanti Beta jaga lu dari orang Yahudi yang sonde suka sang Beta sampe dong mau coba bekin susa sang lu. Biar orang laen ju mau bekin susa sang lu, ma Beta jaga tarús. Te Beta mau kirim lu pi di orang yang bukan orang Yahudi.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Lu pi buka dong pung mata, ko biar dong mangarti, deng idop dalam taráng. Ais dong kasi tenga dong pung jalan idop yang bengko-re'o dong. Deng lu ju musti kasi tunju sang dong jalan idop yang lurus. Lu kasi lapás sang dong dari setan dong pung bos pung kuasa, ais bawa sang dong pi Tuhan Allah. Deng bagitu, Tuhan Allah hapus buang dong pung sala samua. Dong ju jadi Tuhan pung orang, sama-sama deng orang laen yang Tuhan su pili ame, tagal dong parcaya sang Beta. Itu sa yang Beta mau kasi tau sang lu, Saul.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>You go open their eyes, so that they can understand, and live in the light. Then they will leave their life paths which are crooked. And you must show them the life path that is straight. You free them from Satan's power, then bring them to the Lord God. With that, the Lord God will erase throw away all their wrongs. They will also become the Lord's people, together with the other peole whom the Lord has chosen, because they believe in Me. That all that I want to tell you, Saul.’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="added concept of evil (jalan bengko-bengko)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">added concept of evil (jalan bengko-bengko) and righteousnes (jalan lurus) to help explain potentially confusing metaphors of light/dark (glap/trang).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta utus lu ko lu pi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Beta utus lu ko lu pi bekin trang dong pung mata, ko dong bale balakang kasi tenga jalan bengko-bengko di glap, ais iko jalan lurus di trang. Dong musti buang kasi tenga kuasa dari setan dong pung bos bésar, ko iko Tuhan Allah pung kuasa. Abis, Tuhan Allah lupa buang dong pung sala-sala. Dong jadi Tuhan pung orang tapili, tagal dong parcaya sang Beta. Na, Beta pung omong sang lu, bagitu sa, Saulus.'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus kasi tau dia pung karjá [\s2]<bt>Paulus tells about his work [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Paulus omong sambung bilang, &lt;&lt;Jadi bapa raja. Beta su kasi jalan tugas yang beta tarima langsung dari sorga. Sampe sakarang, beta masi karjá tarús, sonde ondor sadiki ju.<bt>Paulus continued speaking saying, &lt;&lt;So (consequently) father raja. I have already undertaken that work/task which I received directly from heaven. Until now, I still work continually, without reversing even a little bit.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pas = langkah (not known by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pas = langkah (not known by UNS's)</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Partama beta kasi tau Yesus pung Jalan Idop sang orang Yahudi dong yang ada di Damsik. Ais itu, beta datang kasi tau sang orang Yahudi yang ada di Yerusalem, deng di propinsi Yudea samua. Ais itu, ju beta jalan kuliling pi orang bukan Yahudi pung negrí dong. Beta omong tarús-taráng sang dong samua, ko dong kasi tenga dong pung jalan idop yang sala, deng sarakan dong pung diri sang Tuhan Allah. Dong ju musti bekin yang bae dalam dong pung idop kasi orang laen, ko jadi tanda bilang, dong su jadi orang baru dalam Tuhan.<bt>First I told Yesus' Life Path to the Yahudi people in Damsik. After that, I came to tell the Yahudi people who were in Yerusalem, and all Yudea province. After that, then I travelled around to the countries of the people who are not Yahudi. I spoke with clarity to them all, so that they would leave their life paths that were wrong, and surrounder themselves to the Lord God. They also had to do good things in their lives for other people, to be a sign that they had become new people in the Lord.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta su kasi tau Yesus pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Beta su kasi tau Yesus pung omong itu sang orang di mana-mana. Bilang dong musti barenti deng dong pung sala ko iko Tuhan pung jalan. Abis, dong musti idop bae ko bekin tanda, bilang, dong su jadi Tuhan pung orang. Beta bacarita bagitu di kota Damsik, abis di kota Yerusalem. Abis itu, beta pi bacarita kuliling propinisi Yudea. Sampe beta ju pi bacarita sang orang yang bukan kotong pung orang Yahudi.</Message></Annotation><note reference="26:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 9:20, 28-29</note><v n="21" />Tagal beta karjá bagitu, ju orang Yahudi dong tangkap sang beta di Ruma Sambayang Pusat di Yerusalem. Dong ju mau bunu sang beta.<bt>Because I worked like that, then the Yahudi people captured me in the Temple in Yerusalem. They wanted to murder me.</bt><v n="22" />Ma Tuhan Allah tolong sang beta. Andia ko beta masi idop sampe sakarang. Tagal itu, beta bisa badiri di sini, ko carita kasi samua orang, kici-bésar, so'al Yesus pung Jalan Idop. Apa yang beta bilang ni, samua cocok deng apa yang ba'i Musa deng Tuhan pung jubir dolu-dolu dong su ajar.<bt>But the Lord God helped me. That's why I am still alive until now. Because of that, I can stand here, to tell to all people, little-big, about Yesus' Life Path. That which I say here, it all matches with what was taught by Gf/Ff Musa and the Lord's spokespersons from before.</bt><v n="23" />Dong ajar so'al Kristus, andia Orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji mau kirim datang. Bilang, Dia musti pikol sangsara, ais Dia mati, ma abis, Dia jadi orang partama yang Tuhan Allah kasi idop kambali. Dia yang nanti kasi taráng sang orang Yahudi dong, deng suku-bangsa laen di bumi.&gt;&gt;<bt>They taught about Kristus, that is the Person whom the Lord God promised to send. Saying, He would shoulder.carry tribulation, then He would die, but after He would become the first person whom the Lord God caused to live again. He [is the one] who would give light to the Yahudi people, and the other ethnic groups on the earth.”</bt><note reference="26:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 42:6, 49:6, 1 Korintus 15:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Paulus masi omong ko kasi tau dia pung karjá, ju Festus langsung potong dia pung omong deng suara karás bilang, &lt;&lt;He, Paulus! Lu su gila mangkali. Lu tau talalu banya, sampe bekin lu pung otak miring.&gt;&gt;<bt>Paulus was still talking about his work, then Festus immediately cut (interrupted) his talking in a loud voice saying, “He! Paulus! You're probably crazy. You know too much, to the point that it has made your brain tilted (=not quite right in the head).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kapala skopeng = otak miring, mad,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kapala skopeng = otak miring, mad, crazy, wierd; ilmu = 1) knowledge, 2) magic, sorcery</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ma Paulus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa gubernor yang beta hormat. Beta sonde gila. Samua yang beta kasi tau ni, memang batúl. Beta sonde karang-karang.<bt>But Paulus replied saying, “Father governor whom I respect. I am not crazy. All which I am telling here, is really true. I have not made it up.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lupa diri = 1) unconscious, 2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">lupa diri = 1) unconscious, 2) carefree, 3) bertindak di luar kontrol; karang-karang = making things up = bekin-bekin</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Bapa raja Agripa sandiri tau batúl, apa yang beta bilang ni. Andia ko beta barani bicara tarús-taráng. Beta parcaya bilang, bapa raja su dengar ini hal samua, tagal apa yang su jadi tu, sonde jadi di tampa sunyi. Bilang, Yesus yang mati, su idop kambali. Samua orang ju su tau itu hal.<bt>Father raja Agripa (=you) himself knows it true, that which I say here. That's why I dare speak with openness. I believe that father raja (=you) has heard all these matter, because that which has happened, has not happened in a lonely place (=so no one hears about it). That, that Yesus who died, has lived again. All people know about that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta omong lurus-lurus bagini tagal Raja"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Beta omong lurus-lurus bagini tagal Raja Agripa sandiri tau itu batúl. Bapa sandiri ju tau, bilang, Yesus memang mati, ais Dia bangun kombali dari Dia pung mati itu. Te itu bukan hal sambunyi-sambunyi. Samua orang tau, na.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Dari dolu-kala, Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong su kasi tau memang ini hal. Beta barani bataru bilang, bapa raja ju parcaya itu jubir dong pung omong, aa?&gt;&gt;<bt>From long ago, the Lord God's spokespersons told ahead about this matter. I'd be willing to bet that father raja  (=you) also believes those spokesperson's talk, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="barani bataru = yakin batul ,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">barani bataru = yakin batul , willing to bet</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, karmana, Raja Agripa? Tempo dolu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Jadi, karmana, Raja Agripa? Tempo dolu Tuhan pake Dia pung jubir ko kasi tau apa yang nanti jadi. Iko Bapa, itu batúl, ko sonde? Sonde, itu memang batúl! Beta tau bapa ju parcaya bagitu.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Raja Agripa langsung potong dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Paulus! Sonde lama lai, lu su mau bekin sang beta jadi orang Kristen!&gt;&gt;<bt>Raja Agripa immediately interrupted his talk saying, “We! Paulus! Soon you will have made me become a Kristen!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="amper-amper = lai sadiki, tar lama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">amper-amper = lai sadiki, tar lama lai, sonde lama lai</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ma Paulus manyao sang raja bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini, bapa. Beta sambayang sang Tuhan Allah, ko biar capát ko lama, bukan cuma bapa raja sa, ma samua orang yang ini hari ada dengar beta pung omong ni, bisa jadi sama ke beta, andia Yesus pung orang! Ma asal bapa dong jang jadi orang yang kaná tahan sama ke beta ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Paulus replied to the raja saying, “It's like this, father. I pray to the Lord God, so whether quickly, or longly, not only just father raja (=you), but all the people who this day are hearing this talk of mine, can become the same as me, that is Yesus' people. But just as long as the fathers don't become a person who is detained like me here.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Paulus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar capát-capát, ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Paulus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar capát-capát, ko plan-plan. Ma beta minta sang Tuhan Allah, kalo bole, bapa percaya sang Yesus sama ke beta. Bukan bapa sandiri yang beta minta, ma samua orang yang ada di sini, beta minta ko dong jadi orang Kristen sama ke beta. Cuma sonde parlú beta pung ika ni. Jang-jangan bosong ju jadi orang bui.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Paulus omong abis bagitu, ju raja Agripa, deng dia pung adi Bernike, deng gubernor Festus, deng samua orang bésar-bésar dong, bangun badiri, ko pulang.<bt>Paulus finished speaking like that, then raja Agripa, and his younger sibling Bernike, and governor Festus, and all the big people, go up, to go home.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Waktu dong jalan kaluar, itu orang dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang sonde bekin apa-apa yang pantas deng hukum mati, ko, kasi maso sang dia pi dalam bui!&gt;&gt;<bt>When they were walking out, those people spoke to each other saying, “This person had not done any thing worthy of the death sentence, or, have him put in jail!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ais raja Agripa kasi tau sang gubernor Festus bilang, &lt;&lt;Kasian, é! Ini orang su minta nae banding pi pusat di Roma. Kalo sonde, ini parkara su bisa abis, deng su bisa lapás sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then raja Agripa told governor Festus saying, “It's too bad. This person has requested an appeal at the center in Roma. If not, this litigation could be finished, and he could be freed.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong bawa sang Paulus pi Roma<bt>They bring Paulus to Roma</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="27" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, gubernor Festus putus ko kirim sang Paulus pi mangada sang raja bésar di Roma, ko putus dia pung parkara di sana. Ais dia sarakan sang Paulus deng barapa orang bui laen dong, pi satu komandán tantara, nama Yulius, ko antar sang dong pi propinsi Italia. Yulius tu, satu komandán dari tantara yang jaga sang keser.<bt>After that, governor Festus decided to send Paulus to face the big raja in Roma, to decide his case there. So he surrendered Paulus, and several other jail people(=prisoners) to an army commander, named Yulius, to deliever them to Italia province. That Yulius, was a commander from the army that guarded Keser.</bt><v n="2" />Itu waktu, beta (andia Lukas) pi iko antar sang Paulus. Ais masi ada satu sodara lai, orang Makedonia dari kota Tesalonika, nama Aristarkus, pi iko ju. Botong samua nae satu kapal yang datang dari kota Adramitium. Iko rancana, itu kapal nanti singga-singga di banya tampa di propinsi Asia.<bt>At that time, I (that is Lukas) went following to escort Paulus. Then there was one other sibling, a Makedonia person from Tesalonika city, named Aristarkus, who also went. We all got in a ship which came from Adramitium city. According to plan, that ship would stop at many places in Asia province.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Botong balayar kasi tenga Kaisarea, ais dia pung beso, botong sampe di kota Sidon. Komandán Yulius bekin sang Paulus deng bae-bae, deng kasi tau sang Paulus ko dia bole pi lia dia pung tamán dong di darat. Dia pung maksud, ko biar dong bisa kasi sang Paulus apa-apa yang dia parlú di laut.<bt>We sailed leaving Kaisarea, and then the next day, we arrived at Sidon city. Commander Yulius was good to Paulus, and he told him that he could go see his friends on land. His intent, was that they could give Paulus whatever he would need on the sea.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin sang P deng bae-bae ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bekin sang P deng bae-bae = tunjuk kemurahan, bersikap baik;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="maps\Bible\HkKsKret.tif" rtfFormat="width:11cm;textWrapping:none;horizontalPosition:center">Dari kota Kaisarea pi pulo Kreta<bt>From Kaisarea to Kreta island</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais botong samua nae ulang pi kapal ko mulai balayar. Ma angin muka talalu kincang, sampe itu kapal amper-amper sonde maju. Ais dong belok ko balayar iko teng-tenga pulo Siprus deng daratan Siria, ko biar tapele dari itu angin muka.<bt>Then we all embarked again on the ship to begin to sail. But the front wind was too strong, to the point that the ship almost could not go forward. Then they turned that ship, to sail following in the middle of Siprus island and mainland Siria, so to be protected from that front wind.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(balayar) opal = tack (sailing), balayar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">(balayar) opal = tack (sailing), balayar sik-sak (zig-zag)</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ais dari situ, botong balayar potong laut di muka propinsi Kilikia deng propinsi Pamfilia. Tarús botong balayar sampe di kota Mira, di da'era Likia. Sampe di situ, botong samua turun kasi tenga itu kapal.<bt>Then from there, we sailed acroos the sea in front of Kilikia province and Pamfilia province. Then2 we sailed until Mira city, in the region Likia. Arriving there, we all got down leaving behind that ship.</bt><v n="6" />Di Mira, komandán Yulius cari-cari kapal laen yang mau balayar pi Italia. Ais dia dapa satu kapal, yang datang dari kota Aleksandria, yang mau balayar pi Italia. Ju dia suru sang botong samua, ko nae pi atas itu kapal.<bt>In Mira, commander Yulius looked for another ship that wanted to sail to Italia. Then he found a ship, which came from Aleksandria city, which wanted to sail to Italia. And he ordered us ll, to get on board that ship.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Botong su balayar barapa hari, ma itu kapal amper-amper sonde mau maju, tagal angin muka talalu kincang. Ais botong balayar satenga mati, sampe amper deka deng kota Knidus. Ma angin masi tiop kincang tarús, jadi botong balayar potong pi pulo Kreta, ko biar tapele dari itu angin. Ais itu, baru botong lewat satu tanjung, nama Salmone.<bt>We had sailed several days, but that ship almost could not advance, because the front wind was too strong. So then we sailed with great difficulty, until almost close to Knidus city. But the wind still blew strong, so we sailed across to Kreta island, in order to be blocked/protected from that wind. After that, then we passed a point, named Salmone.</bt><v n="8" />Botong balayar deng susa-paya lewat itu tanjung, iko-iko pulo Kreta pung pante, baru botong bisa sampe di satu tampa, nama Labuan Bagus. Itu tampa deka deng kota Lasea.<bt>We sailed with great difficulty passing that point, following Kreta island's beach, then we could arrive a place, named Good Harbour. That place was close to Lasea city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="falús ~ fulus = uang (doi)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">falús ~ fulus = uang (doi) [Arabic?]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Di situ, ana bua kapal dong barenti cape sadiki, tagal botong su balayar talalu lama, ma balóm sampe di Italia. Itu waktu, orang Yahudi dong pung hari bésar Dapa Ampon Dosa ju su lewat.<bt>There, the ship underlings stop to take a break, because they had sail very long, but we had not yet arrived in Italia. At that time, the Yahudi people's big day of Getting Forgiveness for Sins had passed.</bt><note reference="27:9" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Waktu taon 59, orang Yahudi dong pung hari bésar Dapa Ampon Dosa jato kaná tanggal 5 Oktober. Itu waktu, su mulai musim barat-laut.<bt>In the year 59, the Yahudi people's big day for Gettiing Forgiven Sin fell on the date 5 Oktober. At that time, the northwest (wind) season was beginning.</bt></note>Dia pung arti, musim angin kincang deng galombang bésar su mulai. Ais ana bua kapal dong batanya bilang, mau balayar tarús, ko sonde. Dengar bagitu, ju Paulus angka omong<bt>It's meaning, the strong wind season and the big waves had started. So then the ship underlings asked if they should sail on, or not. Hearing that, then Paulus started to talk,</bt><v n="10" />bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong samua. Beta minta omong sadiki. Beta kira kalo kotong balayar tarús, nanti kotong bisa dapa susa banya. Bisa-bisa ini kapal tanggalám, barang-barang ilang, deng kotong ju bisa mati samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>saying, “Siblings. I request to talk a bit. I think if we sail on, we will encounter much difficulty. It could be that the ship sinks, things are lost, and we all could ever die.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bisa-bisa = ada kemungkinan, there is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bisa-bisa = ada kemungkinan, there is a possibility, jang sampe,</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ma itu komandán tantara sonde mau dengar sang Paulus. Dia lebe parcaya sang juragan, deng kapal pung tuan. Te dong rancana mau balayar kaluar dari itu tampa.<bt>But that army commander did not want to hear Paulus. He more believed/trusted the boat captain, and the one who owned the boat. Cuz (elaboration) they planned to sail out of that place.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jurangang = boat captain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">jurangang = boat captain</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Dia pung so'al, andia Labuan Bagus tu, sonde aman kalo kapal musti balabu di situ dalam musim galombang. Jadi banya dari dong yang mau ko botong balayar tarús, ko pi kota Feniks. Dong ada harap, kalo bisa, na, botong samua tenga di situ dalam musim galombang ni. Kota Feniks tu, pulo Kreta pung labuan yang paling bae, tagal dia tapele dari angin barat-daya deng barat-laut, deng bebas dari galombang bésar.<bt>The problem was, that Good Harbour there, was not safe for ships to be in harbour there during wave season. So (consequently) many of them who wanted for us to sail on, to go to Feniks city. They hoped, if possible, na, we could all stay there for this wave season. That Feniks city, was Kreta island best harbour, because it was protected from east monsoon winds and free from big waves.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="balabu ; musim ombak ; tapele"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">balabu ; musim ombak ; tapele ; labuan ; angin barat-daya deng angin barat-laut. ~ angin musim barat = (BI) angin muson, (monsoon); tabuka dari = open toward angin sapoi-sapoi fuu =<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sampe di satu teluk, yang orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sampe di satu teluk, yang orang bilang Feniks. Itu teluk Feniks memang teluk bae, te sonde ada angin di situ. Ais dong manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Sonde usa barenti di sini, te ini teluk sonde bae. Lebe bae kotong layar tarús sadiki sampe di teluk Feniks, baru kotong barenti sampe musim angin su abis.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Angin ribut di laut [\s2]<bt>Loud wind on the sea [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Waktu angin salatan mulai tiop palán-palán, dong kira dong su bisa pake itu angin ko balayar pi kota Feniks. Dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini angin bae. Mari kotong balayar suda!&gt;&gt; Jadi dong angka jangkar, deng hela kasi nae layar, ais botong balayar iko-iko pante.<bt>When a south wind began to blow slowly, they thought they could use that wind to sail to Feniks saying, “This is a good wind. Let's sail (imperative)!” So (consequently), they took up the anchor, and dragged up the sail, and we sailed along the shore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="fuu = tiup; fuu-fuu = magic,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">fuu = tiup; fuu-fuu = magic, hex</Message></Annotation><v n="14-15" />Ma botong balóm balayar talalu lama, te angin ribut takuju datang. (Yang orang bilang, &lt;angin timur-laut&gt;). Itu angin tiop bekin anyo itu kapal pi di tenga laut. Ana bua kapal sonde bisa bale aluan yang pas, ais dong kasi tenga sa, ko kapal anyo iko angin pung mau sa.<bt>But we had not sailed very long, and a big wind suddenly came. (Which people call, 'east-sea wind' [=northeast]). That wind blew making the ship drift, into the middle of the sea. The ship's underling could not turn the ship correctly, so they just left it, so that the ship just drifted according to the wind's desire.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anyut ; bale aluan = turn"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">anyut ; bale aluan = turn the ship *** (2009) BT fixed [=northeast]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02042b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Kapal kaná angin ribut<bt>The ship is affected by a big/loud wind</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Botong anyo iko galombang bagitu, sampe deka deng satu pulo kici, nama Kauda. Itu waktu, sakoci masi iko di buritan kapal deng tali. Ais botong hela satenga mati kasi nae itu sakoci pi atas kapal.<bt>We drifted along the waves like that, until close to a small island, named Kauda. At that time, the dingy was still following in back of the ship with a rope. So we pulled with great effort to bring the dingy onto the ship.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sakoci = dingy; kapal pung buritan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sakoci = dingy; kapal pung buritan</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Waktu sakoci su ada di atas kapal, ju dong mulai feo tali kuliling itu kapal pung badan, ko jaga, jang sampe kapal pung papan dong tabuka, ais tanggalám. Dong ju taku, jang sampe galombang banting itu kapal ko takandas di pasir meting Sirtis di Afrika sana. Jadi dong kasi turun jangkar apung di laut, ko kasi kurang itu kapal pung laju.<bt>When the dingy was on the ship, then they began to circle rope around the ship's body, to protect it, lest the ship's boards would get free, and then sink. They were also afraid, lest the waves beat that ship so that it go stuck on the tidal sand Sirtis in Afrika over there/distant. So (consequently) they threw the hanging anchors into the sea, to brake the ship's progress.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="feo tali = melingkarkan; lunas ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">feo tali = melingkarkan; lunas = keel; jangkar apung = hanging anchor, rem; batu piak = offshore rocks, covered at high tide, but visible at low tide; beting = pasir meting yang jao, sandbar; takandas = stuck on ; banting = throw the ship up on</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju kotong ika itu sakoci pi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Ju kotong ika itu sakoci pi atas kapal, ais kotong ika tali kuliling itu kapal, jang-jangan sampe dia pica. Te itu ana bua kapal, dong taku jang sampe angin bawa kotong sampe batu piak(?) di pulo Siritis deka deng Afrika. Jadi dong kasi turun itu kapal pung layar, ko kotong sonde pi jao.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Itu angin kincang banting botong pung kapal kiri-kanan. Jadi dia pung beso, ana bua kapal dong mulai angka buang kapal pung muatan pi dalam laut.<bt>That strong wind beat our ship left-right. Then the next day, the ship's underlings begain to pick up and throw away the ship's cargo into the sea.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia pung beso, itu angin balum"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Dia pung beso, itu angin balum barenti. Ais ana bua kapal dong mulai buang barang di laut.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Dia pung beso lai, angin ribut masi tiop deng karás. Jadi dong tamba taku lai. Andia ko dong bekin ringan kapal, deng buang tamba lai kapal pung muatan. Kapal pung alat dong, ju ana bua angka buang deng dong pung tangan sandiri.<bt>The next day again, the strong wind still blew hard. So they were more afraid. That's why they made the ship light, and threw out more of the ship's cargo. The ship's tools/instuments, the underlings also picked up and threw out with their own hands.</bt><v n="20" />Siang-malam itu angin ribut sonde barenti sadiki ju sampe barapa hari, deng mandúng bagitu tabal sampe botong su sonde bisa lia matahari deng bintang. Botong samua su putus asa, deng rasa bilang, botong su sonde bisa salamat lai.<bt>Day-night that noisy wind did not stop even for a little bit, and it was cloudy so thickly that we could not see the sun or stars. We all had given up hope, and felt that we could not be saved any longer.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mandúng = mendung ; putus asa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">mandúng = mendung ; putus asa</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Su barapa hari ni, botong sonde makan apa-apa lai. Ju Paulus pange sang dong samua, ais dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong samua! Coba, kalo bosong su iko beta pung omong, ko sonde balayar kasi tenga Labuan Bagus, tantu sakarang kotong sonde dapa susa banya bagini, deng sonde rugi apa-apa.<bt>It was already several days, we had not eaten anything. And Paulus called us all, and he said saying, “All sibligs! Look, if you had followed my talk, to not sail leaving behind Good Harbour, surely we would not be in this difficulty now, and we would not have lost anything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te su lama kotong sonde makan."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Te su lama kotong sonde makan. Ais Paulus bakumpul orang dua ratus lebe di itu kapal, ko omong sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;{Term of address}! Kalo bosong sonde lawan sang beta, kotong sonde dapa susa bagini. Kalo kotong sonde kasi tenga itu Teluk Bae, kotong sonde kanal ini susa!</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Ma sakarang, beta minta sang bosong samua ko bekin hati bésar sa. Nanti kotong pung kapal ni, ancor buang. Ma jang taku, te sonde ada orang yang mati.<bt>But now, I ask you all to just take heart (make your livers big). Later this ship of ours, will be destroyed thrown away. But don't fear, because there will not be any person who dies.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati besar = samangat, jang putus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">hati besar = samangat, jang putus asa, take heart, have hope;</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Beta mau bosong samua tau bilang, beta ni, Tuhan Allah pung orang, deng beta dapa tugas dari Dia. Tadi malam, Dia ada utus Dia pung ana bua satu dari sorga, ko datang badiri di beta pung sablá. Ais dia kasi tau sang beta bilang,<bt>I want all of you to know that I here, am the Lord God's person, and I have received a job from Him. Last night, He sent one his angels from heaven, to come stand at my side. Then he told me saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta pung omong ni, batúl. Tagal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Beta pung omong ni, batúl. Tagal Tuhan Allah su kasi tau sang Beta. Itu Tuhan Allah, Tuhan yang beta sambayang. Beta su jadi Dia pung ana. Ais tadi malam Dia suru dia pung utusan dari sorga satu ko pi di beta kasi tau, bilang,</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />&lt;Paulus! Lu sonde usa taku apa-apa. Nanti lu musti mangada sang raja bésar di Roma ko urus lu pung parkara. Tagal Tuhan pung hati bae sang lu, andia ko Dia ju kasi salamat sang ini orang dong samua yang ada di atas ini kapal.&gt;<bt>‘Paulus! You don't need to be afraid of anything. You will stand before big raja in Rome to take care of your litigation. Because the Lord's liver is good to you, that's why He will also save all these people who are on this ship.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng iko Tuhan pung hati bae,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Deng iko Tuhan pung hati bae, = berdasarkan kemurahan Allah</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Jadi sodara dong samua. Bosong sonde usa pata samangat. Beta parcaya batúl sang Tuhan Allah bilang, apa yang Dia kasi tau sang beta tadi malam tu, nanti jadi parsís bagitu.<bt>So (consequently) all you siblings. We don't need to lose ethusiasm. I truly believe the Lord God, that what He told me last night, it will happen exactly like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parsis = tepat, exactly, precisely ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">parsis = tepat, exactly, precisely ; pata samangat</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Ma ini kapal nanti tadampar pi satu pulo.&gt;&gt;<bt>But this ship will be thrown up on an island.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tadampar = thrown up on (implies"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">tadampar = thrown up on (implies more danger than takandas) ; takandas = run aground (kapal masi anteru)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te nanti ini kapal ilang, ma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Te nanti ini kapal ilang, ma kotong samua dapa bernang sampe di pante. Sonde ada satu orang dari kotong yang mati.&gt;&gt; Deng bagitu sa, Paulus tutu dia pung omong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kapal deka-deka darat [\s2]<bt>The ship is close to land [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Itu waktu, ombak-angin puku barmaen deng kasi anyo sang botong su 14 hari di laut Adria. Ma kira-kira tenga malam, ana bua kapal dong rasa ke botong su ada deka-deka darat.<bt>At that time, the waves-wind beat over and over and made us drift already 14 days in the Adria Sea. But approximately mid night, the ships underlings felt like we were near land.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ta'apung = tossed about ; rasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">ta'apung = tossed about ; rasa ke /bilang/yang/kira @@ complementiser</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis itu, itu angin bawa kotong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Abis itu, itu angin bawa kotong iko ombak sampe jao di laut itam, andia itu laut yang dong kasi nama bilang Adria. Kotong iko-iko ombak sampe ampa blas hari. Ais satu malam, amper-amper tenga malam, ana bua kapal dong rasa bilang kotong su deka deng pante.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Ais dong kasi turun lot, ko mau cari tau aer pung dalam. Ju dong ukur dapa 20 depa. Ais kapal maju sadiki lai, dong kasi turun ulang itu lot, deng dapa aer pung dalam, 15 depa.<bt>So they threw down the line with a weight on it, to find out the water's depth. And they measured 20 depa (= fathoms). The the ship advanced a bit more, they put down the line again, and got the water's depth to be 15 depa.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buang/tarek lot1 = buang undi; kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">buang/tarek lot1 = buang undi; kasi turun lot = batu duga (BI) ; lot2 = 1) builders line with weight on end (see LB00125C.tif); line for sounding depth (lead weight with knots spaced at fathom intervals (depa)</Message></Annotation><note reference="27:28" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">20 depa, andia 37 meter. 15 depa, andia 27 meter.<bt>20 fathoms is 37 meters. 15 fathoms is 27 meters.</bt></note><v n="29" />Dong samua taku, jang sampe itu kapal kandas di batu piak. Jadi dong kasi turun jangkar buritan ampa biji di balakang. Ais botong samua harap-harap, ko biar hari capát siang.<bt>They were all afraid, lest tha ship break apart on the off-shore rocks (hidden at high tide). So (consequently) they put down four stern anchors. Then we all hoped, that it would quickly become day.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batu piak = batu karang; piak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">batu piak = batu karang; piak known, but not as widely used</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng bagitu dong tau kotong su"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Deng bagitu dong tau kotong su deka deng tana. Dong masi taku, jang-jangan itu kapal tabrak batu bésar ko pica. Ais dong kasi turun jangkar ampa bua dari kapal pung balakang. Ju dong sambayang minta, kalo bole, cepa-cepa jadi trang.</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Ma ana bua kapal dong basakongkol ko mau lari kasi tenga itu kapal diam-diam. Jadi dong kasi turun sakoci, ko bekin sama ke dong mau kasi turun jangkar haluan dong dari muka.<bt>But the ships underlings were in agreement to run leaving that ship secretly. So they put down the dingy, to make as if they wanted to put down bow anchors from the front.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="haluan = bow/prow of ship, depan;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">haluan = bow/prow of ship, depan; bekin sama ke = seolah-olah, as if</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu ana bua kapal dong pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Itu ana bua kapal dong pung akal ko dong lari kasi tenga kotong di itu kapal. Ais dong kasi turun itu sakoci, pura-pura ke dong mau kasi turun jankar di kapal pung muka.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ma Paulus kasi tau dong pung akal busuk sang komandán deng tantara dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo itu ana bua kapal dong sonde tenga di atas kapal, nanti bosong mati samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Paulus told their evil plan to the commander and those soldiers saying, “If those ship underlings don't stay on this ship, we will all die.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Dengar Paulus omong bagitu, ju itu tantara dong potong kasi putus itu sakoci pung tali, ko kasi tenga itu sakoci anyo. Jadi itu ana bua kapal dong sonde bisa lari lai.<bt>Hearing Paulus talk like that, then those soldiers cut separating that dingy's rope, to let that dingy drift. So (consequently) those ship underlings could not run away anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anyo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">anyo</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Waktu hari mulai siang, ju Paulus buju sang itu orang dong samua ko makan. Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Su dua minggu ni, kotong cuma bisa dudu, ko harap-harap sa, deng sonde isi kotong pung parú deng satu apa ju.<bt>When the day began to get let, then Paulus convinced all those people to eat. He said, “It's now two weeks, we have only sat, just hoping, and have not filled our stomaches with any thing at all.</bt><v n="34" />Jadi beta minta ko biar kotong makan ame sadiki dolo, ko kotong bisa dapa kambali kotong pung tanaga. Beta parcaya bilang, nanti sonde ada satu dari kotong yang dapa calaka. Kotong samua pasti salamat!&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) I request that we eat a little bit, so that we can get our strenght back. I believe that there will not be anyone of us who encouters misfortune. We all can surely be saved!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Omong abis bagitu, ju Paulus angka ame roti. Ais dia sambayang minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan di dong samua pung muka. Ais itu, dia ame satu potong ko makan.<bt>Finishing speaking like that, then Paulus picked up some bread. Then he prayed thankyou to the Lord in front of them all. After that, then he took a piece to eat.</bt><v n="36-37" />Lia bagitu, ju dong pung hati kuat kambali. Ais dong ju iko makan rame-rame. Botong samua yang ada di kapal tu, ada 276 orang. Botong samua makan.<bt>Seeing that, then livers became strong again. And they followed eating with great activity. We who were on that ship, were 276 people. We all ate.</bt><v n="38" />Makan kinyang abis, ju dong mulai angka buang karong-karong padi-gandum pi dalam laut, ko coba bekin ringan tamba itu kapal.<bt>After eating full, then they began to pick up and throw away sacks of wheat-padi (grain) into the sea, to make that ship even lighter.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="padi-gandum = grain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">padi-gandum = grain</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kapal takandas [\s2]<bt>The ship runs aground [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Waktu su taráng, ana bua kapal dong dapa lia daratan. Ma dong sonde tau itu pulo apa. Dong ju dapa lia satu telúk yang dia pung pante bapasir. Jadi dong baharap, kalo bisa, dong mau bawa itu kapal lewat batu-batu piak yang ada di laut, ko pi di itu pante.<bt>When it was light, the ship's underlings saw land. But they did not know what island it was. They also say a point whose beaches were sand. So (consequently) they hoped, if possible, they wanted to bring that ship by the off shore rocks that were in the sea, to go that beach.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batu piak = rocks offshore"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">batu piak = rocks offshore</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Ais dong potong kasi tenga itu jangkar dong di laut. Tarús dong ulur kasi turun kamudi pi dalam laut, ko biar bisa stir itu kapal. Ais dong hela kasi nae layar jip di muka, ko biar angin tiop bawa itu kapal pi di pante.<bt>So then we cut leaving behind those anchors in the sea. Then they loosen letting down the rudder into the sea, so that that ship could be steered. Then they dragged up the jip sail, so that the wind would blow bringing that ship to the beach.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kamudi = rudder ; layar jip"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">kamudi = rudder ; layar jip = foresail, jib sail (small triangular sail at very front used to maintain steerage in high winds); stir = kemudikan; ulur = loosen, sorong</Message></Annotation><v n="41" />Ma itu kapal lari nae gunung pasir dalam laut, ju dia takandas di situ, deng sonde bisa bagarák lai. Tarús galombang bésar puku bekin ancor itu kapal pung buritan.<bt>But that ship ran up on a sand mountain in the sea, and it ran aground there, and could not move again. Then2 the big waves beat destroying that ships stern/backend.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="haring pasir = not known by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">haring pasir = not known by UNS's</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Waktu tantara dong dapa lia bagitu, ju dong maksud mau bunu itu orang bui dong samua. Ko dong taku, jang sampe itu orang bui dong baranáng pi darat, ais bangun lari.<bt>When the soldiers saw that, then they intended to kill all the prisoners. Because they were afraid, lest the prisoners swim to shore, and then get up and run. But commander Yulius forbade his soldiers, because he wanted to save Paulus. Then he gave the order, so that all the people who knew how to swim jump into the sea, to swim to land.</bt><v n="43" />Ma komandán Yulius larang dia pung tantara dong, tagal dia mau kasi salamat sang Paulus. Ju dia kasi parenta, ko samua orang yang tau baranáng malompa maso pi dalam laut, ko baranáng pi darat.<bt>But commander Yulius forbade his soldiers, because he wanted to save Paulus. Then he gave the order, so that all the people who knew how to swim jump into the sea, to swim to land.</bt><v n="44" />Ais orang yang sonde bisa baranáng dong, dia suru ko pegang papan, ko apa sa, ais iko galombang ko pi darat. Jadi botong samua sampe di darat deng salamat.<bt>Then the people who could not swim, he ordered to hold boards, or just whatever, and follow the waves to go to land. So (consequently) we all arrived on land safely.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02045b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none;horizontalPosition:center">Galombang puku bekin ancor kapal<bt>Waves beat the ship apart</bt></fig>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Di pulo Malta [\s2]<bt>On Malta island [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="28" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu botong samua su sampe deng salamat di darat, baru botong dapa tau bilang, itu pulo, nama Malta.<bt>When we had all arrived safely on land, then we found out that island was Malta.</bt><v n="2" />Itu negrí pung orang dong sambut sang botong deng bae. Tagal ada ujan deng udara talalu dingin, andia ko dong bekin api bésar di pante situ, ais dong minta sang botong ko pi panggang api.<bt>That country's people greeted us well. Because there was rain and the weather was very cold, that's why they made a big fire on the beach there, then they requested us to go toast at the fire. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pante is in NLT;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">pante is in NLT;</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Paulus ju iko pi pili-pili kayu, ko mau taro di api. Ma waktu dia mua itu kayu dong di atas api, takuju sa, satu ular baracon kaluar datang, tagal sonde tahan api pung panas. Ju itu ular gigi makaditi di Paulus pung tangan.<bt>Paulus also went looking for wood, to put on the fire. But when he put that wood on top of the fire, suddenly, a poisonous snake came out, because it could not stand the fire's heat. And that snake bit not letting go of Paulus' hand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="detok = fanged him (KM); pagut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">detok = fanged him (KM); pagut = bite (BI); makaditi = melengket, sonde lapas; palo makaditi = cling to s.o.; dedek = sting, bite and release quickly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia su ame kayu barapa potong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Dia su ame kayu barapa potong dari tana, ais dia bawa kombali di itu api. Waktu itu kayu mulai panas, ada ular satu yang kaluar gigi dia pung tangan. Te itu ular, ular bisu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02048b.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Ular baracon gigi makaditi di Paulus pung tangan<bt>A poisonous snake bites not letting go of Paulus' hand</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Waktu orang Malta dong dapa lia itu ular baracon makaditi tagantong di Paulus pung tangan, ju dong ba'omong satu deng satu bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang ni, tantu tukang bunu orang. Biar dia su talapás dari laut pung bahaya, ma itu memang dia pung nasib. Andia ko dia sonde bisa idop lai! Ko sapa yang bekin jahat, na, dia musti pikol dia pung hasil.&gt;&gt;<bt>When the Malta people saw that poisonous snake not letting go hanging on Paulus' hand, then they said to each other saying, “This person here, surely is a murderer. Even though he has been freed from the sea's danger, but it really is his fate. That's why he cannot live any longer! For whoever does evil, na, he must (shoulder)carry it's consequences.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia su lari buang susa dari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Dia su lari buang susa dari laut, ma iko dia pung nasib, dia sonde bole idop lai. Ini batúl, te pasti dia pikol dia pung jahat pung hasil (ujung, luken).</Message></Annotation><v n="5-6" />Itu orang dong pikir bilang, tantu lai sadiki, Paulus pung tangan bangka, deng takuju sa, nanti dia jato mati.<bt>Those people thought that, surely a bit more, Paulus' hand would swell up, and suddenly he would fall down dead.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Paulus kabás buang itu ular pi dalam api. Deng dia sonde rasa saki sadiki ju. Ais, itu orang dong tunggu-tunggu barapa lama, ma Paulus sonde apa-apa. Ju dong pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang-jangan ko dia ni, dewa, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Paulus shook off throw away that snake into the fire. And he did not feel even a littel sick. Then, those people waited a while, but nothing happened to Paulus. They thought that, “Perhaps he here, is a god!” [EXEG: swell up or drop dead (explicit -- implicit). Check your RL.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Sonde jao dari itu tampa, ada gubernor pung ruma-ruma deng tana yang luas. Itu gubernor pung nama, Publius. Dia datang sambut sang botong di pante, ais dia undang sang botong ko datang tenga di dia pung ruma. Di situ, dia urus sang botong tiga hari.<bt>Not far from that place, there was the governor's houses and wide land. That governor's name, was Publius. He came to welcome us on the beach, then he invited u to come stay at his house. There, he took care of us for three days.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Itu waktu, gubernor pung bapa barana ada saki damám, deng mencret sonde pake barenti. Ju Paulus pi lia sang dia di dia pung kamar. Ais dia taro tangan di itu orang saki, ko sambayang kasi dia. Ju itu orang bae memang.<bt>At that time, the governor's birth father was sick with fever, and diarrhea that would not stop. And Paulus went to see him in his room. Then he put his hands on that sick person, and prayed for him. Then he was well right away</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu kotong manumpang deng dia, dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Waktu kotong manumpang deng dia, dia pung papa jato saki panas deng poro ju saki. Dengar bagitu, ais Paulus maso ko lia sang dia. Dia taro dia pung tangan di itu orang saki pung kapala ko sambayang. Sambayang abis, itu orang saki su bae.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Waktu dong lia gubernor pung bapa su bae, ju orang-orang saki laen dong datang sang Paulus. Dong minta tolong sang dia, ju dia bekin bae sang dong.<bt>When they saw that the governor's father was well, then other sick people came to Paulus. They requested he help them, and he make them well.</bt><v n="10a" />Ais, itu orang dong kasi tunju dong pung rasa tarima kasi, deng bawa barang parsén talalu banya ko kasi sang botong.<bt>Then, those people showed their feelings of thanks, and brought a great many presents, to give to us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="barang parsén = hadiah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">barang parsén = hadiah</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais Publius deng dia pung orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Ais Publius deng dia pung orang Malta dong samua minta tarima kasi. Dong bawa barang banya ko kasi kotong. Waktu kotong pi kasi tenga itu pulo, dong antar itu barang samua pi di kapal. Te dong sonde mau kotong ada parlú apa-apa di kapal.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus dong balayar kasi tenga Malta ko pi Italia [\s2]<bt>Paulus them sail leaving behind Malta to go to Italia [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10b-11" />Botong tenga di Malta tiga bulan, sampe musim galombang deng angin ribut barenti. Itu waktu, ada satu kapal dari kota Aleksandria yang su balabu dalam musim galombang di itu pulo. Itu kapal pung nama, Ana Kambár,<bt>We stayed at Malta three months, until the season of waves and loud wind stopped. At that time, there was a ship from Alexandria that was anchored during the wave season at that island. That ship's name, Twin Children,</bt><note reference="28:11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Iko orang di situ pung agama, itu ana kambár pung nama Kastor deng Poluks. Dong dua tu, dewa yang orang kapal songgo.<bt>According to the religion of the people there, those twins names were Kastor and Poluks. Those two, were gods whom ship people worshipped (traditional.worship).</bt></note>tagal ada patong dewa ana kambár di itu kapal pung haluan. Ais botong mau nae itu kapal, ko balayar tarús pi Roma. Jadi waktu botong mau nae kapal, ju orang Malta dong bawa kasi botong bakál deng barang laen yang botong parlú di kapal.<bt>because there were statues of twin gods on that ships bow. So then we wanted to embark on this ship, to sail on to Roma. So (consequently) when we were going to embark, then the Malta people brought giving us travel food and other things that we would need ont the ship.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="patong ; ana bagambar = twins"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">patong ; ana bagambar = twins (stok lama), current = ana kambár</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="maps\Bible\Hk-Rome.tif" rtfFormat="width:6cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Dari pulo Kreta sampe di kota Roma<bt>From Kreta island to Roma city</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Botong balayar palán-palán, ais botong sampe di kota Sirakusa di pulo Sisilia. Botong balabu di situ, tiga hari.<bt>We sailed slowly, then we arrived at Sirakusa city oon Sisilia island. We stayed in harbour there, three days.</bt><v n="13" />Dari situ, botong balayar iko-iko pante Sisilia, ais botong sampe di kota Regium. Dia pung beso, angin salatan tiop deng kuat, ais botong balayar tarús deng capát. Dia pung lusa, botong sampe di satu kota pelabuan, nama Putioli.<bt>From there, we sailed following along the shore of Sisilia, then we arrived at Regium city. The next day, a south wind blew strongly, then we sailed on faster. The second day, we arrived at a harbour city, named Putioli.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="beso, lusa, tula, tubin; fuu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">beso, lusa, tula, tubin; fuu</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Di situ, botong turun kasi tenga itu kapal. Ais botong pi cari Yesus pung orang dong di situ. Waktu botong dapa katumu sang dong, ju dong undang ko botong tenga deng dong. Jadi botong manumpang di situ satu minggu. Ais itu, botong jalan kaki tarús pi Roma.<bt>There, we disembarked from that ship. Then we went to find Yesus' people there. When we found them, then they invited us to stay with them. So (consequently) we stayed as guests there one week. After that, we walked by foot on to Roma.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Waktu Yesus pung orang yang ada di Roma dong dapa dengar bilang, botong mau pi sana, ju dong datang sambut sang botong di tenga jalan. Ada yang dapa sang botong di Pasar Apius; yang laen dong dapa sang botong di satu tampa, nama Pasanggrahan Tiga.<bt>When Yesus' people who were in Roma heard that, we wanted to go there, then they came to welcome us in the middle of the road. There those who met up with us at Apius Market; and those who met us at a place, called Three Inns.</bt><note reference="28:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pasar Apius pung jao dari Roma, kira-kira 70 kilo. Pasanggrahan Tiga pung jao, 53 kilo.<bt>Apius Market's distance from Roma, approximately 70 kilometres. Three Inn's distance, 53 kilometres.</bt></note>Waktu Paulus dapa lia sang dong, ju dia minta tarima kasi bam-banya sang Tuhan Allah, deng dia pung hati jadi kuat.<bt>When Paulus saw them, then he said many thanks to the Lord God, and his liver became strong (=encouraged). [EXEG: Bruce, LN, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TB says Forum Apius and Tres"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">TB says Forum Apius and Tres Taberne from Latin/Greek.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn02054b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none;horizontalPosition:center">Paulus katumu deng orang parcaya di jalan Apius<bt>Paulus meets with the believers on Apirus road</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus di Roma<bt>Paulus in Roma</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Sampe di Roma, [tantara dong kasi maso orang bui dong pi dalam bui.]<bt>Arriving in Roma, [the soldiers put the prisoners in jail.]</bt><note reference="28:16a" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada tulisan Yunani saparu yang tua, yang sonde pake ini kata dalam kurung dong.<bt>There are some old Yunani writings which do not use these words in parentheses.</bt></note>Ma Paulus sonde. Dong kasi loos sang dia, ko bole sewa satu ruma. Di situ, dia tenga deng satu tantara yang jaga tarús sang dia. Dong dua pung tangan sablá-sablá ada bata'ika deng rante.<bt>But not Paulus. They allowed him, to rent a house. There, he stayed with one soldier who continually guarded him. The two of their hands were linked to each other with a chain. [DISCOURSE (background): chain from vs. 20.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bata'ika = tied to each other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">bata'ika = tied to each other</Message></Annotation><note reference="28:16b" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 28:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Abis tiga hari, ju Paulus undang sang tua-tua Yahudi dong di situ, ko datang katumu sang dia. Waktu dong su bakumpul, ju dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara dong samua! Beta ada di sini, tagal orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong tangkap sang beta di Yerusalem. Ais dong sarakan sang beta pi di pamarenta Roma pung tangan. Padahal beta sonde bekin sala apa-apa! Beta sonde bekin apa-apa yang lawan kotong pung bangsa sandiri. Deng beta ju sonde lawan kotong pung atoran adat yang kotong su tarima dari kotong pung nene-moyang.<bt>After three days, then Paulus invited the Yahudi elders there, to come meet him. When they were gathered, then he told them saying, “All siblings! I am here, because the Yahudi peoples' bosses captured/arrested me in Yerusalem. Then they surrendered me to the hands of the Roma government. Even though, I had done nothing wrong! I had done nothing that opposes our own ethnic group. And I also did not oppose our custom regulations which we have received from our ancestors.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Biar beta sonde bekin sala apa-apa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Biar beta sonde bekin sala apa-apa lawan kotong pung bangsa sandiri, ko lawan kotong pung nene-moyang pung adat, ma dong tangkap ame sang beta di Yerusalem, ais dong sarakan sang beta pi pamarenta Roma pung tangan. Abis tiga hari, Paulus minta orang tua Yahudi yang ada di Roma bakumpul di dia pung ruma. Waktu dong su bakumpul abis, dia omong sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa-Bapa {term of address}! Beta sonde bekin jahat apa-apa sang kotong pung orang, ju beta sonde bekin sala apa-apa kotong pung adat. Biar bagitu, ma dong tangkap sang beta di Yerusalem, ais dong buang beta di tangan pamarenta Roma.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Pamarenta su pareksa beta pung parkara di sana. Ma dong sonde dapa beta pung sala satu ju, yang pantas deng hukum mati. Andia ko dong su mau lapás sang beta.<bt>The government examined my case there. But they also did not find a single wrong of mine, that was worthy of a death sentence. That's why they wanted to free me.</bt><v n="19" />Ma tagal orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong tolak pamarenta pung putusan ko mau lapás sang beta, andia ko mau tar mau, beta musti nae banding datang di pusat. Beta bekin bagitu, ma beta sonde ada niat ko mau mangadu sang beta pung bangsa sandiri.<bt>But because the Yahudi people's bosses rejected the government's decision to free me, that's why whether (I) want to or not, I must appeal and come to the centre. I did like that, but I have not made chaos or want to accuse my own ethnic group.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangadu = baparkara, menyampaikan tuduhan, accuse"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">mangadu = baparkara, menyampaikan tuduhan, accuse ; tarpaksa = ambiguous with BI terpaksa, and NEG tar paksa;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong omong memang bagitu, biar beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Dong omong memang bagitu, biar beta sonde ada parkara apa-apa deng dong. Ais beta tapaksa cari jalan kaluar deng beta pung parkara. Ais beta minta Raja Bésar Keser yang dengar beta pung parkara di tampa urus parkara bésar di sini di kota Roma. Te itu memang beta pung hak iko pamarenta Roma.</Message></Annotation><note reference="28:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 25:11</note><v n="20" />Itu parkara yang bekin sampe beta kumpul sang sodara dong di sini. Biar ko kotong bisa ba'omong so'al apa yang orang Yahudi dong ada tunggu-tunggu: andia, kotong samua baharap sang itu Raja yang Tuhan Allah mau kirim datang ko kasi salamat sang kotong bangsa Isra'el. Ini yang bekin sampe dong ika sang beta deng ini rante.&gt;&gt;<bt>That litigation is what made it so that I am together with siblings (=you) here. Allow it, so that we can talk about what the Yahudi people are waiting for: that is, we all hope for that Raja whom the Lord God will send to save us the Israel nation. This is want caused them to tie me with this chain.” [EXEG: Gk “the hope of Israel” here, not Christ or Messiah in this text. Much discussion about how to unpack this in context. Note the ambiguity can skew to Prophet (Isaiah), Priest, King (Davidic), Servant, Messiah, or all of the above. The immediate context (17-20) is political. Note this was originally drafted from the BIS, which tends to use a combined Saviour-King. By using Raja here we evoke the Davidic “hope” that comes through so strongly in Matthew and Psalms, and sometimes Luke. The expanded phrase ties it in to the common explication for ‘Kristus’. In this way, we deliberately signal that this is not just a normal term for Kristus/Mesias here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tagal bagitu, beta su minta papa-papa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Tagal bagitu, beta su minta papa-papa dong bakumpul di sini ko kotong samua tukar pikiran. Te beta mau papa-papa dong tau beta pung ikatan tali ni, pung akar. Kotong orang Yahudi samua batunggu kotong pung Raja datang ko kasi salamat sang kotong. Ma beta percaya bilang ini Raja su datang.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sampe sakarang, botong balóm tarima satu surat ju dari Yudea yang kasi tau sodara pung parkara ni. Bagitu ju, sodara-sodara yang datang dari sana sonde omong apa-apa so'al sodara Paul.<bt>Then they replied saying, “Until now, we have not yet received even one letter from Yudea that tell about this litigation of sibling's(=yours). Like that also, the siblings who come from there have not said anything about sibling Paul.</bt><v n="22" />Ma botong suka dengar apa yang sodara parcaya, tagal botong su dengar di mana-mana bilang, orang dong tolak apa yang partei Kristen dong ajar. Ma dia pung batúl karmana, botong balóm tau. Jadi sodara tolong omong kasi botong dolo.&gt;&gt;<bt>But we want to hear what sibling (=you) believes, because we hear all over the place that people have rejected that which the Kristen party teaches. But what is really true, we don't know yet. So (consequently) sibling (=you) please tell us.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="so'al Ais kotong minta ko bapa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">so'al Ais kotong minta ko bapa kasi jalas ini orang Yesus Karistus pung jalan sang kotong. Te kotong balóm mangarti bae-bae itu kalompok Karistus. Kotong cuma tau, bilang, banya orang yang lawan ajaran dari itu kelompok Karistus.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais ju dong akór sama-sama ko pili satu hari, ko dong mau katumu lai. Sampe dia pung hari, ju orang bam-banya datang bakumpul di Paulus pung ruma. Ju dia mulai carita kasi sang dong, Tuhan Allah pung parenta. Ais dia pake banya ayat dari ba'i Musa pung tulisan dong, deng dari Tuhan pung jubir laen dong pung tulisan, ko mau tarek dong parcaya sang Yesus. Dia omong dari pagi sampe sore.<bt>Then they agreed together to choose a day, for them to meet again. When it arrived at that day, then very many people gathered at Paulus' house. And he began to tell them, the Lord God's commands. Then he used verses from Gf/Ff Musa's books, and from the writings of the Lord God's other spokespersons, to draw them into believing in Yesus. He spoke from morning to late afternoon.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais dong putus waktu ko bakumpul"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Ais dong putus waktu ko bakumpul ulang di laen hari. Waktu itu hari su sampe, orang banya mo mati datang di Paulus pung ruma. Dari pagi-pagi sampe sore dia bacarita kaná deng Tuhan pung suku. Dia angka kata dari Musa pung tulisan, deng Tuhan pung jubir yang laen. Dia kasi jalas bagitu, ko dong bilang itu Yesus, dia itu memang Karistus, itu orang yang Tuhan su lama janji mau kirim.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Waktu dong dengar abis Paulus pung omong, ju ada saparu yang parcaya, ma yang laen sonde.<bt>When they finished hearing Paulus' talk, then there were some who believed, but others who did not.</bt><v n="25" />Dong bamalawan satu deng laen sampe ada yang mau pulang. Ma Paulus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang bosong pung bakanjar ni, pas deng apa yang dolu Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi kasi tau sang ba'i Yesaya<bt>They argued with each other, until Paulus spoke saying, “It's true that your arguement here, fits with what before the Lord God's Holy Spirit told Gf/Ff Yesaya,</bt><v n="26" />bilang,<bt>saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Lu pi kasi tau ini bangsa Yahudi ni bilang,<bt>‘You-sg go tell this ethnic group here saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;&lt;Nanti bosong maen dengar tarús-tarús Beta pung omong,<bt>“You continually hear My talk,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ma sonde mangarti sadiki ju!<bt>but don't understand even a little bit!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong maen lia tarús-tarús apa yang Beta bekin,<bt>You continually see what I have made,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ma bosong sonde ame pusing apa-apa.&gt;&gt;<bt>but you don't care at all.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde mangarti/tangkap dia pung arti."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">sonde mangarti/tangkap dia pung arti.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="27" />Tagal ini bangsa pung hati su karás mau mati.<bt>Because this ethnic group's liver is exceeding hard (stubborn).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong pung talinga su sonde mau dengar lai!<bt>Their ears do not hear anymore!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Deng dong pung mata dong, su tatutu mati!<bt>And their eyes, are shut dead tight!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tenga ko biar dong sonde usa dengar lai;<bt>Just allow it so they don't need to hear anymore;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng tenga ko dong pung mata sonde usa lia lai.<bt>And allow it so their eyes don't need to see anymore;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Deng tenga ko dong pung hati buta tarús.<bt>And allow it so that their livers are continually blind.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sampe dong su sonde tau jalan kambali datang sang Beta lai,<bt>Until they no longer know the path to return to Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jadi karmana ko Beta bisa bekin bae sang dong lai?&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So how can it be that I can heal them anymore?’”</bt><note reference="28:26-27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 6:9-10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ais Paulus tutu dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Jadi bagini, sodara dong! Bosong musti tau bilang, sakarang Tuhan Allah ju sadia kasi salamat sang suku-bangsa yang bukan Yahudi dong, tagal dong ju mau dengar sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Paulus finished his talk saying, “So it's like this, siblings! You must know that now the Lord God is also prepared to save the ethnic groups who are not Yahudi, because they want to hear/obey Him.”</bt><v n="29" />[Paulus omong abis bagitu, ju itu orang dong pulang. Ma dong pung pikiran dong sonde bakatumu, tagal dong bamalawan satu deng satu.]<bt>[Paulus finished speaking like that, then those people went home. But their thoughts were not coming together, because they were opposing each other.]</bt><note reference="28:29" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ini ayat sonde ada di barapa tulisan Yunani yang lama.<bt>This verse is not in several old Yunani writings.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Paulus tenga di dia pung ruma sewa sampe dua taon. Dia tarima deng sanáng samua orang yang datang cari katumu sang dia.<bt>Paulus lived in his rented house for two years. He happily received all the people who came seeking to meet him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Deng bagitu, dia dapa kans ko carita kasi sang dong, Tuhan Allah pung parenta, deng ajar kasi sang dong Tuhan Yesus pung Jalan Idop. Dia omong tarús-taráng deng barani, deng sonde ada halangan apa-apa.<bt>With that, he got the opportunity to tell them, the Lord God's commands, and to teach them the Lord Yesus' Life Path. He spoke openly with braveness, and without any obstacles what so ever.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Bapa Teofilus yang bae. Beta pung carita, sampe di sini sa.<bt>Father Teofilus who is good. My story, finishes here.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Makasi.<bt>Thanks.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Dari beta, Lukas<bt>From me, Lukas.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te dia pung hati tatáp panas"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:19Z">Te dia pung hati tatáp panas ko kasi tau sang dong samua kaná deng Tuhan Allah pung Suku. Dia ju ajar dong kaná deng Tuhan Yesus Karistus. Dia bekin tarús bagitu iko dia pung mau, ju sonde ada orang yang larang.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <fig path="maps\Bible\Hk-pent.tif" />
  </book>
</bible>